<bible xml:lang="bko" backtTranslaltionDefaultLanguage="en" oxes="2.0">
  <book id="DAN" stage="Final" version="A">
    <Annotation class="History">
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2017-09-22 01:10:41Z" when="2017-09-22 01:10:41Z" stage="Draft">Team check at UBB, 13-15 March 2017. Chuck, June, Adriana, Reny, Rina, Yanti Tunliu-Mooy (also Tii MTT), Lena Aplugi (also Dhao MTT); Chuck did the BackTrans; Catherine Rountree queries June 2017; Chuck's adjustments and responses to CR exegetical queries 5 Sept 2017 (27 DAN-Kupang pre-check adjustment-2-CEG.doc); Consultant check in Kupang, UBB, 18-19 Sept 2017; Final approval given by Catherine Rountree by email 22 Sept 2017: no further changes, may be printed.</Message>
    </Annotation>
    <p class="Header" usfm="h">Daniel</p>
    <p class="Title Main" usfm="mt">Daniel pung Carita<bt>Daniel's story</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Daniel deng dia pung tamán dong di Babel<bt>Daniel and his friends in Babel [NOTE: term covers both Babel and Babylon]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="1" />
      <v n="1" />Ini carita jadi waktu Yoyakim su pegang parenta tiga taon di da'era Yahuda.<bt>This story happened/took place when Yoyakim had been ruling for three years in the region of Yahuda.</bt><note reference="1:1" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ini carita jadi kira-kira taon 605 SM (Sebelum Masehi).<bt>This story happened around the year 605 SM (Before Messiah = BC).</bt></note>Itu waktu, ada satu raja Babel, nama Nebukadnesar, datang di kota Yerusalem. Dia pung tantara dong kurung ame kota Yerusalem, ko biar orang sonde bisa maso, deng sonde bisa kaluar.<bt>At that time, there was a king of Babel, named Nebukadnesar, who came to the city of Yerusalem. His army surrounded the city of Yerusalem, so that people could not enter, and could not leave. [EXEG: unpack Heb. vayyatsar: ‘besiege, shut in’] [NOTE: TB: Yoyakim.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Jeremiah 46:2 605 fourth year."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Jeremiah 46:2 605 fourth year. How did they count? Babylonian calendar began in the fall; Hebrew religious calendar began in the spring, and an agricultural calendar that matched the Babylonian calendar.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vayyatsar: he shut it in,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vayyatsar: he shut it in, laid siege to it.</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Raja-raja dong 24:1; 2 Sajara Isra'el deng Yahuda 36:5-7; Yeremia 46:2</note><v n="2" />Ju Tuhan kasi biar ko raja kasi kala raja Yoyakim. Ais waktu Nebukadnesar su mau pulang pi kota Babel, dia ju ame bawa barang mahal saparu yang dong pake dalam Tuhan pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat di Yerusalem. Waktu kambali pi dia pung da'era sandiri,<bt>And/then God2 allowed the raja to defeat raja Yoyakim. Then when Nabukadnesar was about to return home to Babel, he also took away some of the expensive things that they used in God's Central/Main House of Worship/Prayer (KT: *Temple) in Yerusalem. When he returned to his own region,</bt><note reference="1:2" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Ibrani tulis bilang, dia pulang pi &lt;Sinear&gt;. Sinear tu, dia pung da'era. Sinear pung kota bésar tu, andia Babel.<bt>The Ibrani language Bible writes saying, he returned home to &lt;Sinear&gt;. Sinear is his region. The capital city of Sinear is Babel.</bt></note>ju dia simpan itu barang di dia pung ruma songgo di sana.<bt>he stored those things in his traditional.worship house there (remote). [EXEG: it is by implication that these implements used in the Temple are valuable (IVP, TH). RL would make that explicit, otherwise there is no reason to mention them at all. Heb. ‘treasury/ treasure-house of his god’ = CEV ‘temple of his own god’; TWOT notes that the term is sometimes figurative. In eastern Indonesia, valuable objects are kept in the special idol house or clan house, not in a separate edifice, and this would functionally be the ‘divine storehouse’. It is also not clear that the Hebrew implies a separate edifice either, even though that is the impression from the English noise.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qətsat: end, sum"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qətsat: end, sum</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:2-4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Raja-raja dong 20:17-18, 24:10-16; 2 Sajara Isra'el deng Yahuda 36:10; Yesaya 39:7-8</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ais satu kali, raja Nebukadnesar suru dia pung kapala urusan di istana, nama Aspenas bilang, &lt;&lt;Pi kumpul ame ana-ana orang Isra'el saparu yang botong su bawa pulang di sini. Pili ame ana-ana dari dong pung raja pung kelu deng dari bangsawan dong ju.<bt>Then one time, raja Nebukadnesar ordered the manager of the palace, named Aspenas saying, &lt;&lt;Go gather some of the children of the people of Isra'el whom we brought back/home here. Choose children from the families of their king, and also from (the families of) their nobles. [DISCOURSE: 3-4 made direct speech according to RL norms.] [DISCOURSE: implicit-to-explicit: whom we brought back/home here. NLT1, TH, CR, HCE]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) partəmiym: nobles"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) partəmiym: nobles</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) SariySayw: court people, eunuchs"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) SariySayw: court people, eunuchs</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rav: chief, like the President's"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rav: chief, like the President's chief of staff</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Cari nyong-nyong badan ba'isi, yang sehat deng sonde ada pung cacat, yang su balajar samua bidang, mangarti banya hal, deng capát tangkap orang pung maksud. Dong musti bisa layani di beta pung istana. Ajar sang dong ko biar dong bisa ba'omong pake kotong orang Kasdim pung bahasa. Ais ajar sang dong ko bisa baca-tulis kotong pung bahasa, ko biar dong ju tau kotong pung adat dong samua.&gt;&gt; Ais, itu orang bekin iko bagitu.<bt>Look for young [unmarried] men/boys with well-formed/muscled bodies, who are healthy and without deformity, who have studied all fields/disciplines, understand many things (=wise1), and quickly catch people's meaning/intent. they must be able to serve in my palace. Teach them so they can speak using our Kasdim language. And teach them so they can read-write our language, so they also know all of our culture/customs/ values/laws/traditions.&gt;&gt; Then that person did accordingly. [EXEG: HCE, NRSV, NLT, CEV; Heb. at least age of puberty, avoid “little boys”.] [NOTE to daughter translations: FYI if anyone asks: the language of Babylon was Aramaic, but the language of the ruling dynasty of the Chaldeans (TB: Kasdim) here was Akkadian. TH, IVP.] [EXEG: The Heb Sefer is polysemous ‘1) letters, writing, 2) books, literature’ Some versions go with sense #1, and others with sense #2, but in this context we think both senses are in focus. It almost matches Malay adat-istiadat ‘customs and laws’, but is broader.] [DISCOURSE: last sentence added to make irrealis to realis, as required by RL discourse patterns.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləshown: language"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləshown: language</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Sefer: writing, book"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Sefer: writing, book</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) heykhal: palace"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) heykhal: palace</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) koach: ability, strength"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) koach: ability, strength</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) maddaʕ: knowledge"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) maddaʕ: knowledge</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) maskiyliym (skl hif partcpl pl):"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) maskiyliym (skl hif partcpl pl): ones having insight</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mar'eh: appearance"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mar'eh: appearance</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mə' uwm (q. muwm): blemish"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mə' uwm (q. muwm): blemish</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cot\co01343c.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Waktu dong samua su kumpul abis, ais raja ju ator ko biar tiap hari dong makan-minum dari raja pung meja sandiri. Guru dong musti ajar itu nyong dong sampe tiga taon, baru angka sang dong saparu jadi pagawe di istana.<bt>When they were all gathered, then the raja also arranged so that they would eat from the raja's own table every day. The teachers must teach those young men for three years, before appointing some of them to become officials in the palace. [EXEG: CEV includes vs. 5 in direct speech with vs.4, but in the Heb it is not included in the grammatical complementiser of what the king commanded Ashpenaz, so we also don't include it.] [DISCOURSE: 1st clause added for reduced tail-head RL linkage patterns.] [DISCOURSE: implicit-to-explicit: ‘some of them’ to imply a weeding out process as suggested by the immediate context. NIV, NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) pat-bag: food-food; Persian loan word"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) pat-bag: food-food; Persian loan word</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vayman (mnh piʕel): he appointed."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vayman (mnh piʕel): he appointed. TWOT: The idea appoint or ordain is usual in the intensive stems. Twice in Dan (1:5, 10) and four times in Jon (1:17 [H 2:1]; 4:6-8), inanimate things—Daniel's food, Jonah's fish, the gourd, worm, and hot wind—are under the control of God. In Dan 1:11 and I Chr 9:29, a hierarchy of authority is identified by manah as men or other creatures are given specific responsibilities.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Dari itu nyong samua, ada ampa orang dari suku Yahuda ju. Iko dong pung nama bahasa Ibrani, dong tu, andia: Daniel, Hananya, Misael, deng Asarya.<bt>From (among) all those young men, there were also four people from the tribe/clan of Yahuda. Following their Ibrani (Hebrew) language names, they were: Daniel, Hananya, Misael, and Asarya. [NOTE: Indonesian TB: Hananya, Misael, Azarya]</bt><v n="7" />Ma kapala urusan kasi dong nama baru, iko orang Babel pung nama. Andia:<bt>But the head manager gave them new names, according to Babel people's names. That is:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Daniel dapa nama Beltasasar;<bt>Daniel got the name Beltasasar;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Hananya dapa nama Sadrak;<bt>Hananya got the name Sadrak;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Misael dapa nama Mesak;<bt>Misael got the name Mesak;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Asarya dapa nama Abednego.<bt>Asarya got the name Abednego.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shemowt: names. ABC: depersonalizing the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shemowt: names. ABC: depersonalizing the students by substituting names related to Yahweh by names related to Babylonian gods.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ma Daniel putus bilang, dia sonde mau makan-minum dari raja pung meja, te di situ ju ada makanan yang Tuhan su cap pamali kasi orang Isra'el dong. Andia ko dia pi cari kapala urusan bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa. Jang mara ma, kasi loos sang beta ko jang makan-minum dari bapa raja pung meja. Beta sonde bisa, te Tuhan Allah su bilang itu makanan kamomos kasi botong orang Isra'el.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Daniel decided that he did not want to eat-drink from the raja's table, cuz (elaboration) there, there was also food which God2 had branded/categorised as taboo for the people of Isra'el. That is why he went looking for the head manager and said, &lt;&lt;Father/sir. Don't be angry (Idiom: I apologise) but give me permission to not eat-drink from the raja's table. I can't do that, cuz (elaboration) God has already said that food is dirty/defiled/unclean for we-exc people of Isra'el.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: (background-JEG): Heb. yitga'al (hitp): he would [not] defile, pollute himself. NET: Various reasons have been suggested as to why such food would defile Daniel. Perhaps it had to do with violations of Mosaic law with regard to unclean foods, or perhaps it had to do with such food having been offered to idols. Daniel's practice in this regard is strikingly different from that of Esther, who was able successfully to conceal her Jewish identity. UBS: In ancient times meat usually came from animals offered in sacrifice to a deity. Ordinary secular slaughtering of animals was rarely practiced. So for Daniel, a good Jew, to eat the meat of an animal that had been offered in sacrifice to Babylonian gods would constitute a serious offense against his God and would therefore make him impure or ritually unclean. It was the same with regard to the wine, since a small amount of it would have been poured out as a libation, or drink offering, to the Babylonian gods. IVPC: There are numerous examples in intertestamental literature of Jews seeing the necessity of refraining from the food served by Gentiles (Tobit, Judith, Jubilees). It is not so much something in the food that defiles as much as it is the total program of assimilation. At this point the Babylonian government is exercising control over every aspect of their lives. (Names, food, education--CEG)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yitga'al (hitp): he would [not]"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yitga'al (hitp): he would [not] defile, pollute himself. NET: Various reasons have been suggested as to why such food would defile Daniel. Perhaps it had to do with violations of Mosaic law with regard to unclean foods, or perhaps it had to do with such food having been offered to idols. Daniel's practice in this regard is strikingly different from that of Esther, who was able successfully to conceal her Jewish identity. UBS: In ancient times meat usually came from animals offered in sacrifice to a deity. Ordinary secular slaughtering of animals was rarely practiced. So for Daniel, a good Jew, to eat the meat of an animal that had been offered in sacrifice to Babylonian gods would constitute a serious offense against his God and would therefore make him impure or ritually unclean. It was the same with regard to the wine, since a small amount of it would have been poured out as a libation, or drink offering, to the Babylonian gods. IVPC: There are numerous examples in intertestamental literature of Jews seeing the necessity of refraining from the food served by Gentiles (Tobit, Judith, Jubilees). It is not so much something in the food that defiles as much as it is the total program of assimilation. At this point the Babylonian government is exercising control over every aspect of their lives.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cot\co01344c.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Padahal Tuhan su ator ko biar itu kapala urusan mau kasi tunju sayang deng kasian sang Daniel.<bt>In actual fact [+contrary to expectation] God2 had already arranged so that the head manager wanted to show love/pity/compassion and mercy to Daniel. [EXEG: Heb. rachəmiym: acts of compassion, mercy. NRSV: compassion. TH: ‘The second noun has the meaning of "pity" or "compassion" in some contexts, but here the meaning seems to be more like "goodwill" or "sympathy."’ NIV/NLT ‘respect’ doesn't quite capture it in this context.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rachəmiym: acts of compassion, mercy"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rachəmiym: acts of compassion, mercy</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) cheSed: loyalty [at least in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) cheSed: loyalty [at least in this context]</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Ma dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia pung masala bagini: beta taku, te beta pung bos, andia bapa raja sandiri, yang suru bilang bosong musti ame makan-minum dari dia pung meja. Jadi kalo lu sonde makan bagitu, ais nanti bapa raja dapa lia lu pung badan sonde sehat deng sonde ba'isi sama ke nyong yang laen dong dari lu pung kalompok, nanti dia pung mara tapo'a kasi sang beta. Jang sampe dia potong buang beta pung kapala.&gt;&gt;<bt>But he responded saying, &lt;&lt;The problem is like this: I'm afraid, cuz (elaboration) my bos, that is the raja himself, is the one who ordered that you-pl must take food-drink from his table. So (consequently) if you-sg do not eat like that, and then later the king happens to see your body not healthy and not filled out like the other young men from your group, then his anger will be poured out on me. May it not get to the point that he cuts off my head.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Heb. dejected, looking unwell, NRSV: poorer condition, NLT: become pale and thin, CEV: looking worse than, TH: bodies not as good/strong as...]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chiyyavtem: you would put my"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chiyyavtem: you would put my head in jeopardy. TWOT: Used but once in the Piel stem. In Dan 1:10 with the word ro4)sh it means to endanger one's head (KJV, ASV, RSV). The NEB paraphrases the clause, "It will cost me my head."</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) giylkhem: like your (pl) age"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) giylkhem: like your (pl) age</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) zoʕəfiym: looking embittered, dejected"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) zoʕəfiym: looking embittered, dejected</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) minnah (piʕel): he has assigned,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) minnah (piʕel): he has assigned, determined</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yare' (adj): in a state"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yare' (adj): in a state of fearing</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="HCE needs close quotes at end"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">HCE needs close quotes at end of verse (I reported this)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ais ju Daniel pi ba'omong deng orang jaga yang kapala urusan su utus ko jaga deng ator sang dia, Hananya, Misael, deng Asarya. Daniel omong bae-bae bilang,<bt>Then Daniel went and talked with the overseer/guardian/guard whom the head manager had commissioned to watch/guard and manage him, Hananya, Misael, and Asarya. He spoke politely saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) meltsar: guardian"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) meltsar: guardian</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />&lt;&lt;Bapa. Beta minta ko bapa uji sang beta deng beta pung tamán tiga orang ni. Uji sang botong bagini: salama sapulu hari kalo botong dudu makan, na, kasi makan botong deng macam-macam sayur deng kacang sa. Botong ju minum aer kosong sa.<bt>&lt;&lt;Father/sir. I request that father (=you) test me and my 3 friends here. Test us like this: for ten days when we sit and eat, na, just feed us various kinds of vegetables and nuts/beans/legumes. We will also just eat empty water (idiom: plain drinking water). [EXEG: the gloss of “vegetable” is quite unfortunate, since the Heb is a deverbal noun based on the action of “sowing seed”, the most common/normal of which TWOT &amp; IVP mention as “grain/wheat” and “animal feed”. (JEG) A general term for something that is sown, but usually denoting edible seeds which can be cooked, such as lentils, beans, etc. In Kupang this would be like sayur with kacang nasi, or sup kacang mera--poor man's food.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) zeroʕiym: herbs? things sown (by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) zeroʕiym: herbs? things sown (by scattering) = grain. NOT "vegetables." TWOT: refers to the action of sowing seed in the fields (Gen 26:12; Isa 37:30). It is used with the accusative of the type of seed sown, e.g. sowing wheat (Jer 12:13), or with the accusative of the field sown (Ex 23:10; Lev 25:3). Occasionally, it is also followed by the double accusative of both seed and field (e.g. Lev 19:19; Deut 22:9, "You shall not sow your field with two kinds of seed"). IVPC: the text does not suggest that they are being provided with a restaurant-style prepared and served meal. As explained above (1:5), to eat from the king's table meant only that they were provided rations at the expense of the royal budget. Military rations, for example, consisted of measured amounts of grain that the soldiers then used to prepare their meals. IVPD: A general term for something that is sown, but usually denoting edible seeds which can be cooked, such as lentils, beans, etc. In the biblical context the word is used of the plain vegetable food sought by Daniel and his friends, instead of the rich diet of the king's table.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yitnuw (ntn jussive): may they"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yitnuw (ntn jussive): may they be given to us</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) naS-na' (nSh imperv): please test."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) naS-na' (nSh imperv): please test. UBS: the force of the imperative is softened in Hebrew by the addition of a particle, so that the resulting form is not a command but more of a polite request. This particle is used especially when an inferior is speaking to a superior person. In order to avoid giving the impression that Daniel and his friends gave an order to the guard, it may be well to insert the word "please" (see NRSV) or something similar (as in NIV, NJB, NAB, and AB).</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Ais nanti, kalo itu sapulu hari su abis, na, banding botong deng nyong yang laen dong dari botong pung kalompok. Lia abis, baru putus mau bekin karmana deng botong.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then later, when those ten days are over, na, compare us-exc with the other young men from our group. After looking/scrutinizing, only.then decide what you want to do with us. (lit: want to do how with us)&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ais orang jaga yang urus sang dong tarima bae. Dia bekin bagitu ko uji sang dong salama sapulu hari.<bt>Then the guardian who managed/oversaw them agreed. He did like that to test them for 10 days. [NOTE to daughter translations: in other local languages, the concept of “salama/during time span” is difficult. Discuss carefully and test.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Waktu itu sapulu hari su abis, tau-tau te itu ana-ana dari Isra'el lebe sehat deng lebe ba'isi dari nyong yang laen dong samua.<bt>When those ten days were finished, [+contrary to expectation] those boys from Isra'el were healthier and more filled out than all the other young men. [NOTE: age not in focus with these terms.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) basar: flesh, firmness of flesh"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) basar: flesh, firmness of flesh</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vəriy'ey: fat of, healthy of."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vəriy'ey: fat of, healthy of. In Hebrew, "fat" didn't necessarily mean "obese." It meant "the best kind"</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Andia ko orang jaga yang urus sang dong kasi biar ko dong makan macam-macam sayur deng kacang, deng minum aer kosong sa. Dia sonde paksa ko dong makan dari raja pung meja deng minum aer anggor.<bt>That is why the guardian who managed/oversaw them let them keep eating various vegetables and nuts/beans/legumes, and drink empty water. He did not force them to eat from the raja's table and drink wine. [EXEG: see note at vs. 12.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) zerʕoniym: things sown"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) zerʕoniym: things sown</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Tuhan kasi itu ampa nyong Isra'el dong ko dong balajar bam-banya. Ju dong mangarti banya hal. Dong baca banya buku, ju dong tamba pintar tarús. Tuhan ju kasi karunya sang Daniel ko biar dia bisa kasi tau orang pung mimpi dong pung arti.<bt>God2 made those four young men of Isra'el so that they learned a lot. They also understood many things. They read many books, and they kept increasing in knowledge/cleverness. God2 also gave special.gifting to Daniel so that he could explain the meaning of people's dreams. [NOTE to daughter translations: Heb is “dreams and visions”; Kupang has to conflate them with a single term, but some vernaculars here have different terms for each category. Use them if you have them.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəlomowt: dreams"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəlomowt: dreams</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chazown: vision(s), TWOT: The revelatory"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chazown: vision(s), TWOT: The revelatory vision granted by God to chosen messengers, i.e. prophets. Such apparently was the experience of Balaam the son of Beor (Num 24:4, 16). This vision of the prophets took place sometimes in the waking state, but also in "the spirit" (see Num 24:2). Sometimes the experience of "seeing" a revelatory dream is designated by chazah and ha6za4) (Aram). See Dan 2:26, 4:5,9 [H 2,6] etc.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) heviyn (byn hif): he understood"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) heviyn (byn hif): he understood</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hokhmah: wisdom. TWOT: Wisdom is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hokhmah: wisdom. TWOT: Wisdom is seen in the skill of technical work in making garments for the high priest (Ex 28:3), craftsmanship in metal work (Ex 31:3, 6), as well as the execution of battle tactics (Isa 10:13). Wisdom is required from government leaders and heads of state for administration (Deut 34:9; II Sam 14:20), including pagan leaders as well as Israelites (Ezk 28:4-5). The Messiah demonstrates wisdom and discernment in his function as leader of his people (Isa 11:2). Wisdom is expressed in shrewdness. The woman of Tekoa averted a town's bloodshed in her clever plea for its safety (II Sam 20:22).</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) haskel: insight"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) haskel: insight</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) maddaʕ: thought. TWOT: Knowledge, science,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) maddaʕ: thought. TWOT: Knowledge, science, thought. This masculine noun is used in contexts with wisdom (chokmah). Solomon's request was for wisdom and knowledge (II Chr 1:10-12). The Hebrew children surpassed others in knowledge (Dan 1:4, 7; KJV and ASV, "science"; RSV, "learning").</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Dong balajar tiga taon, sama ke raja Nebukadnesar su bilang. Abis, itu kapala urusan antar bawa sang dong ko datang mangada sang raja di dia pung istana.<bt>They studied for three years, just as raja Nebukadnesar had said. After that, the head manager escorted them to come before the raja in his palace.</bt><v n="19" />Ju raja ba'omong deng samua nyong yang balajar sama-sama salama tiga taon. Dari dong samua, dia bisa lia kalo Daniel, Hananya, Misael, deng Asarya lebe pintar dari tamán dong. Andia ko dia angka sang dong jadi pagawe di istana.<bt>And the raja spoke with all the young men who had studied together for three years. From (among) all of them, he could see/perceive that Daniel, Hananya, Misael, and Asarya were more clever/knowledgable than their friends/companions. That is why he elevated/appointed them to become officials at the palace.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vaydabber (piʕel): he spoke"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vaydabber (piʕel): he spoke</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cot\co01345c.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Mulai itu waktu, kalo raja tanya apa-apa sang itu ampa ana Isra'el, dia lia dong tau banya, dong mangarti banya hal, ju dong tau akurang ko orang bekin satu hal. Yang batúl, raja dapa lia kalo dong sapulu kali lebe pintar dari samua orang pintar, tukang suanggi deng tukang rai-rai yang ada di dia pung karaja'an.<bt>Beginning from that time, if/when the raja asked anything to those four boys from Isra'el, he saw that they knew much, and understood many things, and they knew why a person did something. Actually, the raja could see/perceive that they were ten times more clever than all the seers/smart people, sorcerers, and diviners there in his kingdom. [DISCOURSE: following HCE, identify the four young men as from “Isra'el” to help the reader get the bigger socio-political dynamics at play here. Heb is vague “them”.] [EXEG: Heb. charTummiym: soothsayer-priests led the worship of the gods and they recognized signs of the future. IVPC: The first term used here refers to Egyptian dream interpreters. The Babylonians were known to include Egyptian dream interpreters among their court advisors. Heb. 'asshafiym: conjurers. they are also grouped with the mekashshepim (sorcerers) and kasdim (Chaldeans). The Aramaic word gazerin (soothsayers/astrologers) in the lists of Dan 4:7, 5:7, and 11 is the equivalent of the Heb mekashshepim used elsewhere. IVPC: The second term refers to the Mesopotamian specialist in exorcism: defending against threatening messages in the omens or in dreams. The latter’s skills include identifying the threatening sign, determining a course of action to avert the evil, and performing apotropaic rituals and reciting incantations to turn aside the danger. Sickness was often included in the group of threatening signs, so the exorcist was counted among the "health care professionals" of Babylonian society.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'asshafiym: conjurers. TWOT: All occurrences"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'asshafiym: conjurers. TWOT: All occurrences are in the book of Daniel (1:20 and 2:2 [Heb]; 2:10, 27; 4:4; 5:7, 11, 15 [Aramaic]). The Assyrian a=shipu means the same... in Dan 1:20 )ashsha4p|&lt;m are parallel to charTummiym (magicians, q.v.), while in 2:2 they are also grouped with the mekashshep|&lt;m (sorcerers) and kas8d|&lt;m (Chaldeans). The Aramaic word ga4zer|&lt;n (soothsayers/astrologers) in the lists of Dan 4:7, 5:7, and 11 is the equivalent of the Heb mekashshep|&lt;m used elsewhere. IVPC: The second term refers to the Mesopotamian specialist in exorcism: defending against threatening messages in the omens or in dreams. The latter’s skills include identifying the threatening sign, determining a course of action to avert the evil, and performing apotropaic rituals and reciting incantations to turn aside the danger. Sickness was often included in the group of threatening signs, so the exorcist was counted among the "health care professionals" of Babylonian society.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) charTummiym: soothsayer-priests led the worship"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) charTummiym: soothsayer-priests led the worship of the gods and they recognized signs of the future. IVPC: The first term used here refers to Egyptian dream interpreters. It is the same word used in Genesis 41:8 and Exodus 7:11. The Babylonians were known to include Egyptian dream interpreters among their court advisors.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ais Daniel jadi pagawe di istana tarús-tarús, sampe taon partama yang raja Kores pegang parenta di Babel.<bt>So then Daniel became an official in the palace continually until the first year in which raja Kores held rule in Babel. [TEXT: here in 1:21 it says “1st year of Cyrus”. In 10:1 it says “3rd year of Cyrus”.] [TB: Kores.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 605-539, same length of time"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 605-539, same length of time as the exile. Chapter 10 dates it to the third year, 537.</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:21" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Andia, taon 539 SM (Sebelum Masehi). Dong angkat sang dia taon 605 SM, jadi Daniel pegang itu tugas 65 taon.<bt>That is, the year 539 SM (Before Messiah). They elevated/appointed him in the year 605 SM, so Daniel held that responsibility for 65 years. [EXEG: NLT note, CEV note, IVP, (TH says 538)]</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Raja Nebukadnesar pung mimpi<bt>Raja Nebukadnesar's dream</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="2" />
      <v n="1" />Waktu raja Nebukadnesar su pegang parenta dua taon di Babel, ju dia mimpi. Ma dia pung mimpi buruk dong maen ganggu sang dia, sampe dia sonde bisa sonu sadiki ju.<bt>When raja Nebukadnesar had ruled for two years in Babel, he dreamed. But his nightmares/bad dreams kept bothering/disturbing him, to the point that he could not sleep soundly even a little. [EXEG: Heb. is plural “dreamed dreams” here and in vs.2, implying a series of dreams. Vs. 3 is sg.] [DISCOURSE/EXEG: vs. 2-12 is all about the king demanding not only that they interpret his dream, but that they tell him WHAT he dreamed. So either a) he is testing them, or b) he can't remember exactly what he dreamed but nevertheless knows they are very disturbing. IVP (at 2:5-9) and HCE favour b. TH discusses both. NET note favours a. It is possible that he uses his inability to not remember the contents to test the legitimacy of his seers (BOTH a &amp; b).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nihyətow (hyh nif): was gone."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nihyətow (hyh nif): was gone. BDB occur, come to pass, be done, be brought about; be done, be finished, be gone</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shnatow: his sleep"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shnatow: his sleep</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ruwchow: his mind? his spirit?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ruwchow: his mind? his spirit?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vattitpaʕem (pʕm hitp fem): it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vattitpaʕem (pʕm hitp fem): it was disturbed</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəlomowt: dreams. Series of dreams?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəlomowt: dreams. Series of dreams? UBS: The focus of the passage is on one particular dream that caused difficulty. Hence the singular is used in TEV, NAB, and NJV. NJB, on the other hand, highlights the plural by translating "had a series of dreams." But it is probably better to use the singular form in most languages. NET: Heb "dreamed dreams." The plural is used here and in v. 2, but the singular in v. 3. The plural "dreams" has been variously explained. Some interpreters take the plural as denoting an indefinite singular (so GKC §124o). But it may be that it is describing a stream of related dreams, or a dream state, an understanding that is reflected in the translation adopted above. See further, Montgomery, Daniel (ICC), 142.</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Jadi raja suru pange sang dia pung orang pintar, dia pung tukang suanggi, dia pung tukang rai-rai, deng orang Kasdim yang pintar lia bintang dong samua ko datang bakumpul. Te dia pung batúl, dong tu yang bisa kasi tau orang pung mimpi pung arti. Ju dong datang bakumpul di raja pung muka.<bt>So (consequently) the raja summoned his wise/knowledgable people [Note: Kupang term also refers to those involved with the occult.], his sorcerers, his diviners, and the Kasdim people skilled at observing stars, for all of them to come and gather. Cuz (elaboration) in actual fact, these were the ones who could/should explain the meaning of a person's dream. And they came and gathered before the raja. [EXEG: Chaldeans following NLT note, TB, TH, HCE.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhaggiyd"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhaggiyd</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kasdiym: Chaldeans. NET: The term"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kasdiym: Chaldeans. NET: The term Chaldeans (Hebrew kasdim) is used in the Book of Daniel both in an ethnic sense and, as here, to refer to a caste of Babylonian wise men and astrologers.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məkhasshəfiym: UBS: The Aramaic word"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məkhasshəfiym: UBS: The Aramaic word ga4zer|&lt;n (soothsayers/astrologers) in the lists of Dan 4:7, 5:7, and 11 is the equivalent of the Heb mekashshep|&lt;m used elsewhere.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'asshafiym: sorcerers"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'asshafiym: sorcerers</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'asshafiym: conjurers, enchanters. TWOT: All"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'asshafiym: conjurers, enchanters. TWOT: All occurrences are in the book of Daniel (1:20 and 2:2 [Heb]; 2:10, 27; 4:4; 5:7, 11, 15 [Aramaic]). The Assyrian a=shipu means the same... in Dan 1:20 'asshafiym are parallel to charTummiym (magicians, q.v.), while in 2:2 they are also grouped with the mekashshep|&lt;m (sorcerers) and kas8d|&lt;m (Chaldeans). IVPC: The second term refers to the Mesopotamian specialist in exorcism: defending against threatening messages in the omens or in dreams. The latter’s skills include identifying the threatening sign, determining a course of action to avert the evil, and performing apotropaic rituals and reciting incantations to turn aside the danger. Sickness was often included in the group of threatening signs, so the exorcist was counted among the "health care professionals" of Babylonian society.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) charTummiym (1:20): soothsayer-priests led the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) charTummiym (1:20): soothsayer-priests led the worship of the gods and they recognized signs of the future. IVPC: The first term used here refers to Egyptian dream interpreters. It is the same word used in Genesis 41:8 and Exodus 7:11. The Babylonians were known to include Egyptian dream interpreters among their court advisors. TWOT: This word, describing some variety of occultist, appears in both Hebrew (h[art[umm|&lt;m) and Aramaic (h[art[umm|&lt;n). It is the word for Egyptian "magicians" (Gen 41:8, 24; Ex 7:11, 22; 8:3, 14-15; 9:11) and for the Babylonian "magicians" (Dan 1:20; 2:2, 10, 27; 4:4, 6; 5:11).</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Sampe deng sampe ju, raja omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini. Beta mimpi. Ma itu mimpi buruk maen datang ganggu sang beta tarús, te beta sonde tau itu mimpi pung arti apa. Tolong doo!&gt;&gt;<bt>When they arrived, the raja spoke saying, &lt;&lt;It's like this. I dreamed. But that nightmare/bad dream kept bothering/disturbing me, cuz (elaboration) I did not know the meaning of that dream. Please help!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ruwchiy: my spirit"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ruwchiy: my spirit</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tippaʕem (pʕm nif): my spirit"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tippaʕem (pʕm nif): my spirit is disturbed</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Itu orang Kasdim yang pintar lia bintang dong manyao pake bahasa Aram bilang, &lt;&lt;Biar ko bapa raja idop tarús! Bapa tolong kasi tau sang botong bapa pung mimpi pung isi dolo. Te botong ni bapa raja pung hamba dong. Jadi, kasi tau dia pung isi sang botong doo, ko biar botong bisa kasi tau bapa pung mimpi pung arti sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>The Kasdim people who are skilled at observing stars responded using the Aram language saying, &lt;&lt;May father king live forever! Father (=you) please tell us-exc the contents of your dream first. Cuz (elaboration) we here are father raja's (=your) servants. So (consequently) tell us the contents first, so that we can tell you the meaning of the dream.&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE (STYLE): Aram. `avdayikh (q. `avdakh): your servants. NRSV: Tell your servants the dream. NLT1: Tell us the dream. NRSV reflects the style of the middle eastern courts, which also reflects the style for using classical Malay and local lgs when addressing sultans and rajas in island SE Asia and Timor. NLT reflects modern English style. We retain the more formal style here as appropriate to the sociolinguistic context. TH] [TEXT: Original writing shifts from Hebrew to Aramaic from the middle of 2:4 until 7:28.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nəchawwe': explain, point out. TWOT:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nəchawwe': explain, point out. TWOT: The traditional English translation of the word as "show" (or "shew") does not emphasize the fact that not only is the king seeking to be shown the dream which he insisted the professionals must recount to him, but he is also demanding an appropriate interpretation of that dream.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) pishra': interpretation of a dream"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) pishra': interpretation of a dream</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕavdayikh (q. ʕavdakh): your servants"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕavdayikh (q. ʕavdakh): your servants</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chelma': dream"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chelma': dream</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əmar: tell"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əmar: tell</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəyiy (hy' peʕal imperv): may"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəyiy (hy' peʕal imperv): may you live</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:4" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan asli dari 2:4 sampe deng 7:28, dong tulis pake bahasa Aram, bukan pake bahasa Ibrani lai. Bahasa Aram deng bahasa Ibrani tu, satu rumpun bahasa.<bt>The original writings from 2:4 through until 7:28, they wrote using the Aram language, not using the Ibrani (=Hebrew) language anymore. The Aram language and the Ibrani language are from one language clump/cluster.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ma bapa raja kasi tau sang orang yang pintar lia bintang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Dengar bae-bae, te beta su putus bagini: kalo bosong sonde bisa kasi tau sang beta, beta pung mimpi pung isi, deng beta pung mimpi pung arti, na, nanti beta suru orang ko potong buang bosong pung kaki-tangan, ais bongkar buang bosong pung ruma sampe sonde ada sisa ju.<bt>But the raja told the people skilled at observing stars saying, &lt;&lt;Listen carefully, cuz (elaboration) I have already made a decision as follows: if you-pl are not able to tell me the contents of my dream and the meaning of my dream, na, I will order people to cut off your feet-hands (can also be legs-arms), and tear apart your houses until there is nothing left. [EXEG: See discussion in TH re: meaning of Aram. 'azda': [the command] is promulgated by me. as “this is a public decree” (NRSV), or  “the decision is firm” or “the matter is irrevocable” (cf. NAB, NIV, TEV, CEV, NLT). The Kupang rendering covers both of the latter options.] [EXEG: last clause trying to capture the fuller sense of Aram. nəwaliy: ‘rubbish pile’ to better reflect the king's attitude here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yitsamuwn (sym hitp): BDB be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yitsamuwn (sym hitp): BDB be made, be set, be laid</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nəwaliy: rubbish pile"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nəwaliy: rubbish pile</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vatteykhown: your (pl) houses"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vatteykhown: your (pl) houses</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) titʕavduwn (F): BDB be made"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) titʕavduwn (F): BDB be made into; be done, be wrought, be performed, be executed, be carried out</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) damiyn: members of the body,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) damiyn: members of the body, limbs</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) uwfishrehh: and its interpretation"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) uwfishrehh: and its interpretation</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) təhowdʕuwnnaniy (afel): you (pl) will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) təhowdʕuwnnaniy (afel): you (pl) will cause me to know</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) la': not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) la': not</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hen: if"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hen: if</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'azda': [the command] is promulgated"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'azda': [the command] is promulgated by me</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) minniy: from me?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) minniy: from me?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) milləta' (məlal): word, thing; like"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) milləta' (məlal): word, thing; like Heb dbr</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləkhasdaye' (q. ləkhasda'ey): Chaldeans as"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləkhasdaye' (q. ləkhasda'ey): Chaldeans as astrologers</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Ma kalo bosong bisa kasi tau beta pung mimpi pung isi, deng beta pung mimpi pung arti, na, nanti beta kasi sang bosong harta bam-banya, ju angka bosong pung nama di rakyat dong pung muka, ko biar dong hormat sang bosong. Jadi, tolong kasi tau sang beta, beta pung mimpi pung isi, deng beta pung mimpi pung arti. Sakarang ju!&gt;&gt;<bt>But if you are able to tell me the contents of my dream, and the meaning of my dream, na, I will give you much wealth/things, and elevate your names before the populace, so that they respect you. So (consequently) please tell me the contents of my dream and the meaning of my dream. Right now!&gt;&gt; [EXEG: ‘gifts’ and ‘rewards’ treated as synonyms here and underdifferentiated following NLT, CEV, HCE, TH.] [DISCOURSE: Last sentence reflecting higher level discourse pragmatics--the pressure is mounting. Note CEV ‘now’ and NLT ‘just’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hachəwoniy (afel): make known to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hachəwoniy (afel): make known to me, interpret to me, explain to me</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qadamay: from before me"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qadamay: from before me</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) təqabbəluwn: you will receive"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) təqabbəluwn: you will receive</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) saggiy': great, much, many"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) saggiy': great, much, many</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) viyqar: and honor, majesty"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) viyqar: and honor, majesty</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nəvizbah: reward"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nəvizbah: reward</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mattənan: gift"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mattənan: gift</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) təhachəwon (chwh afel): you (pl)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) təhachəwon (chwh afel): you (pl) will make known</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ju dong omong ulang lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Bae. Te bapa ni, raja. Ma tolong kasi tau itu mimpi sang botong dolo, ko biar botong bisa kasi tau dia pung arti sang bapa raja.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they spoke again saying, &lt;&lt;Fine. Cuz (elaboration) you are the raja. But please tell us the dream first, so that we can explain its meaning to father raja.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tinyanuwt: a second time"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tinyanuwt: a second time</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕənow: they answered, responded"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕənow: they answered, responded</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8-9" />Ma raja manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta su tau parsís bosong ada coba mau bekin karmana. Te bosong ni, cuma buang-buang waktu sa, ko biar jang kaná itu hukuman. Beta su putus, deng su parenta sang bosong. Jadi, kalo bosong sonde kasi tau beta pung mimpi pung arti apa, na, cuma ada satu hukuman kasi sang bosong samua. Te bosong su ator siasat ko mau tipu ame sang beta so'al ini mimpi dong. Bosong mau putar-balek sang beta, te bosong pikir nanti beta cari jalan laen. Bagini: kalo bosong kasi tau itu mimpi pung isi, baru beta tau bilang, bosong bisa kasi tau itu mimpi pung arti ju.&gt;&gt;<bt>But the raja responded saying, &lt;&lt;I know exactly what you are trying to do. Cuz (elaboration) you are just trying to waste time, so that you do not get punished. I have already decided, and have already commanded you. So (consequently), if you do not tell me the meaning of my dream, na, there is only one sentence/punishment for all of you. Cuz (elaboration) you have plotted/schemed together to deceive2 me about these dreams. You want to con/deceive1 me, cuz (elaboration) you think then I will look for a different way. It's like this: if you tell the contents of the dream, only.then will I know that you are able to tell the meaning of the dream also.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: ‘one verdict’ = one outcome, the same punishment for all of you. NRSV, HCE, TH.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) təhachəwunnaniy: you will interpret for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) təhachəwunnaniy: you will interpret for me</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) pishrehh: the interpretation, its interpretation"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) pishrehh: the interpretation, its interpretation</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'indaʕ: I will know. IVPC:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'indaʕ: I will know. IVPC: An alternative is that Nebuchadnezzar felt that the dream was so ominous that it could too easily be used as a mechanism for subversion against the throne... He sought evidence that the interpretation represented the gods’ message rather than human agenda by requiring that the gods reveal the dream to the interpreter.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) lahen: therefore; except"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) lahen: therefore; except</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yishtanne' (itpaal): it will change"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yishtanne' (itpaal): it will change</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'iddana': its time"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'iddana': its time</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕad: up to, until"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕad: up to, until</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qadamay: from before me"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qadamay: from before me</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləme'mar: to say"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləme'mar: to say</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hazmintuwn 'you have come to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hazmintuwn 'you have come to a decision' (q. hizdəmintuwn 'you have agreed together')</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shəchiytah: corrupt"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shəchiytah: corrupt</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) khidvah: lie, apposition to millah"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) khidvah: lie, apposition to millah</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) millah: the affair, the matter"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) millah: the affair, the matter</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) datkhown (dat): judgment on you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) datkhown (dat): judgment on you (pl)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chədah: one, the same"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chədah: one, the same</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) təhowdʕunnaniy: you cause me to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) təhowdʕunnaniy: you cause me to know</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) milləta': the matter"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) milləta': the matter</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'azda': is promulgated, decreed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'azda': is promulgated, decreed</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəzeytown: you see, perceive"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəzeytown: you see, perceive</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qəvel: because. TWOT: front, in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qəvel: because. TWOT: front, in front of, before, because of; when followed by diy, because that. This very common Aramaic preposition is often preceded by le or kol. It is more often used for causation than for mere position, which is usually qodam (q.v.).</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) zavniyn: buy"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) zavniyn: buy</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'antuwn: you plural"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'antuwn: you plural</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕiddana': time. TWOT: Two basic"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕiddana': time. TWOT: Two basic meanings are equally a "point" in time or a "span" of time.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) diy: which, relative pronoun"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) diy: which, relative pronoun</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'ənah: I, emphatic"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'ənah: I, emphatic</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) min-yattsiyv: BDB certain, true; with"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) min-yattsiyv: BDB certain, true; with min: of a truth.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="HCE has space before last full"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">HCE has space before last full stop. I reported this.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Ju orang yang pintar lia bintang dong kasi tau sang bapa raja bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini, bapa. Sonde ada satu orang ju yang bisa kasi tau bagitu. Di anteru dunya ju sonde ada. Dia pung batúl bagini: dari dolu-dolu sampe sakarang sonde parná ada satu raja ju yang minta bagitu dari dia pung orang pintar, dia pung tukang suanggi, ko, dia pung orang yang pintar lia bintang dong. Biar itu raja pung nama deng kuasa luar biasa ju, sonde parná ada. Kalo kasi tau satu mimpi pung arti sa, bisa. Ma kalo kasi tau satu mimpi pung isi, sonde mungkin, bapa!<bt>Then the people skilled at observing the stars told the raja saying, &lt;&lt;It's like this, father. There is nobody who can tell like that. In the entire world there is none. In truth, from long ago until now there has never been a single raja who has requested like that from his wise people, his sorcerers, or his people skilled at observing stars. Even if a king had extraordinary name/reputation and power/authority, there has never been one. Telling the meaning of a dream, is possible/we can. But telling the contents of a dream, is not possible, father/sir!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) khasday: Chaldeans, astrologers"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) khasday: Chaldeans, astrologers</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'ashaf: 1:20, 2:2 can [block]"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'ashaf: 1:20, 2:2 can [block] wen somebody put kahuna</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) charəTTom: TWOT: magician-astrologer. Usage similar"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) charəTTom: TWOT: magician-astrologer. Usage similar to the Hebrew (q.v.). It may be an Egyptian loan word through the Hebrew. 1:20, 2:2 can tell wat da dreams mean</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shə' el: he required, ask"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shə' el: he required, ask</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) dənah: this"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) dənah: this</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shalliyT: having mastery, authority. TWOT:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shalliyT: having mastery, authority. TWOT: This root appears also in Hebrew, where it is called late by BDB.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rav: great"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rav: great</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kol-qavel: because. TWOT: front, in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kol-qavel: because. TWOT: front, in front of, before, because of; when followed by d|&lt;, because that. This very common Aramaic preposition is often preceded by le or kol. It is more often used for causation than for mere position, which is usually qo6da4m (q.v.).</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhachəwayah: to explain, interpret. TWOT:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhachəwayah: to explain, interpret. TWOT: The basic meaning of the root in Daniel (it does not occur elsewhere) is "to explain" or "point out." Both Pael and Haphel (or Aphel) forms are employed, but with no distinction in meaning.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yuwkhal: is able to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yuwkhal: is able to</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) millat: the matter of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) millat: the matter of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yabbeshta': on the earth, dry"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yabbeshta': on the earth, dry ground</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'iytay: there is [not]"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'iytay: there is [not]</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qadam: before (time or position)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qadam: before (time or position)</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Bapa raja pung minta sang botong tu, talalu barát! Sonde ada satu orang ju yang bisa kasi tau bagitu. Cuma dewa-dewi dong sa yang bisa kasi tau bagitu, ma dong sonde idop di manusia pung teng-tenga.&gt;&gt;<bt>Father raja's request to us-exc is too heavy/difficult! There is not one person who can explain like that. Only the gods are the ones who can explain like that, but they do not live in the midst of humans.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'iytowhiy: they are not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'iytowhiy: they are not</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) bisra': flesh (= people)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) bisra': flesh (= people)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mədarhown: dwelling"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mədarhown: dwelling</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəchawwinnahh: who can interpret it,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəchawwinnahh: who can interpret it, explain it</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'achəran: another"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'achəran: another</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yaqqiyrah: difficult"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yaqqiyrah: difficult</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Dong pung omong tu, bekin raja mara batúl. Ais dia suru dia pung orang dong ko bunu bekin mati abis samua orang pintar di Babel.<bt>What they said made the raja extremely angry. So then he ordered his people to kill off all the wise people in Babel.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chakkiymey: TWOT: wise men. Used"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chakkiymey: TWOT: wise men. Used mostly of the court astrologers in Daniel.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) howvadah ('bd hofal): destroy. IVPC:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) howvadah ('bd hofal): destroy. IVPC: The annihilation of entire groups suspected of conspiracy or incompetence is all too familiar in the ancient world. Herodotus records a couple of instances during the Persian period.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) saggiy': very, much"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) saggiy': very, much</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qətsaf: he became furious"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qətsaf: he became furious</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) bənaS: he became angry"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) bənaS: he became angry</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) dənah: this"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) dənah: this</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kol-qavel: because"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kol-qavel: because</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Raja pung putusan su kaluar. Ais ju dong siap-siap ko mau bunu bekin mati samua orang pintar di Babel. Andia ko tantara dong pi cari-cari sang Daniel deng dia pung kawan dong ju.<bt>The decision of the king had gone forth. So then they prepared to kill all the wise people in Babel. That is why the soldiers went looking for Daniel and his friends also. [EXEG: Q: who went looking for Daniel? A: See referential info and note in 2:14 ‘execution squad’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) End of P section."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) End of P section.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhitqəTalah (hitpeʕel): to be slain"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhitqəTalah (hitpeʕel): to be slain</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chavrowhiy: his friends, comrades. TWOT:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chavrowhiy: his friends, comrades. TWOT: Usage similar to Hebrew.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vəʕow: he was on the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vəʕow: he was on the point of, ran the risk of (NOT "sent to find")</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mitqaTTəliyn (partcpl pl): being slain"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mitqaTTəliyn (partcpl pl): being slain (particple as historical present? NET: The Aramaic participle is used here to express the imminent future.)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nefqat: was issued"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nefqat: was issued</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) data': the decree. TWOT: A"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) data': the decree. TWOT: A Persian loan word used also in the Hebrew of Ezra and in Esther.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Itu waktu, raja pung komandán yang parenta tantara yang hukum kasi mati orang, nama Ariok. Ma Daniel ju pintar baca orang deng pintar omong alus. Andia ko waktu Ariok dong muncul datang ko mau hukum kasi mati Daniel deng dia pung kawan dong,<bt>At that time, the raja's commander who commanded the soldiers who killed people was named Ariok. But Daniel was also skilled at reading people (character) and skilled a speaking finely (diplomatically). That is why, when Ariok (collective) came to carry out the death sentence on Daniel and his friends, [EXEG: Aram: Tabbachayya': chief executioner (NRSV, JEG).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nəfaq (partcpl): going out, about"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nəfaq (partcpl): going out, about to go out</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Tabbachayya': guard? execution squad, like"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Tabbachayya': guard? execution squad, like Potiphar in Genesis 37:36: da head guy fo da army guys dat kill da prisonas dat da king like kill.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Təʕem: taste, judgment, command. TWOT:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Təʕem: taste, judgment, command. TWOT: The Hebrew is similar, but the meaning "command" is rare in Hebrew.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕeTa': counsel"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕeTa': counsel</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hətiyv (twb B): return. TWOT:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hətiyv (twb B): return. TWOT: Used, as is the Hebrew cognate shuwb, to include restoration and returning an answer. The common Hebrew adverbial usage of doing something again ("return and do") is not witnessed in BA.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'ədayin: then"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'ədayin: then</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />ju Daniel tanya sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa. Beta tau bapa dong karjá iko bapa raja pung parenta. Ma beta sonde mangarti akurang ko bapa raja kasi kaluar ini putusan yang talalu karás ni. Bapa Ariok tolong carita kasi beta ini parkara pung akar dolo.&gt;&gt; Ais ju Ariok kasi tau samua-samua sang Daniel.<bt>Daniel asked him, &lt;&lt;Father/sir. I know that father (=you) are carrying out the raja's command. But I don't understand why the raja has put out this decision that is so harsh/severe. Father Ariok please narrate for me the root/source/cause of this matter.&gt;&gt; So then Ariok explained everything to Daniel. [EXEG: Aram meaning disputed. Strongest sources favour a) ‘harsh, severe’, but some think it could also mean b) ‘urgent’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) howdaʕ: caused to know"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) howdaʕ: caused to know</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'ədayin: then"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'ədayin: then</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məhachətsəfah (chtsp partcpl fem): harsh,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məhachətsəfah (chtsp partcpl fem): harsh, severe</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) data': issued the decree"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) data': issued the decree</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shalliyTa': person in authority; Sir"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shalliyTa': person in authority; Sir</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Dengar abis sang Ariok pung carita, ju Daniel pi mangada sang raja bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini. Bapa tolong kasi beta waktu sadiki dolo, ko biar beta bisa kasi tau bapa raja pung mimpi pung arti.&gt;&gt;<bt>After hearing Ariok's story, Daniel went before the raja saying, &lt;&lt;It's like this. Father please give me a little time, so that I can tell father king (=you) the meaning of your dream.&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: direct speech following RL patterns. See also CEV.]</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cot\co01346c.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Raja manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Neu.&gt;&gt;<bt>The raja responded saying, &lt;&lt;Neu. (=fine, OK)&gt;&gt; [EXEG: implicit to explicit from vs. 17-18, HCE also makes it explicit.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) End of P section"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) End of P section</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhachəweyah: to interpret it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhachəweyah: to interpret it</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yinten-lehh: allow him, give him"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yinten-lehh: allow him, give him time, set a date</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) zəman: time"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) zəman: time</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vəʕah min-: made a request"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vəʕah min-: made a request of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕal (ʕll): went in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕal (ʕll): went in</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan buka ame raja pung mimpi sang Daniel [\s2]<bt>God2 reveals the raja's dream to Daniel [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Dengar bagitu, ju Daniel pulang. Ais dia carita samua-samua sang dia pung tamán dong, andia Hananya, Misael, deng Asarya.<bt>Hearing that, Daniel went home. Then he narrated everything to his friends, that is Hananya, Misael, and Asarya. [DISCOURSE: CEV replaces names with “3 friends”. Probably not a good referent tracking strategy since they have been off-stage from 1:19 and over a span of several years of the story.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) howdaʕ: BDB let someone know,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) howdaʕ: BDB let someone know, communicate, inform, cause to know</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əzal"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əzal</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Dia ju minta sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Tolong sambayang ko minta Tuhan Allah di langit kasi tunju Dia pung rasa kasian sang kotong, deng buka kasi tau itu mimpi yang tasambunyi sang kotong. Deng bagitu, raja sonde hukum kasi mati abis sang kotong deng orang pintar yang laen dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>He also requested of them saying, &lt;&lt;Please pray to ask God in heaven to show His pity/mercy to us-inc, and reveal telling that hidden dream to us. In that way, the raja will not death punish us and the other knowledgable people.&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: direct speech following RL discourse patterns. See also CEV.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shə'ar: remaining, other"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shə'ar: remaining, other</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəhovduwn ('bd B): will destroy"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəhovduwn ('bd B): will destroy</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) razah: secret"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) razah: secret</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləmivʕe' (bʕh inf): requesting, seeking"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləmivʕe' (bʕh inf): requesting, seeking</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rachəmiyn: compassion"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rachəmiyn: compassion</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cot\co01347c.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Itu malam ju, Tuhan kasi tunju itu rahasia sang Daniel, tingka ke dalam mimpi. Lia bagitu, ju Daniel angka nae puji sang Tuhan Allah di langit,<bt>That night, God2 showed that secret to Daniel as if in a dream. Seeing that, Daniel lifted up praise to God in heaven, [EXEG: Aramaic: ‘a vision of the night’ is taken as ‘that very night’ as per TH, NLT, TEV, HCE.] [EXEG: Aramaic: barikh: ‘he blessed’. In these RL lgs, one cannot ‘bless’ God, because that is asking a higher authority to do good things to someone of lower status/condition. But the Aramaic, Hebrew, and Greek terms often translated as ‘bless’ often mean ‘say good things about’ or ‘praise’. (see any scholarly source.)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shmayya': heaven"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shmayya': heaven</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) barikh: he blessed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) barikh: he blessed</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) gəliy (glh peil passive): was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) gəliy (glh peil passive): was revealed, disclose</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chezwa': the vision, apparition"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chezwa': the vision, apparition</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />bilang,<bt>saying</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Beta mau angka nae puji sang Tuhan Allah sonde putus-putus!<bt>&lt;&lt;I want to lift up praises to God without ceasing!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Te biar karmana ju, ma Tuhan tau jalan kaluar yang pas.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) no matter what, God2 knows the just.right way out [of difficulty].</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng Tuhan pung kuasa mampu karjá samua-samua.<bt>And God2's power/authority is able to do/work/accomplish everything.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) gəvuwrta': might"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) gəvuwrta': might</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chakhməta': wisdom"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chakhməta': wisdom</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕalma': BDB perpetuity, antiquity, for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕalma': BDB perpetuity, antiquity, for ever</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shmehh (shwm): his name"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shmehh (shwm): his name</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) lehəwe' (hwh): may he be."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) lehəwe' (hwh): may he be. TWOT: A peculiarity of the Aramaic is that in the imperfect a lamedh is used instead of the usual preformative yodh. Also in Aramaic the verb ha6wa= is often used with a participle to make a periphrastic tense expressing continuous and habitual action (e.g. Dan 6:10 [A 11], "as he used to do formerly").</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="21" />Tuhan ator waktu deng musim,<bt>God2 arranges the time and the seasons,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko biar pas deng Tuhan pung maksud.<bt>so that they fit.perfectly with God2's plans/intentions/purpose.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan yang angka nae raja saparu ko dong pegang parenta,<bt>God2 is the one who elevates/appoints some raja's so they govern/rule,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng angka buang raja saparu ko dong jang pegang parenta lai.<bt>and deposes (lit: lift throwing away) some raja's so they no longer govern/rule.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan yang kasi orang yang pintar dong,<bt>God2 is the one who gives/allows knowledgable/wise people,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko biar dong mangarti banya hal iko Tuhan pung pikiran,<bt>so that they understand many things according to God2's thinking, [EXEG: this is our normal fuller explication of ‘wisdom’.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">deng tau dia pung jalan kaluar yang bae.<bt>and know the good way(s) out [of difficulty]. [DISCOURSE: Aram. parallelism conflated, since we don't have the lexemes to make it work literally. The two are taken as synonymous.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) viynah: insight"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) viynah: insight</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləyadʕey: to the ones who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləyadʕey: to the ones who know</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mandəʕa': knowledge, ability to know"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mandəʕa': knowledge, ability to know things</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chakkiymiym: wise people"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chakkiymiym: wise people</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yahev: he gives"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yahev: he gives</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) malkhiyn: kings"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) malkhiyn: kings</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məhaqeym (qwm hafel): he sets"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məhaqeym (qwm hafel): he sets up, establishes kingdoms</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məhaʕdeh (afel): he removes, deposes"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məhaʕdeh (afel): he removes, deposes</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) zimnayya': BDB appointed time, time"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) zimnayya': BDB appointed time, time</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕiddanayya': times. TWOT: Dan 2:9"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕiddanayya': times. TWOT: Dan 2:9 employs (idda4n to mean "situation" (NASB), i.e., circumstances. Later, in his prayer praising God for revealing the king's dream to him, Daniel proclaims that God is the one who changes "times and epochs" ((idda4ndnayya4) wezimnayya4) v. 21). In this context, (idda4n refers to far more than the brief moment of one tough circumstance comparable to that facing the would-be wise men of King Nebuchadnezzar. Rather this is testimony to the sovereign power of God to control the sweep of history. UBS: the verb used here expresses somewhat indirectly the idea that God has authority over time and history. This is in contrast with the Babylonian idea of history, which seemed to indicate that the gods could do nothing to modify its course.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məhashne' (shn' B): the one"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məhashne' (shn' B): the one who changes</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="22" />Tuhan yang buka kasi tunju hal yang tasambunyi,<bt>God2 is the one who opens/unveils/reveals things that are hidden,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">yang susa ko orang mangarti.<bt>which are difficult for people to understand.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan ju yang tau samua barang yang ada dalam galáp,<bt>God2 is also the one who knows everything that is in the dark (can be literal or figurative--usually about ignorance [things that are unkown or unseen], but sometimes about evil.)</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal taráng kaluar datang dari Tuhan.<bt>because light comes forth out from God2.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shəre'"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shəre'</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nəhiyra' 'light' (q. nəhowra')"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nəhiyra' 'light' (q. nəhowra')</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəshowkha': darkness"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəshowkha': darkness</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məSatrata': things that are hidden,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məSatrata': things that are hidden, removed from sight</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕammiyqata': deep (Holladay impenetrable)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕammiyqata': deep (Holladay impenetrable)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) gale': he reveals"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) gale': he reveals</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="23" />Tuhan jadi beta pung nene-moyang pung Tuhan Allah.<bt>God2 is the Lord God of my ancestors (doublet).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Beta mau angka nae puji deng sukur sang Tuhan,<bt>I want to lift praise and gratitude to God2,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">te Tuhan yang kasi beta mangarti banya hal,<bt>cuz (elaboration) God2 is the one who give me/makes me/allows me to understand many things,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">deng Tuhan yang kasi beta kuasa.<bt>and God2 is the one who gives me power/authority.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Beta su sambayang minta Tuhan ko buka kasi tau sang beta raja pung mimpi pung isi,<bt>I have prayed asking God2 to reveal to me the contents of raja's dream,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng raja pung mimpi pung arti.<bt>and the meaning/interpretation of raja's dream.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ju Tuhan balas botong pung sambayang,<bt>And God2 has answered/responded to our-exc prayer,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng kasi tau itu samua-samua sang botong.<bt>and told/explained everything to us.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Andia ko beta angka nae puji deng sukur bam-banya sang Tuhan!&gt;&gt;<bt>That is why I lift so much praise and gratitude to God2!&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: verse repackaged for RL logic.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) howdaʕtena' (paʕʕel): you have made"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) howdaʕtena' (paʕʕel): you have made known to us</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) millat: the matter of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) millat: the matter of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) bəʕeyna' (bʕh pəʕal): we request"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) bəʕeyna' (bʕh pəʕal): we request of you</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) khəʕ an: at this time"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) khəʕ an: at this time</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəhavt: you give"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəhavt: you give</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) gəvuwrta': might"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) gəvuwrta': might</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chokhməta': wisdom"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chokhməta': wisdom</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'ənah: I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'ənah: I</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məshabbach (paʕʕel): praising"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məshabbach (paʕʕel): praising</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məhowde' (hofʕel): the one who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məhowde' (hofʕel): the one who is praising. UBS: here the two verbs reinforce each other, but the first carries the particular sense of expressing gratitude, and it is good to bring this out in the translation.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Daniel buka ame raja pung mimpi<bt>Daniel reveals/explains the raja's dream</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Tuhan kasi tunju bagitu, andia ko Daniel pi cari Ariok. Te dia tu, orang yang raja su kasi tugas ko bunu bekin mati sang samua orang pintar dong di Babel. Sampe deng sampe ju, Daniel kasi tau sang Ariok bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini, bapa. Bapa dong jang bunu bekin mati orang pintar dong di Babel dolo. Antar sang beta pi mangada sang bapa raja dolo, ko biar beta bisa kasi tau dia pung mimpi pung arti.&gt;&gt;<bt>God2 showed/revealed like that, so that is why Daniel went to look for Ariok. Cuz (elaboration) he was the person the raja had tasked with killing all the knowledgable people in/of Babel. Upon arriving, Daniel told Ariok saying, &lt;&lt;It's like this, father/sir. Father (=you) should not kill the knowledgable people in/of Babel first/right away/before doing something else. Take/escort me to go before the raja first, so that I can explain the meaning of his dream. [DISCOURSE: Tail-head linkage with reduced adverbial clause in RL to reflect Heb ‘because of all that’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) End of S section."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) End of S section.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əchawwe': I will show"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əchawwe': I will show</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) təhowved: [don't] kill"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) təhowved: [don't] kill</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) khen: thus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) khen: thus</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əzal: he went"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əzal: he went</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləchakkiymey: the wise men of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləchakkiymey: the wise men of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhowvadah ('bd hafʕel): kill, destroy"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhowvadah ('bd hafʕel): kill, destroy</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) manniy (mnh paʕʕel): whom he"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) manniy (mnh paʕʕel): whom he had appointed</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ju Ariok langsung antar bawa sang Daniel ko mangada sang raja bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa raja! Beta su dapa satu orang yang bisa buka kasi tau bapa raja pung mimpi pung arti. Dia tu, orang dari da'era Yahuda, yang kaná usir dari sana pi sini dari dolu.&gt;&gt;<bt>So Ariok straightaway escorted taking Daniel to go before the raja saying, &lt;&lt;Father raja! I have found a person who can reveal explaining the meaning of father raja's dream. He is a person from the region of Yahuda, who was exiled/cast out from there to here from before/long ago.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) galuwta': exiles"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) galuwta': exiles</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) gəvar: a man, a certain"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) gəvar: a man, a certain one</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hashkachat (hafʕel): I have found"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hashkachat (hafʕel): I have found</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hanʕel (ʕll hafʕel): he brought,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hanʕel (ʕll hafʕel): he brought, caused to go</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hitbəhalah (hitpeʕel inf): in a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hitbəhalah (hitpeʕel inf): in a hurry</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Tarús raja tanya sang Daniel (yang pung nama laen, Beltasasar) bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl, ko? Lu bisa kasi tau beta pung mimpi pung isi, deng beta pung mimpi pung arti ju, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then3 the raja asked Daniel (whose other name was Beltasasar) saying, &lt;&lt;Is that right/true? You-sg are able to explain the contents of my dream and the meaning of my dream, right?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəzeyt (chzh paʕel): I saw"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəzeyt (chzh paʕel): I saw</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chelma': the dream"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chelma': the dream</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhowdaʕutaniy (ydʕ hafʕel inf): cause"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhowdaʕutaniy (ydʕ hafʕel inf): cause me to know</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kahel (peʕal partcpl): one who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kahel (peʕal partcpl): one who can</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ha'iytayikh (q. ha'iytakh): is there"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ha'iytayikh (q. ha'iytakh): is there with you? can you?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ju Daniel manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Yang batúl bagini: sonde ada satu orang ju yang bisa kasi tau apa yang bapa raja minta. Sonde ada satu orang pintar, ko tukang suanggi, ko tukang ilmu, ko tukang rai-rai yang bisa.<bt>Then Daniel responded saying, &lt;&lt;What is true is like this: there is not a single person who can tell what father raja is requesting. There is not a single wise/knowledgable person, or sorcerer, or magician, or diviner who is able. [EXEG: CEV is badly undertranslated here.] [NOTE to daughter translations: compare with 2:2 and 2:12. The 4th group is new here, but is repeated later in 4:7, 5:7,11.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhachəwayah (chwh hafʕel): show, explain"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhachəwayah (chwh hafʕel): show, explain</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) gazriyn: astrologers? those who consult"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) gazriyn: astrologers? those who consult the livers of sacrificed animals (haruspex)?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) charTummiyn: dream interpreters, 2:2"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) charTummiyn: dream interpreters, 2:2</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'ashfiyn: Mesopotamian specialist in exorcism:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'ashfiyn: Mesopotamian specialist in exorcism: defending against threatening messages in the omens or in dreams</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hakkiymiym: wise men"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hakkiymiym: wise men</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) sha'el: requesting"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) sha'el: requesting</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) razah: secret"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) razah: secret</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕaneh: answered"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕaneh: answered</Message></Annotation><v n="28" />Ma ada satu Tuhan Allah di sorga yang bisa buka rahasia deng kasi tau hal yang tasambunyi dong. Dia pung batúl, Dia su kasi tau memang sang bapa raja Nebukadnesar apa yang nanti mau jadi. Naa, sakarang biar ko beta kasi tau bapa raja pung mimpi pung isi. Biar ko beta kasi tau samua-samua yang bapa raja dapa lia dalam kapala otak waktu tidor di atas koi.<bt>But there is a Lord God in heaven who is able to reveal secrets and explain things that are hidden. In actual fact, He has already told ahead of time to father raja Nebukadnesar what is going to happen. Naa [+shift], now allow me to tell the contents of father raja's dream. Allow me to explain everything that father raja saw in your head brain (idiom) when sleeping/lying on (your) bed. [EXEG: CEV badly undertranslated.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) End of P section"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) End of P section</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chezwiy: visions, things seen"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chezwiy: visions, things seen</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'achəriyt: the future? the end"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'achəriyt: the future? the end of time? UBS: the Aramaic words used here correspond to the common Hebrew expression (Hos 3.5; Isa 2.2; Dan 10.14) and are normally taken as a reference to the end time. So it has been translated "at the end of this age" (NEB/REB) or "in the final days" (NJB). Other versions, however, use less precise terminology. Compare "in the future" (TEV) and "in days to come" (NAB and NIV).</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) lehəwe' (hwh): will happen. TWOT:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) lehəwe' (hwh): will happen. TWOT: A peculiarity of the Aramaic is that in the imperfect a lamedh is used instead of the usual preformative yodh.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) howdaʕ: he has let someone"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) howdaʕ: he has let someone know, communicated</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) raziyn: secrets"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) raziyn: secrets</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) gale' (partcpl): a revealer of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) gale' (partcpl): a revealer of mysteries</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) bəram: nevertheless"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) bəram: nevertheless</Message></Annotation><v n="29" />Te waktu bapa raja ada tidor, bapa mulai pikir-pikir so'al apa yang nanti mau jadi. Ma Tuhan Allah tu, yang bisa buka rahasia. Dia yang kasi tunju apa yang nanti mau jadi.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) when father raja was sleeping/lying there, father (=you) began to think about things that would happen. But God s the one who can open/reveal secrets. He is the one who showed what was/is going to happen.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Səliquw: they came up"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Səliquw: they came up</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) raʕyownakh: your thoughts, manaʕo"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) raʕyownakh: your thoughts, manaʕo</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'antah (q. 'ant): you sg"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'antah (q. 'ant): you sg masc</Message></Annotation><v n="30" />Dia su kasi tau sang beta bapa raja pung mimpi pung arti. Dia sonde bekin bagitu tagal beta lebe pintar dari orang laen yang idop. Dia kasi tau sang beta bagitu, ko biar bapa raja bisa dapa tau itu mimpi pung arti. Deng bagitu, bapa raja bisa mangarti itu pikiran yang bataputar dalam kapala otak.<bt>He has told/explained to me the meaning of father raja's dream. He has not done that because I am smarter/cleverer that other living people. He has told me like that, so that father raja can know the meaning of that dream. In that way, father raja will understand the thought that were circulating in (your) head brain.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tindaʕ: you will know"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tindaʕ: you will know</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) livəvakh: your heart, your brain"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) livəvakh: your heart, your brain</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) raʕyowney: thoughts of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) raʕyowney: thoughts of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəhowdʕuwn (ydʕ hafʕel): they may"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəhowdʕuwn (ydʕ hafʕel): they may cause to know. BDB let someone know, communicate, inform, cause to know</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) divrat: the cause, the reason"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) divrat: the cause, the reason</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) lahen"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) lahen</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chayyayya': living beings, all men"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chayyayya': living beings, all men alive</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Dolu, waktu bapa raja ada mimpi, bapa raja dapa lia satu patong model ke manusia yang talalu bésar mati pung! Itu patong pung mangkilat lai! Dia badiri pas di muka idong, ju bekin bulu badan badiri.<bt>Previously, when father raja was dreaming, father raja saw a statue in the form/model of a human which was extremely large/huge! That statue was shining. It stood right in front, and made the hair on (your) body stand up (=terrifying, frightening).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) dəchiyl (partcpl): frightening"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) dəchiyl (partcpl): frightening</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rewehh: its appearance"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rewehh: its appearance</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləqavlakh: in front of you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləqavlakh: in front of you</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qa'em (qwm partcpl): standing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qa'em (qwm partcpl): standing</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yattiyr: extraordinary"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yattiyr: extraordinary</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ziywehh: its brightness, splendor"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ziywehh: its brightness, splendor</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rav: big"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rav: big</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) dikken: it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) dikken: it</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tsalma': the statue"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tsalma': the statue</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) saggiy': huge"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) saggiy': huge</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chad: one"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chad: one</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tselem: statue"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tselem: statue</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əluw: lo!"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əluw: lo!</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) həwayta: you came to be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) həwayta: you came to be aware of. BDB let become known (with participle of knowing). TWOT: Also in Aramaic the verb ha6wa= is often used with a participle to make a periphrastic tense expressing continuous and habitual action (e.g. Dan 6:10 [A 11], "as he used to do formerly").</Message></Annotation><v n="32" />Dia pung kapala, dari mas tulen. Dia pung dada deng tangan dong, dari perak. Dia pung parú deng paha dong, dari tambaga.<bt>Its head was from pure gold. Its chest and arms were from silver. Its stomach/abdomen and thighs were from bronze.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yarkhatehh: its upper thighs"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yarkhatehh: its upper thighs</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məʕ owhiy: its belly"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məʕ owhiy: its belly</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) dəraʕowhiy: its arms"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) dəraʕowhiy: its arms</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chədowhiy: its chest"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chədowhiy: its chest</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) dəhav: gold"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) dəhav: gold</Message></Annotation><v n="33" />Dia pung bitis dong, dari bési. Dia pung kaki bagian bawa dong, dari tana liat bakar campor bési.<bt>Its lower.legs were from iron/steel. The bottom part of its legs (=feet) were from baked clay mixed with iron/steel. [EXEG: Heb: chəSaf: clay, in this case probably baked as ceramic, not unbaked and sticky.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəSaf: clay, in this case"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəSaf: clay, in this case probably baked as ceramic, not unbaked and sticky</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) minnəhown (q. minnəheyn): from them"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) minnəhown (q. minnəheyn): from them</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) farzel: iron"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) farzel: iron</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shaqowhiy: its lower legs"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shaqowhiy: its lower legs</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Tarús bapa raja lia satu batu yang kaná pahat dari gunung, ma sonde pake manusia pung tangan. Itu batu tu, talempar kaná itu patong di kaki bagian bawa dong. Kaná ais, ju itu kaki dari bési campor tana liat dong pica buang.<bt>Then father raja saw a rock which has been chiseled from a mountain, but not using human hands. That rock was thrown hitting that statue at its feet. When it hit, the feet made of iron mixed with clay were (completely) shattered. [EXEG (lex choice); Heb. ‘cut out, broken off’. The first sense makes more sense in combination with the phrase ‘not by human hands’, but ‘cut’ does not collocate with ‘rock’, so we must use chisel.] [TEXT: ‘cut (from a mountain)’ is in some mss, followed by NLT, CEV, HCE and defended by TH from context or for RL naturalness--as is necessary here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) himmown: them"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) himmown: them</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) haddeqet: break into pieces"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) haddeqet: break into pieces</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məchat (mch'): it hit"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məchat (mch'): it hit</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hitgəzeret (hitpəʕ el): got cut"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hitgəzeret (hitpəʕ el): got cut out, broke off</Message></Annotation><v n="35" />Kaki dong ancor dolo, ais itu patong anteru kaná ancor buang ju. Jadi, itu bési, tana liat, tambaga, perak, mas dong samua jadi abu. Ju angin fuu buang sampe sonde ada sisa sadiki ju, sama ke waktu musim koru padi, angin fuu buang uuk dong. Ma itu batu yang kaná pahat tu, batamba bésar jadi satu gunung yang tutu ame ini dunya anteru.<bt>The feet were destroyed first, then the whole statue was (completely) destroyed too. So (consequently) that iron/steel, clay, bronze, silver, and gold all became dust. And the wind blew (it) away to the point that there was nothing left remaining, just like during the rice/grain harvest season, the wind blows away the chaff. But that rock that had been chiseled, increased in size becoming a mountain that enveloped/covered the entire world.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məlat: it filled up"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məlat: it filled up</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Tuwr: mountain, cliff (Heb tsuwr)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Tuwr: mountain, cliff (Heb tsuwr)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hishtəkhach (hitpəʕel): it was [not]"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hishtəkhach (hitpəʕel): it was [not] found</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'ətar: track, place"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'ətar: track, place</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qayiT: summer"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qayiT: summer</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'iddərey: threshing place of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'iddərey: threshing place of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕuwr: chaff"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕuwr: chaff</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) khachədah: as one, all at"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) khachədah: as one, all at the same time</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) daquw (dqq): they broke up"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) daquw (dqq): they broke up</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cot\co01349c.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Naa, itu bapa raja pung mimpi pung isi. Sakarang, beta mau kasi tau itu mimpi pung arti.<bt>Naa [+shift], that is the contents of father raja's dream. Now I'm going to tell the meaning of that dream. [EXEG: Heb. we; 4 different interpretations. Cf. TH, HCE notes. We take the 4th, that it is a plural of modesty, avoiding ‘I’ as a way of showing humility. CEV, HCE.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) The reference got tangled up,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) The reference got tangled up, so we had to repeat that it was Daniel talking.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ne'mar: we tell. UBS: Four"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ne'mar: we tell. UBS: Four different explanations have been proposed: a) that this is a royal "we" or plural of majesty; but this hardly suits the context of Daniel before the king; b) that "we" refers to Daniel and his three friends; but it is quite likely that the three friends were not present during this conversation with Nebuchadnezzar; c) that "we' refers to Daniel and God; but this does not fit the style of Daniel who would have been more likely to say, "God (through me) will give the interpretation"; d) that "we" is a kind of plural of modesty, a way of showing the humility of the speaker; this allows the speaker to avoid the use of "I," which may be understood as pretentious or a kind of boasting. While it is impossible to be certain, the last of these four explanations seems most likely. In some languages it may be possible to avoid either pronoun by using an impersonal turn of phrase (for example, a passive in those languages that use such forms naturally).</Message></Annotation><v n="37" />Bapa raja ni, raja bésar yang parenta raja laen dong. Padahal Tuhan Allah di langit yang angka sang bapa jadi raja, yang kasi kuasa, yang bekin bapa jadi kuat, deng yang bekin orang angka tinggi-tinggi bapa pung nama.<bt>Father raja here (=you) are a big/important raja who rules/governs other rajas. Whereas in fact it is the Lord God in heaven who elevated/appointed father to become raja, who gives power/authority, who made father become strong,/powerful, and who makes people elevate/exalt on high father's name/reputation.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) viyqara': and the honor, esteem"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) viyqara': and the honor, esteem</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) taqpa': strength"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) taqpa': strength</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chiSna': the might"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chiSna': the might</Message></Annotation><v n="38" />Dia yang sarakan rakyat ko biar bapa raja parenta sang dong. Dia ju yang kasi bapa ator binatang utan dong, deng burung yang tarbáng di langit dong. Dong samua tenga di mana sa, ma Tuhan yang angka sang bapa raja ko jadi bos yang ator sang dong. Jadi bapa sama ke itu patong pung kapala yang dong bekin dari mas.<bt>He is the one who handed over/entrusted the populace so that father raja rules/governs them. He is also the one who gave/allowed/entrusted for father to manage the wild animals, and the birds that fly in the sky. They stay/live wherever, but God2 is the one who elevated father raja to be the bos that manages/has responsibility for them. So (consequently) father (=you) are like the head of that statue which was made of/from gold.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) khalləhown: all of them"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) khalləhown: all of them</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hashləTakh (hafʕel): he causes you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hashləTakh (hafʕel): he causes you to rule</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) biydakh: in your hand, in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) biydakh: in your hand, in your power</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) bara': field"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) bara': field</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) cheywat: animals"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) cheywat: animals</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) bəney-'ənasha': sons of men, humankind"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) bəney-'ənasha': sons of men, humankind</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) da'əriyn (q. dayriyn partcpl pl):"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) da'əriyn (q. dayriyn partcpl pl): the ones who dwell</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Naa, nanti kalo bapa raja su parenta abis, ada pamarenta baru yang muncul datang. Itu pamarenta sonde sama hebat deng bapa raja, sama ke perak sonde sama hebat deng mas.<bt>Naa [+shift], later when father raja (=you) have finished ruling/governing, there will be a new government that arises/appears coming [Serial Verb Construction = svc]. That government will not be as impressive as father raja (=you), just like silver is not as impressive as gold.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Kalo pamarenta kadua su parenta abis, ada pamarenta katiga yang muncul datang. Itu sama ke patong tadi pung bagian dari tambaga. Nanti dong parenta anteru dunya ju.<bt>If/when the second government has finished ruling, there is a third government which will arise/appear coming. That is like that aforementioned statue part (made) from bronze. They will govern/rule the entire world.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əraʕ': earthy, inferior (should we"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əraʕ': earthy, inferior (should we mention the silver? the "not so awesome"?)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'achəriy: another"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'achəriy: another</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) malkhuw: a kingdom (dynasty?)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) malkhuw: a kingdom (dynasty?)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vatrakh: in your place"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vatrakh: in your place</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40" />Ais ju, ada pamarenta ka'ampat yang muncul datang. Dong sama ke itu patong pung bagian dari bési, te nanti dong kasi ancor buang samua pamarenta laen dong, sama ke kotong pake bési ko puku kasi ancor barang laen dong.<bt>After that, there is a fourth government that arises/appears coming. They are like the statue's part (made) from iron/steel, cuz (elaboration) they will destroy all the othr governments, like we use iron/steel to beat destroying other things.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) teroaʕ (rʕʕ): it crushes"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) teroaʕ (rʕʕ): it crushes</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) taddiq (dqq 'afʕel): causes to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) taddiq (dqq 'afʕel): causes to break</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'illeyn: these things"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'illeyn: these things</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məraʕaʕ (partcpl): shattering"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məraʕaʕ (partcpl): shattering</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kolla': all of it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kolla': all of it</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chashel (partcpl): shattering"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chashel (partcpl): shattering</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məhaddeq (paʕʕel partcpl): breaking in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məhaddeq (paʕʕel partcpl): breaking in pieces</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) taqqiyfah: strong, mighty, prodigious"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) taqqiyfah: strong, mighty, prodigious</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tehəwe': it will be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tehəwe': it will be</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rəviyʕayah (q. rəviyʕa'ah): fourth"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rəviyʕayah (q. rəviyʕa'ah): fourth</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Naa, bapa raja su lia itu kaki bagian bawa deng dia pung jari kaki dong yang tana liat campor bési. Itu kasi tunju bilang, itu pamarenta ka'ampat pung rakyat sonde ta'ikat jadi satu. Ma dia pung rakyat dong tabagi-bagi. Di satu sisi, dia kuat, sama ke bési.<bt>Naa [+shift], father raja has seen those feet with its toes from clay mixed with iron/steel. That shows/indicates that the populace of that fourth government are not bound together (united) as one. But its populace are divided. From one aspect, it is strong, like iron/steel. [EXEG: Heb. ‘potter’ undertranslated here as in NLT, CEV, TH, HCE.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Tiyna': baked clay"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Tiyna': baked clay</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) maʕarav (pass partcpl): mixed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) maʕarav (pass partcpl): mixed</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nitsbəta': the firmness, hardness"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nitsbəta': the firmness, hardness</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) fəliygah: divided"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) fəliygah: divided</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) fechar: potter"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) fechar: potter</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəSaf: clay, ceramic"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəSaf: clay, ceramic</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'etsbəʕata': the toes"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'etsbəʕata': the toes</Message></Annotation><v n="42" />Biar ada bagian yang kuat bagitu, ma ada bagian laen lai yang gampang ancor ju.<bt>Even though there is the part that is strong, nevertheless there is another part that is easy to destroy. [DISCOURSE: Heb has high levels of repetition of NPs in this section (41-44) that would be too heavy in the RL. See TH.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) təviyrah: fragile"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) təviyrah: fragile</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) taqqiyfah: strong, mighty"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) taqqiyfah: strong, mighty</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qətsat: part"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qətsat: part</Message></Annotation><v n="43" />Ju dia pung rakyat dong kawin campor deng suku laen. Ma dong sonde batahan lama, sama ke bési deng tana liat sonde bisa bacampor batúl.<bt>And it populace intermarry with other tribes/ethnic groups. But they do not endure/stand long, like iron and clay cannot really mix.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) he': behold"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) he': behold</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) davqiyn (partcpl pl): sticking together,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) davqiyn (partcpl pl): sticking together, holding together</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) zəraʕ: seed, offspring"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) zəraʕ: seed, offspring</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mitʕarviyn (hitpaʕʕal partcpl): mixed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mitʕarviyn (hitpaʕʕal partcpl): mixed</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="44" />Ma waktu itu raja-raja dong ada pegang parenta, Tuhan Allah yang pegang parenta di langit mau kasi jalan Dia pung karaja'an sandiri. Ma Tuhan pung karaja'an tu, batahan kuat. Sonde ada yang bisa kasi kala ko kasi ancor sang dong. Sonde ada yang sarakan itu korsi parenta pi di bangsa laen ju.<bt>But when those rajas are holding rule/ governing, God who holds rule in heaven wants to/is going to establish/set up his own kingdom. But God2's kingdom remains strong. There is nobody who can defeat or destroy them. There is nobody who hand over that throne to other ethnic groups/races.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) təquwm"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) təquwm</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) taSeyf (Swp 'afʕel): it will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) taSeyf (Swp 'afʕel): it will put an end to</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) taddaq (dqq): it will break"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) taddaq (dqq): it will break up</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tishtəviq (shbq hitpəʕel): be left"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tishtəviq (shbq hitpəʕel): be left to, pass on its sovereignty to</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'achəran: different, other"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'achəran: different, other</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) titchabbal (chbl hitpaʕʕal): it will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) titchabbal (chbl hitpaʕʕal): it will [not] perish, be destroyed</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəqiym (qwm 'afʕel): set up,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəqiym (qwm 'afʕel): set up, establish</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'innuwn: those, they,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'innuwn: those, they,</Message></Annotation><v n="45" />Itu batu yang kaná pahat dari gunung ma sonde pake manusia pung tangan tu, dia yang kasi ancor buang itu bési, tambaga, tana liat, perak, deng mas.<bt>That rock that was chiseled from a mountain but not using human hands, is the one who destroys that iron, bronze, clay, silver and gold. [NOTE to daughter translations: cf wording in vs. 34.] [EXEG: TH recommends retaining the different order of the Heb. here, rather than fixing it as in some Gk versons.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Jadi bapa raja musti inga bilang, Tuhan Allah yang paling hebat su kasi tunju memang sang bapa raja, samua-samua yang nanti mau jadi. Itu mimpi bagitu, deng dia batúl. Bapa raja bisa parcaya dia pung arti yang beta su kasi tau ju. Bagitu su, bapa.&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently) father raja (=you) must remember that the most amazing God has revealed beforehand to father raja everything that is going to happen. That was how the dream was, and it is true/correct. Father raja can beleive/trust its meaning/interpretation which I have explained. That is all, father.&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: natural RL closure.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) End of P section."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) End of P section.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) pishrehh: its interpretation"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) pishrehh: its interpretation</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məheyman (passive partcpl): trustworthy"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məheyman (passive partcpl): trustworthy</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yattsiyv (adj): true, reliable"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yattsiyv (adj): true, reliable</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) haddeqet: it broke something in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) haddeqet: it broke something in pieces</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) biydayin: by the hand of,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) biydayin: by the hand of, power of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'itgəzeret ('itpəʕel): it was quarried,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'itgəzeret ('itpəʕel): it was quarried, cut out</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) miTTuwra': from the mountain, cliff"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) miTTuwra': from the mountain, cliff</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Raja angka nae sang Daniel deng dia pung kawan dong<bt>The raja elevates/appoints Daniel and his friends</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="46" />Dengar Daniel kasi tau itu mimpi pung isi deng dia pung arti, ju raja Nebukadnesar tikam lutut deng muka sampe di tana di Daniel pung muka ko kasi tunju hormat sang dia. Ais dia parenta dia pung orang dong ko kasi hasil kabón deng dara kayu wangi sang Daniel, ko biar Daniel bisa pake jadi persembahan sang Tuhan Allah di langit.<bt>Hearing Daniel explain the contents and the meaning of the dream, then raja Nebukadnesar knelt with his face to the ground before Daniel to show respect to him. Then he ordered his people to give yield/produce from the garden/fields and aromatic tree sap to Daniel, so that Daniel could use it as an offering to God in heaven. [DISCOURSE: high level tail-head to transition from previous section, following RL patterns.] [EXEG: Heb term ‘honored’, BART ‘pay homage’; cf discussion in TH and HCE note as well. NRSV, NLT translation of ‘worship’ not necessary, and inappropriate to the social context.] [EXEG: Q: give offerings and incense “to Daniel”? (NRSV); “before/in front of Daniel” (NLT); “to be offered in honor of Daniel” (CEV); “to Daniel, so Daniel can make sacrifice to God” (HCE). HCE takes the Heb infinitive to mean l^naSSakhah (inf): ‘for him to make an offering with’, and this is consistent with BART. We follow this as making the most sense of the grammar in context of what would have been going through the king's head. In the context it is Daniel's God who is impressive, and Daniel is obviously connected, so use Daniel to get the king ‘safe’ with this God. And transitions to vs.47.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) lənaSSakhah (inf): for him to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) lənaSSakhah (inf): for him to make an offering with</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nichochiyn: soothing, tranquilizing things ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nichochiyn: soothing, tranquilizing things = incense?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) minchah: grain offering (possibly for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) minchah: grain offering (possibly for him to offer to Yahweh on behalf of the king)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Səgid: honored"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Səgid: honored</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'anpowhiy: his face"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'anpowhiy: his face</Message></Annotation><v n="47" />Ju raja kasi tau sang Daniel bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu pung Tuhan tu, batúl-batúl lebe dari samua tuhan yang laen dong. Dia yang hak parenta sang botong yang raja-raja dong. Dia yang kasi tabuka hal yang tasambunyi dong. Beta tau ini samua batúl, tagal lu bisa kasi tau beta pung mimpi pung arti.&gt;&gt;<bt>And the raja told Daniel saying, &lt;&lt;That God2 of yours-sg is truly greater/more than all other *gods [same word; same strategy used in Indo Bible]. He is the one who has the right to rule us-exc rajas. He is the one who reveals/unveils things that are hidden. I know all this is true, because you are able to tell the meaning of my dream.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) razah: secret"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) razah: secret</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləmigle' (inf): to interpret"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləmigle' (inf): to interpret</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) raziyn: secrets"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) raziyn: secrets</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) galeh (partcpl): the one who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) galeh (partcpl): the one who interprets</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mare': lord"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mare': lord</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qəshoT: truth"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qəshoT: truth</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cot\co01350c.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="48" />Ais raja angka sang Daniel jadi orang bésar, ju kasi dia barang bam-banya. Daniel jadi gubernor di propinsi Babel, ju dia yang musti ator ame samua orang pintar di situ.<bt>So then the raja elevated/appointed Daniel to become an important persom, and also gave him many things. Daniel became governor in the province of Babel, and he also had to manage/ oversee all the wise/knowledgable people there. [DISCOURSE: reordered for RL worldview.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rav Signiyn: chief prefect"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rav Signiyn: chief prefect</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mədiynat: district, province"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mədiynat: district, province</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hashləTehh (shlT hafʕel): he made"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hashləTehh (shlT hafʕel): he made him a ruler</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) saggiy'an: much"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) saggiy'an: much</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ravrəvan: lord, noble"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ravrəvan: lord, noble</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) matnan: present"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) matnan: present</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rabbiy (paʕel): he made great"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rabbiy (paʕel): he made great</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="49" />Ais Daniel minta sang raja bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bisa, tolong angka beta pung kawan tiga orang dong, andia: Sadrak, Mesak, deng Abednego, ko biar dong bisa bantu beta parenta di propinsi Babel.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Daniel requested of the raja saying, &lt;&lt;If possible, please elevate/appoint my three friends also, they are: Sadrak, Mesak, and Abednego, so that they can help/assist me in governing the province of Babel.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dengar bagitu, ju raja manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Neu.&gt;&gt; Ma dari itu ampa orang dong, cuma Daniel sandiri yang tenga di istana deka deng raja.<bt>Hearing that, the raja responded saying, &lt;&lt;Neu. [OK, fine.]&gt;&gt; But from those four people, only Daniel himself is the one who stayed/lived in the palace near the raja. [DISCOURSE: made direct speech following RL preferences. In RL patterns, Daniel's (irrealis) request also has to be accepted, otherwise it is an unfulfilled request.] [CHECK connector for last sentence. Discuss.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) End of P section"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) End of P section</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) təraʕ: gate, court, easily accessible"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) təraʕ: gate, court, easily accessible to the king</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕəviydta': administration"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕəviydta': administration</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) manniy (paʕʕel): he appointed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) manniy (paʕʕel): he appointed</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) bəʕa': requested"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) bəʕa': requested</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Raja kasi badiri patong tinggi dari mas<bt>The raja erects a tall statue (made) from gold</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="3" />
      <v n="1" />Satu kali, raja Nebukadnesar suru dia pung orang dong ko bekin ame satu patong dari mas. Dia pung tinggi musti 27 meter. Dia pung lebar, amper 3 meter.<bt>One time, raja Nebukadnesar ordered his people to make a statue from gold. Its height must be 27 meters. Its width, almost 3 meters.</bt><note reference="3:1" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan asli bahasa Aram tulis bilang, dia pung tinggi 60 hasta, deng dia pung lebar, 6 hasta.<bt>The original Aram language writings write saying, its height was 60 hasta (Indo: cubit), and its width 6 hasta.</bt></note>Bekin abis, ju dia suru ko dong kasi badiri itu patong di dataran Dura, sonde jao dari kota Babel.<bt>After making it, then he order them to erect/stand up that statue on the plain/flats of Dura, not far from the city of Babel. [DISCOURSE: time margin added to make this episode separated by time from the previous verse.] [EXEG: Dura near city, cf CEV.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mədiynat: province"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mədiynat: province</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) viqʕat: plain"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) viqʕat: plain</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əqiymehh (qwm 'afʕel): he set"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əqiymehh (qwm 'afʕel): he set it up</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shit: six. JG: That's less"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shit: six. JG: That's less in proportion than half the width of an ordinary person, measured across the shoulders. Those proportions would make it over 28 feet wide. But maybe if we subtracted the headdress and the pedestal, it would be a bit less awkward, like 20 feet wide. TCBC: Archaeologists have discovered a large platform forty-five feet square and twenty feet high that may have served as the pedestal for Nebuchadnezzar's image.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) pətayehh: its width"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) pətayehh: its width</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shitiyn: sixty"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shitiyn: sixty</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'ammiyn: cubit"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'ammiyn: cubit</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ruwmehh: its height"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ruwmehh: its height</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) dəhav: gold"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) dəhav: gold</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tsəlem: a statue. It doesn't"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tsəlem: a statue. It doesn't say it was an idol, or that it was a statue of the king. Just a statue.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕəvad (pəʕal): he made"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕəvad (pəʕal): he made</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Ais raja kirim tukang bawa pasán pi mana-mana ko pange datang dia pung orang dong samua yang pegang parenta di negara laen dong yang dengar-dengar sang dia. Andia: samua pagawe tinggi, gubernor, wakil gubernor, tukang putus parkara, tukang kasi nasiat, bendahara, deng kapala urusan dong. Te raja pung mau ko dong samua hadir jadi saksi waktu dia bekin resmi itu patong.<bt>Then the raja sent messengers everywhere to summon all of his people who ruled in other countries who listened to/obeyed him. They were: all high officials, governors, vice governors, judges, treasurers/money managers, and managers/dept heads. Cuz (elaboration) the raja wanted all of them to be present as witnesses when he dedicated (lit: made formal) that statue. [DISCOURSE / EXEG: generic-specific as appropriate to RL discourse. Aram. has 8 categories. We have to conflate judges &amp; magistrates; satraps, prefects, and governors.] [GRAMM / EXEG: ‘all’ from ‘all the officials from the provinces’ and by implication. Needed to signal plural and lighten in information load to that each category/phrase does not need to be marked PL separately.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chənukkat: dedication of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chənukkat: dedication of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləmete': to come"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləmete': to come</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shilToney: officials of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shilToney: officials of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tiftaye': magistrates. TWOT: magistrate (KB,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tiftaye': magistrates. TWOT: magistrate (KB, NIV). Name of a provincial offcer of unknown station.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) dətavrayya': the judges"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) dətavrayya': the judges</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) gədavrayya': the keepers of treasure."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) gədavrayya': the keepers of treasure. They didn't get what you could call "money" until Darius I, who got it from kingdoms like that of Croesus.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'ədargazrayya': the counsellors (Holladay). From"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'ədargazrayya': the counsellors (Holladay). From here on, the list is by function, not by place in the hierarchy.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) pachəwata': governors. IVP: Heb. Pexa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) pachəwata': governors. IVP: Heb. Pexa (cf. Assyr. PachaTu) is the most frequent, meaning the ruler of a district under a king, e.g. an Assyrian provincial governor (Is. 36:9), Chaldean and Persian governors (Ezk. 23:6, 23; Est. 3:12; 8:9), the Persian Tattenai (Ezr. 5:3; 6:6), whose satrapy included Palestine, Phoenicia and Egypt; and Nehemiah and Zerubbabel as governors of Judah (Ne. 5:14; Ezr. 6:7). JG: ruler of a district under a king (or perhaps a satrap). These top three levels are really high up, and they get repeated elsewhere.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Signayya': the prefects, governors. IVP:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Signayya': the prefects, governors. IVP: sAgAn ('deputy', 'lieutenant', e.g. Dn. 3:2, RSV 'governors'). JG: assistants to the satraps?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əchashdarpənayya': the satraps, in charge"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əchashdarpənayya': the satraps, in charge of conquered kingdoms. Darius I reduced the number of satraps to 20.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləmikhnas: to gather"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləmikhnas: to gather</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Andia ko dong datang bakumpul bagitu. Waktu dong samua su badiri di muka itu patong,<bt>That is why they all came and gathered together like that. When they were all standing before that statue, [DISCOURSE (referent tracking) STYLE: Aram. repeats the categories. That would be much too heavy in RL discourse.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qa'əmiyn (q. qaymiyn partcpl): coming"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qa'əmiyn (q. qaymiyn partcpl): coming on the scene, standing</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mitkannəshiyn (knsh hitpaʕal partcpl pl):"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mitkannəshiyn (knsh hitpaʕal partcpl pl): were coming together</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />ju raja pung tukang bawa acara kasi tau kuat-kuat bilang, &lt;&lt;Samua orang dengar bae-bae! Ada atoran baru yang turun dari raja Nebukadnesar kasi sang samua suku, samua bahasa, deng samua negara.<bt>then the raja's ceremony bringer (MC) explained loudly saying, &lt;&lt;Everyone listen carefully! There is a new regulation handed down from raja Nebukadnesar to all tribes/ethnic groups, all languages, and all countries. [EXEG: Aram. herald, MC, announcer.] [EXEG: CEV forgot ‘language’.] [DISCOURSE: local announcements always identify the authority up front.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) lisshanayya': languages"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) lisshanayya': languages</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'ummiyya': nations"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'ummiyya': nations</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕaməmayya': peoples"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕaməmayya': peoples</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'amriyn: it is commanded"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'amriyn: it is commanded</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləkhown: to you (pl), to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləkhown: to you (pl), to all of you</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) khayil with strength, loudly"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) khayil with strength, loudly</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kharowza': a herald, master of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kharowza': a herald, master of ceremonies, announcer. This word may have come from Greek, though most loans in Daniel are from Persian.</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Bagini: nanti kalo bosong su dengar alat musik dong babunyi sama-sama, bosong musti barenti dari samua karjá. Ais bosong musti langsung tondo sampe tana ko sémba sang ini patong yang bapa raja Nebukadnesar su kasi badiri ni. Itu alat musik yang babunyi dong, conto ke: tarompet, sasando, gitar, biola. Nanti dong babunyi karás-karás.<bt>It is like this: later when you-pl hear the musical instruments sounding together/at the same time, you must stop all your work. Then you must immediately bow to the ground to worship this statue which father raja Nebukadnesar has erected here. The musical instruments that will sound are the ones like: trumpets, sasandos (local stringed instruments -- used in other books already translated), guitar, biola (local viola/violin, not Bible Institute of Los Angeles). They will sound loudly (the volume will be up high). [DISCOURSE: RL order, generic-specific. Main instructions then elaboration of details.] [DISCOURSE: ellipted proposition implicit-explicit: stop what you are doing.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) dahəva': gold"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) dahəva': gold</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tiSgəduwn: you (pl): are to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tiSgəduwn: you (pl): are to pay homage to. SK: jus like worshiping idols, den. NET: The imperfect Aramaic verbs have here an injunctive nuance.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) zəmara': musical instrument. Zithers and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) zəmara': musical instrument. Zithers and dulcimers, which have been suggested, are not found in the archeological reports. The instruments used here, except for the "guitar," are not.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) zəney: all kinds"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) zəney: all kinds</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Suwmponyah: bagpipe? or ensemble (from"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Suwmponyah: bagpipe? or ensemble (from the Greek meaning of symphoonia)?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) pəSanteriyn: Greek psalterion, perhaps a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) pəSanteriyn: Greek psalterion, perhaps a lyre or harp; lyre, lighter than the harp</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Sabbəkha: trigon, a harp with"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Sabbəkha: trigon, a harp with four strings stretched between two members at a little less than a right angle, so the strings make the third side of a triangle. TWOT: Apparently a triangular instrument with four strings. The Greek equivalent is sambykee, but it is not sure whether the Greek borrowed from the Semitic or vice versa.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qiytarowS (q. qatrowS): lyre or"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qiytarowS (q. qatrowS): lyre or zither. A lyre is a portable harp; a zither is more like a samisen</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mashrowqiyta': the flute. More like"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mashrowqiyta': the flute. More like a fife or a recorder, blow straight into it</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qar'əna': the horn, either as"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qar'əna': the horn, either as a musical instrument or the horn of an animal</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tishməʕuwn: you (pl) hear"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tishməʕuwn: you (pl) hear</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) bəʕ iddana': at the point"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) bəʕ iddana': at the point in time, as soon as</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Andekata ada orang yang sonde tondo, na, itu orang langsung kaná lempar buang pi dalam satu api bésar yang panas mati pung! Itu api dalam satu tampa ke ofen yang talalu bésar.&gt;&gt;<bt>If perchance [+hypothetical] there is a person who does not bow down, na, that person will be immediately thrown into a huge fire that is incredibly hot! That fire is in a place like a very  large oven. [EXEG: Aramaic seems ambiguous. NRSV, TB are descriptive ‘who does not bow’; NLT and CEV are volitional ‘who refuses to...’] [NOTE to daughter translations: large furnaces/ kilns are used around Kupang (Tana Mera) for baking bricks. Smaller ones are used for smelting gold, silver, and forging iron. Also mud stoves for boiling down lontar sap into palm sugar. Discuss with team if there are terms that are widely known.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yaqidta' (yqd pəʕal): it burns"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yaqidta' (yqd pəʕal): it burns</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nuwra': the fire"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nuwra': the fire</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'attuwn: furnace. What sorts of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'attuwn: furnace. What sorts of furnace do people know besides the 'imu? Portuguese baking oven. This one needs to be deep enough to throw somebody into. IVPC: Furnaces were used for baking pottery or bricks for construction projects, as well as for metalwork (forging, smelting and casting). There is not a lot of information about furnaces in the ancient Near East, but many early furnaces were enclosed and domed with side doors for ventilation. They were built of clay or brick, though the inside chamber was often lined with specially selected types of stone.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) gow': in the middle of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) gow': in the middle of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yitrəme' (rm' hitpəʕel): he will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yitrəme' (rm' hitpəʕel): he will be thrown</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shaʕəta': moment"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shaʕəta': moment</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cot\co01354c.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Sampe dia pung waktu, kalo itu alat musik dong babunyi, ju samua orang dari samua suku, samua bahasa, deng samua negara langsung barenti ko tondo sampe tana, ais sémba sang itu patong.<bt>At the appointed time, when those musical instruments sounded, then all people from all ethnic groups, all languages, and all countries immediately stopped to bow to the ground and worship that statue. [DISCOURSE: referent tracking streamlined as appropriate for RL discourse. Retrievable from previous verses.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kədiy: like that which"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kədiy: like that which</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) zimna'"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) zimna'</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Naa, waktu itu alat musik dong babunyi, ju ada orang Kasdim yang pintar lia bintang dong saparu pake kasampatan ko datang mangada sang raja ko lempar sala sang orang Yahudi dong.<bt>Naa [+shift], when those musical instruments sounded, there were some Kasdim people skilled at observing stars who used the opportunity to come before the raja to accuse/throw accusations at the Yahudi people. [EXEG: Aram. ‘approached, came forward’ = went to the king. TH, NLT, CEV.] [EXEG: opportunism; cf. TH, NJB, CEV. TH also notes the Aram. idiom “ate (or chewed up) the pieces of.” indicates spiteful slander, or malicious pettiness. Discuss with team if that sense is coming through.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəhuwdaye': Jews"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəhuwdaye': Jews</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qartseyhuwn: small pieces, part of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qartseyhuwn: small pieces, part of the idiom</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'akhaluw: they ate; idiom for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'akhaluw: they ate; idiom for slander</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) guvriyn: certain ones"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) guvriyn: certain ones</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qrivuw: they approached"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qrivuw: they approached</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Dong kasi tau raja bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa raja yang mulia! Biar ko bapa raja umur panjang, deng idop sonde putus-putus!<bt>They told the raja saying, &lt;&lt;Most glorious father raja! May father raja (=you) have live long, and live forever!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəyiy (imperv): live!"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəyiy (imperv): live!</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Naa, bapa raja sandiri yang kasi turun parenta bilang, kalo orang su dengar alat musik dong babunyi, na, samua orang musti tondo ko sémba itu patong yang bapa bekin dari mas.<bt>Naa [+shift], father raja yourself is the one who handed down the comand saying when people hear the musical instruments sound, na, everyone must bow and worship that statue that father (=you) made from gold.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Təʕem: decree"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Təʕem: decree</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'antah (q. 'ant): you (emphasized)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'antah (q. 'ant): you (emphasized)</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Ju itu parenta bilang, kalo ada orang yang sonde tondo ko sémba itu patong, na, itu orang musti kaná lempar buang pi dalam satu api bésar yang panas mati pung!<bt>And that command says, if there is a person who does not bow to worship that statue, na, that person must be thrown into a very big fire that is incredibly hot!</bt><v n="12" />Ma dia pung masala bagini: ada orang Yahudi saparu yang bapa raja su angka jadi pagawe tinggi ko urus pamarenta di propinsi Babel. Itu orang dong pung nama, andia: Sadrak, Mesak, deng Abednego. Dong tu, sonde mau dengar sang bapa raja. Te dong sonde mau kasi tunju hormat deng songgo bapa raja pung dewa-dewi dong, ju sonde mau sémba sang itu patong mas yang bapa raja su bekin tu.&gt;&gt;<bt>But the problem is like this: there are some Yahudi people whom father raja has elevated to become high officials to manage the government in the province of Babel. Those people are named Sadrak, Mesak, and Abednego. They are the ones who don't want to listen to/obey father raja. Cuz (elaboration) they don't want to show respect and traditional.worship father raja's deiteis, and don't want to worship that gold statue which father raja has made.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) End of S section."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) End of S section.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) falchiyn (partcpl): [not] respecting"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) falchiyn (partcpl): [not] respecting</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) le'lahayikh (q. le'lahakh): to your"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) le'lahayikh (q. le'lahakh): to your gods q. god</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕəlayikh (q. ʕəlakh): to you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕəlayikh (q. ʕəlakh): to you</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) samuw: they did [not] put"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) samuw: they did [not] put</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'illekh: these, those"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'illekh: these, those</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕal-ʕəviydat: over the administration"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕal-ʕəviydat: over the administration</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yatəhuwn: DIROBJ them"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yatəhuwn: DIROBJ them</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) manniyta (paʕʕ el): you have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) manniyta (paʕʕ el): you have appointed</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) guvriyn: certain ones"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) guvriyn: certain ones</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cot\co01355c.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Dengar bagitu, ju raja Nebukadnesar mara bésar. Ais dia suru dia pung orang dong ko pi tangkap bawa sang Sadrak, Mesak, deng Abednego. Ju dong pi tangkap ame sang dong tiga, ais bawa mangada sang raja.<bt>Hearing that, raja Nebukadnesar was furious (lit: big angry). So he ordered his people to go catch/arrest and bring Sadrak, Mesak, and Abednego. so they went and arrested the three of them, and brought them before the raja.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhaytayah ('th hafʕel inf): to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhaytayah ('th hafʕel inf): to bring them</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəmah: anger"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəmah: anger</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) birgaz: in a rage"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) birgaz: in a rage</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Ju raja tanya sang dong tiga bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl, ko? Omong jujur sa! Bosong tiga sonde mau kasi tunju hormat deng sémba beta pung dewa-dewi dong, ko? Deng bosong ju sonde mau sémba sang itu patong mas yang beta bekin, ko?<bt>Then the raja asked the three of them saying, &lt;&lt;Is it true? Speak honestly! The three of you-pl do not want to show respect and worship my deiteis, ro [not]? And you also don't want to worship that gold statue which I made, or [not]? [DISCOURSE: in RL an angry king would not use their names. That would indicate polite respect, which clashes with the situation.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) palchiyn: serve, pay reverence to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) palchiyn: serve, pay reverence to</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'iyteykhown ('iytay): with l-, you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'iyteykhown ('iytay): with l-, you do not hold my god in reverence</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hatsəda': is it true? UBS:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hatsəda': is it true? UBS: derived from a root that has the idea of solidness or firmness, and it is so rendered in many ancient versions. This meaning has further been confirmed by the discovery of an Aramaic inscription where it is also used. This has led some scholars to think that the best translation of the word may be "Is it deliberate?" BDB The equivalent in Hebrew (tsədiyah) also is used of evil purpose.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Beta kasi salák sakarang. Kalo bosong dengar itu alat musik babunyi ini kali, ais bosong tondo ko sémba sang itu patong yang beta bekin tu, samua beres. Aman sa! Ma dengar bae-bae! Te kalo bosong sonde mau tondo deng sonde mau sémba bagitu, nanti beta pung orang dong lempar buang sang bosong pi dalam itu api bésar yang panas mati pung. Kalo su bagitu, kira-kira tuhan macam karmana yang bisa kasi salamat sang bosong dari beta pung hukuman? Sonde ada, to!?&gt;&gt;<bt>I'll give a chance/opportunity now. When you hear the musical instruments sound this time, and you bow to worship that statue which I have made, everything is fine/in order/as it should be. It's all good/safe! But listen carefully! Cuz (elaboration) if you-pl do not want to bow and do not want to worship like that, my people will throw you into that big fire that is soo incredibly hot. If that's the case, what kind of god is able to save you from my punishment? There aren't any, right!?&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: ellipted proposition: implicit-explicit: I'll give you another chance... See: NLT, CEV.] [EXEG: Aram. ‘deliver you out of my hands’; our rendering of ‘rescue you from my punishment’ seems better in the context than NLT ‘rescue you from my power’.] [DISCOURSE: RQ provided with response.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəsheyzvinkhown (shaʕel): rescue, save you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəsheyzvinkhown (shaʕel): rescue, save you (pl)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) titrəmown: you will be thrown"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) titrəmown: you will be thrown</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shaʕətah: immediately"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shaʕətah: immediately</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕavdet: I have made"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕavdet: I have made</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕiddana': time"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕiddana': time</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕətiydiyn: ready, prepared"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕətiydiyn: ready, prepared</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hen: whether"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hen: whether</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kəʕ an"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kəʕ an</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cot\co01357c.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ais Sadrak, Mesak, deng Abednego manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa raja! Botong sonde parlú bela diri di bapa pung muka.<bt>Then Sadrak, Mesak, and Abednego responded saying, &lt;&lt;Father raja! We-exc don't need to defend ourselves before you. [EXEG: Aram. ‘in this matter, in this affair’ undertranslated; implied by ‘defend ourselves’ in the matter that the king has raised.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhətavuwtakh (hafʕel inf): to return"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhətavuwtakh (hafʕel inf): to return an answer to you</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) pitgam: this affair, this matter"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) pitgam: this affair, this matter</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chashchiyn: need"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chashchiyn: need</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Biar bapa raja pung orang dong lempar buang sang botong pi dalam itu api bésar yang talalu panas, ma botong pung Tuhan Allah yang botong layani, masi bisa kasi salamat sang botong dari bapa raja pung hukuman.<bt>Even if father raja's people throw us-exc into that big fire that is so very hot, nevertheless our God whom we serve is still able to save/rescue us from father raja's punishment. [DISCOURSE: ellipted proposition made explicit, as per NLT, HCE.] [EXEG: Aram. ‘deliver us ... out of your hand’. See note at vs. 15 above = punishment.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) palchiyn: serving"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) palchiyn: serving</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əlahana': our God"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əlahana': our God</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Ma asal bapa raja tau sa, biar Tuhan sonde kasi lapás sang botong dari bapa raja pung hukuman, ma botong sonde mau sémba bapa raja pung dewa-dewi dong, deng sonde mau songgo sang itu patong mas yang bapa raja bekin tu.&gt;&gt;<bt>But as long as father raja knows, even if God2 does not free/rescue us from father raja's punishment, nevertheless we are not going to worship father raja's deities, and are not going to traditional.worship that gold statue which father raja has made.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) End of S section."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) End of S section.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) palchiyn: serving"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) palchiyn: serving</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'iytayna' (q. 'iytana'): there will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'iytayna' (q. 'iytana'): there will [not] be for us? '</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) lehəwe' (hwh inf): come to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) lehəwe' (hwh inf): come to pass, happen, become</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yədiyaʕ (pass partcpl?): let it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yədiyaʕ (pass partcpl?): let it be known</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong lempar buang 3 orang pi dalam api<bt>They throw 3 people into the fire</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Dengar dong tiga pung omong bagitu, ju raja Nebukanesar talalu mara, sampe dia pung muka babangka. Ais dia suru dia pung orang dong ko bekin api di ofen tuju kali lebe panas.<bt>Hearing what the three of them had to say like that, raja Nebukadnesar was very angry, to the point that his face was distorted/swollen. So he ordered his people to make the fire in the oven/furnace seven times hotter. [DISCOURSE: too heavy in this context to use the 3 names of S, M, and A.] [EXEG: Aram. ‘the form of his face was altered’. How is rage manifested in the face in your RL language/culture?] [EXEG: ‘than was usual, normal’. In Kupang this is implied by comparative ‘7x hotter’ (which sources acknowledge is hyperbole).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləmezyehh: for heating it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləmezyehh: for heating it</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəzeh: was usual, normal"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəzeh: was usual, normal</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chad: one"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chad: one</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) meze' ('z' inf): light a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) meze' ('z' inf): light a fire, heat up</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'eshtannuw (q. 'eshtanniy) (shn' 'itpaʕʕal):"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'eshtannuw (q. 'eshtanniy) (shn' 'itpaʕʕal): became altered</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'anpowhiy: his face"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'anpowhiy: his face</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tsəlem: form of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tsəlem: form of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəma': anger"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəma': anger</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hitməliy (hitpəʕel): was filled"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hitməliy (hitpəʕel): was filled</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Ais raja suru dia pung tantara yang paling kuat dong ko ika ame sang Sadrak, Mesak, deng Abednego, ko lempar buang sang dong pi dalam itu api bésar tu.<bt>Then the raja ordered his strongest soldiers to tie up Sadrak, Mesak, and Abednego, to throw them into that great fire.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləmirme' (rm' inf): to throw"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləmirme' (rm' inf): to throw</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləkhappatah (kpt paʕel inf): to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləkhappatah (kpt paʕel inf): to tie up</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cot\co01360c.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ju dia pung tantara dong ika ame sang dong deng pakean di badan, deng kaen ika kapala samua, ais lempar buang sang dong pi dalam itu ofen bésar yang manyala panas mati pung.<bt>So his soldiers tied them up complete with the clothes they were wearing and their headcloths, and threw them into the large oven/furnace which was radiating incredible heat. [EXEG: Aram. ‘tunics, trousers, turbans, and other garments’. Undertranslated like CEV. NLT order different from NRSV and TB.] [NOTE to daughter translations: CHECK that this phrasing does not give the impression that the clothes were tied up separately, but rather that they were wearing them.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rəmiyw (pəʕil): were thrown"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rəmiyw (pəʕil): were thrown</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləvusheyhown: garments"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləvusheyhown: garments</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kharbəlathown: caps, hats. TWOT: cap,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kharbəlathown: caps, hats. TWOT: cap, turban. The Hebrew word involves clothing thrown over like a mantle. The Akkadian cognate refers to some kind of cap. Perhaps the reference is to a turban, but the precise significance is uncertain. Occurs only in Dan 3:21.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) paTTiysheyhown (q. paTTəsheyhown): coat or"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) paTTiysheyhown (q. paTTəsheyhown): coat or trousers</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Sarbaleyhown: trousers or cloak"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Sarbaleyhown: trousers or cloak</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kəfituw (pəʕil): were tied up"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kəfituw (pəʕil): were tied up</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Tagal raja suru dia pung orang dong ko bekin itu api tamba panas lai, andia ko waktu dong lempar buang itu tiga orang Yahudi pi dalam api, na, raja pung orang sandiri dong tabakar sampe mati.<bt>Because the raja ordered his people to make the fire even hotter, that is why when they threw the three Yahudi people into the fire, na, the raja's own people were burned to death. [NOTE: Can this last sentence be made more vivid?] [EXEG: Aram. the king's command was ‘harsh, severe.’ UBS: In this context it indicates that the king's order was firm and uncompromising.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nuwra': the fire"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nuwra': the fire</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shiəviyva': the flame"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shiəviyva': the flame</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) himmown: they"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) himmown: they</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qaTTil (pəʕil): was killed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qaTTil (pəʕil): was killed</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) haSSiquw (Slq hafʕel): take up"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) haSSiquw (Slq hafʕel): take up</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yattiyra': extremely"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yattiyra': extremely</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'ezeh ('zh partcpl passive): heated,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'ezeh ('zh partcpl passive): heated, heat</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) machtsəfah ('afʕel partcpl): harsh, severe."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) machtsəfah ('afʕel partcpl): harsh, severe. UBS: In this context it indicates that the king's order was firm and uncompromising.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) millat: command of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) millat: command of</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Ais ju, dong kasi jato itu tiga orang Yahudi yang ta'ika dong pi dalam itu ofen bésar.<bt>So then they dropped those three Yahudi people who were bound into that large oven/furnace. [EXEG: Aram: nəfaluw: they fell. UBS: the verb used here should not be one that is used for an accidental fall, but rather one that clearly indicates that the men were very intentionally dropped into the fire by other people.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) End of P section."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) End of P section.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məkhaptiyn (pəʕil partcpl): tied up"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məkhaptiyn (pəʕil partcpl): tied up</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yaqidta': burning"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yaqidta': burning</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nəfaluw: they fell. UBS: the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nəfaluw: they fell. UBS: the verb used here should not be one that is used for an accidental fall, but rather one that clearly indicates that the men were very intentionally dropped into the fire by other people.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) təlattehown: three of them"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) təlattehown: three of them</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yaqidta': burning"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yaqidta': burning</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Takuju sa, raja Nebukadnesar tanganga! Ais dia balompa kaluar dari dia pung korsi, ju tanya dia pung pagawe yang biasa kasi nasiat sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Karmana?! Tadi kotong lempar buang tiga orang pi dalam api, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>Suddenly raja Nebukadnesar was amazed/agape! Then he lept out of his chair, and asked his officials who often advised him saying, &lt;&lt;Weh [+there is a problem]Q What's going on?! We just threw three people into the fire, or [not]?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl, bapa.&gt;&gt;<bt>They responded saying, &lt;&lt;Correct, father.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yattsiyva': certainly"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yattsiyva': certainly</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hadavrowhiy: his high royal officials"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hadavrowhiy: his high royal officials</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hitbəhalah (bhl hitpəʕal): in haste"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hitbəhalah (bhl hitpəʕal): in haste</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qam: he stood up [suddenly]."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qam: he stood up [suddenly]. Would "jump up" work in Pidgin? OK.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) təwahh (twh): was amazed, alarmed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) təwahh (twh): was amazed, alarmed</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cot\co01362c.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ais raja kasi tau tamba bilang, &lt;&lt;Ma lia bae-bae doo! Te beta lia ada ampa orang yang jalan pi-datang dalam itu api. Dong sonde ta'ika. Dong sonde tabakar ju! Itu orang nomer ampa tu, kantara ke dewa satu!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then the raja spoke further saying, &lt;&lt;But look carefully! Cuz (elaboration) there are four people walking around in that fire. They are not bound. They are also not being burned! That number four one, appears like a god/deity!&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Aram. ‘appearance like a son of the gods’. = characteristics associated with gods; cf. ‘brood of vipers’, ‘sons of thunder’ etc. TH, NRSV, NLT, CEV, HCE, BIS, IVP, NET (and NET note). Unfortunately, TB has gone literal here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) End of S section."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) End of S section.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) bar-'əlahiy: a son of the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) bar-'əlahiy: a son of the gods; supernatural being (probably not "Son of God". Used in Job 1 probably for angels.)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) dameh: it is like"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) dameh: it is like</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rəviyʕaya' (q. rəviyʕa'ah): the fourth"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rəviyʕaya' (q. rəviyʕa'ah): the fourth one</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rewehh: their appearance"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rewehh: their appearance</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəval: hurt, injury"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəval: hurt, injury</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mahələkhiyn: walking around"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mahələkhiyn: walking around</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shərayin (shrh pass partcpl pl):"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shərayin (shrh pass partcpl pl): released</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Ais raja pi deka-deka deng ofen pung pintu kasi maso arang, ju batarea pi dalam itu api bilang, &lt;&lt;Hoe, bosong tiga! Sadrak, Mesak, deng Abednego, yang layani sang Allah yang Paling Tinggi tu! Mari kaluar suda!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then the raja went close to the oven/furnace door for putting in coal, and shouted into the fire, saying, &lt;&lt;Hoe [+attention], you three! Sadrak, Mesak, and Abednego, who serve the Most High God! Come on out!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Jadi dong tiga jalan kaluar dari dalam ofen.<bt>So (consequently) the three of them came out from inside the oven/furnace.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nafqiyn: they came out"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nafqiyn: they came out</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ve'ətow ('th): come!"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ve'ətow ('th): come!</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) puquw (npq imperv): come forth!"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) puquw (npq imperv): come forth!</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əlaha' ʕillaya' (q. ʕilla'ah): equivalent"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əlaha' ʕillaya' (q. ʕilla'ah): equivalent to 'el ʕelyon (Genesis 14:18)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yaqidta' (yqd partcpl): the one"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yaqidta' (yqd partcpl): the one burning</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) təraʕ: doorway, gate"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) təraʕ: doorway, gate</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ju itu orang dong samua yang pegang parenta di negara laen dong yang dengar-dengar sang raja Nebukadnesar, samua pagawe tinggi, gubernor, wakil gubernor, tukang putus parkara, tukang kasi nasiat, bendahara, deng kapala urusan dong lia deng mata kapala sandiri. Ais dong baku rampas ko mau lia bae-bae dolo. Dong samua lia bilang, itu api yang panas mati pung tu, sonde bekin apa-apa sang itu tiga orang Yahudi dong. Te dong pung badan, sonde angus. Dong pung rambu satu urat ju sonde tabakar. Dong pung pakean, sonde tabakar sadiki ju. Dong sonde baboo asap ju, sama ke itu api sonde sonto ame sang dong.<bt>Then all those people who ruled/governed in other countries who listened to/obeyed raja Nebukadnesar, all the high officials, governors, vice governors, judges, advisors, treasurers, and managers/dept. heads saw [this] with their own eyes. So they scrambled over each other [can be figurative] to try to see even better. They all saw that that incredibly hot fire had not done anything to those three Yahudi people. Cuz (elaboration) their bodies were not burned/singed. Not even one hair was burned2. Their clothes were also not burned evne a little. They did not smell of smoke either, as if that fire had not touched them at all. [DISCOURSE: list of officials mostly from 3:2 (and one from 3:24), so probably needs to be repeated here for referent tracking.] [DISCOURSE: Repetition and recap used in RL discourse to emphasize important points. Last clause is restatement, not addition.] [EXEG: check for good collocations: bodies - burned; hair - singed ; clothes - scorched. See NLT.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕədat: pass to them"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕədat: pass to them</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) reyach: smell"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) reyach: smell</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shənow: were [not] changed, damaged"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shənow: were [not] changed, damaged</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Sarbaleyhown: their robes"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Sarbaleyhown: their robes</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hitcharakh (chrk hitpaʕal): singe"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hitcharakh (chrk hitpaʕal): singe</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) səʕar: one hair"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) səʕar: one hair</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) geshməhown: their bodies"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) geshməhown: their bodies</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shəleT: had [no] power over"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shəleT: had [no] power over</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chazayin: they saw"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chazayin: they saw</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) haddavrey: high government officials"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) haddavrey: high government officials</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) fachəwata': territorial governors over districts"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) fachəwata': territorial governors over districts of a satrapy?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Signayya': assistants to the satraps"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Signayya': assistants to the satraps</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əchashdarpənayya': satraps, king's representatives put"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əchashdarpənayya': satraps, king's representatives put over conquered kingdoms (like MacArthur in Japan or Paul Bremer in Iraq)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mitkannəshiyn (knsh hitpaʕal): they assembled,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mitkannəshiyn (knsh hitpaʕal): they assembled, crowded around them, gathered</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cot\co01364c.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Lia itu samua-samua, ju raja Nebukadnesar angka omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Awii! Ini tiga orang ni, andia Sadrak, Mesak, deng Abednego, pung Tuhan Allah talalu hebat! Kotong musti angka nae puji sang Dia, te Dia su kirim Dia pung ana bua dari sorga satu ko kasi salamat sang Dia pung orang karjá dari ini hukuman api ni. Dong parcaya batúl sang Dia, sampe-sampe dong barani malawan raja. Dong ju sonde taku mati, asal dong sonde manyangkal dong pung Tuhan Allah sandiri, ko sémba dewa laen dong. Dong sémba sang Tuhan Allah sa, deng sonde mau bale balakang sang Dia ko biar dong bisa idop. Hebat, é!<bt>Seeing all that, raja Nebukadnesar began to speak saying, &lt;&lt;Awii [+amazement]! These three people here, that is Sadrak, Mesak, and Abednego, have an amazing God! We-inc must elevate praise to Him, cuz (elaboration) He has sent his underling (*angel) from heaven to save/rescue His workers from the punishment of fire. They truly believe (in) Him, to the point that they have the courage to oppose a raja/rajas (generic). They were not afraid of detah, as long as they did not deny their own God, to worthip other deities. They worship God alone, and do not want to turn their backs/reject His so that they could live. Amazing, é! [DISCOURSE: Last two clauses mostly recap for emphasis, following RL discourse patterns.] [EXEG: Aram. ‘yielded up their  bodies’ = ‘willing to die’ TH, NLT, CEV, HCE.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) le'lahəhuwn: to their own god"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) le'lahəhuwn: to their own god</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əlahh: gods"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əlahh: gods</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yiSgəduwn: they [did not] pay"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yiSgəduwn: they [did not] pay homage to</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yifləchuwn: they [did not] serve"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yifləchuwn: they [did not] serve</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) viyhavuw: they surrendered their bodies"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) viyhavuw: they surrendered their bodies</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shanniyw (shn' paʕʕel): they frustrated"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shanniyw (shn' paʕʕel): they frustrated</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕalowhiy: on him"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕalowhiy: on him</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hitrəchitsuw: they relied on, put"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hitrəchitsuw: they relied on, put their trust in</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Jadi, dengar bae-bae, te beta kasi turun atoran baru bagini: mulai sakarang, orang sonde bole omong tar bae sang ini orang Yahudi dong pung Tuhan Allah pung nama bae. Biar orang dari bangsa mana, ko, negara mana, ko, bahasa mana, ma sonde bole omong bekin rusak ini Sadrak, Mesak, deng Abednego pung Tuhan pung nama. Deng kalo ada orang yang langgar beta pung atoran ni, nanti beta suru orang ko potong buang dong pung kaki-tangan, ais bongkar buang dong pung ruma sampe sonde ada sisa ju. Te sonde ada tuhan laen yang bisa kasi salamat orang bagini!&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently) listen carefully, cuz (elaboration) I am handing down a new regulation like this: beginning now, people are not allowed to speak badly (=slander) to/toward/about these Yahudi people's God's name/reputation. [That applies] for people from no matter which race/ethnic group, which country, which language, [+contrary to expectation] they may not speak destructively of this Sadrak, Mesak, and Abednego's God2's name/reputation. And if there is a person who transgresses/violates this regulation of mine, I will order people to cut off their legs-arms (also: feet-hands), then tear apart/tear down/ dismantle their house(s), to the point that there is nothing left. Cuz (elaboration) there is no other god who can save/rescue people like this!&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: restructured broad-specific. Paragraph added for shift in theme.] [NOTE to daughter translations: similar phrasing to 2:5, but 2p -- 3p]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhattsalah (ntsl hafʕel): deliver"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhattsalah (ntsl hafʕel): deliver</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yikkul: is able"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yikkul: is able</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yishtawweh (sym hitp): BDB be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yishtawweh (sym hitp): BDB be made, be set, be laid</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nəwaliy: rubbish pile"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nəwaliy: rubbish pile</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vaytehh: his house"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vaytehh: his house</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yitʕəved (F): BDB be made"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yitʕəved (F): BDB be made into; be done, be wrought, be performed, be executed, be carried out</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) damiyn: members of the body,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) damiyn: members of the body, limbs (like 2:5)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shelah (q. shaluw): neglect, remissness;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shelah (q. shaluw): neglect, remissness; disrespect</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Təʕem: decree"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Təʕem: decree</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) siym: put"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) siym: put</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) minniy: from me"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) minniy: from me</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Ais itu ju, raja angka sang Sadrak, Mesak, deng Abednego ko jadi dia pung pagawe yang lebe tinggi lai di propinsi Babel.<bt>After that, the raja elevated/appointed Sadrak, Mesak, and Abednego to become his officials who were even higher (=raise in rank) in the province of Babel. [CHECK: lai (more important than before the event).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) End of P section."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) End of P section.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hatslach (tslch hafʕel): cause to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hatslach (tslch hafʕel): cause to prosper</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Raja Nebukadnesar kasi tau dia pung mimpi so'al satu pohon<bt>Raja Nebukadnesar tells his dream about a tree [TEXT: In the Aramaic text, this part is numbered as Daniel 3:31-33. KM is numbered as in the English translation, so that KM Daniel 4:4 corresponds to Aramaic Daniel 4:1. Indo. TB is versed like the English here.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="4" />
      <v n="1" />Ais satu kali, raja Nebukadnesar tulis satu surat ko kirim kasi samua bangsa, samua negara, deng samua bahasa di anteru dunya yang dia parenta dong. Itu surat pung bunyi bagini:<bt>Then one time, raja Nebukadnesar wrote a letter to send out to all races/ethnic groups, all countries, and all languages throughout the entire world that he governed. The letter sounded like this: [DISCOURSE/STYLE: The Aram. goes straight into direct speech here. NLT and CEV nicely build a kind of quote margin introducing the letter. NRSV is confusing, lacking signals that indicate any shift. We follow NLT style.] [EXEG: ‘throughout the earth’ hyperbole; see TH discussion. Restricted so not to be taken literally. (I can envision people in SE Asia starting to hunt for this edict. Several M &amp; C sects have been started with that sort of thing.)] [DISCOURSE: this is a different dream from the one in chapter 2, so the high-level discourse opener here should not imply a close connection with ch. 3.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Hormat deng salam dari beta, Nebukadnesar, yang jadi bosong samua pung raja bésar.<bt>&lt;&lt;Respect and greetings from me, Nebukadnesar, who is the raja over all of you-pl.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Biar ko bosong samua idop aman deng dame. Biar ko bosong dapa hasil bae dalam samua karjá.<bt>May you-pl all live in security-peace and relational-peace. May you-pl get good results in all your work. [EXEG: Aram. shəlamkhown: ‘well-being, prosperity, peace’. Unpacked to sound like a more formal opening from the king.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yisge' (sg' jussive): may it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yisge' (sg' jussive): may it grow great</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shəlamkhown: your (pl) well-being, prosperity,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shəlamkhown: your (pl) well-being, prosperity, peace</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Might have been Nabonidus, NBW,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Might have been Nabonidus, NBW, but Qumran Prayer of Nabonidus doesn't quite fit.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) da'əriyn (q. dayriyn dwr partcpl"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) da'əriyn (q. dayriyn dwr partcpl pl): who dwell. TWOT: The participle of such ayin-waw verbs regularly develops a medial aleph in BA: da'riyn.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="2" />Beta mau kasi tau sang bosong samua tanda heran yang Tuhan Allah yang Paling Tinggi su kasi tunju sang beta.<bt>I want to tell you-pl (about) all the *amazing signs (miracles) that the Most High God has shown to me. [DISCOURSE: the backwards literary syntax of the Aramaic should not be mirrored in the RLs in this region. It will only confuse. RLs indicate literary genre by word choice, parallelisms and doublets.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhachəwayah (chwh hafʕel inf): make"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhachəwayah (chwh hafʕel inf): make known</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qadamay: in my sight, in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qadamay: in my sight, in my judgment</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shəfar: BDB be fair, seemly."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shəfar: BDB be fair, seemly. The Hebrew equivalent emphasizes more the idea of beauty, which appears in an Aramaic derivative also.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕillaya' (q. ʕilla'ah): superior, highest"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕillaya' (q. ʕilla'ah): superior, highest</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕimmiy: toward me, on my"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕimmiy: toward me, on my behalf</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕəvad: he made"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕəvad: he made</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) timhayya' (təmahh): the wonders"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) timhayya' (təmahh): the wonders</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'atayya': the miraculous signs, wonders."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'atayya': the miraculous signs, wonders. Occurring only three times, this word is used similarly to its Hebrew cognate 'ot.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="3" />Te Dia pung tanda dong, talalu hebat!<bt>Cuz (elaboration) His signs are truly amazing!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia pung hasil karjá dong, kasi tunju Dia pung kuasa ju!<bt>The results/fruits of His work also shows/demonstrates His power/authority!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia pung pegang parenta sonde tau barenti.<bt>His rule/governing never ends.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia ju jadi raja dari turunan satu pi turunan laen dong, sonde putus-putus.<bt>He is raja from one generation to the next (plural), without ceasing.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shalTanehh: his sovereignty"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shalTanehh: his sovereignty</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) malkhuwtehh: his kingdom"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) malkhuwtehh: his kingdom</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) taqqiyfiyn. (pl): strong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) taqqiyfiyn. (pl): strong</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ravrəviyn (pl reduplicated): great"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ravrəviyn (pl reduplicated): great</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Dia pung carita bagini: satu kali, beta, andia raja Nebukadnesar, ada dudu biasa-biasa dalam beta pung istana sa. Samua jalan deng bae.<bt>The story is like this: one time I, raja Nebukadnesar, was just sitting as usual in my palace. Everything was going well. [DISCOURSE: 1st clause, signal shift to narrative.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) raʕənan: prosperous, flourishing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) raʕənan: prosperous, flourishing</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) həweyt (hwh): it happened, it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) həweyt (hwh): it happened, it was</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shəleh: be at ease"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shəleh: be at ease</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Ma ais satu malam, beta ada tidor di beta pung koi, ju beta dapa satu mimpi yang bekin beta taku. Itu hal dong yang beta lia tu, bekin beta jadi taku mau mati sa!<bt>But then one night, I was sleeping/laying on my bed, and I had/encountered/experienced a dream which made me afraid. The things which I saw made me terrified! [EXEG: time margin added to signal shift from generic-specific, following NLT, HCE.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəvahəlunnaniy (bhl paʕʕel): frightened me"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəvahəlunnaniy (bhl paʕʕel): frightened me</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) harhoriyn: mental conceptions, fantasies, images,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) harhoriyn: mental conceptions, fantasies, images, mental pictures, fancies, imaginings</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) viydachəlinnaniy (dchl paʕʕel): it made"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) viydachəlinnaniy (dchl paʕʕel): it made me afraid</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Jadi beta suru kumpul samua orang pintar dong di Babel, ko biar dong datang kasi tau sang beta itu mimpi pung arti.<bt>So (consequently) I ordered together all my wise/knowledgable people in Babel, so that they could come and tell me the meaning of my dream. [NOTE to daughter translations: cf. your term in 2:12.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəhowdʕunnaniy (ydʕ hafʕel): they were"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəhowdʕunnaniy (ydʕ hafʕel): they were to inform me. BDB let someone know, communicate, inform, cause to know</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) fəsar: interpretation"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) fəsar: interpretation</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chakkiymey: wise men of. TWOT:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chakkiymey: wise men of. TWOT: Used mostly of the court astrologers in Daniel.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhanəʕalah (ʕll hafʕel inf): bring"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhanəʕalah (ʕll hafʕel inf): bring in</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Təʕem: decree, order"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Təʕem: decree, order</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) minniy: from me"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) minniy: from me</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Andia ko dong samua datang bakumpul. Andia: orang pintar, tukang suanggi, tukang rai-rai, deng orang Kasdim yang pintar lia bintang dong samua datang bakumpul. Beta carita kasi tau itu mimpi pung isi, ma dong sonde bisa kasi tau itu mimpi pung arti.<bt>That is why they all came and gathered. That is: the wise/knowledgable people, the sorcerers, the diviners, and the Kasdim people who are skilled at observing the stars came and gathered. I told the contents of that dream, but they were not able to tell/explain the meaning of that dream. [NOTE to daughter translations: cf. your list of terms in 2:2.] [DISCOURSE: repetition following RL patterns.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Lama-lama, baru satu orang datang. Dia pung nama Daniel. Dia pung nama laen, andia Beltasasar, iko beta pung dewa pung nama. Ju kuasa dari dewa-dewi yang barisi dong ada di dia pung idop. Ais beta carita kasi tau beta pung mimpi sang dia,<bt>Eventually, one person came. His name is Daniel. His other name is Beltasasar, according to the name of my god/deity. And the power/authority of the holy/clean deities was in/on his life. So then I narrated my dream to him, [DISCOURSE: restructured for RL background-foreground patterns.]</bt><v n="9" />bilang, &lt;Beltasasar, dengar sang beta. Beta inga bilang, lu ni jadi mandor yang ator ame samua orang pintar di Babel. Beta ju tau bilang, kuasa dari dewa-dewi yang barisi dong ada di lu pung idop. Lu bisa buka rahasia dong. Sonde ada rahasia yang talalu susa kasi sang lu. Naa, dengar beta pung mimpi, ko biar lu bisa kasi tau itu mimpi pung arti.<bt>saying, &lt;Beltasasar, listen to me. I remember that you are a supervisor who manages/oversee the wise/knowledgable people in Babel. I also know that the power/authority of the holy/clean deities is in/on your life. You can reveal secrets. There are no secrets which are too difficult for you. Naa [+shift], listen to my dream, so that you can tell the meaning of that dream. [NOTE to daughter translations: cf. your term in 2:48.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chezwey: visions of, apparitions of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chezwey: visions of, apparitions of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'aneS: oppress, distress"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'aneS: oppress, distress</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) raz: secret"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) raz: secret</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Yang beta lia dalam mimpi waktu beta ada tidor di atas koi, bagini:<bt>What I saw in a dream while I was sleeping/laying on the bed was like this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ada satu pohon di dunya pung teng-tenga.<bt>There was a tree in the middle of the world. [EXEG: Aram. ‘middle/inside of land/world/ earth’. HCE note: UBS: the exact geographical location of the tree is unimportant. What is significant is that it is the center of attention for the whole world. The tree is a common biblical symbol for life and power. IVPC: The concept of the cosmic tree in the center of the world is a common motif in the ancient Near East. It is also used in Ezekiel 31. The roots of the tree are fed by the great subterranean ocean, and its top merges with the clouds, thus binding together the heavens, the earth and the netherworld.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Itu pohon talalu tinggi.<bt>That tree was very high.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) saggiy': great"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) saggiy': great</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ruwmehh: its height"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ruwmehh: its height</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'arʕa': land, world, earth. UBS:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'arʕa': land, world, earth. UBS: the exact geographical location of the tree is unimportant. What is significant is that it is the center of attention for the whole world. The tree is a common biblical symbol for life and power. IVPC: The concept of the cosmic tree in the center of the world is a common motif in the ancient Near East. It is also used in Ezekiel 31. The roots of the tree are fed by the great subterranean ocean, and its top merges with the clouds, thus binding together the heavens, the earth and the netherworld.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) gow' (gaw): the middle, inside"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) gow' (gaw): the middle, inside</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'iylan: tree"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'iylan: tree</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əluw: behold! lo!"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əluw: behold! lo!</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) həweyt: exist, be there, there"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) həweyt: exist, be there, there was, there appeared</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chazeh: he saw, looked"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chazeh: he saw, looked</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="11" />Itu pohon batumbu jadi bésar deng kuat.<bt>That tree grew becomeing large and strong.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia pung ujung sampe di langit.<bt>The tips reached to the sky/heaven.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Samua orang bisa dapa lia itu pohon,<bt>All people could see that tree,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dari dunya pung huk-huk.<bt>from the ends/corners of the world.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Sowf: end"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Sowf: end</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəzowtehh: its visibility"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəzowtehh: its visibility</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yimTe': it reached, extended"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yimTe': it reached, extended</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) təqif: it grew strong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) təqif: it grew strong</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ravah: it grew tall and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ravah: it grew tall and large. UBS: the two verbs in Aramaic indicate clearly a change in the state of the tree.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="12" />Dia pung daon dong, garui.<bt>Its leaves were lush.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia pung bua dong talalu banya,<bt>Its fruit were abundant,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sampe samua-samua yang ada di ini dunya bisa makan dari itu pohon.<bt>to the point that everyone on earth could eat from that tree.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Binatang utan dong cari sombar di itu pohon.<bt>Wild animals seek shade under that tree.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Burung di langit dong basarang di dia pung ujung-ujung.<bt>Birds in the sky nest in its branches.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Samua yang idop, makan dari itu pohon.<bt>Everything that lives, eats from that tree.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) bisra': flesh, all living things"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) bisra': flesh, all living things</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yitziyn: (zwn histafʕal? yitpaʕʕal?): fed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yitziyn: (zwn histafʕal? yitpaʕʕal?): fed themselves</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tsippərey: birds of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tsippərey: birds of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəduruwn (q. yəduwran): they dwelt"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəduruwn (q. yəduwran): they dwelt</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕanfowhiy: its branches"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕanfowhiy: its branches</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) bara' (bar): the field"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) bara' (bar): the field</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) cheywat: beasts. BDB The Hebrew"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) cheywat: beasts. BDB The Hebrew "chay" means both "living" and "living thing or animal." The Aramaic "chewah" seems more specialized for beasts—both the literal animals and the symbolic beasts of Daniel.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) taTlel (Tll hafʕel): it had"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) taTlel (Tll hafʕel): it had shade. BDB Used only in the Haphel. This word is not related to the noun Tal, but comes from the Hebrew tsalal hif 'give shade'. Note the T-ts interchange.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) təchotowhiy: under it. BDB under"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) təchotowhiy: under it. BDB under the shadow of a tree (Dan 4:12, 21 [A 9, 18]).</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kholla': all. Holladay: all (persons"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kholla': all. Holladay: all (persons and things)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mazown: food"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mazown: food</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) saggiy': great; much, many"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) saggiy': great; much, many</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ' inbehh ('ev): BDB fruit,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ' inbehh ('ev): BDB fruit, fresh, young, greening</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shappiyr: BDB fair, beautiful (of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shappiyr: BDB fair, beautiful (of foliage)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕ afyehh: its leafage, foliage"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕ afyehh: its leafage, foliage</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Naa, waktu beta ada tidor di atas koi, beta lia tarús. Yang beta lia dalam mimpi, bagini:<bt>Naa [+shift], when I was sleeping/laying on the bed, I kept looking. What I saw in a dream was like this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ada satu tukang bawa pasán yang turun datang dari langit.<bt>There was a messenger who came down from the sky/heaven. [EXEG: Aram. ‘watcher’, NRSV ‘watcher’, NLT ‘messenger’, CEV ‘angel’ (but not normal term for angel, so CEV is problematic); TB ‘guard’; In our RLs a ‘watcher’ would be a passive role, whereas in vs. 14-17 he gives instructions, so we go with ‘bringer of instructions/messenger’ from context, following NLT.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia tu, barisi kasi sang Tuhan.<bt>He was clean/holy to/for God2.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nachit (nəchat partcpl): coming down,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nachit (nəchat partcpl): coming down, descending</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qaddiysh: holy"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qaddiysh: holy</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕiyr: angelic watcher. BDB watchful"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕiyr: angelic watcher. BDB watchful (i.e. an angel). Cognate to the Hebrew (u=r I, "awake."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="14" />Ju dia batarea ukur kuat bilang,<bt>And he shouted with all his might saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">&lt;&lt;Tabáng buang itu pohon su!<bt>&lt;&lt;Cut down/fell that tree now!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Potong buang dia pung cabang dong!<bt>Cut off its branches!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Koru buang dia pung daon samua!<bt>Strip off all its leaves!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ketu buang dia pung bua!<bt>Pick off all its fruit!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Biar ko binatang dong batasiram buang dari itu pohon.<bt>Let the animals be scattered away from that tree.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Biar ko burung dong kaná usir buang dari dia pung ujung dong!<bt>Let the birds be chased away from its branches/tips!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) cheywəta': the wild animals"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) cheywəta': the wild animals</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tənud (nwd imperv)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tənud (nwd imperv)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'inbehh: its fruit"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'inbehh: its fruit</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vaddaruw (bdr imperv): scatter"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vaddaruw (bdr imperv): scatter</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'attaruw (ntr 'afʕel imperv): strip"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'attaruw (ntr 'afʕel imperv): strip off</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕanfowhiy: its branches"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕanfowhiy: its branches</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qattsitsuw (paʕʕel imperv): lop off,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qattsitsuw (paʕʕel imperv): lop off, cut off, chop off</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) godduw (gdd imperv pl): cut"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) godduw (gdd imperv pl): cut down, chop down</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chayil: strength, strong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chayil: strength, strong</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qare': he announced with force"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qare': he announced with force (3:4)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="15" />Ma kasi tenga dia pung akar deng dia pung batang sisa,<bt>But leave its roots and its stump,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tadudu di tana.<bt>sitting in the ground.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Pake galáng dari bési deng tambaga ko ika sang itu batang sisa.<bt>Use bracelets/rings of iron/steel and bronze to bind that stump.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng kasi tenga ko rumput baru dong batumbu kuliling batang sisa.<bt>And allow new grass to grow around the stump.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Itu sama ke satu orang yang kaná basa abis,<bt>That is like a person who is made wet (all over), [DISCOURSE / EXEG: Aram. shift in pronoun from ‘it (stump)’ to ‘him’ -- interpreted as the ruler from vs. 17, which later is revealed to be Nebukadnesar. HCE note: At this point the commentators recommend that it be clear that from here on the watcher/messenger/angel is talking about a person, not a tree.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dari kabut yang turun datang dari langit.<bt>from dew/mist that comes down from the sky.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Biar ko dia idop sama ke binatang dong,<bt>Let him live like the animals,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">yang idop cuma makan rumput sa.<bt>who live only eating grass.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕəsav: green stuff, grass"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕəsav: green stuff, grass</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəlaqehh: his portion, possession, lot"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəlaqehh: his portion, possession, lot</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yitsTabbaʕ (tsbʕ hitpaʕʕal): be wet"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yitsTabbaʕ (tsbʕ hitpaʕʕal): be wet</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Tal: dew. At this point"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Tal: dew. At this point the commentators recommend that it be clear that from here on the angel is talking about a person, not a tree.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) bara': the field"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) bara': the field</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) dit'a': the grass"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) dit'a': the grass</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əSuwr: with a band"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əSuwr: with a band</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shəvuquw (puʕʕal imperv [passive] pl):"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shəvuquw (puʕʕal imperv [passive] pl): let them be left</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shrshowhiy: its taproot"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shrshowhiy: its taproot</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕiqqar: stump"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕiqqar: stump</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) bəram: only, nevertheless"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) bəram: only, nevertheless</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="16" />Biar ko itu orang sonde pikir sama ke manusia lai,<bt>Let that person no longer think like humans,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma dia pikir sama ke binatang dong,<bt>but he thinks like animals,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sampe tuju taon su lewat.<bt>until seven years have passed. [EXEG: Aram. ‘let 7 times pass over him’; see discusssion in TH which recommends translating it as ‘years’, followed by TEV, CEV, and HCE. HCE note: Aram. ‘times’; Daniel uses this for ‘years’. UBS: The use of the word for “time” as “year” is peculiar to Daniel (compare 4.23, 25, 32; 7.25; 12.7), but it is well established.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yachləfuwn (chlp): may they pass"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yachləfuwn (chlp): may they pass over</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕiddaniyn: times; Daniel uses this"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕiddaniyn: times; Daniel uses this for 'years'. UBS: The use of the word for "time" as "year" is peculiar to Daniel (compare 4.23, 25, 32; 7.25; 12.7), but it is well established.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yityəhiv (yhb yitpəʕel): let it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yityəhiv (yhb yitpəʕel): let it be given to him</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəshannown (shnh paʕʕel pl): transform"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəshannown (shnh paʕʕel pl): transform</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="17" />Tukang bawa pasán dong yang kasi tau ini hukuman,<bt>The messengers who told this punishment, [DISCOURSE: Aram. is rendered in poetic parallelisms.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dong yang barisi buat Tuhan yang kasi turun ini putusan,<bt>they are clean/holy to God2 who handed down this decision,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko biar samua yang idop bisa tau bilang,<bt>so that everything that lives can know that,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Yang Paling Tinggi pegang parenta di manusia pung karaja'an samua.<bt>The One Most High rules/governs all human kingdoms.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Te Dia yang pili ame sapa yang jadi raja,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) He is the one who chooses/ selects who becomes raja,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">iko Dia pung suka.<bt>according to His liking.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia ju yang bisa angka nae<bt>He is also the one who can elevate/appoint</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">orang yang sonde ada pung nama,<bt>people who have no name/reputation (=insignificant),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko pegang parenta di satu negara.&gt;&gt;<bt>to rule/govern in a country.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕəlayyahh (q. ʕəlahh): over it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕəlayyahh (q. ʕəlahh): over it [a kingdom]</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəqiym (qwm hafʕel imperf): he"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəqiym (qwm hafʕel imperf): he raises up, establishes</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shəfal: the lowliest in status"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shəfal: the lowliest in status</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yitninnahh (pəʕal imperf): he gives."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yitninnahh (pəʕal imperf): he gives.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yitsbe' (tsbh): he likes, wishes"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yitsbe' (tsbh): he likes, wishes</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləman: because of that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləman: because of that</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'ənowsha' (q. 'ənasha'): men"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'ənowsha' (q. 'ənasha'): men</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) malkhuwt: kingdom, real"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) malkhuwt: kingdom, real</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕillaya' (q. ʕilla'ah)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕillaya' (q. ʕilla'ah)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shalliyT: he has the authority"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shalliyT: he has the authority</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chayyayya': the ones who are"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chayyayya': the ones who are alive</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yindəʕuwn"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yindəʕuwn</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) divrat: cause, reason"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) divrat: cause, reason</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shə'elta': question, matter, affair"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shə'elta': question, matter, affair</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) pitgama': BDB command, word, affair."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) pitgama': BDB command, word, affair. Loan word from Persian. UBS: it is important that the translation avoid giving the impression that the angels are capable of making decisions themselves. They are, in fact, only messengers or bearers of the decision made by God.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕiyriyn. UBS: The parallelism at"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕiyriyn. UBS: The parallelism at the beginning of this verse should be translated in such a way as to avoid making the reader think of two different events. The word sentence corresponds to decision; and the watchers obviously has the same meaning as the holy ones.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) gəzerat: decree of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) gəzerat: decree of</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Beta pung mimpi bagitu sa. Itu samua tu, yang beta, andia raja Nebukadnesar, ada lia dalam mimpi. Naa, sakarang lu, Beltasasar, musti kasi tau itu mimpi pung arti. Te dari beta pung orang pintar samua yang ada di negara yang beta parenta dong, sonde ada satu ju yang bisa kasi tau itu mimpi pung arti. Ma pasti lu bisa, te kuasa dari dewa-dewi yang barisi dong ada di lu pung idop.&gt;&gt;<bt>My dream was like that. All of that is what I, raja Nebukadnesar, saw in my dream. Naa [+shift], now you, Beltasasar, must explain the meaning of that dream. Cuz (elaboration) from/among all of my wise/knowledgable people that are in the countries that I govern, there is not even one person who can explain the meaning of that dream.  But surely you can, cuz (elaboration) the power/authority of the clean/holy deities is in/on your life.&gt;&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: cf. 4:8-9 for how you rendered ‘spirit of the holy gods’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kahel: is able"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kahel: is able</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Daniel buka ame itu mimpi so'al pohon pung arti<bt>Daniel unveils the meaning of the dream about a tree</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ju raja sambung dia pung surat bilang, &lt;&lt;Waktu dia dengar beta pung omong bagitu, ju Daniel (yang kotong kanál deng nama Babel, andia Beltasasar), ilang kira. Dia ju hati susa, te itu mimpi pung arti ada bekin taku sang dia. Ais beta kasi tau sang dia bilang, &lt;Beltasasar, dengar bae-bae sang beta! Lu sonde usa taku deng itu mimpi deng dia pung arti.&gt;<bt>The raja continued his letter saying, &lt;&lt;When he heard what I had to say like that, then Daniel (who we also know with/by the Babel name, that is Beltasasar), was stunned/lost thought. His liver was troubled, cuz (elaboration) the meaning of that dream was frightening him. So/then I told him saying, &lt;Beltasasar, listen carefully to me! You do not need to be frightened by the dream and its meaning.&gt; [EXEG: Aram: 'eshtowmam (shmm itpolel): be appalled, stunned. BDB be appalled. Used only in Dan 4:19. NRSV ‘severely distressed’; NLT ‘overcome’; CEV ‘terribly confused’; HCE ‘no can tink an come real bum out’. Aram: shaʕahh: brief time, moment ‘for a moment, for a time, for a while’ understranslated here, implied by context as in HCE.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju dia manyao sang beta bilang, &lt;Bagini, bapa raja. Lebe bae, biar ko itu mimpi kaná deng orang yang bamusu deng bapa. Deng itu mimpi pung arti jato kaná di orang yang malawan sang raja. Ma dia pung batúl, itu mimpi jato kaná di bapa raja.<bt>Then he responded to me saying, &lt;It's like this, father raja. It would be better/best if that dream applied to people who are enemies with father (=you). And the meaning of that dream fall upon those who oppose the raja. But in fact/truth, that dream applies to father raja. [DISCOURSE: structured as poetic parallelism.] [EXEG: High level syntax implies that this is not so, but is actually about the king. NLT &amp; CEV both try to reflect this with ‘I wish’ (NLT also adds ‘and not to you’). TH notes this clear implication. HCE makes the implication explicit ‘But az not how going be. Da dream bout you!’ TB is ambiguous and could easily be read incorrectly.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕarayikh (q. ʕarakh): your enemies"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕarayikh (q. ʕarakh): your enemies</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) san'eyikh (q. san'akh): the ones"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) san'eyikh (q. san'akh): the ones who hate you</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mar'iy (q. mariy): my lord"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mar'iy (q. mariy): my lord</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəvahəlakh: may it now dismay"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəvahəlakh: may it now dismay you, alarm you</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) həlunnehh (puʕal): were dismayed, alarmed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) həlunnehh (puʕal): were dismayed, alarmed</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) raʕyonohiy: his thoughts"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) raʕyonohiy: his thoughts</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chədah: one"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chədah: one</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shaʕahh: brief time, moment"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shaʕahh: brief time, moment</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'eshtowmam (shmm itpolel): be appalled,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'eshtowmam (shmm itpolel): be appalled, stunned. BDB be appalled. Used only in Dan 4:16. This is the word which in the Hebrew sections of Dan refers to the "abomination of desolation," Dan 12:11, etc.</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Te dalam itu mimpi, bapa raja dapa lia satu pohon yang talalu tinggi. Dia batumbu jadi bésar deng kuat. Dia pung ujung ju sampe di langit. Samua orang bisa dapa lia itu pohon dari dunya pung huk-huk.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) in that dream, father raja can see a very tall tree. It grows to become large and strong. Its tips reach the sky. Everyone can see that tree from the far corners of the earth. [NOTE to daughter translations: check your phrasing in 4:10-11.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəzowtehh: its visibility"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəzowtehh: its visibility</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Dia pung daon dong, garui. Dia pung bua dong talalu banya, sampe samua-samua yang ada di ini dunya bisa makan dari itu pohon. Binatang utan dong cari sombar di itu pohon. Burung di langit dong basarang di dia pung ujung-ujung.<bt>Its leaves are lush. It has an abundance of fruit, to the point that everyone/thing in this world can eat from that tree. Wild animals seek shade at (under) that tree. Birds in the sky nest in its branches/tips. [NOTE to daughter translations: cf wording in 4:12.]</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cot\co01363c.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Naa, itu pohon tu, satu gambar dari bapa raja sandiri! Te bapa raja su batumbu jadi bésar deng kuat. Bapa raja pung nama yang hebat su tasiar pi mana-mana, sampe di langit ju. Deng bapa raja ada pegang parenta sampe di dunya pung huk-huk.<bt>Naa [+shift], that tree is a picture of father raja himself/yourself! Cuz (elaboration) father raja has grown great and strong. Father raja's impressive name/reputation has spread reaching everywhere, even to the sky/heaven. And father raja rules/governs as far as the far ends of the earth. [DISCOURSE: shift to interpretation.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məTat (fem): it extends"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məTat (fem): it extends</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rəvuwtakh: your greatness"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rəvuwtakh: your greatness</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ais itu ju, bapa raja lia ada satu tukang bawa pasán yang turun datang dari langit. Dia tu, barisi buat Tuhan. Ju dia kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Tabáng buang itu pohon deng kasi ancor buang su! Ma kasi tenga dia pung akar deng dia pung batang sisa, tadudu di tana sa. Pake galáng dari bési deng tambaga ko ika sang itu batang sisa. Deng kasi tenga ko rumput baru dong batumbu kuliling itu pohon. Itu sama ke satu orang yang kaná basa abis dari kabut yang turun datang dari langit. Biar ko dia idop sama ke binatang yang idop cuma makan rumput dong, sampe lewat tuju taon.&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, father raja saw a messenger come down from sky/heaven. He was clean/holy to God2. And he told saying, &lt;&lt;Cut down/fell that tree and destroy it now! But leave its roots and its stump sitting in the ground. Use bracelets/ rings of iron and bronze to bind that stump. And allow new grass to grow around that tree. That is like a person who is made wet (all over) from dew/ mist that comes down from sky/heaven. Let him live like the animals that live only by eating grass, until seven years have passed.&gt;&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: cf 4:13-16 with several changes in wording. EXEG: ditto.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yachləfuwn: let them pass over"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yachləfuwn: let them pass over</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yitsTabbaʕ (tsbʕ hitpaʕal): let him"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yitsTabbaʕ (tsbʕ hitpaʕal): let him be wet</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shəvuquw (imperv pl): leave it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shəvuquw (imperv pl): leave it there</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chabbəluwhiy: let them destroy it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chabbəluwhiy: let them destroy it</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) godduw: let them hew, chop,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) godduw: let them hew, chop, cut down</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nachit (partcpl): coming down"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nachit (partcpl): coming down</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕiyr: angelic messenger"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕiyr: angelic messenger</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Naa, bapa raja yang mulia! Tuhan Allah yang Paling Tinggi su putus memang apa yang mau jadi di bapa raja. Itu mimpi pung arti bagini:<bt>Naa [+shift], most glorious father raja! God Most High has already decided beforehand what is going to happen to father raja (=you). the meaning of that dream is like this:</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məTat: it reaches, extends"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məTat: it reaches, extends</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) gəzerat: decree"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) gəzerat: decree</Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Nanti rakyat dong mau usir buang sang bapa raja ko tenga deng binatang utan dong. Nanti bapa makan rumput sama ke sapi dong. Nanti bapa kaná basa dari kabut yang turun datang dari langit. Kalo su lewat itu tuju taon, nanti bapa mangarti batúl bilang, Tuhan Allah yang Paling Tinggi yang pegang kuasa. Dia yang ada pung hak ko parenta samua pamarenta di ini dunya. Dia ju yang putus iko Dia pung suka sandiri so'al sapa yang pegang parenta di mana-mana.<bt>The populace are going to evict father raja to live among the wild animals. Father will eat grass like cows. Father will become wet from dew/mist that comes down from sky/heaven. After seven years have passed, then father will truly understand that the Most High God is the one who holds power/authority. He is the one who has the right to rule/govern all the govenrments on earth. He is also the one who decides as he likes about who will rule/govern in all places/wherever. [EXEG: gives it = allows to rule; NLT, CEV, HCE]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yitninnahh: he gives it [kingship]"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yitninnahh: he gives it [kingship]</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yitsbe': he wants to do."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yitsbe': he wants to do. Like 4:17</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tindaʕ (ydʕ pəʕal): you know,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tindaʕ (ydʕ pəʕal): you know, come to know?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mətsabbəʕiyn (paʕʕel partcpl): one who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mətsabbəʕiyn (paʕʕel partcpl): one who wets something</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəTaʕəmuwn (paʕʕel): will cause to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəTaʕəmuwn (paʕʕel): will cause to eat</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) towriyn: BDB bull, young bull,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) towriyn: BDB bull, young bull, ox (for sacrifice)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕisba': grass"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕisba': grass</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mədorakh: your dwelling place"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mədorakh: your dwelling place</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Tardiyn (partcpl pl): they will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Tardiyn (partcpl pl): they will drive away, drive from, chase away</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Dalam bapa raja pung mimpi tu, ada yang suru ko kasi tenga itu pohon pung akar deng dia pung batang sisa, tadudu di tana sa. Itu, dia pung arti bilang, kalo bapa su mangarti deng mangaku batúl bilang, Tuhan Allah yang Paling Tinggi yang batúl-batúl pegang parenta, na, pasti Dia nanti angka ulang sang bapa ko jadi raja lai.<bt>In that dream of father raja, there is someone who orders to leave that trees roots and its stump sitting in the ground. The meaning of that is that if/when father truly understands and acknowledges that the Most High God is the one who truly rules/governs, na, surely He will restore father to become raja again.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qayyamah: it is preserved [for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qayyamah: it is preserved [for you]</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'iylana': the tree"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'iylana': the tree</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mishbaq (pəʕal inf): leave undisturbed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mishbaq (pəʕal inf): leave undisturbed</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cot\co01365c.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Jadi bagini, bapa raja. Jang mara kalo beta omong jujur sa. Beta ju minta ko bapa tarima bae beta pung nasiat bagini: angka buang samua sala deng jahat, andia samua parkara deng pikiran yang malawan sang Tuhan Allah, deng samua yang bekin Dia pung hati tar enak. Jang bekin ulang lai! Idop iko Tuhan pung jalan lurus. Kasi tunju hati bae sang orang kasian dong, deng tolong orang yang kaná tendes dong. Deng bagitu, moga-moga bapa raja bisa pegang parenta sampe lama ju.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently) it's like this, father raja. Do not be angry (= I apologise) if I speak honestly. I also request that father (=you) accept positively my advice like this: get rid of all wrongs and evil, that is everything and all thinking which opposes God, and everything that makes Him feel displeased. Don't do it again! Live according to God2's straight path. Show good liver/kindness to unfortunate people, and help people who are oppressed. In that way, may father raja (=you) be able to hold rule/govern for a long time.&gt;&gt;&gt; [EXEG: translations go in many directions on all parts of this verse. A couple of Heb. thoughts are reinforced here from two angles, all supported by various sources. Repetition and rephrasing is good RL style, and I think better reflects the intent of the Aramaic here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) lishlewətakh: for your rule"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) lishlewətakh: for your rule</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'arkhah: BDB prolongation, lengthening, prolonging"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'arkhah: BDB prolongation, lengthening, prolonging</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕənayin: those who are miserable"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕənayin: those who are miserable</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) michan (inf): by showing favor"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) michan (inf): by showing favor</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕəwayatakh: your offenses"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕəwayatakh: your offenses</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) fəruq (imperv): break off, tear"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) fəruq (imperv): break off, tear away</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vachəTayakh (q. vachəTa'akh): kətiv your"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vachəTayakh (q. vachəTa'akh): kətiv your sin, qəre': your sin-offering</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yishpar: may it seem good"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yishpar: may it seem good to you</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) milkiy: my advice"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) milkiy: my advice</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) lahen: therefore"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) lahen: therefore</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Bapa raja pung mimpi, jadi batúl</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Naa, samua-samua yang Daniel kasi tau tu, jato kaná di raja Nebukadnesar.<bt>Naa [+shift], everything that Daniel told, happened to raja Nebukadnesar. [DISCOURSE: clarify what ‘this’ means.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) End of P section."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) End of P section.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mməTa'"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mməTa'</Message></Annotation><v n="29" />Satu kali, waktu 12 bulan su lewat, raja ada jalan cari angin di dia pung istana pung teras atas di kota Babel.<bt>One time, when 12 months had passed, the raja was walking seeking wind (idiom: taking a stroll) on the upper terrace of his palace in Babel. [EXEG: Aram: məhallekh: ‘walking around’ = Kupang idiom ‘look for wind’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məhallekh: walking around"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məhallekh: walking around</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) malkhuwta': royal"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) malkhuwta': royal</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) heykhal: [on top of] the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) heykhal: [on top of] the</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tərey (təriyn): two"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tərey (təriyn): two</Message></Annotation><v n="30" />Lia-lia kota Babel, ju dia pikir bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini kota ni pung bagus lai! Hebat, ó! Beta yang kasi bangun ini kota pake beta pung kuasa deng beta pung pintar sandiri, ko biar dia pantas jadi pusat ko beta pegang parenta dari sini. Deng bagitu, samua orang bisa angka tinggi beta pung nama yang hebat.&gt;&gt;<bt>Looking around at the city of Babel, he thought, &lt;&lt;This city is really beautiful! Amazing, ó! I have built this city using my own power/authority and my own smarts/cleverness, so it is fitting to be/become the center for me to rule/govern from here. In that way, everyone can lift up/exalt my amazing name/reputation.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Aram: təqaf: in strength; chiSniy: my might; we take this as a doublet to highlight 2 aspects of bragging rights he used to build the city. In Kupang, ‘power/authority’ and ‘cleverness/skill’ are the natural candidates.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hadriy: my honor, majesty"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hadriy: my honor, majesty</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) liyqar: for honor, esteem, value"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) liyqar: for honor, esteem, value</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chiSniy: my might"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chiSniy: my might</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) təqaf: in strength"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) təqaf: in strength</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) malkhuw: royal palace"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) malkhuw: royal palace</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Waktu dia masi omong bagitu, ju ada suara yang turun datang dari sorga bilang, &lt;&lt;Raja Nebukadnesar, dengar dolo, te Beta ada omong sang lu! Beta su cabu ame lu pung kuasa. Lu sonde pegang hak parenta lai.<bt>While he was still talking like that, there was a voice came down from heaven saying, &lt;&lt;Raja Nebukadnesar, listen up, cuz (elaboration) I am speaking to you! I have withdrawn (e.g. pulled up [roots], taken sword out of scabbard, pulled a plug) your power/authority. You no longer hold the right to rule/govern anymore.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕədat: has passed away"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕədat: has passed away</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'amriyn (partcpl pl): am saying"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'amriyn (partcpl pl): am saying</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nəfal: come down, fall"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nəfal: come down, fall</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) bəfum: mouth"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) bəfum: mouth</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) milləta': the word"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) milləta': the word</Message></Annotation><v n="32" />Nanti rakyat dong mau usir buang sang lu ko tenga deng binatang utan dong. Nanti lu makan rumput sama ke sapi dong. Kalo su lewat itu tuju taon, nanti lu mangarti batúl bilang, Tuhan Allah yang Paling Tinggi yang pegang kuasa. Dia yang ada pung hak ko parenta samua pamarenta di ini dunya. Dia ju yang putus iko Dia pung suka sandiri so'al sapa yang pegang parenta di mana-mana.&gt;&gt;<bt>The populace will evict/chase you out to live with the wild animals. You will eat grass like the cows. When seven years have passed, then you will truly understand that the Most High God is the one who holds power/authority. He is the one who has the right to rule/govern all governments on this earth. He is also the one who decides as He likes about who it is that will hold rule in all places/everywhere/wherever. [NOTE to daughter translations: cf. 4:25, but no mention of dew here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəTaʕəmuwn: they will cause you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəTaʕəmuwn: they will cause you to eat</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mədorakh: your dwelling"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mədorakh: your dwelling</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Tardiyn: they will drive you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Tardiyn: they will drive you away</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(cn) Oh, this book is encouraging!"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(cn) Oh, this book is encouraging!  God is in charge!</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cot\co01366c.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Pas itu suara omong abis ju, itu samua jadi, parsís ke Daniel pung omong! Ais rakyat dong usir buang sang Nabukadnesar ko tenga deng binatang utan dong. Dia makan rumput sama ke sapi dong. Dia ju kaná basa dari kabut yang turun datang dari langit, sampe-sampe dia pung rambu jadi panjang garui ke burung élang pung bulu. Deng dia pung kuku jari sama panjang deng burung pung cakar.<bt>Just as that voice finished speaking, all of that happened, exactly as Daniel had said! So the populace evicted Nebukadnesar to live among the wild animals. He ate grass like the cows. He also became wet from the dew/mist which came down from sky/heaven, until eventually his hair became long and lush/full (idiom) like the feathers of an eagle. And his fingernails became long like a bird's claws.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tsipriyn: birds"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tsipriyn: birds</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Tifrowhiy: his fingernails"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Tifrowhiy: his fingernails</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ravah: it grew long"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ravah: it grew long</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nishriyn: eagles"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nishriyn: eagles</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) saʕrehh: the hair on his"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) saʕrehh: the hair on his head</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yitsTabbaʕ (tsbʕ yitpaʕʕal): got him"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yitsTabbaʕ (tsbʕ yitpaʕʕal): got him repeatedly wet?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) gishmehh: his body"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) gishmehh: his body</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ye'khul: he ate"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ye'khul: he ate</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Safat: was completed, fulfilled"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Safat: was completed, fulfilled</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shaʕəta': moment"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shaʕəta': moment</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Nabukadnesar angka nae puji sang Tuhan Allah [\s2]<bt>Nebukadnesar lifts up praise to God [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Waktu itu tuju taon su lewat, Nebukadnesar sandiri carita dia pung pangalaman bilang, &lt;&lt;Satu kali, beta ada angka beta pung hati sang Dia yang Pegang Parenta di sorga. Bekin bagitu ju, langsung beta mulai pikir lurus, te beta su jadi bae kambali!<bt>When those seven years had passed, Nebukadnesar himself told the story of his experience saying, &lt;&lt;One time, I was lifting my liver to Him who Holds Rule in heaven. As I was doing that, immediately I began to think straight, cuz (elaboration) I had become well again!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Jadi beta angka nae puji sang Tuhan Allah yang Paling Tinggi.<bt>So (consequently) I lifted up praise(s) to the Most High God.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Beta kasi tunju hormat sang Dia yang idop sonde putus-putus,<bt>I honoured/showed respect to Him who lives forever,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">te Dia yang kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang beta.<bt>cuz (elaboration) He had shown His good liver/goodness/kindness/grace to me. [EXEG: Implied by the word for ‘blessed’ as a response to being healed, and made explicit in HCE. TH notes “In many languages the verb ‘to bless’ is not appropriate in this context, since blessing is something that can only be done by a superior to an inferior. ” and after further discussion recommends “So different terms should be found if at all possible.” This last clause is part of that.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia pung kuasa sonde ada pung batas,<bt>His power/authority has no limit,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng Dia pung pegang parenta sonde parná putus.<bt>and His rule/governing never ceases.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Te Dia parenta tarús dari turunan satu pi turunan laen dong, sonde putus-putus.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) He governs continually from one generation to another, without interruption.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Dia su parenta bagitu dari dolu-dolu.<bt>He has governed like that from long ago.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Deng nanti Dia parenta tarús bagitu sampe salamanya.<bt>And He will govern like that continually until forever.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) dar: generation"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) dar: generation</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) malkhuwtehh: his kingdom"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) malkhuwtehh: his kingdom</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕalam: forever"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕalam: forever</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shalTan: is a rule"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shalTan: is a rule</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shalTanehh: his rule, sovereignty"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shalTanehh: his rule, sovereignty</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hadret: I glorified"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hadret: I glorified</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shabbəchet: I lauded, praised, adulated,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shabbəchet: I lauded, praised, adulated, adored</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕalma': perpetuity, antiquity, for ever"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕalma': perpetuity, antiquity, for ever</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chay: the One Who Lives"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chay: the One Who Lives</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) barkhet: I blessed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) barkhet: I blessed</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) uwləʕillaya' (q. uwləʕilla'ah): the Most"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) uwləʕillaya' (q. uwləʕilla'ah): the Most High</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yətuwv: it returned"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yətuwv: it returned</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mandəʕiy: my power of knowing."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mandəʕiy: my power of knowing. TWOT: knowledge. Derived from the verb yedaʕ, this Aramaic noun develops the nun by dissimilation from the form maddaʕ. This noun was later used as the equivalent of the Greek gnosis. The Aramaic Gnostics were called Mandaeans.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) niTlet: I lifted up"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) niTlet: I lifted up</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yowmayyah: the days"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yowmayyah: the days</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) liqtsat: at the end of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) liqtsat: at the end of</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="35" />Tuhan Allah bekin iko Dia pung mau sandiri,<bt>God does according to His own will,[DISCOURSE: several clauses reordered here to better fit RL patterns.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko urus Dia pung ana bua dong di sorga,<bt>to manage/oversee His underlings in heaven (*angels).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng samua orang di ini dunya ju.<bt>and everyone here on earth also.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Kalo banding kotong deng Dia,<bt>If we compare ourselves to Him,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">kotong manusia sonde ta'itong,<bt>we humans are not counted (=insignificant),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">deng sonde ada pung arti sadiki ju.<bt>and do not have even a little meaning/ significance. [EXEG: see discussion in TH. We need to be careful here theologically! In one sense we are entirely insignificant, but in another sense absolutely not -- otherwise why bother to sacrifice His son to redeem us? Or show mercy and grace to Nebukadnesar? This problem is handled nicely by NLT “all the people of the earth are nothing compared to him”.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Sonde ada yang bisa tahan ame sang Dia.<bt>There is none who is able to restrain Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Sonde ada satu orang ju yang ada pung hak tanya sang Dia bilang,<bt>There is not even one person who has the right to ask Him saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">&lt;Akurang ko Lu ada bekin bagitu?!&gt;<bt>&lt;Why are You doing that?!&gt; [STYLE: phrased here as a challenge. cf. NLT. Direct speech in the Aramaic.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəmache' (paʕʕel): will hinder"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəmache' (paʕʕel): will hinder</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) cheyl: army, force"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) cheyl: army, force</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'aved: make, do"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'aved: make, do</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mitsbəyehh (inf): according to his"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mitsbəyehh (inf): according to his will</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəshiyviyn (chshb pəʕil): they are"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəshiyviyn (chshb pəʕil): they are accounted [by God] as</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kəlah: as nothing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kəlah: as nothing</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) da'ərey (q. dayrey): the ones"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) da'ərey (q. dayrey): the ones who dwell in</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Jadi waktu beta mulai pikir lurus kambali, rakyat dong ju kasi tunju hormat sang beta lai, te dolu beta jadi dong pung raja! Beta pung pagawe dong yang dolu kasi nasiat sang beta cari muka deng beta lai. Ju gubernor deng orang laen yang pegang parenta dong mau bakawan bae deng beta lai. Beta pung nama bae su kambali, ju batamba hebat. Beta nae jadi raja kambali. Deng bagitu, beta pung kuasa sakarang lebe bésar dari beta pung kuasa dolu.<bt>So (consequently) when I began to think straight again, the populace also showed me respect again, cuz (elaboration) I had previously been their raja! My officials who had formely advised me sucked up to me again (lit: sought face). And governors and other people who ruled/ governed wanted to be my good friend again. My good name/reputation was restored, and became even greater. I rose up to become raja again. In that way, my power/authority now was greater than my power/authority formerly. [DISCOURSE: reordered for RL naturalness.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) huwSfat (ySp hofʕal): was added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) huwSfat (ySp hofʕal): was added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yattiyrah: extremely"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yattiyrah: extremely</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ravuw: I became even greater"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ravuw: I became even greater</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hatqənat (tqn hofʕal): were reestablished"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hatqənat (tqn hofʕal): were reestablished</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəvaʕown (paʕʕel): they sought me"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəvaʕown (paʕʕel): they sought me out eagerly</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ravrəvanay: my nobles"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ravrəvanay: my nobles</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) haddavray: my counsellors, ministers"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) haddavray: my counsellors, ministers</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ziwiy: my brightness"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ziwiy: my brightness</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hadriy: my honor, majesty"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hadriy: my honor, majesty</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəqar: honor, esteem"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəqar: honor, esteem</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) zimna': time. TWOT: Probably a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) zimna': time. TWOT: Probably a Persian loan word. Used for seasons, appointed times, periods of times— but not for the celebrated seven times (years) Dan 4:13ff., which is ʕiddan.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cot\co01367c.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Andia ko sakarang beta, andia Nebukadnesar, bosong pung raja, angka nae puji deng hormat sang Tuhan Allah di sorga. Beta angka nae tinggi-tinggi Dia pung nama ko biar samua orang bisa tau Dia pung hebat! Samua yang Dia bekin tu, lurus deng batúl. Samua yang Dia putus tu, adil. Kalo ada yang sombong, ko, suka bamulu bésar, na, Dia bisa kasi jato sang dong, sampe dong sonde ada pung nama lai.&gt;&gt;<bt>That is why now I, that is Nebukadnesar, your raja, lift up praises to God in heaven. I lift up on high His name/reputation so that everyone can know His amazingness! Everything He does is right and straight/just. Everything that He decides is just/fair. If there is (someone) who is arrogant, or likes to boast, na, He can cause them to fall (morally/socially), to the point that they have no more name/reputation/influence.&gt;&gt;  [DISCOURSE: The phrase ‘Now I’, reflected by CEV ‘That's why I say’ seems to imply a contrast with ‘previously’. That is behind this structure. Paragraph added at shift to conclusion &amp; new theme. Last sentence uses repetition/rephrasing in good RL style.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) End of P section."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) End of P section.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hashpalah (shpl hafʕel inf): bring"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hashpalah (shpl hafʕel inf): bring them low</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yakhil (partcpl): he is able"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yakhil (partcpl): he is able</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) gewah: pride"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) gewah: pride</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mahləkhiyn: the ones who walk"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mahləkhiyn: the ones who walk</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) diyn: judgment, justice"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) diyn: judgment, justice</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'orchatehh: his ways, paths, courses"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'orchatehh: his ways, paths, courses of life (BDB)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qəshoT: truth"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qəshoT: truth</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) maʕəvadowhiy: his works"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) maʕəvadowhiy: his works</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məhaddar (paʕʕel partcpl): I glorify"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məhaddar (paʕʕel partcpl): I glorify</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mərowmem (rmm paʕʕel partcpl): I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mərowmem (rmm paʕʕel partcpl): I lift up</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məshabbach (paʕʕel partcpl): I praise"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məshabbach (paʕʕel partcpl): I praise</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kəʕ an: now, at this"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kəʕ an: now, at this time</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Raja Belsasar bekin pesta<bt>Raja Belsasar makes a feast</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="5" />
      <v n="1" />Waktu raja Nebukadnesar su mati lama, ju ada orang baru, nama Belsasar yang pegang parenta di Babel. Satu kali, dia bekin satu pesta, ju dia undang dia pung pagawe dong saribu orang ko makan-minum sama-sama.<bt>When raja Nebukadnesar had been long dead, there was a new person, named Belsasar who held rule/governed in Babel. One time he made a feast, and he invited a thousand of his officials to eat-drink together. [DISCOURSE: establish new timeframe. cf. NLT, HCE, TH discussion.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shateh: he drank. UBS: the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shateh: he drank. UBS: the writer almost certainly does not mean that the king was the only one to drink wine at the banquet while all the invited guests looked on. If a literal translation gives this impression, it should be modified.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chamra': wine"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chamra': wine</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'alpa': the thousand"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'alpa': the thousand</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) laqəvel: in the presence of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) laqəvel: in the presence of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ravrəvanowhiy: his lords, nobles"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ravrəvanowhiy: his lords, nobles</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləchem: bread, food, feast. UBS"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləchem: bread, food, feast. UBS regards it as a state banquet</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) belsha'ttsar malka': literally Belshazzar the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) belsha'ttsar malka': literally Belshazzar the king. But this is October 539, 30 years later than Chapter 4, and Nebukadnezzar has been dead for 23 years. Belshazzar is actually the acting king, while the real King, Nabonidus, is away.</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:1" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Waktu raja Nebukadnesar mati, ada satu orang, nama Nabonidus yang ganti sang dia. Ini Belsasar ni, andia itu Nabonidus pung anak. Orang yang pintar so'al Alkitab bilang ini ayat ni jato di bulan Oktober taon 539 SM (Sebelum Masehi). Kira-kira su maju 30 taon dari Daniel 4:37.<bt>When raja Nebukadnesar died, there was a person named Nabonidus who replaced him. This Belsasar here, is that Nabonidus' child/nephew. People knowledgable about the Bible say this verse fell on the month of October in the year 539 SM (Before Messiah). [We have] advanced approximately 30 years from Daniel 4:37. [EXEG: TH discussion, HCE notes, IVP.]</bt></note><v n="2" />Ais ju, waktu raja su mulai mabo sadiki, ju dia suru dia pung orang dong ko pi bawa kasi tunju samua alat mas deng perak yang dolu raja Nebukadnesar su rampas ame kaluar dari Tuhan pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat di kota Yerusalem. Te dia mau pake sang dong ko biar dia, deng dia pung pagawe dong, dia pung bini sah dong, deng dia pung bini laen dong, samua bisa minum pake itu alat dong.<bt>Then, when the raja had begun to get a little drunk, he ordered his people to go bring and show all the gold and silver tools/implements which previously raja Nebukadnesar had snatched out of God2's Central House of Prayer/Worship (*Temple) in the city of Yerusalem. Cuz (elaboration) he wanted to use them so that he, his officials, his legal wives, his other wives, could all drink using those implements. [EXEG: Aram. 'əvuwhiy: his father, his ancestor; much discussion, with strong consensus that Neb. was not Bel's father (Nabonidus probably was his father, grandfather or uncle). There is also general agreement (but not complete consensus) that Neb. was not actually a direct ancestor of Bel. So see NLT ‘predecessor’ as the solution that we follow here. Surprisingly CEV has abandoned meaning-based translation here and gone literal (but wrong) ‘father’.] [DISCOURSE: NOTE to daughter translations: go to direct speech here if you need to. It is setting the stage, not peak, so direct speech is possibly not required here in many of our lgs.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləchenatehh: his concubines"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləchenatehh: his concubines</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) sheglatehh: his concubines? wives?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) sheglatehh: his concubines? wives?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əvuwhiy: his father, his ancestor"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əvuwhiy: his father, his ancestor (predecessor?). There is no information available on whether he was royal or not.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hanpeq (hafʕel): had brought out"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hanpeq (hafʕel): had brought out of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ma'ney: vessels, utensils; probably the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ma'ney: vessels, utensils; probably the gold cups and bowls that could be used for drinking</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləheytayah ('atah hafʕel inf): told"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləheytayah ('atah hafʕel inf): told them to bring</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) biTʕem (noun): in testing, tasting,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) biTʕem (noun): in testing, tasting, judging. UBS: this does not mean that, after sipping only a small amount of wine, the following events occurred. On the contrary the meaning is more likely "after having become slightly drunk."</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Ais dong pi ame bawa itu alat dari mas yang dolu dong su angka ame dari Ruma Sambayang Pusat di Yerusalem. Ju dong samua pake ko minum.<bt>So they went and got bringing those implements from gold which they had taken away from the Central Worship House in Yeruslaem. And they all used them to drink (from). [DISCOURSE (referent tracking): Aram. repeats the categories of people just mentioned in vs. 2. That would be too heavy in RL style.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'ishtiyw: they drank from them"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'ishtiyw: they drank from them</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Waktu dong ada minum aer anggor dari itu alat mahal dong, ju dong ba'omong angka puji so'al dong pung patong songgo yang dong pung orang su bekin dari mas, perak, tambaga, bési, kayu, deng batu.<bt>While they were drinking wine from those expensive implements, they were speaking (among themselves) praising their idols of traditional worship which their people had made from gold, silder, bronze, iron/steel, wood, and stone.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'aʕa': wood"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'aʕa': wood</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) parzəla': iron"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) parzəla': iron</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nəchasha': bronze"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nəchasha': bronze</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shabbachuw (paʕʕel): they praised"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shabbachuw (paʕʕel): they praised</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ada tulisan yang muncul di tembok [\s2]<bt>There was writing that appeared on a wall [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Waktu dong masi minum, ju dong dapa lia manusia pung jari tangan satu muncul datang! Ju itu jari mulai tulis di istana pung tembok pung plester, yang badeka deng lampu yang taráng dong. Raja sandiri ju dapa lia itu jari tulis di tembok.<bt>While they were still drinking, they happened to see a human finger appear! Then that finger began to write on the plaster of the wall of the palace, near the bright lamps/lanterns. The raja himself could see that finger writing on the wall. [EXEG: Aram. nevrashta': lampstand. TH “consider ‘where the light was strongest’ or ‘where people could see very clearly.’”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) paS: hand, palm of hand"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) paS: hand, palm of hand</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chazeh: he saw"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chazeh: he saw</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) heykhla': palace of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) heykhla': palace of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kətal: wall"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kətal: wall</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) giyra': plaster. IVPC: The excavation"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) giyra': plaster. IVPC: The excavation of the throne room in Babylon can offer some explanation. It was a 170-by-55-foot hall entered through three spacious courtyards that led from the entrance just inside the Ishtar Gate. Some of the wall space was covered with blue enameled brick, while other parts were plaster.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nevrashta': lampstand"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nevrashta': lampstand</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'etsbəʕan: fingers"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'etsbəʕan: fingers</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nəfaquw (q. nəfaqah): appeared, came"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nəfaquw (q. nəfaqah): appeared, came out</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shaʕətah: moment"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shaʕətah: moment</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:5" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Orang yang pintar so'al Alkitab dong yang su gali di itu istana bilang itu kamar pesta pung bésar tu, andia 60 meter kali 20 meter. Orang maso pi situ lewat tiga tana lapang yang ada pung tembok. Tembok saparu tu, batu bata. Deng saparu pake plester.<bt>People who are knowledgable about the Bible who have dug in that palace say the size of that party room is 60 meters by 20 meters. People entered there via three open fields/yards which had walls. Some of those walls vers from brick. And some used plaster. [EXEG: IVP, HCE note.]</bt></note><v n="6" />Lia bagitu ju, dia pung mata tape'e memang. Ais dia taku mau mati, sampe muka pucat deng dia gamatar dingin. Dia pung badan noe, ju dia ilang kira.<bt>Seeing that, his eyes opened wide. Then he became terrified, to the point that his face was pale and he shook with fear (lit: shake cold). His body was weak and he couldn't think.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) naqshan: knocked together. UBS: an"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) naqshan: knocked together. UBS: an observable trembling in the legs. It may or may not be natural in a given language to speak of the knees actually coming together as a result of this shaking.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləda': to the other"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləda': to the other</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) da': the one"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) da': the one</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'akhubbatehh: his knees"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'akhubbatehh: his knees</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mishtarayin (shr' hitpaʕʕal partcpl pl):"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mishtarayin (shr' hitpaʕʕal partcpl pl): were loosened, shook, knocked together. UBS: the word for loins or hips may, in fact, refer to the entire midsection of the body, which was the source of physical strength, according to ancient thinking. Sudden and extreme anxiety can cause the loss of physical force. So the meaning of this expression is something like "his hips gave way" or "he became extremely weak all over."</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chartsehh: hip joints (core muscles?)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chartsehh: hip joints (core muscles?)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qiTrey: joints of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qiTrey: joints of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəvahəluwnneh (bhl paʕʕel): they alarmed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəvahəluwnneh (bhl paʕʕel): they alarmed him, dismayed him</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) raʕyonohiy: his thoughts"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) raʕyonohiy: his thoughts</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shənowhiy (shn'): it changed. UBS:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shənowhiy (shn'): it changed. UBS: the change in physical appearance that comes over a person when he is paralyzed with fear.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ziywohiy: his brightness? his complexion,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ziywohiy: his brightness? his complexion, colors</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'ədayin: then, thereupon"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'ədayin: then, thereupon</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="hk-lb\hk00288c.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ais dia batarea suru orang pi pange sang dia pung orang pintar, dia pung tukang rai-rai, deng orang Kasdim yang pintar lia bintang dong samua ko datang bakumpul. Ju dia kasi tau sang Babel pung orang yang pintar yang ada di situ bilang, &lt;&lt;Dengar bae-bae! Sapa sa yang bisa baca ini tulisan ni, deng kasi tau dia pung arti sang beta, nanti beta angka sang dia ko pegang kuasa nomer tiga di beta pung karaja'an. Beta kasi dia baju panjang warna ungu yang mahal ke botong raja-raja biasa pake. Beta ju kasi pake dia satu kalong dari mas di dia pung leher.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then he shouted ordering people to go summon his wise/knowledgable people, his diviners, and the Ksdim people who were skilled at observing stars to come gather. And he told all the wise/knowlegable/clever people of Babel saying, &lt;&lt;Listen carefully! Whoever is able to read this writing, and tell me its meaning, I will elevate/appoint him to hold power/authority number three in my kingdom. I will give him expensive long clothes of purple colour like we-exc rajas normally wear. I will also cause him to wear a golden necklace on his neck.&gt;&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: compare with Dan. 2:2. No sorcerers here. Reordered for information load.] [EXEG: Problem: vs.7 “the king said to the wise men of Babylon”. vs.8 “Then all the king's wise men came in...” TH discusses the “logical difficulties”. Like TH and NLT, we take it as (7) those who were already present at the event who came forward, and (8) the rest of them when they arrived.] [EXEG: Aram. taltiy: third in rank. Nabonidus was the emperor, Belshazzar (who may have been his son or grandson) was number two, acting as king while Nabonidus was in Arabia.] [DISCOURSE: reordered for natural RL info flow.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) End of S section."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) End of S section.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yishlaT: have power, rule"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yishlaT: have power, rule</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) taltiy: third in rank. Nabonidus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) taltiy: third in rank. Nabonidus was the emperor, Belshazzar (who may have been his son or grandson) was number two, acting as king while Nabonidus was in Arabia.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tsawwə'rehh: his neck"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tsawwə'rehh: his neck</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hammownkha' (q. hamniykha'): necklace"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hammownkha' (q. hamniykha'): necklace</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'argəwana': red-purple"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'argəwana': red-purple</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəchawwinnaniy (chwh paʕʕel): shows me"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəchawwinnaniy (chwh paʕʕel): shows me</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) pishrehh: its interpretation"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) pishrehh: its interpretation</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yiqreh: reads"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yiqreh: reads</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chakkiymey: wise men of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chakkiymey: wise men of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) gazrayya': the diviners who examined"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) gazrayya': the diviners who examined entrails</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kasdaye' (q. kasda'ey): the Chaldeans"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kasdaye' (q. kasda'ey): the Chaldeans (astrologers)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'ashfayya': the ones who could"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'ashfayya': the ones who could block a curse</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chayil: strong, loudly"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chayil: strong, loudly</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Waktu dia pung orang yang pintar dong samua su bakumpul abis, sonde ada satu ju yang bisa baca itu tulisan tu, ko kasi tau dia pung arti sang raja.<bt>When all of his wise men had finished gathering, there was not one single one who could read that writing, to explain its meaning to the raja.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhowdaʕah (ydʕ hafʕel): make known"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhowdaʕah (ydʕ hafʕel): make known</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləmiqre' (qr' inf): read"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləmiqre' (qr' inf): read</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) khahəliyn (khl partcpl): they could"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) khahəliyn (khl partcpl): they could [not]</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Lia bagitu ju, raja tamba taku. Dia pung muka pucat. Dia pung pagawe dong babingung ju.<bt>Seeing that, the raja became increasingly afraid/even more afraid. His face was pale. His officials were confused.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mishtabbəshiyn (shbsh hitpaʕal partcpl pl):"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mishtabbəshiyn (shbsh hitpaʕal partcpl pl): they were perplexed, baffled</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕalowhiy: on him?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕalowhiy: on him?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shanayin (shnh): was changed (again)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shanayin (shnh): was changed (again)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ziywohiy: his brightness, his countenance,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ziywohiy: his brightness, his countenance, the color of his face</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mitbahal (hitpaʕʕal partcpl): alarmed, dismayed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mitbahal (hitpaʕʕal partcpl): alarmed, dismayed</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) saggiy': great, much"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) saggiy': great, much</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cot\co01370c.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Waktu raja pung mama dapa dengar orang di kamar pesta dong ada baribut, ju dia maso datang. Sampe di raja pung muka, ju dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Biar ko bapa raja idop panjang. Jang jadi pikiran bagitu, sampe taku deng muka pucat.<bt>When the raja's mother heard people in the party room getting noisy, she came in. Arriving before the raja, she spoke saying, &lt;&lt;May father raja live long. Do not become worried like that, to the point that your face is pale. [EXEG: malkəta': the queen, queen mother. NLT, IVP, TH favour queen mother here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yishtannow (shn' hitpaʕʕal jussive): may"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yishtannow (shn' hitpaʕʕal jussive): may it [not] be changed!</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ziywaykh: your face, countenance, brightness"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ziywaykh: your face, countenance, brightness</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) raʕyownakh: your thought"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) raʕyownakh: your thought</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəvahəluwkh (bhl paʕʕel jussive): [don't]"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəvahəluwkh (bhl paʕʕel jussive): [don't] be alarmed, dismayed</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəyiy (chyh imperv): live!"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəyiy (chyh imperv): live!</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləʕ almiyn: forever"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləʕ almiyn: forever</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mishtəya': banquet, feast"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mishtəya': banquet, feast</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) milley: words of, matters of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) milley: words of, matters of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) laqavel: in view of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) laqavel: in view of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) malkəta': the queen. IVPC: Nabonidus's"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) malkəta': the queen. IVPC: Nabonidus's mother, Adad-Guppi, was a very influential person and the quintessential queen mother. Her 104 years, however, had come to a close about 546, so she was no longer alive at this time. Nabonidus's wife, Belshazzar's mother, identified by Herodotus as Nitocris, is more likely referred to here.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Dengar sang beta doo! Te di kotong pung karaja'an ada satu orang yang dolu bisa bantu waktu raja Nebukadnesar masi pegang parenta. Kuasa dari dewa-dewi yang barisi dong ada di dia pung idop. Dia mangarti banya hal, dia tau banya, deng dia pikir tajam sama ke dewa-dewi dong. Raja Nebukadnesar parná angka sang dia ko urus samua orang pintar, tukang suanggi, tukang rai-rai, deng orang Kasdim yang pintar lia bintang dong di Babel.<bt>Listen to me now/first! Cuz (elaboration) in our-inc kingdom there is a person who previously was able to help while raja Nebukadnesar still ruled/governed. Power/authority of the clean/holy deities was in/on his life. He understood many things, he knew alot, and he thought sharply like the deities. Raja Nebukadnesar once elevated/appointed him to manage/oversee all the wise people, sorcerers, diviners, and Kasdim people who are skilled at observing the stars in Babel. [NOTE to daughter translations: compare wording in Dan. 4:8.] [EXEG: Aram. father = ‘predecessor’ here, as in NLT, CEV, HCE. See discussion at 5:2.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) həqiymehh (qwm hafʕel): established him,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) həqiymehh (qwm hafʕel): established him, appointed him</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rav: chief"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rav: chief</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əvuwkh: your father/ grandfather/ ancestor"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əvuwkh: your father/ grandfather/ ancestor</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hishtəkhachat (shkch hitpəʕal): has been"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hishtəkhachat (shkch hitpəʕal): has been found. TWOT: disclosure of a covered or forgotten thing</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) sakhlətanuw (noun): insight"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) sakhlətanuw (noun): insight</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nahiyruw (noun): illumination of the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nahiyruw (noun): illumination of the mind (Halladay)</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Naa, ini Daniel ni, raja kasi nama baru, andia Beltasasar. Dia orang hati bae, yang ada pung kuasa deng karunya ko bisa mangarti banya hal, bisa kasi tau mimpi dong pung arti, bisa cari jalan kaluar dari susa, deng bisa kasi jawaban di parkara yang talalu barát. Beta pung usul bagini: pange datang sang ini Daniel. Te nanti dia yang bisa kasi tau ini tulisan ni pung arti apa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa [+shift], this Daniel here [that I am talking about], the raja gave a new name, that is Beltasasar. He is a good livered person (=good character), who has the power/authority and special.gifting to be able to understand many things, be able to tell the meaning of dreams, be able to find a way out of difficulty, and able to give answers to very heavy/difficult matters. My suggestion is like this: summon this Daniel. Cuz (elaboration) he is the one who will be able to tell what is the meaning of this writing.&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: reordered to better fit RL patterns of broad to narrow.] [EXEG: for Daniel's abilities, see discussion in TH. HCE.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) End of P section."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) End of P section.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəhachəwih (chwh hafʕel): he will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəhachəwih (chwh hafʕel): he will show</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yitqərey (qr' hitpəʕel jussive): let"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yitqərey (qr' hitpəʕel jussive): let him be summoned</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kəʕ an: at this time,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kəʕ an: at this time, until now</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shəmehh: his name"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shəmehh: his name</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qiTriyn: knots (metaphor for solving"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qiTriyn: knots (metaphor for solving problems, figuring out how to do difficult tasks)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məshare' (shrh inf): loosening of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məshare' (shrh inf): loosening of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əchiydan: riddles"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əchiydan: riddles</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) va'achəwayat (chwh 'afʕel inf cs):"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) va'achəwayat (chwh 'afʕel inf cs): the making known of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məfasshar (paʕʕel partcpl): interpreting"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məfasshar (paʕʕel partcpl): interpreting</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) sakhlətanuw: insight"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) sakhlətanuw: insight</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mandaʕ: knowledge, power of knowing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mandaʕ: knowledge, power of knowing</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yattiyrah: extreme, extraordinary"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yattiyrah: extreme, extraordinary</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Daniel buka ame itu tulisan pung arti [\s2]<bt>Daniel reveals the meaning of the writing [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Waktu raja suru orang pi pange sang Daniel, ju dong pi bawa datang sang dia. Waktu dia mangada sang raja, ju raja tanya sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu ni, Daniel, ko? Andia orang yang raja dolu bawa datang dari tana Yahuda abis paráng, ko?<bt>When the raja ordered people to go call/summon Daniel, they went and brought him back. When he was before the raja, the raja asked him saying, &lt;&lt;So you are Daniel, right? That is, the person that previous raja(s) brought here from the land of Yahuda after the war, right? [DISCOURSE: make Daniel's summons realis, using tail-head.] [Note to daughter translations: Check placement of “after the war” in your language) raja dolu bawa datang dari tana Yahuda abis paráng, ko? vs. raja dolu bawa datang abis paráng dari tana Yahuda, ko?]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) haytiy ('th hafʕel): he brought"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) haytiy ('th hafʕel): he brought</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəhuwd: Judah"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəhuwd: Judah</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) galuwta': the exiles"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) galuwta': the exiles</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) huʕal (ʕlh hufʕal): was brought"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) huʕal (ʕlh hufʕal): was brought</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Beta su dengar bilang, kuasa dari dewa-dewi yang barisi dong ada di lu pung idop. Orang bilang lu mangarti banya hal, tau banya, deng pikir panjang sama ke dewa-dewi dong.<bt>I have heard that power/authority from the clean/holy deities is in/on your life. People say you understand many things (=wise), and think long (=think through implications) like the deities. [NOTE to daughter translations: cf. Dan. 4:8, 5:11.]</bt><v n="15" />Beta pung masala bagini: beta suru ko samua orang pintar deng tukang rai-rai, bakumpul di sini, biar ko dong bisa baca ini tulisan deng kasi tau dia pung arti sang beta. Ma dong sonde ontong sadiki ju.<bt>Here is my problem: I have ordered that all the wie/knowledgable people, and the diviners gather here, so that they can read this writing and tell me its meaning. But they are completely unable.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhachəwayah (chwh hafʕel): to explain"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhachəwayah (chwh hafʕel): to explain</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhowdaʕutaniy (ydʕ hafʕel inf): for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhowdaʕutaniy (ydʕ hafʕel inf): for them to cause me to know</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cot\co01371c.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ais beta dengar bilang, lu mangarti banya hal, deng bisa cari jalan kaluar dari susa. Jadi bagini: kalo lu bisa baca ini tulisan deng kasi tau dia pung arti sang beta, na, nanti beta angka sang lu ko pegang kuasa nomer tiga di beta pung da'era parenta. Beta kasi lu baju panjang warna ungu yang mahal ke botong raja-raja biasa pake. Ais beta kasi pake lu satu kalong dari mas di lu pung leher ju.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then I heard that you understand many things, and are able to find ways out of difficulty. So (consequently) here is how it is: if you are able to read this writing and tell me its meaning, na, I will elevate/appoint you to hold power/ authority number three in the realm that I govern/ rule. I will give you to wear expensive long purpor coloured clothes like we-exc rajas normally wear. And I will also cause you to wear a gold necklace on your neck.&gt;&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: compare 5:7.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) End of P section."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) End of P section.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'argəwana': royal purple"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'argəwana': royal purple</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləmishre': to loosen [knots, hard"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləmishre': to loosen [knots, hard problems]</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ju Daniel manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Biar bapa raja sonde usa kasi beta hadia apa-apa. Ko, kasi pi orang laen sa, ju bae. Biar bagitu, ma beta mau baca itu tulisan deng kasi tau dia pung arti sang bapa raja.<bt>Then Daniel responded, &lt;&lt;Father raja really does not need to give me any gifts whatsoever. Or, give (them) away to other people is fine too. Even that being the case, nevertheless I am going to read that writing and tell its meaning to father raja.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) bəram: nevertheless, but"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) bəram: nevertheless, but</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hav (yhb imperv): give"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hav (yhb imperv): give</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'achəran: another one, somebody else"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'achəran: another one, somebody else</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nəvazbəyatakh: your rewards"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nəvazbəyatakh: your rewards</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhewyan (hwh): let them be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhewyan (hwh): let them be</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) matnatakh: your gifts"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) matnatakh: your gifts</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Dengar sang beta dolo! Te Tuhan Allah yang Paling Tinggi yang parná angka nae raja dolu, andia raja Nebukadnesar, ko pegang parenta. Tuhan yang kasi itu raja nama yang hebat, sampe orang dong hormat batúl sang dia. Deng Tuhan ju yang kasi biar ko dia bisa kasi bangun istana deng karaja'an yang talalu hebat.<bt>Listen to me now! Cuz (elaboration) the Most High God is the one who once elevated/ appointed a/the previous raja, that is raja Nebukadnesar, to rule/govern. God2 is the one who gave that raja the amazing name/reputation, to the point that people truly honoured him. And God2 is also the one who allowed him to build a palace and kingdom that are so very impressive. [EXEG: Aram. hadrah: majesty, glory.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hadrah: majesty, glory"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hadrah: majesty, glory</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəqara': honor, esteem"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəqara': honor, esteem</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ravuwta': greatness"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ravuwta': greatness</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) malkhuwta': kingship"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) malkhuwta': kingship</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Tagal Tuhan yang angka sang dia bagitu, ju orang dari samua negara deng samua bahasa hormat deng taku sang dia. Raja mau bunu sapa, na, dia bunu sa. Raja mau kasi salamat sang sapa, na, dia kasi salamat sa. Dia mau kasi tunju hormat sang sapa, na, dia kasi tunju hormat iko dia pung suka sa. Dia mau kasi jato sang sapa, na, dia kasi jato begitu sa, ko biar dong sonde ada pung nama lai.<bt>Because God2 is the one who elevated/appointed him like that, people from all countries and all languages honoured and feared him. The raja wanted to kill whoever, na, he just killed him. The raja wanted to save/rescue whoever, na, he just saved/rescued him. He wanted to show honour/respect to whoever, na, he just showed respect as he liked. He wanted to cause to fall (socially, morally) whoever, na, he just cause to fall like that, so that they no longer had a name/reputation/influence.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mashpiyl (shpl hafʕel partcpl): humiliating"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mashpiyl (shpl hafʕel partcpl): humiliating</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mariym (rwm 'afʕel partcpl): exalting"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mariym (rwm 'afʕel partcpl): exalting</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mache' (chy' hafʕel partcpl): he"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mache' (chy' hafʕel partcpl): he kept alive</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qaTel (paʕel partcpl): he slew"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qaTel (paʕel partcpl): he slew</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) həwa': it happened"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) həwa': it happened</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tsave' (tsbh partcpl): wishing, wanting"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tsave' (tsbh partcpl): wishing, wanting</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) həwah: it was, it happened"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) həwah: it was, it happened</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) dachəliyn (partcpl pl): fearing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) dachəliyn (partcpl pl): fearing</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) za'əʕiyn (q. zayʕiyn zwn partcpl"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) za'əʕiyn (q. zayʕiyn zwn partcpl pl): trembling</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) həwow: they were, became"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) həwow: they were, became</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) lisshanaya': the languages"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) lisshanaya': the languages</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'umayya': the tribes"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'umayya': the tribes</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕaməmayya': the peoples"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕaməmayya': the peoples</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rəvuwta': the greatness"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rəvuwta': the greatness</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ma lama-lama, itu raja jadi sombong deng kapala batu ju. Dia kira dia bisa iko dia pung mau-mau sandiri sa. Andia ko Tuhan Allah kasi turun sang dia dari dia pung korsi parenta, sampe-sampe orang dong sonde kasi tunju hormat sang dia lai.<bt>But eventually, that raja became arrogant and stubborn (lit: rock head). He thought he could just do whatever he wanted. That is why God deposed (lit: brought him down) from his ruling chair (=throne), to the point that people did not show respect to him anymore. [DISCOURSE (participant ref): because God has been the active subject in v.19, need to reintroduce Neb. with NP here. don't use pron ‘he’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) heʕdiyuw (ʕdh hafʕel): they took"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) heʕdiyuw (ʕdh hafʕel): they took away, caused to pass over</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) viyqarah: his majesty, honor, esteem"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) viyqarah: his majesty, honor, esteem</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) karSe': the throne"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) karSe': the throne</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hanchat (ncht hofʕal): he was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hanchat (ncht hofʕal): he was deposed</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) lahəzadah (zwd hafʕel): to act"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) lahəzadah (zwd hafʕel): to act presumptuously</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tiqfat (tqp): his spirit grew"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tiqfat (tqp): his spirit grew strong, hardened, became arrogant</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rim (rwm pəʕ al): it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rim (rwm pəʕ al): it was lifted up</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) khədiy: as, when"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) khədiy: as, when</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Rakyat dong usir buang sang dia. Dia pung pikiran jadi sama ke binatang utan dong. Dia idop jao dari kampong di keledai utan dong pung tenga-tenga, ju makan rumput sama ke sapi. Dia kaná basa dari kabut yang turun datang dari langit. Lama-lama baru dia mangarti batúl bilang, dia pung batúl, andia Tuhan Allah yang Paling Tinggi yang pegang kuasa. Tuhan yang ada pung hak ko parenta samua pamarenta di ini dunya. Tuhan ju yang putus iko Dia pung suka sandiri so'al sapa yang pegang parenta di mana-mana.<bt>The populace evicted him. His thinking became like the wild animals. He lived far from village(s) among the wild donkeys, and ate grass like cows. He became (thoroughly) wet from the dew/mist that comes down from the sky. Eventually ha came to truly understand that in actual fact, it is the Most High God who holds power/authority. God2 is the one who has the right to rule/govern all the governments on this earth. God2 is also the one who decides according to His own desires about who will hold rule/govern wherever. [NOTE to daughter translations: cf. 4:25.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕəleyahh (q. ʕəlahh): over it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕəleyahh (q. ʕəlahh): over it</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəhaqeym (qwm hafʕel): he appoints"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəhaqeym (qwm hafʕel): he appoints</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yitsbeh (tsbh): he wishes"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yitsbeh (tsbh): he wishes</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləman: to whoever"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləman: to whoever</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) malkhuwt: kingship"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) malkhuwt: kingship</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕillaya' (q. ʕilla'ah): the Most"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕillaya' (q. ʕilla'ah): the Most High God</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shalliyT (adj): BDB having mastery,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shalliyT (adj): BDB having mastery, having authority, ruling</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yitsTabbaʕ (tsbʕ hitpaʕʕal): was wet"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yitsTabbaʕ (tsbʕ hitpaʕʕal): was wet</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) gishmehh: his body"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) gishmehh: his body</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəTaʕəmuwnnehh (paʕʕel): they fed him"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəTaʕəmuwnnehh (paʕʕel): they fed him</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) towriyn: bulls, cows"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) towriyn: bulls, cows</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕisba': grass"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕisba': grass</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mədowrehh: his dwelling place"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mədowrehh: his dwelling place</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕəradayya': the wild donkeys"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕəradayya': the wild donkeys</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shəwiy (q. shawwiyw 'changed to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shəwiy (q. shawwiyw 'changed to be like'): was made to become like</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Təriyd (pəʕil): he was driven"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Təriyd (pəʕil): he was driven away, chased away</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ma bapa raja, dia pung masala bagini: bapa raja sandiri parenta baiko di balakang itu raja Nebukadnesar. Jadi ini bukan hal baru kasi sang bapa raja. Ma bapa raja sandiri talalu sombong, deng sonde tau randa hati.<bt>But father raja, the problem is like this: father raja (=you) yourself rule/govern in turn behind that raja Nebukadnesar. So (consequently) this is not a new matter for you. But you yourself are too/very arrogant, and do not know how to be humble (lit: low livered). [EXEG: successor (NLT). See previous discussion about ‘father’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="CHECK spelling randa prob best. Change"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">CHECK spelling randa prob best. Change all??</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Sampe-sampe bapa raja su angka diri lebe tinggi dari Tuhan Allah yang parenta di langit, ju bekin hina sang Dia! Te bapa raja su suru orang ko pi ame bawa itu alat mewa yang dolu dong su angka ame dari Dia pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat, ko biar bapa raja, bapa pung pagawe dong, bapa pung bini sah dong, deng bapa pung bini laen dong, samua bisa pake ko minum dari itu alat dong. Tamba lai, bapa dong angka puji sang patong songgo yang orang su bekin dari mas, perak, tambaga, bési, kayu, deng batu. Padahal, itu patong dong sonde bisa lia, sonde bisa dengar, deng sonde tau apa-apa ju. Ma bapa raja sonde toe sang Tuhan Allah yang kasi bapa napas, yang bisa tarek itu napas ju, deng yang pegang bapa raja pung nasib di Dia pung tangan. Padahal, bapa sonde kasi tunju hormat sang Dia na!<bt>To the point that you have elevated/exalted yourself to be higher than God who rules/governs in heaven, and also ridiculed/slandered/offended Him! Cuz (elaboration) you have ordered people to go get bringing those fancy implements which previously they had taken from His Central House of Worship, so that you, your officials, your legal wives, and your other wives, could all use for drinking from those implments. Furthermore, you have lifted praises to statues of traditional worship which people have made from gold, silver, bronze, iron/steel, wood, and stone. Whereas in fact, those statues are not able to see, are not able to hear, and do not know anything either. But you do not care about God who gave you breath, who is able to pull away that breath, and who holds your fate (assimilated loan: Arab) in His hand(s). In fact, you do not show respect to Him! [EXEG: see NLT and discussion in TH for this long and complex verse.] [NOTE to daughter translations: many of the terms in this verse have been used in previous verses. See TH for references to which verses.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) haddarta: you [did not] glorify"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) haddarta: you [did not] glorify</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'orchatakh: your path of life,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'orchatakh: your path of life, your way</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) biydehh: in his hand"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) biydehh: in his hand</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nishmətakh: your breath of life"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nishmətakh: your breath of life</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shabbachta: you praised"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shabbachta: you praised</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yadʕiyn: they [do not] know"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yadʕiyn: they [do not] know</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shamʕiyn: they [do not] hear"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shamʕiyn: they [do not] hear</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chazayin: they [do not] see"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chazayin: they [do not] see</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'avna': the stone"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'avna': the stone</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'aʕa': the wood"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'aʕa': the wood</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) bəhown: from them, in them"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) bəhown: from them, in them</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shatayin: they drank"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shatayin: they drank</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chamra': wine"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chamra': wine</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləchenatakh: nonroyal wives? entertainers, mistresses?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləchenatakh: nonroyal wives? entertainers, mistresses?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) sheglatakh: wives? royal wives? concubines?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) sheglatakh: wives? royal wives? concubines?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) heytiyw ('th hafʕel): you caused"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) heytiyw ('th hafʕel): you caused somebody to bring</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ma'nayya': the vessels, receptacles"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ma'nayya': the vessels, receptacles</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hitrowmamta (rwm hitpolel): you lifted"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hitrowmamta (rwm hitpolel): you lifted yourself up, exalted yourself</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mare': lord, king BDB in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mare': lord, king BDB in the sense of domineering</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Andia ko Dia kirim itu tangan ko tulis di tembok.<bt>That is why He has sent that hand to write on the wall. [DISCOURSE: RSV, NRSV have paragraph break before 24. NLT, CEV have it after. TH notes 23 is leading up to 24, so they should be kept together.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rəshiym (rshm): it wrote, inscribed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rəshiym (rshm): it wrote, inscribed</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəda': the hand"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəda': the hand</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) paSSa': the palm"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) paSSa': the palm</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shəliyach (pəʕil): was sent"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shəliyach (pəʕil): was sent</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qadamowhiy: his presence"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qadamowhiy: his presence</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cot\co01375c.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ais, itu tulisan bilang bagini:<bt>So that writing says like this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <span class="Italic">Mene, mene, tekel,</span> deng <span class="Italic">parsin.</span><bt><span class="Italic">Mene, mene, tekel,</span> and <span class="Italic">parsin.</span> [TEXT: KJV, TB, and the Cook picture say “upharsin”. No modern sources use or mention this; they all say “parsin”. Interpreting the form in BART, it appears that the /u-/ is a conjunction “and”. Issue not discussed in TH, IVP, or NET notes.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Ini kata dong pung arti bagini:<bt>These words have a meaning like this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <span class="Italic">Mene</span> ada pung arti bilang ‘itong’ — te Tuhan Allah su itong hari yang bapa raja ada pegang parenta, ais putus bilang itu waktu su musti abis.<bt><span class="Italic">Mene</span> has the meaning ‘count’ — cuz (elaboration) God has counted the days for you to hold rule, and has decided that that time must already end. [NOTE: See structure and formatting in NLT.] [NOTE to daughter translations: discuss which metaphor works better for your language for time, ‘count (days)’ or ‘measure (length)’?]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hashləmahh (shlm hafʕel): he wraps"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hashləmahh (shlm hafʕel): he wraps it up. BDB finish, bring to an end, render in full</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mənah: he has numbered, measured."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mənah: he has numbered, measured. Mina, a weight; but Daniel read it as a verb.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="27" />
      <span class="Italic">Tekel</span> ada pung arti bilang ‘timbang’ — te Tuhan su timbang samua-samua yang bapa raja su bekin, ma hal bae dong kasi sang rakyat masi talalu kurang.<bt><span class="Italic">Tekel</span> has the meaning ‘weigh/evaluate’ — cuz (elaboration) God2 has weighed/evaluated everything that you have done, but good things that you have done for the populace are still very lacking.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Or declining weights Mene ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Or declining weights Mene = Nebuchadnezzar, Tekel = Nabonidus, Parsin = Belshazzer. But Daniel doesn't take that route.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chaSSiyr: defective, of poor quality"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chaSSiyr: defective, of poor quality</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hishtəkhachat (shkch hitpəʕel): you are"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hishtəkhachat (shkch hitpəʕel): you are found</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mo'zanya': the scales"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mo'zanya': the scales</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) təqiyltah (tql pəʕil): you have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) təqiyltah (tql pəʕil): you have been weighed (corresponds to shekel)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="28" />
      <span class="Italic">Peres</span> ada pung arti bilang ‘bagi kasi’ — te Tuhan su bagi bapa raja pung da'era parenta jadi dua. Saparu kasi sang orang Media dong, deng saparu kasi sang orang Persia dong.&gt;&gt;<bt><span class="Italic">Peres</span> has the meaning ‘divide out’ — cuz (elaboration) God2 has already divided your region of rule/governing into two (parts). Half for the Media people, and half for the Persia people.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) maday: Medes. Rather than use"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) maday: Medes. Rather than use the name of their country, Media, we'd better use the ethnonym so we don't have to explain that it does not mean the people in charge of the TV networks and newspapers.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) pəriySat: it has been split."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) pəriySat: it has been split. Weights. Persians.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) parsin (plural)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) parsin (plural)</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:28" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Di ayat 25 tulisan bahasa Aram asli tulis bilang <span class="Italic">Parsin,</span> andia bentuk jamak &lt;orang Persia dong&gt;. Ma di ayat 28 ni, tulisan asli tulis bilang <span class="Italic">Peres,</span> andia bentuk tunggal &lt;orang Persia&gt;. <span class="Italic">Upharsin</span> di gambar ada pung arti bilang &lt;deng Parsin&gt;.<bt>In verse 25 the original Aram writings write saying <span class="Italic">Parsin,</span> that is the plural for &lt;the Persia people (pl)&gt;. But in verse 28 the original writings say <span class="Italic">Peres,</span> that is the singular form ‘Persian person&gt;. <span class="Italic">Upharsin</span> in the picture has the meaning ‘with/and the Persia people&gt;.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Dengar Daniel kasi tau itu tulisan dong pung arti bagitu, ju raja suru dia pung orang dong ko kasi pake sang Daniel baju panjang warna ungu yang mahal ke raja dong biasa pake. Ju kasi pake sang dia satu kalong dari mas di dia pung leher. Deng bagitu dia angka nae sang Daniel jadi orang nomer tiga yang pegang parenta di raja Belsasar pung da'era parenta.<bt>Hearing Daniel explain the meaning of the writing like that, the raja ordered his people to cause Daniel to wear an expensive purple cloth like kings normally wear. And also cause to wear a golden necklace on his neck. In that way he elevated/appointed Daniel to become the number three person who held rule/governed in raja Belsasar's domain of rule. [DISCOURSE: Reduced adverbial tail-head recap in good RL style for this region. Also reordered to build toward Daniel's new rank in good RL sequence.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hakhrizuw (krz hafʕel): had him"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hakhrizuw (krz hafʕel): had him proclaimed. Nabonidus was number one, Belshazzar number two, Daniel number three.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) halbiyshuw (hafʕel): caused him to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) halbiyshuw (hafʕel): caused him to be dressed</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30-31" />Ma itu malam ju, tantara orang Media dong datang saráng, ais bunu bekin mati sang Belsasar, yang jadi raja di Babel.<bt>But that same night, the army of the Media people came and attacked, and killed Belsasar, who was raja in Babel. [EXEG: Chaldean = Babylonian. See TH, NLT note, HCE. Ftn dating: see NLT note.]</bt><note reference="5:30-31" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan asli bahasa Aram tulis bilang &lt;Kasdim&gt;. Kasdim kasi tunju suku. Dong pung da'era, andia Babel. Orang Media deng orang Persia kasi kala Babel, bulan Oktober, taon 539 SM (Sebelum Masehi).<bt>The original Aram writings write saying &lt;Kasdim&gt;. Kasdim designates a tribe/ethnic group. Their region is Babel. The Media people and the Persia people defeated Babel in the month of October, in the year 539 SM (Before Messiah).</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju orang Media satu, nama Darius nae jadi raja baru di Babel. Waktu dong angka nae sang dia, dia su umur 62 taon.<bt>And a Media person named Darius rose to become a/the new raja in Babel. When they elevated/appointed him, his age was 62 years.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qabbel (paʕel): he received [the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qabbel (paʕel): he received [the kingdom]</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) End of P section."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) End of P section.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Pagawe tinggi dong cari hal<bt>High officials cause trouble (Idiom: look for a matter/excuse)</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="6" />
      <v n="1" />Ais satu kali, raja Darius putus ko mau angka 120 orang jadi gubernor di tiap propinsi di dia pung da'era parenta.<bt>Then one time, raja Darious decided to elevate/appoint 120 people to become governors in each province in his domain(s). [EXEG: 1) he set up his own people in existing provinces, 2) he reorganised the empire into 120 provinces and put people over the new divisions. NLT, CEV. Our protocols say to preserve the ambiguity of the original where we can, as in NRSV, TB.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) lehown (hwh): they became. TWOT:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) lehown (hwh): they became. TWOT: In general this verb is used like the related Hebrew verb hayah. A peculiarity of the Aramaic is that in the imperfect a lamedh is used instead of the usual preformative yodh. Also in Aramaic the verb hawah is often used with a participle to make a periphrastic tense expressing continuous and habitual action (e.g. Dan 6:10 [A 11], "as he used to do formerly").</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əchashdarpənayya': satraps, provincial governors. IVBB:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əchashdarpənayya': satraps, provincial governors. IVBB: The primary administrative geographical division in the Persian empire was the satrapy. The number of these varied between twenty and thirty-one, so the text must be referring to lower-level administrative governors (for whom this term is used in Greek historical sources).</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vahəqiym (hafʕel): he appointed, set"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vahəqiym (hafʕel): he appointed, set up</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qədam: before"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qədam: before</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shəfar: it seemed good"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shəfar: it seemed good</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Dia ju angka tiga pagawe tinggi ko urus itu gubernor dong samua, deng jaga bae-bae raja pung urusan. Gubernor dong musti lapor sang itu tiga pagawe dong. Daniel ju maso dari dong tiga.<bt>He also elevated/appointed three high officials to manage/oversee all those governors, and carefully guard the raja's (business/governing) affairs. The governors had to report to those three officials. Daniel was included in those three. [EXEG: suffer no loss = NLT protect the king's interests. Also TH.] [DISCOURSE: 1-2 background for developments in 3.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) naziq: harm, injury; suffer"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) naziq: harm, injury; suffer</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) lehəwi': so he would [not]"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) lehəwi': so he would [not] be</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Taʕma': report, judgment"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Taʕma': report, judgment</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhown: to them"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhown: to them</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yahəviyn (yhb partcpl pl): customarily"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yahəviyn (yhb partcpl pl): customarily were to give</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'illeyn: these"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'illeyn: these</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) lehəwon: they are, they will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) lehəwon: they are, they will be</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chad: one"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chad: one</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) təlata': three"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) təlata': three</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Sarkhiyn: overseers"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Sarkhiyn: overseers</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) minnəhown: of them, from them,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) minnəhown: of them, from them,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Sonde lama te, su jalás bilang Daniel urus dia pung tanggong-jawab lebe bae dari itu dua pagawe deng gubernor laen dong samua. Te dia orang hati bae, yang rajin bekin yang batúl. Andia ko raja mau angka sang dia ko ator dia pung da'era parenta samua.<bt>Soon after that, [+contrary to expectation] it was clear that Daniel managed his responsibilities better than the other two officials and all the other governors. Cuz (elaboration) he was a person with a good liver, who was diligent to do what was right/correct. That is why the raja wanted to elevate/appoint him to handle all of the regions he governed. [EXEG: Aram yattiyra' (adj): pre-eminent, surpassing, extreme, extraordinary; NRSV excellent spirit; NLT more capable; TB roh luar biasa; TH.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhəqamuwtehh (hafʕel inf): to appoint"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhəqamuwtehh (hafʕel inf): to appoint him</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yattiyra' (adj): pre-eminent, surpassing, extreme,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yattiyra' (adj): pre-eminent, surpassing, extreme, extraordinary</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qavel: because"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qavel: because</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mitnattsach (ntsch hitpaʕʕal partcpl): distinguishing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mitnattsach (ntsch hitpaʕʕal partcpl): distinguishing himself</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) həwa': he was + partcpl"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) həwa': he was + partcpl</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) dənah: this"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) dənah: this</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Andia ko itu dua pagawe yang laen dong, deng gubernor dong mau cari hal ko lempar kasi jato sang Daniel. Dong pareksa sampe alus-alus dia pung cara ator pamarinta, ma sonde dapa dia pung sala sadiki ju. Dong cari bukti korupsi, ma sonde dapa dia pung sala sadiki ju. Te dia satu orang yang jujur, rajin, deng bekin iko apa yang dia omong.<bt>That is why those two other officials and the governors wanted to look for a matter (find an excuse, cause trouble) to accuse Daniel and cause him to fall (socially, morally, politically). They examined down to the finest details the way he governed, but they could not find any wrong with him. Cuz (elaboration) he was a person who was honest, diligent, and did according to what he said.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕəlowhiy: on him, in him"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕəlowhiy: on him, in him</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hishtəkhachat (shkch hitpaʕʕal): NET: &quot;no"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hishtəkhachat (shkch hitpaʕʕal): NET: "no negligence or corruption was found in him."</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shaluw: negligence"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shaluw: negligence</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məheyman ('mn hafʕel): he he"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məheyman ('mn hafʕel): he he was trustworthy</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shəchiytah: being corrupt"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shəchiytah: being corrupt</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tsad: side, from the side"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tsad: side, from the side</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhashkachah (shkch hafʕel inf): to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhashkachah (shkch hafʕel inf): to find</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕillah: grounds for an accusation"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕillah: grounds for an accusation</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vaʕayin (bʕ' partcpl): they were"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vaʕayin (bʕ' partcpl): they were seeking</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Ais dong ator siasat bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini. Ini orang idop lurus talalu. Jadi sonde mungkin kotong bisa dapa bukti apa-apa ko lempar sala sang dia. Cuma deng dia pung atoran agama sa, kotong bisa cari hal. Te dia pung parcaya laen dari yang laen!&gt;&gt;<bt>So then they plotted saying, &lt;&lt;It's like this. This person lives too straight/honest/righteous/just/fair. So (consequently) it is not likely that we-inc will find any proff/evidence to accuse him of wrong. Only with his religious regulations, are we able to find an excuse (to cause trouble). Cuz (elaboration) his belief is different from the others!&gt;&gt; [EXEG: implicit-explicit proposition. Last clause following HCE. Note: ‘except’ and ‘unless’ relationships are very difficult to express in the lgs of this region. This is one good way to do it.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) End of S section."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) End of S section.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) dat: decrees, laws of his"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) dat: decrees, laws of his God</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕilla': grounds for accusation"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕilla': grounds for accusation</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) guvrayya'"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) guvrayya'</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ais itu dua pagawe tinggi yang laen deng samua gubernor dong datang mangada sama-sama sang raja. Ju dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa raja yang mulia! Biar ko bapa raja umur panjang!<bt>Then those other two high officials and all the governors came together before the raja. And they said, &lt;&lt;Most glorious father raja! May you have long life!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hargishuw: go together as a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hargishuw: go together as a crowd (122 very important people)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'illen: these"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'illen: these</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Botong yang pagawe tinggi, gubernor, pagawe pamarenta deng tua-tua adat dong samua su barunding sama-sama. Naa, botong mau usul bagini: biar ko bapa raja kasi turun satu atoran baru bilang, samua orang musti sambayang sang bapa raja sandiri sa. Sonde bole sambayang sang orang laen, ko tuhan laen, ko dewa laen. Ini atoran jalan 30 hari. Sapa sa yang langgar ini atoran, nanti kaná lempar buang pi dalam goa yang ponu deng singa buas dong.<bt>We-esc the high officials, governors, civil servants, and traditional (clan) elders have all consulted together. Naa [+shift], we-exc want to suggest this: father raja (=you should hand down a new regulation saying, everyone must pray only to you alone. (They) may not pray to a different person, or a different god, or a different deity. This regulation goes for 30 days. Whoever violates/transgresses this regulation, will [+certain] be thrown into a cave which is full of savage lions (loan). [EXEG: ‘lions’ is a foreign concept which some learn about in school. Characteristic ‘wild, savage, ferocious’ made explicit here on first mention.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'aryawata': lions"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'aryawata': lions</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) gov: pit"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) gov: pit</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yitrəme' (rm' yitpəʕel): he will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yitrəme' (rm' yitpəʕel): he will be thrown, get himself thrown</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) minnakh: from you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) minnakh: from you</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) lahen: except"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) lahen: except</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əlahh: god"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əlahh: god</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vaʕuw: petition, request, prayer"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vaʕuw: petition, request, prayer</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yivʕeh (bʕh): asks, requests"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yivʕeh (bʕh): asks, requests</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əSar: prohibition"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əSar: prohibition</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) lətaqqafah (tqp paʕʕel): enforce"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) lətaqqafah (tqp paʕʕel): enforce</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləqayyamah qəyam (paʕʕel inf): to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləqayyamah qəyam (paʕʕel inf): to set up, establish a statute</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) fachəwata': fathers"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) fachəwata': fathers</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hadavrayya': high government officials"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hadavrayya': high government officials</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Signayya: governors, prefects"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Signayya: governors, prefects</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'ityaʕaTuw' (yʕT 'itpaʕʕal): they have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'ityaʕaTuw' (yʕT 'itpaʕʕal): they have taken counsel together</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Botong mau usul bilang, bapa raja sandiri yang putus deng teken ini atoran, ko biar orang laen sonde bisa roba deng sonde bisa cabu kambali sang dia. Itu yang biasa kalo kotong orang Media deng orang Persia pung raja sandiri yang putus atoran.&gt;&gt;<bt>We want to suggest that you yourself be the one to decide and sign this regulation, so that other people cannot change and cannot revoke/withdraw it again. That is the custom for we-inc Media people and Persia people when the raja himself is the one who decides a regulation.&gt;&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: phrased as in Esther.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) teʕde': pass away"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) teʕde': pass away</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) faraS: Persia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) faraS: Persia</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) maday: Medes"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) maday: Medes</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) dat: decree, law"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) dat: decree, law</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhashnayah (hafʕel): to change it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhashnayah (hafʕel): to change it</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tirshum (imperv): sign the document"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tirshum (imperv): sign the document</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əSara': the prohibition, interdict, decree"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əSara': the prohibition, interdict, decree of prohibition</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) təqiym (hafʕel): set up, establish"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) təqiym (hafʕel): set up, establish</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kaʕan: at this time"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kaʕan: at this time</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Andia ko raja Darius teken itu atoran bilang orang musti sambayang pi sang dia sandiri sa.<bt>That is why raja Darius signed that regulation saying people must pray to him alone.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əSara': the prohibition"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əSara': the prohibition</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong lempar maso sang Daniel pi dalam goa yang ponu deng singa [\s2]<bt>They throw Daniel into the cave full of lions [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Waktu Daniel dapa dengar bilang raja su teken itu atoran, ju dia pulang pi dia pung ruma. Iko dia pung biasa, dia nae pi kamar atas, ju tikam lutut ko sambayang sang dia pung Tuhan bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan Allah. Beta minta tarima kasi bam-banya sang Tuhan, ju angka nae puji sang Tuhan, tagal Tuhan masi kasi tunju Tuhan pung hati bae sang botong, sama ke dari dolu-dolu.&gt;&gt; Naa, Daniel pung biasa satu hari, sambayang tiga kali. Waktu dia sambayang ju, itu kamar atas pung jendela dong tabuka mangada sang kota Yerusalem yang jao.<bt>When Daniel heard that the raja had signed that regulation, he went back to his house. Following his normal (practice), he went up to the upper room, and knelt to pray to his God2 saying, &lt;&lt;Lord God. I give many thanks to God2 (=You), and lift up praise to God2 (=You), because You still/continue to show Your good liver/kindness/grace to us-exc, just as before/previously.&gt;&gt; Naa [+shift], Daniel's norm was in one day to pray three times. And while he was praying, the window of that room was opened facing the far-away city of Yerusalem. [EXEG: Cnj, TH “the word translated ‘when’ in RSV and TEV may be better rendered as in NAB and AB, ‘Even after.’ NRSV renders it ‘Although.’ If this example is followed, then the verb ‘to know’ is logical; but if the translator follows the majority in translating ‘When’, then the subsequent verb is better rendered ‘learned’ (NJV, NEB/REB) or ‘heard’ (NJB and NAB), or possibly ‘found out’.”] [DISCOURSE: made direct speech following common RL patterns, but OK to leave indirect here if preferred. Reordered for more natural RL flow.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) End of S section."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) End of S section.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) dənah: he"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) dənah: he</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qadmat: formerly"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qadmat: formerly</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕaved (partcpl): doing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕaved (partcpl): doing</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) həwa' (hwh): he was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) həwa' (hwh): he was</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mowde' ('afʕel partcpl): praising"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mowde' ('afʕel partcpl): praising</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mətsalle' (paʕʕel): he prayed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mətsalle' (paʕʕel): he prayed</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) birkowhiy: on his knees"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) birkowhiy: on his knees</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) barekh (paʕʕel): blessed, praised (only"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) barekh (paʕʕel): blessed, praised (only of God as object). In pəʕal it means "kneel". Psalm 55:17</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) neged: facing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) neged: facing</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕilliytehh: most high, highest room"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕilliytehh: most high, highest room</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) pətiychan (pəʕil): were open, had"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) pətiychan (pəʕil): were open, had been opened</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) khawwiyn: windows"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) khawwiyn: windows</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rashiym (pəʕil): was written"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rashiym (pəʕil): was written</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cot\co01376c.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ais itu orang yang cari-cari hal dong pi sama-sama di Daniel pung ruma, ju dapa lia dia ada sambayang ko minta tolong sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>Then those people who were looking for trouble/excuses went together to Daniel's house, and were able to see he was praying asking God for help.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mitchannan (hitpaʕʕal partcpl): imploring favor"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mitchannan (hitpaʕʕal partcpl): imploring favor</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) baʕe': asking"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) baʕe': asking</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hashkachuw (hafʕel): they found"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hashkachuw (hafʕel): they found</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hargishuw (hafʕel): go together in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hargishuw (hafʕel): go together in a tumultuous throng</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Lia dia langgar itu atoran baru bagitu, ju dong pi mangada sang raja ko kasi inga bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa raja baru kasi turun itu atoran baru yang bilang, samua orang musti sambayang sang bapa raja sandiri sa. Sonde bole sambayang sang orang laen, ko tuhan laen, ko dewa laen. Ini atoran mau jalan 30 hari. Sapa sa yang langgar ini atoran, nanti dia pung hukuman kaná lempar buang pi dalam goa yang ponu deng singa dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>Seeing him violating that new regulation in that way, they went before the raja to remind/warn him saying, &lt;&lt;Father raja (=you) have just handed down that new regulation that says, everyone must pray only to father raja alone. They may not pray to another person, or another god, or another deity. This regulation goes for 30 days. Whoever violates this regulation, he will be punished by being thrown into a cave which is full of lions.&gt;&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: see wording in 6:7.]</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cot\co01377c.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju raja bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl. Itu atoran babunyi bagitu. Deng beta sandiri yang teken itu atoran, ko biar orang laen sonde bisa roba deng sonde bisa cabu kambali sang dia. Te itu yang biasa kalo kotong orang Media deng orang Persia pung raja yang putus atoran.&gt;&gt;<bt>And the raja said, &lt;&lt;True/That's right. That is how that regulation sounds (=is worded). And I myself am the one who signed that regulation, so that other people cannot change and cannot revoke/withdraw it. Cuz (elaboration) that is the custom when we-inc Media people and Persia people's raja is the one who decides a regulation.&gt;&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: see wording in 6:8.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) teʕde': pass away"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) teʕde': pass away</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) milləta': the matter"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) milləta': the matter</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yattsiyva': it is certain, true,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yattsiyva': it is certain, true, sure</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) həla': isn't it so?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) həla': isn't it so?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qəriyvuw: they approached"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qəriyvuw: they approached</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ais dong kasi tau sang raja bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia pung masala bagini, bapa raja. Ada itu orang, nama Daniel, yang orang Babel pung tantara dong culik ame dari tana Yahuda. Dia sonde mau dengar sang bapa raja, deng sonde mau bekin iko bapa raja pung atoran tu. Te tiap hari dia masi sambayang pi dia pung Tuhan, tiga kali dalam satu hari.&gt;&gt;<bt>So then they told the raja saying, &lt;&lt;The problem is like this, father raja. There is that person, named Daniel, whom the army of the Babel people kidnapped from the land of Yahuda. He does not want to listen/obey father raja, and does not want to follow that regulation of father raja. Cuz (elaboration) every day he still prays to his God2 three times in one day.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: the decree does not forbid praying, but forbids praying to anyone other than the king. So praying is not the violation. We make this explicit as in NLT, CEV.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) baʕuwtehh: his prayer, supplication"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) baʕuwtehh: his prayer, supplication</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Təʕ em: decree"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Təʕ em: decree</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) malka': O King"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) malka': O King</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) sam: he [does not] pay"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) sam: he [does not] pay attention</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Dengar dong pung omong bagitu, ju raja ilang kira. Ais dia mulai cari jalan kaluar, te dia mau kasi salamat sang Daniel. Dia putar otak ko cari jalan kaluar sampe matahari tanggalám.<bt>Hearing them talk like that, the raja's thoughts disappeared (quandary, couldn't think what to do). So then he began to look for a way out, cuz (elaboration) he wanted to rescue/save Daniel. He turned his brain in circles to find a way out until the sun went down. [EXEG: JEG: The Aramaic is talking about exercise of the mind to rescue Daniel, not about the king's emotional state. CEV and NRSV's wording evokes emotional disturbance, which is secondary. He was in a quandary.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhattsaluwtehh (ntsl hafʕel): to extricate"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhattsaluwtehh (ntsl hafʕel): to extricate him, rescue him</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mishtaddar (shdr hitpaʕʕal partcpl): he"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mishtaddar (shdr hitpaʕʕal partcpl): he was striving</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shimsha': the sun"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shimsha': the sun</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) maʕaley: setting of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) maʕaley: setting of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləsheyzavuwtehh: to rescue him"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləsheyzavuwtehh: to rescue him</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) bal: mind"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) bal: mind</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕəlowhiy: about him"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕəlowhiy: about him</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) bə' esh: be evil, be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) bə' esh: be evil, be bad, be displeasing</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) saggiy': much"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) saggiy': much</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) milləta': the matter"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) milləta': the matter</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ma itu orang yang cari-cari hal dong datang mangada sang raja satu kali lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa raja! Inga te, kalo kotong orang Media deng orang Persia pung raja yang putus atoran, orang sonde bisa roba deng sonde bisa cabu kambali sang dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>But those people who were looking for trouble/excuses came before the raja one more time saying, &lt;&lt;Father raja! Remember that when our-inc raja of the Media people and the Persia people is the one to decide a regulation, people cannot change and cannot revoke/withdraw it.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhashnayah (shn' hafʕel): to alter"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhashnayah (shn' hafʕel): to alter</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Jadi, mau sonde mau raja suru orang ko pi tangkap ame sang Daniel. Tangkap ame sang dia bagitu, ju dong lempar maso sang dia pi dalam goa yang ponu deng singa dong. Ju raja kasi tau sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Daniel. Lu talalu rajin sémba deng layani sang lu pung Tuhan. Biar ko Dia yang kasi salamat sang lu, te beta sonde bisa!&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently) like it or not, the raja ordered people to go catch/arrest Daniel. After arresting him like that, then they threw him into a/the case which was full of lions. And the raja told him saying, &lt;&lt;Daniel. You are too diligent to worship and serve your God2. May He be the one to rescue/save you, cuz (elaboration) I am not able to!&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Aram. yəsheyzvinnakh: may he save you. UBS: This should probably be understood as more than a fond hope or mere wishful thinking. Instead, it is to be seen as a rather firm affirmation of faith. Brought out by last clause, following HCE, hinted at by CEV and fuller TH discussion.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəsheyzvinnakh: may he save you."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəsheyzvinnakh: may he save you. UBS: This should probably be understood as more than a fond hope or mere wishful thinking. Instead, it is to be seen as a rather firm affirmation of faith.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) bitdiyra': continually"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) bitdiyra': continually</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) palach: serve, pay respeck to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) palach: serve, pay respeck to</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rəmow: threw him"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rəmow: threw him</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) haytiyw ('th hafʕel): they brought"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) haytiyw ('th hafʕel): they brought</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cot\co01380c.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ju raja pung orang dong bawa datang satu batu bésar ko tutu ame itu goa pung mulu. Ais dong segel kuliling itu batu pake tana liat. Raja taro dia pung cap di itu tana liat. Itu pagawe tinggi dong taro dong pung cap di itu tana lia ju, ko jadi tanda bilang, orang sonde bole bekin apa-apa ko tolong sang Daniel.<bt>Then the raja's people brought a large rock to cover/close the mouth of that cave. Then they sealed around that rock using clay. The raja placed his stamp on/in that clay. Those high officials also placed their stamps on that clay, as a sign that people may not do anything to help Daniel.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tsəvuw: situation, thing determined"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tsəvuw: situation, thing determined</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕizqətehh: his signet ring"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕizqətehh: his signet ring</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chatmahh: he sealed it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chatmahh: he sealed it</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) pum: mouth, opening"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) pum: mouth, opening</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Ais itu, ju raja pulang pi dia pung istana. Ma itu malam ju, dia puasa. Dia sonde mau tarima orang maen musik, ko, bawa hiburan laen dong. Biar bagitu ju, ma dia sonde bisa tidor.<bt>After that, the raja went home to his palace. But that (same) night, he fasted. He did not want to accept/receive people to play music, or bring other comfort/entertainment. Even that being the case, nevertheless he still could not sleep. [EXEG: TH: the word here rendered as ‘diversions’ is found nowhere else in Aramaic literature known to the present. It has been understood to refer to ‘concubines’ (NJB), women (NEB and REB), ‘dancing girls’ (Mft), ‘entertainers’ (NAB), and ‘musical instruments’ (NJB note). NLT ‘he refused his usual entertainment’. HCE ‘no like nobody play music o make party fo him o do odda stuff.’]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) naddat: fled"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) naddat: fled</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shintehh: sleep"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shintehh: sleep</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qadamowhiy: in front of him"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qadamowhiy: in front of him</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hanʕel (ʕll hafʕel): brought"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hanʕel (ʕll hafʕel): brought</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) dachəwan: concubine? table? music? entertainment?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) dachəwan: concubine? table? music? entertainment?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Təwat: hungrily"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Təwat: hungrily</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vat: he spent the night"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vat: he spent the night</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əzal: he went off"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əzal: he went off</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cot\co01382c.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan kasi salamat sang Daniel<bt>God2 rescues/saves Daniel</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Dia pung beso papagi, ju raja bangun ko capát-capát pi itu goa yang ponu deng singa dong.<bt>Early the following morning, the raja got up and quickly went to that cave which was full of lions.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hitbəhalah: with haste"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hitbəhalah: with haste</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nagha': at first daylight"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nagha': at first daylight</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shəpparpara': dawn"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shəpparpara': dawn</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Sampe deng sampe ju, dia pange pake suara barát bilang, &lt;&lt;Hoi, Daniel! Lu yang rajin jadi Tuhan Allah pung orang karjá! Lu pung Tuhan yang idop tarús! Kira-kira Dia su bisa kasi salamat sang lu, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>Upon arriving there, he called out using a heavy (=sad) voice saying, &lt;&lt;Hoi [+attention], Daniel! You-sg who are so diligent in being God's worker! Your God2 lives forever!  Perhaps He has been able to rescue/save you, ya?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləsheyzavuwtakh (yzb shafʕel inf): to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləsheyzavuwtakh (yzb shafʕel inf): to deliver you</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hayəkhil: has he been able?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hayəkhil: has he been able?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tədiyra': continuing, all the time"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tədiyra': continuing, all the time</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) palach (partcpl): serving to him"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) palach (partcpl): serving to him</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) zəʕ iq: he cried"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) zəʕ iq: he cried</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕətsiyv: sad"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕətsiyv: sad</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qal: voice"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qal: voice</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) miqrəvehh (qrb inf): as he"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) miqrəvehh (qrb inf): as he approached</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ju Daniel manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa raja yang mulia! Biar ko bapa raja umur panjang!<bt>And Daniel responded saying, &lt;&lt;Glorious father raja! May you have long life! [NOTE to daughter translations: cf. wording at Dan. 3:9, 6:6]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mallil (mll paʕʕel): he spoke"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mallil (mll paʕʕel): he spoke [with]</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Beta pung Tuhan su kirim Dia pung ana bua dong dari sorga ko tutu ame itu singa dong pung mulu, ko biar dong sonde gigi ame sang beta. Dong sonde bekin apa-apa sang beta, tagal Tuhan sandiri yang tau bilang, beta orang hati lurus. Deng beta sonde parná bekin sala sang bapa raja ju.&gt;&gt;<bt>My God2 has sent his underlings from heaven (*angels) to shut the mouth of those lions, so they they do not bite me. They have done nothing to me, because God2 himself knows that I am a straight livered person (honest/pure/without guilt or guile). And I have also never done anything wrong to/toward father raja (=you).&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕavdet: I did [not] do"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕavdet: I did [not] do</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəvuwlah: harm"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəvuwlah: harm</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qadamayich (q. qadamakh): before you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qadamayich (q. qadamakh): before you</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'af: also"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'af: also</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hishtəkhachat liy (shkch hitpəʕel): it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hishtəkhachat liy (shkch hitpəʕel): it found itself, it was found on me</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) zakhuw: innocent. IVPBC: Most trials"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) zakhuw: innocent. IVPBC: Most trials by ordeal in the ancient Near East involved dangers such as water, fire or poison. When the accused was exposed to these threats, he or she was in effect being assumed guilty until the deity declared otherwise.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qadamowhiy: before him"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qadamowhiy: before him</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chabbəluwniy (chbl paʕʕel): they did"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chabbəluwniy (chbl paʕʕel): they did [not] harm/destroy me</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Səgar: he shut"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Səgar: he shut</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cot\co01385c.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Dengar Daniel pung suara bagitu, ju raja talalu sanáng. Ais dia suru dia pung orang dong ko angka ame sang Daniel kaluar dari itu goa. Dia kaluar bagitu, ais dong pareksa bae-bae sang dia. Ma sonde ada dia pung luka sadiki ju, te dia parcaya batúl sang dia pung Tuhan Allah.<bt>Hearing Daniel's voice like that, the raja was very happy. So/Then he order his people to lift Daniel up out of that cave. When he got out, they examined him carefully. But [+contrary to expectation] there was not any sign of a wound, cuz (elaboration) he truly believed (in) his God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) heymin ('mn hafʕel): he trusted"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) heymin ('mn hafʕel): he trusted in</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hishtəkhach (shkch hitpəʕel): it was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hishtəkhach (shkch hitpəʕel): it was [not] found</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəval: harm"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəval: harm</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) huSSaq (Slq hofʕal): he was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) huSSaq (Slq hofʕal): he was lifted up, brought up</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hanSaqah (Slq hafʕel): to bring"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hanSaqah (Slq hafʕel): to bring him up</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕəlowhiy: to him, for him"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕəlowhiy: to him, for him</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Tə' ev: it was good"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Tə' ev: it was good</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) saggiy': exceedingly"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) saggiy': exceedingly</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Ais itu ju, raja suru dia pung orang dong ko pi tangkap ame itu orang cari hal dong, yang lempar sala sang Daniel. Tarús dia suru ko lempar buang sang dong, sama-sama deng dong pung bini-ana samua pi dalam itu goa yang ponu deng singa. Balóm sampe di tana ju, singa dong su gigi ame, deng makan buang sang dong. Sampe gigi kasi pata tulang dong ju.<bt>After that, the raja ordered his people to go catch/arrest those people who were looking to make trouble/excuses, who had accused Daniel. Then3 he ordered (them) to be thrown into the cave full of lions, together with their wives/children. Before they reached the ground/floor, the lions had bitten them and eaten them up. Even to the point of breaking their bones. [NOTE to daughter translations: Check what a dog does with crunching bones.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) haddiquw: they crushed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) haddiquw: they crushed</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) garmeyhown: their bones"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) garmeyhown: their bones</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shəliTuw: they attacked"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shəliTuw: they attacked</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) lə'arʕiyt: to the earth of,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) lə'arʕiyt: to the earth of, the bottom</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məTow: they reached"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məTow: they reached</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'innuwn: them"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'innuwn: them</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rəmow (rwm): they threw"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rəmow (rwm): they threw</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) gov: pit, den"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) gov: pit, den</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qartsowhiy: their piece. TWOT: Used"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qartsowhiy: their piece. TWOT: Used with the verb 'akal "to eat a piece," idiomatically to mean "slander, denounce," an idiom well attested in Akkadian (e.g. in the Amarna tablets).</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əkhaluw: the ate (BDB eat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əkhaluw: the ate (BDB eat their pieces (in a phrase, that is, slander them))</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'illekh: those"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'illekh: those</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) guvrayya': the men"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) guvrayya': the men</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) haytiyw ('th hafʕel): they caused"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) haytiyw ('th hafʕel): they caused to come, brought</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cot\co01387c.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ais itu ju, raja Darius tulis surat kasi sang samua suku, samua negara, deng samua bahasa di anteru dunya yang dia parenta dong. Itu surat pung bunyi bilang bagini:<bt>Then raja Darius wrote a letter to all tribes/ethnic groups, all countries, and all languages in the entire world that he governed. The sound (wording) of the letter was like this: [NOTE to daughter translations: use your wording in 4:1.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Biar ko bosong samua idop aman deng dame!<bt>&lt;&lt;May you-pl live in safety-peace and relational-peace!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yisge' (jussive): may it grow"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yisge' (jussive): may it grow great</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) səlamkhown: your well-being"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) səlamkhown: your well-being</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) dayriyn (partcpl): dwelling"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) dayriyn (partcpl): dwelling</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="26" />Beta putus bagini: samua orang di beta pung da'era parenta dong musti hormat deng taku sang Daniel pung Tuhan Allah.<bt>I have made a decision like this: everyone in the regions that I govern must respect and fear Daniel's God.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Te Dia tu, Allah yang batúl-batúl idop,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) He is a/the God who truly lives,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng idop sonde putus-putus.<bt>and lives eternally/without ceasing.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Sonde ada satu ju yang bisa kasi kala sang Dia,<bt>There is not one who is able to defeat Him,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng sonde ada satu ju yang bisa kasi ancor sang Dia,<bt>and there is not one who is able to destroy Him,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">te Dia tu, Raja yang parenta sonde pake barenti.<bt>cuz (elaboration) He is the King who rules/governs without ceasing2.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Sowfa': till the conclusion"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Sowfa': till the conclusion</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shalTanehh: his sovereignty"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shalTanehh: his sovereignty</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) titchabbal (hitpaʕʕal): it will [not]"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) titchabbal (hitpaʕʕal): it will [not] be destroyed</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qayyam: enduring"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qayyam: enduring</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chayya': living"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chayya': living</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qədam: the presence"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qədam: the presence</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) dachəliyn (partcpl): be shaking"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) dachəliyn (partcpl): be shaking</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) za'əʕiyn (q. zayʕiyn partcpl): be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) za'əʕiyn (q. zayʕiyn partcpl): be trembling</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) lehəwon (hyh inf): it is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) lehəwon (hyh inf): it is to happen</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shalTan: realm"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shalTan: realm</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Təʕem: decree, order"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Təʕem: decree, order</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) siym (pəʕil): it is decreed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) siym (pəʕil): it is decreed</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qədamay: my presence"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qədamay: my presence</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="27" />Dia kasi salamat sang Dia pung orang dong,<bt>He rescues/saves His people,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng kasi lapás sang dong dari susa.<bt>and frees/releases them from trouble/difficulty.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia bekin tanda heran macam-macam di langit deng di bumi.<bt>He does various sorts of amazing signs (*miracles) in heaven and on earth.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Conto ke: Dia yang su kasi salamat sang Daniel,<bt>For example: He is the one who has rescued/saved Daniel,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko biar singa dong sonde sonto ame sang Daniel sadiki ju.&gt;&gt;<bt>so that the lions did not even touch Daniel a little bit.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) sheyziyv"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) sheyziyv</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shəmayya': in the heavens"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shəmayya': in the heavens</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) timhiyn: wonders"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) timhiyn: wonders</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'atiyn: miraculous signs (4:2)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'atiyn: miraculous signs (4:2)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mattsil (ntsl partcpl): rescuing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mattsil (ntsl partcpl): rescuing</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məsheyziv (shyzv shafʕel partcpl): delivering"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məsheyziv (shyzv shafʕel partcpl): delivering</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cot\co01388c.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Andia ko, Daniel pung nama bae, deng samua-samua jadi bae kasi sang dia, waktu Darius pegang parenta, deng waktu Kores dudu jadi raja di Persia.<bt>That is why Daniel had a good name/reputation, and everything became good for him, while Darius held rule/governed, and while Kores sat as raja in Persia. [EXEG: TH “prospered: the translation of this verb should not focus on physical prosperity. ... the verb used here suggests the idea of Daniel's political success. FRCL translates "occupied an important position," and NAB reads "fared well."]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Daniel pung mimpi so'al 4 binatang buas dong<bt>Daniel's dream about 4 vicious/ferocious/fearsome animals</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="7" />
      <v n="1" />Waktu raja Belsasar balóm pegang parenta satu taon di Babel,<bt>When raja Belsasar had not yet held rule/governed for one year in Babel,</bt><note reference="7:1" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ini, kira-kira taon 554 SM (Sebelum Masehi).<bt>This was approximately the year 554 SM (Before Messiah). [EXEG: CEV note says 554 BC. NLT note says 556/553. IVP says 556/552.]</bt></note>ju Daniel dapa mimpi. Waktu dia ada tidor di atas koi, tingka ke dia lia gambar macam-macam. Ais itu ju, dia tulis samua yang dia su lia dong.<bt>Daniel had a dream. When he was sleeping/lying on the bed, it was as if he saw various pictures. After that he wrote down everything that he had seen. [NOTE to daughter translations: make sure this king's name is different from the name given to Daniel in 1:7.] [EXEG: re'sh: beginning, content, sum, summary, main things, essential content. This term suggests the focus was not on the details.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əmar: he told, related"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əmar: he told, related</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) milliyn: matters"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) milliyn: matters</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) re'sh: beginning? content? sum? summary?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) re'sh: beginning? content? sum? summary? main ting? essential content</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chelma': the dream"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chelma': the dream</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) be'dayin: thereupon, from that time"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) be'dayin: thereupon, from that time</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mishkəvehh: his bed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mishkəvehh: his bed</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) re'shehh: his head"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) re'shehh: his head</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chezwiy: vision"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chezwiy: vision</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəzah: he saw"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəzah: he saw</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chelem: dream"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chelem: dream</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Dia tulis bilang,<bt>He wrote saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Beta ni, Daniel. Malam-malam beta lia banya hal, tingka ke dalam mimpi. Ada angin ribut mangamok di laut. Itu angin dong fuu bekin kaco dari mana-mana.<bt>I am Daniel. At night I saw many things, as if in a dream. There was a storm raging on the sea. That wind blew causing chaos from everywhere/all directions. [EXEG: Aram məgiychan ('afʕel partcpl): stirring up, churning up. IVPBC: a typical mythical scene in which the churning of the cosmic ocean disturbs the creatures (often sea monsters) who represent the forces of chaos and disorder.] [EXEG: tension on rendering the number “4” here. a) literal (as NRSV) to match the beasts in vs.3, or b) figurative (as NLT) meaning “from all directions”. 4 canonical points of compass not a strong part of RL worldview around Timor. But dominant seasonal wind directions are (east, west, northwest, southeast [with the latter two subordinate]), so coming from all directions all at once could be terrifying.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məgiychan ('afʕel partcpl): stirring up,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məgiychan ('afʕel partcpl): stirring up, churning up. IVPBC: a typical mythical scene in which the churning of the cosmic ocean disturbs the creatures (often sea monsters) who represent the forces of chaos and disorder. In Enuma Elish the sky god, Anu, creates the four winds that stir up the deep and its goddess, Tiamat. There, as here, it is a disruptive wind bringing unrest.</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Ais, ada ampa binatang buas yang bésar kaluar datang dari laut. Itu binatang dong laen-laen.<bt>Then there were four large vicious/ferocious/fearsome animals that came out from the sea. Those animals were different from each other. [NOTE to daughter translations: start by using the terms already processed in Rev for the great beasts.] [EXEG: Aram ravrəvan (adj pl): great (and scary). UBS: The character of the vision is that it presents a challenge to the reader to discover what the symbolism stands for, and this character must be maintained.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) da' min da': this from"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) da' min da': this from this</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shanyan (partcpl): differing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shanyan (partcpl): differing</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Salqan (partcpl): arising, coming up"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Salqan (partcpl): arising, coming up</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ravrəvan (adj pl): great (and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ravrəvan (adj pl): great (and scary). UBS: The character of the vision is that it presents a challenge to the reader to discover what the symbolism stands for, and this character must be maintained.</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dunya Model Baru 13:1, 17:8</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="4" />Binatang yang partama kantara ke singa, ma dia ada pung sayap sama ke burung élang. Ais waktu beta ada nonton, takuju sa dia pung sayap kaná cabu buang. Ju ada yang hela kasi badiri sang dia di atas dua kaki, sama ke manusia badiri ju. Tarús dia bisa pikir sama ke manusia pikir ju.<bt>The first animal appeared to be like a lion (loan), but it had wings like an eagle. Then while I was viewing, suddenly its wings were plucked out. Then there was something/one that pulled it to a standing position on its two feet, like a human stands. Then3 it was able to think like humans think. [EXEG: ‘lifted up’ here does not mean ‘lifted off the ground’, but rather ‘made to stand, pulled up to a standing position’. See NLT, CEV. TB and NRSV are misleading in the context by staying literal.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəhiyv (pəʕ il passive): was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəhiyv (pəʕ il passive): was given</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləvav: heart, mind"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləvav: heart, mind</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) həqiymat (hufʕal): he was made"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) həqiymat (hufʕal): he was made to stand</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'arʕa': the ground. The image"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'arʕa': the ground. The image starts in the sea, but now the reference point is solid land, where the beast stands.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nəTiylat (pəʕil): he was lifted"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nəTiylat (pəʕil): he was lifted up</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məriyTuw (mrT pəʕil pl): plucked"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məriyTuw (mrT pəʕil pl): plucked off</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) həweyt: I was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) həweyt: I was</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chazeh (partcpl): seeing, looking, watching"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chazeh (partcpl): seeing, looking, watching</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nəshar: eagle"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nəshar: eagle</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) gappiyn: wings"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) gappiyn: wings</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qadmayta': first"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qadmayta': first</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:4-6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dunya Model Baru 13:2</note></p>
    <fig path="hk-lb\lb00047c.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="5" />Ais beta lia binatang buas yang kadua, tingka ke baruang. Dia ada jongko, deng dia gepe tiga tulang rusuk di dia pung gigi. Ju ada yang suru sang dia bilang, &lt;Badiri su! Makan ame daging bam-banya!&gt;<bt>Then I saw the second fearsome animal, like a bear (loan). It was squatting, and it clamped three rib bones in its teeth. Then there was someone/thing that ordered it saying, &lt;Stand up! Eat up/devour a lot of  meat!&gt; [EXEG: Aram lisTar-chad: on one side. ‘raised up on one side’ (NRSV), ‘rearing up on one side’ (NLT). ‘standing on its hind legs’ (CEV), but TH points out while that makes sense, it negates the following command to ‘Rise up!’ TH suggests following NEB ‘half crouching’.] [EXEG: Aram ʕilʕiyn: ribs (NLT, CEV, TB). NRSV ‘tusks’ is problematic on several points.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) bəsar: meat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) bəsar: meat</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'amriyn: he told"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'amriyn: he told</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shinnayyahh (q. shinnahh): his teeth"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shinnayyahh (q. shinnahh): his teeth</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) beyn: between"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) beyn: between</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕilʕiyn: ribs"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕilʕiyn: ribs</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) təlat: three"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) təlat: three</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) həqimat (qwm hofʕal): it was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) həqimat (qwm hofʕal): it was made to stand</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) lisTar-chad: on one side"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) lisTar-chad: on one side</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) dov: bear"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) dov: bear</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) damyah (partcpl): being like"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) damyah (partcpl): being like</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tinyanah: second"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tinyanah: second</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'achəriy: another"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'achəriy: another</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="hk-lb\lb00048c.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="6" />Ais waktu beta ada lia-lia, binatang buas yang barikut muncul, tingka ke harimau. Ma dia ada ampa sayap, sama ke burung pung sayap kaluar dari dia pung balakang. Ais dia ada ampa kapala ju. Deng ada yang kasi dia kuasa bésar ko parenta bam-banya.<bt>Then while I was looking, the next fearsome animal appeared, something like a tiger/large feline (loan, also covers leopards, panthers, pumas). But it/he had four wings, like a bird's wings coming our of its back. And/then he had four heads too. And there was (someone/thing) who gave him great power/authority to rule much/many things. [EXEG: Aram gabbayyahh (q. gabbahh): back, sides. TWOT: back or side. Where would RL say wings attach?] [EXEG: nəmar: leopard. Note: Indonesian /macan tutul/ was not known by several educated MTTs, so we went more generic.] [DISCOURSE: last sentence is non-referential and impersonal--a functional equivalent of a passive.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəhiyv (yhb pəʕil): it was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəhiyv (yhb pəʕil): it was given, there was given to it</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shalTan: dominion, sovereignty"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shalTan: dominion, sovereignty</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) cheywata': the beast"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) cheywata': the beast</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) gabbayyahh (q. gabbahh): back, sides."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) gabbayyahh (q. gabbahh): back, sides. TWOT: back or side. In Dan 7:6 the word is singular in the Qere, which derives it from the Hebrew root ga4bah. The Kethib takes it as plural, "sides," probably deriving it from a root g]anaba found in Arabic.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) gappiyn: wings"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) gappiyn: wings</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nəmar: leopard"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nəmar: leopard</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'achəriy: another"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'achəriy: another</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) va'əruw: and behold!"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) va'əruw: and behold!</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) həweyt (hwh): I happened? TWOT:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) həweyt (hwh): I happened? TWOT: in Aramaic the verb hawah is often used with a participle to make a periphrastic tense expressing continuous and habitual action (e.g. Dan 6:10 [A 11], "as he used to do formerly").</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chazeh (pəʕal partcpl): seeing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chazeh (pəʕal partcpl): seeing</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) dənah: that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) dənah: that</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ba'tar: trace, place. BDB trace,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ba'tar: trace, place. BDB trace, place. ba'tar, with beth, is used for time, after. Used similarly to the Hebrew 'asher</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="hk-lb\bk00049c.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="7" />Itu malam ju, beta lia dalam mimpi binatang buas yang nomer ampa. Dia talalu kuat deng bekin taku sampe bulu badan badiri. Dia pung gigi bésar dari bési. Dia pake itu gigi ko makan kasi ancor dia pung mangsa. Kalo ada yang dia sonde makan buang, na, dia pake dia pung kaki ko inja-inja kasi ancor buang sang dong. Ini binatang ni, laen dari yang laen. Te ada sapulu tandok di dia pung kapala.<bt>That same night I saw in a dream the fearsome animal number four. He was very strong and fearsome to the point that body fur stood up (idiom). He had large teeth from iron/steel. He used those teeth to eat/devour and destroy its prey. If there was (something) that he did not eat up (completely), na, he used his feet to step all over/trample destroying it/them. This (fourth) animal was exceptional/different from the others. Cuz (elaboration) it had ten horns on its head. [CHECK: Reorder last 2 sentences?? But last sentence leads into vs.8. Team says Keep this order.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qarniyn: horns. IVPBC: It was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qarniyn: horns. IVPBC: It was common in Mesopotamia for kings and gods to wear crowns featuring protruding or embossed horns.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qadamayhh: before him"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qadamayhh: before him</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chaywata': the beasts"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chaywata': the beasts</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məshannəyah (paʕʕel partcpl): he is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məshannəyah (paʕʕel partcpl): he is changed, different</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rafSah (partcpl): trampling, treading underfoot"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rafSah (partcpl): trampling, treading underfoot</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shə' ara': the rest, the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shə' ara': the rest, the remainder; the remains of those he has eaten</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) maddəqah (dqq/dwq 'afʕel partcpl): smashing,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) maddəqah (dqq/dwq 'afʕel partcpl): smashing, splintering</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'akhlah (partcpl): devouring, eating like"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'akhlah (partcpl): devouring, eating like an animal</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ravrəvan (reduplicated): big"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ravrəvan (reduplicated): big</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shinnayin (dual): teeth"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shinnayin (dual): teeth</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yattiyra': extremely"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yattiyra': extremely</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) taqqiyfa': strong, powerful"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) taqqiyfa': strong, powerful</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'eymtaniy: scary, frightful"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'eymtaniy: scary, frightful</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) dəchiylah: horrific, terrifying, frightening, frightful"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) dəchiylah: horrific, terrifying, frightening, frightful</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rəviyʕayah (q. rəviyʕa'ah): fourth"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rəviyʕayah (q. rəviyʕa'ah): fourth</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) cheywah: beast"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) cheywah: beast</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chezwiy: visions of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chezwiy: visions of</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dunya Model Baru 12:3, 13:1</note></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="8" />Waktu beta ada pikir-pikir ko cari tau itu tandok dong pung arti, takuju sa ada satu tandok yang kici muncul datang. Ma itu sapulu tandok laen talalu basesak. Andia ko tiga tandok kaná cabu buang dari akar, ko biar itu tandok kici dapa tampa. Ini tandok kici ni, ada mata ke manusia pung mata, deng ada mulu babengko yang omong sombong.<bt>While I was pondering to try and understand/find out the meaning of those horns, suddenly a small horn appeared. But those other ten hords were too crowded. That is why three of the horns were plucked out from/by their root, so that that small horn could get a place. This small horn [that we are talking about here], had eyes like human eyes, and had a twisted mouth that spoke arrogantly.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məmallil (paʕʕel partcpl): who was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məmallil (paʕʕel partcpl): who was speaking</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qarna': that horn"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qarna': that horn</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'ənasha': human"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'ənasha': human</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕayniyn: eyes"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕayniyn: eyes</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qədamayyahh (q. qədamahh): before it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qədamayyahh (q. qədamahh): before it</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'etʕəqaruw (q. 'etʕəqarah) (ʕqr 'itpəʕel)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'etʕəqaruw (q. 'etʕəqarah) (ʕqr 'itpəʕel) rooted itself up, got rooted up</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qadmayata': first ones"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qadmayata': first ones</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) beyneyhown (q. beyneyhen): between them,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) beyneyhown (q. beyneyhen): between them, in the middle of them</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Silqat: it came up"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Silqat: it came up</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) zəʕeyrah: small"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) zəʕeyrah: small</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) va'əluw: behold!"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) va'əluw: behold!</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mishtakkal (shkl 'itpaʕʕal partcpl): while"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mishtakkal (shkl 'itpaʕʕal partcpl): while considering. UBS: the main component of this verb is the idea of looking intently at an object. It may be better translated "looked at," "was gazing upon" (njv), "examined" (frcl), "watched" (at, njb, and Mft). niv translates " thinking about," but this is less desirable.</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dunya Model Baru 13:5-6</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="9" />Waktu beta lia-lia,<bt>While I was looking, [DISCOURSE: NRSV and CEV put a section header here. NLT and TB do not. A careful reading of the context (see vs. 11-12) show this is a continuation of the 4 beasts and the little horn, so we do not put a section break here.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ada yang ator ko biar korsi hakim dong muncul datang di tampa yang pas.<bt>there was something/one that arranged for judges chairs to appear in their appropriate places. [EXEG: these ‘thrones’ are for judges, not kings. See TH, HCE, and NLT next clause.]</bt><note reference="7:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dunya Model Baru 20:4, 1:14</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ais Yang Su Ada Memang Dari Dolu-dolu,<bt>Then The One Who Existed Beforehand From Long Ago, [EXEG: Aram ʕattiyq: ancient one. TWOT: Used only of God, in Dan 7:9, 13, 22. Derivatives of the Hebrew root include the ideas of value and eminence.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dudu di Dia pung korsi putus parkara.<bt>sat in His chair for deciding siputes/litigations/cases.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia pung pakean puti mangkilat sama ke salju.<bt>His clothes were shining white like snow (loan).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia pung rambu puti barisi, sama ke domba pung bulu puti.<bt>His hair was pure white (lit: clean white = Max degree), like sheep's white fur. [NOTE to daughter translations: Check your phrasing in Rev. 1:14.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia pung korsi hakim tadudu di atas kareta.<bt>His judge's chair was sitting/seated on a wagon. [EXEG: See discussion in TH.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Itu korsi manyala ke lida api,<bt>That chair shone like a flame of fire, [EXEG: Sources are unclear whether the throne was actually burning, or just having the appearance of burning. See TH.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">deng dia pung roda dong manyala ke tabakar ju.<bt>and its wheels shone like they were on fire also. [NOTE to daughter translations: focus on the vision; avoid phrasing that implies the throne or wheels are being consumed by fire.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) daliq (partcpl): burning"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) daliq (partcpl): burning</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) galgillowhiy: its wheels"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) galgillowhiy: its wheels</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nuwr: fire"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nuwr: fire</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shəviyviyn: flames"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shəviyviyn: flames</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) karSəyehh: his throne"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) karSəyehh: his throne</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nəqe': pure, clean"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nəqe': pure, clean</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕəmar: wool"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕəmar: wool</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) səʕ ar: hair of the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) səʕ ar: hair of the head</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chiwwar: white"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chiwwar: white</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) təlag: snow"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) təlag: snow</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləvuwshehh: his clothes"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləvuwshehh: his clothes</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yətiv: he took his seat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yətiv: he took his seat</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yowmiyn: days"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yowmiyn: days</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕattiyq: ancient one. TWOT: Used"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕattiyq: ancient one. TWOT: Used only of God, in Dan 7:9, 13, 22. Derivatives of the Hebrew root include the ideas of value and eminence.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rəmiyw (rmʕ pəʕil pl): they"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rəmiyw (rmʕ pəʕil pl): they were thrown, set up</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kharSawan: thrones"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kharSawan: thrones</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="10" />Dari Dia pung tampa dudu pung muka tu,<bt>From in front of His sitting place,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ada lida api dong kaluar datang,<bt>there were flames of fire coming forth, [EXEG: Aram is grammatically sg, but CEV goes pl to indicate the volume; pl idea is supported by TH.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">sama ke arus kali yang jalan tarús.<bt>like the flow/current of a river that keeps on going/moving.</bt><note reference="7:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dunya Model Baru 5:11, 20:12</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Baribu-ribu orang layani sang Dia,<bt>A thousand-thousand people serve Him,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sampe sonde bisa itong ame sang dong.<bt>to the point that there is none that can (successfully) count them. [EXEG: See discussion in TH.] [EXEG: Aram does not specify what kind of being. Our RLs need to. TH prefers ‘people’ (TEV, HCE) over ‘angels’ (NLT1).]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Bajuta-juta orang badiri ko kasi jalan Dia pung karjá.<bt>A million-million people stand to carry out His work.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ais itu, tukang putus parkara dong dudu ko mau timbang parkara,<bt>After that, deciders of disputes/judges sit to weigh/evaluate the cases,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ju dong buka buku-buku dong.<bt>and they open various books. [NOTE: CEV note says “containing the record of the good and evil that each person has done.”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) pətiychuw (pəʕil): were opened"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) pətiychuw (pəʕil): were opened</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Sifriyn: books"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Sifriyn: books</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yətiv: sat, took its place"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yətiv: sat, took its place</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) diyna': the court"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) diyna': the court</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəquwmuwn: stood (in his presence)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəquwmuwn: stood (in his presence)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rabbəwan (q. rivəvan): ten thousands"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rabbəwan (q. rivəvan): ten thousands</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ribbow: ten thousand of. TWOT:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ribbow: ten thousand of. TWOT: Only used in Dan 7:10 for a very large number "ten thousand times ten thousand." [PAN *Ribu ???]</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəshamməshuwnnehh (shmsh paʕʕel): they served"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəshamməshuwnnehh (shmsh paʕʕel): they served him</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'alfayim (q. 'alfiyn) two thousands,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'alfayim (q. 'alfiyn) two thousands, q. thousands</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'elef: thousand"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'elef: thousand</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) min-qadamowhiy: from in front of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) min-qadamowhiy: from in front of him</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nafeq: coming forth"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nafeq: coming forth</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) naged (paʕʕel partcpl): it flowed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) naged (paʕʕel partcpl): it flowed</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Tagal itu tandok kici pung omong sombong tu, andia ko beta lia-lia ko mau lia apa yang jadi sang dia. Waktu beta ada lia ju, ada yang datang bunu bekin mati itu binatang buas nomer ampa, ais lempar buang pi dalam api ko biar api makan buang dia pung mayat.<bt>Because of that small horn's arrogant speech, that is why I kept looking to see what was going to happen to him/it. While I was looking, there was something/one that came and killed the fourth fearsome animal, and threw it into the fire, so that the fire devoured/consumed its corpse. (yes, fires can ‘eat’.) [EXEG: See TH and CEV.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) liyqedat: to burning"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) liyqedat: to burning</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) viyhiyvat (yhb pəʕil): it was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) viyhiyvat (yhb pəʕil): it was given</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) gishmahh: its body"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) gishmahh: its body</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) huwvad ('bd hufʕal): was destroyed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) huwvad ('bd hufʕal): was destroyed</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qəTiylat (pəʕil): it was killed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qəTiylat (pəʕil): it was killed</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ravravata': big, arrogant, boastful, insolent"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ravravata': big, arrogant, boastful, insolent</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) millayya': the words, speech"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) millayya': the words, speech</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />(Ada yang cabu ame itu tiga binatang buas yang laen dong pung kuasa deng hak parenta, ma kasi tenga ko dong bole idop lebe lama sadiki.)<bt>(There was someone/thing that plucked away/withdrew the power/authority of those other three fearsome animals and their right to rule/govern, but left it so they were allowed to live for awhile longer.) [DISCOURSE: framed as a narrator's side comment reflecting Aramaic intro, as in HCE.] [EXEG: Aram ‘for a season and a time’ = unspecified, but limited. See NLT, CEV, TH and TWOT.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕiddan: time. TWOT: Still, it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕiddan: time. TWOT: Still, it is not necessary to view ʕiddan as a specific period in these verses, and the NASB translation, "seven periods of time" is probably preferable to anything more specific both in Dan 4 and in Dan 7:12.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) zəman: an appointed time, agreed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) zəman: an appointed time, agreed upon time</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hown: them"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hown: them</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəhiyvat (yhb pəʕil): they were"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəhiyvat (yhb pəʕil): they were given</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chayyiyn: their life"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chayyiyn: their life</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'arkhah: lengthening, prolongation of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'arkhah: lengthening, prolongation of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) heʕdiyn (ʕdh hafʕel): removed, took"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) heʕdiyn (ʕdh hafʕel): removed, took away; caused to vanish</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shə'ar: the rest, remainder"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shə'ar: the rest, remainder</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(Kalo itu tiga binatang buas yang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(Kalo itu tiga binatang buas yang laen dong, ada yang cabu ame dong pung kuasa deng hak parenta, ma kasi biar ko dong bole idop sadiki lai.)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ais, waktu beta masi ada mimpi malam-malam,<bt>Then, while I was  still dreaming at night,</bt><note reference="7:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 24:30, 26:64; Markus 12:36; 13:26, 14:62; Lukas 21:27; Dunya Model Baru 1:7,13, 14:14</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Beta lia satu orang macam ke manusia tulen<bt>I saw a person like a genuine/authentic human [EXEG: phrased to resonate with our KT in NT. Aram kəvar 'ənosh: like a son of man. UBS: Here in 7.13 the meaning of the term is also "human being," but the context is quite different. The framework is that of an apocalyptic vision, and the words "son of man" come immediately after the Aramaic particle usually translated by the English adverb "like." This shows that the one referred to resembles a human being but in fact is not mortal. In the New Testament apocalypse the writer intentionally uses words very similar to what we find in this crucial passage (Rev 1.13; 14.14). While the being referred to is anything but human, the expression "son of man" in itself may still be rendered "a human being." Most translators will probably have in their language a particle corresponding to the English "like" which will indicate that, although the being resembled a mortal in some ways, it was different. ... Just as the four horrifying and vile beasts (7.3-7) are not real animals but symbols, pure and simple, of the pagan kingdoms... so too the 'one in human likeness' is not a real individual, celestial or terrestrial, but is only a symbol of 'the holy ones of the Most High,' a title given to the faithful Jews – men, women and children...” (page 87; see also the article " 'Son of Man' and Contextual Translation" in The Bible Translator, April 1989, pages 201-208).  It turns out that this is the Messiah for the faithful Jews -- but it isn't until Jesus appropriates the term that it becomes a Christian technical term that also resonates here. Here, it's just a description.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">turun datang deng awan dari langit,<bt>come down with clouds from the sky,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia datang deka-deka ko mangada sang<bt>He came close to face to/toward</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Yang Su Ada Memang Dari Dolu-dolu.<bt>The One Who Existed Beforehand From Long Ago. [EXEG: NRSV: he (1-active) came to the Ancient One and (2-passive) was presented before Him; NLT1: He (1-active) approached the Ancient One and (2-passive) was led into his presence. Problem: Our lgs in the Timor region tend to not have clear passives. TH notes the problem and observes that one source has conflated the two. “Was presented before him: once again the transformation of the passive to an active form will be required in many languages, but the agent should not be identified too clearly. The text literally says "they (indefinite) led him into his presence." Note that the GECL rendering takes this clause as parallel with ‘he came to the Ancient of Days’ and therefore renders the two as a single statement.” CEG-Since God is the object/Goal, God should not also be the subject/Agent. So who is escorting the Son of Man here? I find one rendering of “The people there brought...” unsatisfying. Our rendering focuses on the Result, rather than the Process, and does not skew the focus by making a problematic agent explicit.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) haqrəvuwhiy (qrv hafʕel): they brought"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) haqrəvuwhiy (qrv hafʕel): they brought him near</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qədamowhiy: in front of him"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qədamowhiy: in front of him</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məTah: reach, arrive, come"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məTah: reach, arrive, come</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'ateh ('th partcpl): coming"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'ateh ('th partcpl): coming</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kəvar 'ənosh: like a son"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kəvar 'ənosh: like a son of man. UBS: Here in 7.13 the meaning of the term is also "human being," but the context is quite different. The framework is that of an apocalyptic vision, and the words "son of man" come immediately after the Aramaic particle usually translated by the English adverb "like." This shows that the one referred to resembles a human being but in fact is not mortal. In the New Testament apocalypse the writer intentionally uses words very similar to what we find in this crucial passage (Rev 1.13; 14.14). While the being referred to is anything but human, the expression "son of man" in itself may still be rendered "a human being." Most translators will probably have in their language a particle corresponding to the English "like" which will indicate that, although the being resembled a mortal in some ways, it was different. ... Just as the four horrifying and vile beasts (7.3-7) are not real animals but symbols, pure and simple, of the pagan kingdoms... so too the 'one in human likeness' is not a real individual, celestial or terrestrial, but is only a symbol of 'the holy ones of the Most High,' a title given to the faithful Jews – men, women and children...” (page 87; see also the article " 'Son of Man' and Contextual Translation" in The Bible Translator, April 1989, pages 201-208.)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="14" />Ais Yang Su Ada Memang Dari Dolu-dolu<bt>Then The One Who Existed Beforehand From Long Ago,[EXEG: supply Actor for passive, as per HCE.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sarakan hak parenta kasi sang Dia,<bt>handed over/surrendered [his] right to rule/govern to Him,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ju ator ko biar orang kasi tunju hormat sang Dia,<bt>and arranged so that people would show respect to Him,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng angka sang Dia ko jadi raja,<bt>and elevate/appoint Him to be/become raja,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">sampe-sampe orang dari samua suku, samua bangsa, samua negara, deng samua bahasa,<bt>to the point/with the result that people from every tribe/ethnic group, every race, every country, and every language, [EXEG: see 3:4.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dengar-dengar sang Dia,<bt>listened to/obeyed Him,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ju kasi tunju hormat deng sémba sang Dia.<bt>and showed respect to and worshipped Him. [EXEG: Aram yifləchuwn: BDB serve, worship, revere, minister for, pay reverence to. TH: this verb is used of worshiping Nebuchadnezzar's gods in chapter 3, and of worshiping the true God in chapter 6.]</bt><note reference="7:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dunya Model Baru 11:15</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia pung kuasa tu,<bt>That power/authority of His,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sonde tau barenti.<bt>never stopped (lit: did not know how to end).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia pung hak parenta tu,<bt>His right to rulegovern,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sonde tau putus-putus.<bt>never ceased.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng sonde ada yang bisa kasi kala sang Dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>And there was nobody/nothing who was able to defeat Him.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) End of P section."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) End of P section.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) titchabbal (chbl hitpaʕal): be destroyed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) titchabbal (chbl hitpaʕal): be destroyed</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yeʕdeh (ʕdh imperf): it will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yeʕdeh (ʕdh imperf): it will [not] pass away</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yifləchuwn: BDB serve, worship, revere,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yifləchuwn: BDB serve, worship, revere, minister for, pay reverence to</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) malkhuw: his kingdom, kingship"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) malkhuw: his kingdom, kingship</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) viyqar: honor, esteem"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) viyqar: honor, esteem</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shalTan: power to rule"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shalTan: power to rule</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəhiyv: he was given"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəhiyv: he was given</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Daniel dapa tau itu mimpi pung arti<bt>Daniel finds out the meaning of that dream</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ais Daniel tulis sambung bilang, &lt;&lt;Waktu beta lia itu hal dong di beta pung kapala otak, na, beta taku mati pung! Beta pung hati rasa taganggu deng pikiran sonde tanáng.<bt>Then Daniel continued writing saying, &lt;&lt;When I saw those things in my brain/head (lit: head brain), na, I was terrified! My liver felt disturbed and my thinking would not calm/settle down. [DISCOURSE: quote margin inserted to assist referent tracking, as per CEV.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəvahəlunnaniy (bhl paʕʕel): frighten, alarm,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəvahəlunnaniy (bhl paʕʕel): frighten, alarm, dismay</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nidneh: sheath. NET: The Aramaic"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nidneh: sheath. NET: The Aramaic text includes the phrase "in its sheath," apparently viewing the body as a container or receptacle for the spirit somewhat like a sheath or scabbard is for a knife or a sword. For this phrase the LXX and Vg have "in these things."</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) bəgow': in the midst of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) bəgow': in the midst of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'etkəriyyat (krh 'itpəʕel): it was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'etkəriyyat (krh 'itpəʕel): it was distressed, grieved; Holladay anxious</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Andia ko beta pi deka-deka deng satu orang yang badiri di korsi hakim pung sablá, ko tanya sang dia bilang, &lt;Ini hal yang beta lia dong pung arti apa?&gt;<bt>That is why I went close to a person who was standing beside the judge's chair, to ask him saying, &lt;These things that I have seen have what meaning?&gt; (=what is the meaning of those things I have seen?)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəhowdʕinnaniy (ydʕ hafʕel): he caused"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəhowdʕinnaniy (ydʕ hafʕel): he caused me to know. BDB let someone know, communicate, inform, cause to know</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) fəshar: interpretation of a dream"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) fəshar: interpretation of a dream</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'evʕe': I requested"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'evʕe': I requested</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yattsiyva': the truth, what was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yattsiyva': the truth, what was true</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qa'əmayya': the ones standing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qa'əmayya': the ones standing</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais dia manyao ko biar beta bisa mangarti ini hal dong pung arti bilang,<bt>Then he responded so that I could understand the meaning of these things saying,</bt><v n="17" />&lt;Itu ampa binatang buas dong, andia ampa raja yang nanti muncul datang, yang pegang parenta di ini dunya.<bt>&lt;Those four fearsome animals, are four rajas who will appear later, who hold rule/govern in this world. [EXEG: Aram malkhiyn: lit: kings, but actually refers to empires here. UBS: Both hottp and ctat advocate translating the text that says "kings," but under the "proposed interpretation" of ctat the following is stated: "One may indicate in a note that each of the 'kings' in fact incarnates one of the empires which followed each other in the Ancient Near East." (page 455).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) malkhiyn: kings, but it refers"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) malkhiyn: kings, but it refers to empires. UBS: Both hottp and ctat advocate translating the text that says "kings," but under the "proposed interpretation" of ctat the following is stated: "One may indicate in a note that each of the 'kings' in fact incarnates one of the empires which followed each other in the Ancient Near East." (page 455).</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'inniyn: these"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'inniyn: these</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Ma Tuhan Allah yang Paling Tinggi nanti sarakan hak parenta kasi Dia pung orang barisi dong. Ju dong pegang parenta sonde pake barenti.&gt;<bt>But God Most High will hand over/surrender the right to rule/govern to His clean/holy people. And they will hold rule/govern without ceasing.&gt; [EXEG: Q: who are these ‘holy ones’? A: 1) TH: The reference here is to those who are faithful to the true God, namely, the people of Israel. But within the framework of this apocalyptic vision it is unwise to say this too clearly, although it is probably a good idea to make it clear that "people" are involved. 2) IVP points out the term is most frequently used to describe supernatural beings (this is also true in the use of the equivalent term in Ugaritic and Aramaic, as well as in the Dead Sea Scrolls literature). We follow #3 (a variation on #1): KD: neither the Jews, who are accustomed to call themselves "saints," in contrast with the heathen, nor the converted Israel of the millenium, but, as we argue from Ex. 19:6, Deut. 7:6, the true members of the covenant nation, the New Testament Israel of God...]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vəyachSənuwn (chSn 'afʕel): they will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vəyachSənuwn (chSn 'afʕel): they will take possession</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕelyowniyn (pl): the Most High,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕelyowniyn (pl): the Most High, used of God. Would this be the 'əlohiym plural?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qaddiyshey: holy ones. IVPBC: While"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qaddiyshey: holy ones. IVPBC: While many interpreters think this refers to godly people, the term is most frequently used to describe supernatural beings (this is also true in the use of the equivalent term in Ugaritic and Aramaic, as well as in the Dead Sea Scrolls literature). This would receive further support since it is the host of heaven that is under assault in the related vision of next chapter (8:10). KD: neither the Jews, who are accustomed to call themselves "saints," in contrast with the heathen, nor the converted Israel of the millenium, but, as we argue from Ex. 19:6, Deut. 7:6, the true members of the covenant nation, the New Testament Israel of God...</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) malkhuwta': kingship, sovereignty; kingdom, realm"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) malkhuwta': kingship, sovereignty; kingdom, realm</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) viyqabbəluwn (paʕʕel): they will receive"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) viyqabbəluwn (paʕʕel): they will receive</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dunya Model Baru 22:5</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ais beta mau cari tau so'al binatang buas nomer ampa tu. Te dia laen dari yang laen. Dia bekin taku sampe bulu badan badiri, tagal dia pake dia pung gigi dari bési, ko gigi kasi ancor apa sa, iko dia pung mau. Ju dia pake dia pung cakar dari tambaga, ko inja-inja kasi ancor buang apa sa yang masi idop.<bt>Then I wanted to find out about that fearsome animal number four. Cuz (elaboration) he was different from the others. He caused fear to the point that body hair stood up (=terrifying), because he used his teeth from iron/steel to bite destroying whatever, according to his desire. And he used his claws from bronze, to trample (completely) destroying whatever was still living.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rafSah: trampling"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rafSah: trampling</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shə'ara: and the rest '"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shə'ara: and the rest '</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) maddəqah (dqq 'afʕel partcpl): breaking"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) maddəqah (dqq 'afʕel partcpl): breaking in pieces, shattering</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nəchash: bronze"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nəchash: bronze</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Tifrayhh: its claws"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Tifrayhh: its claws</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shinnayyahh (q. shinnahh): its teeth"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shinnayyahh (q. shinnahh): its teeth</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yattiyrah: exceedingly"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yattiyrah: exceedingly</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) dəchiylah (partcpl): being horrific"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) dəchiylah (partcpl): being horrific</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kalləhown (q. kalləheyn): all of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kalləhown (q. kalləheyn): all of them</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shanyah (shn' partcpl): different"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shanyah (shn' partcpl): different</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləyattsava': make stand, make certain,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləyattsava': make stand, make certain, gain certainty, know the truth, be certain</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tsəviyt: I longed, desired"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tsəviyt: I longed, desired</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Beta mau mangarti ju so'al itu sapulu tandok yang ada di dia pung kapala, deng tiga tandok yang kaná cabu buang dari akar, ko biar itu tandok kici dapa tampa. Andia itu tandok kici yang ada mata ke manusia pung mata, deng ada mulu babengko yang omong sombong tu. Te beta kira itu tandok lebe pantíng dari tandok yang laen dong.<bt>I also wanted to understand about those ten horns which were on his head, and the three horns that were pulled out by the root, so that that small horn could have a place. That is, the small horn which had eyes like humans eyes, and had a twisted mouth which spoke arrogantly. Cuz (elaboration) I thought/assumed that horn was more important than the other horns. [NOTE to daughter translations: compare with your phrasing in 7:8.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chavratahh: its fellows"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chavratahh: its fellows</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chezəwahh: its appearance"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chezəwahh: its appearance</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) dikken: that one"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) dikken: that one</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nəfaluw (q. nəfalah): they fell"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nəfaluw (q. nəfalah): they fell down</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Silqat: came up"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Silqat: came up</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'achəriy: other"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'achəriy: other</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ais waktu beta ada lia-lia, te itu tandok kici baparáng malawan Tuhan pung orang barisi dong. Ju dia mulai kasi kala sang dong.<bt>Then while I was looking, [+contrary to expectation] that small horn warred against God2's clean/holy people. And it began to defeat them. [CHECK: who is ‘dia’? Team says ‘smal horn’. UNSs say ‘small horn’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yakhlah (partcpl): he was prevailing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yakhlah (partcpl): he was prevailing</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qaddiyshiyn: holy ones (angels? saints"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qaddiyshiyn: holy ones (angels? saints on earth?)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qərav: war"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qərav: war</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕavdah: doing, making"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕavdah: doing, making</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dunya Model Baru 13:7</note><v n="22" />Dia malawan tarús bagitu, sampe Yang Su Ada Memang Dari Dolu-dolu, andia Yang Paling Tinggi, datang. Ju Dia putus bilang, &lt;Orang dong yang idop barisi kasi Beta, dong tu yang batúl!&gt; Te dia pung waktu su sampe ko Dia pung orang barisi dong yang pegang parenta.&gt;&gt;<bt>He kept opposing like that, until/to the point that The One Who Existed Beforehand From Long Ago, that is The Most High, came. Then He decided saying, &lt;The person/people who live clean/holy for Me, they are the ones that are true/correct!&gt; Cuz (elaboraton) the time has arrived for His clean/holy people who hold rule/government.&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: / EXEG: The Most High needs to be understood as the same referent as The Ancient of Days. See NLT's rendering.] [DISCOURSE: made direct speech following RL patterns.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hechəSinuw (hafʕel): take possession of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hechəSinuw (hafʕel): take possession of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qaddiyshey ʕelyowniyn: the ones dedicated"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qaddiyshey ʕelyowniyn: the ones dedicated to the Most High. Needs to be understood as the same one as the Ancient of Days. UBS: In some languages it will be necessary to avoid giving the impression that the Ancient of Days and the Most High (later in this verse) refer to two different beings.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəhiv: was given"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəhiv: was given</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) diyna': judgment"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) diyna': judgment</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dunya Model Baru 20:4</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ais itu orang yang tarangkan sang beta, kasi tau tamba bilang,<bt>Then that person who was explaining to me told additionally saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Itu binatang buas nomer ampa tu,<bt>&lt;That fearsome animal number four,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sama deng kuasa nomer ampa yang datang parenta di ini dunya.<bt>is like/the same as power/authority number four which comes and rules/govern on this earth.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia laen dari yang laen.<bt>He is different from the others. [EXEG: See how NLT rebrackets this verse for better cohesion.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Te dia pegang parenta di dunya anteru,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) he holds rule/government throughout the entire world,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sama ke dia inja-inja kasi ancor buang samua,<bt>just as he trampled on and destroyed everything,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ju kodo ame samua.<bt>and swallowed up everything.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) taddəqinnahh (hafʕel): it will break"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) taddəqinnahh (hafʕel): it will break it in pieces</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) təduwshinnahh: it will trample it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) təduwshinnahh: it will trample it</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) te'khul: it will devour"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) te'khul: it will devour</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) malkhəwata': the kingdoms"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) malkhəwata': the kingdoms</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tishne': it will be differcountryent"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tishne': it will be differcountryent</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tehəwe': it will be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tehəwe': it will be</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rəviyʕaya' (q. rəviyʕa'ah): a fourth"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rəviyʕaya' (q. rəviyʕa'ah): a fourth</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rəviyʕayita': the fourth one"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rəviyʕayita': the fourth one</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) cheywəta': the animal"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) cheywəta': the animal</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="24" />Itu sapulu tandok dong tu,<bt>Those ten horns,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sama ke sapulu negara yang muncul datang dari itu kuasa yang satu tu.<bt>are like ten countries which appear from that one power/authority.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Jadi ada sapulu raja yang pegang parenta.<bt>So (consequently) there were/are ten rajas who hold rule/government.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ais itu ju, ada satu lai yang muncul datang.<bt>After that, there is another one who appears.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia laen dari yang laen.<bt>He is different from the others.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Nanti dia kasi jato deng kasi kala tiga raja.<bt>Later he will cause to fall and cause to lose the three rajas.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəhashpil (shpl hafʕel): he will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəhashpil (shpl hafʕel): he will bring low</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qadmaye': the former"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qadmaye': the former</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yishne' (partcpl): different"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yishne' (partcpl): different</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) malkhuwtah: kingdom, country?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) malkhuwtah: kingdom, country?</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dunya Model Baru 17:12</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="25" />Nanti dia omong malawan sang Tuhan Allah yang Paling Tinggi.<bt>Later he will speak opposing/against God Most High.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Nanti dia bekin sangsara sang Tuhan pung orang barisi dong.<bt>Later he will make difficulty for God2's clean/holy people. [EXEG: Aram yəvalle': he will wear down, wear out. NET: Aram "wear out." The word is a hapax legomenon in biblical Aramaic, but in biblical Hebrew it especially refers to wearing out such things as garments. UBS: in 1 Chr 17.9 the corresponding Hebrew word is used of oppressing people. It carries the idea of a long drawn-out persecution. TH: oppress, harass, torment.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia mau coba roba Tuhan pung Atoran<bt>He will attempt to change God2's Regulations</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">so'al kapan agama pung hari-hari bae dong,<bt>about when religious holidays are,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng kapan bekin korban persembahan dong.<bt>and when to make sacrificial offerings. [EXEG: cf. HCE, giving fuller sense of what is implied by ‘sacred seasons, times for festivals’.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Nanti dia dapa hak parenta<bt>Later he will get/obtain the right to rule/govern</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sang Tuhan pung orang barisi,<bt>(over) God2's clean/holy people,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sampe tiga taon satenga.<bt>for three and a half years. [EXEG: See discussion in TH. HCE.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) flag: half. Most translations take"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) flag: half. Most translations take this as three and a half years, but not all scholars agree.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕiddaniyn (pl): times"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕiddaniyn (pl): times</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕiddan: time"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕiddan: time</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) biydehh: to his hand, his"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) biydehh: to his hand, his power</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yityahəvuwn ('hb hitpəʕ el): be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yityahəvuwn ('hb hitpəʕ el): be given</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) dat: decree, law (of God)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) dat: decree, law (of God)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) zimniyn: set times, agreed upon"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) zimniyn: set times, agreed upon times for festivals</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hashnayah (paʕel inf): to change"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hashnayah (paʕel inf): to change</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yiSbar: he will think, plan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yiSbar: he will think, plan</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəvalle': he will wear down,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəvalle': he will wear down, wear out. NET: Aram "wear out." The word is a hapax legomenon in biblical Aramaic, but in biblical Hebrew it especially refers to wearing out such things as garments. UBS: in 1 Chr 17.9 the corresponding Hebrew word is used of oppressing people. It carries the idea of a long drawn-out persecution.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəmallil (mll paʕʕel): he will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəmallil (mll paʕʕel): he will speak</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕillaya' (q. ʕilla'ah): the Most"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕillaya' (q. ʕilla'ah): the Most High</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tsad: side, beside"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tsad: side, beside</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) umilliyn: matter"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) umilliyn: matter</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:25" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dunya Model Baru 12:14, 13:5-6</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Ma nanti itu tukang putus parkara dong mau dudu ko timbang parkara. Ais dong putus ko cabu ame itu raja pung hak parenta, ju kasi ancor buang sang dia pung kuasa sampe salamanya.<bt>But later those judges will sit to wiegh/evaluate cases/disputes/litigation. Then they will decide to withdraw that raja's right to rule/govern, and destroy his power/authority forever.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Sowfa': the end, the conclusion"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Sowfa': the end, the conclusion</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhowvadah ('bd hafʕel inf): to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhowvadah ('bd hafʕel inf): to cause to perish. Both infinitives are rendered "wipe out" in Pidgin.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhashmadah (shmd hafʕel inf): to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhashmadah (shmd hafʕel inf): to destroy</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəhaʕdown (ʕdh hafʕel): they will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəhaʕdown (ʕdh hafʕel): they will remove, take away</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shalTanehh: his sovereignty"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shalTanehh: his sovereignty</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yittiv: it will sit, the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yittiv: it will sit, the court will convene</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Ais Tuhan Allah yang Paling Tinggi sarakan hak parenta sang Dia pung orang barisi dong. Dia ju kasi Dia pung raja dong hak ko parenta raja laen dong di ini dunya. Nanti dong pegang parenta sonde putus-putus. Samua suku deng bangsa dengar-dengar sang dong, deng kasi jalan Dia pung karjá.&gt;<bt>Then God Most High handed over the right to rule/govern to His clean/holy people. He also gave His rajas the right to rule other rajas here on earth. They will hold rule/govern without interruption/ceasing. Every tribe/ethnic group and race will listen to/obey them and carry out His work.&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yishtamməʕuwn (shmʕ hitpaʕʕal): show themselves"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yishtamməʕuwn (shmʕ hitpaʕʕal): show themselves obedient</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yifləchuwn: serve"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yifləchuwn: serve</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕam: people (earlier it was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕam: people (earlier it was apparently the ones in the sky)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) malkhəwat: kingdoms"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) malkhəwat: kingdoms</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rəvuwta': greatness"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rəvuwta': greatness</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shalTana': dominion, sovereignty, right to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shalTana': dominion, sovereignty, right to rule</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) malkhuwtah: kingdom"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) malkhuwtah: kingdom</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dunya Model Baru 20:4, 22:5</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Beta pung carita sampe di sini sa. Itu hal dong bekin beta, andia Daniel, talalu taku sampe bulu badan badiri, deng beta pung muka pucat. Biar bagitu, ma beta pikir ame itu hal dong tarús.&gt;&gt;<bt>My story arrives just to here. Those matters made me, that is Daniel, very afraid to the point that my body hair stood up (=terrified), and my face became pale. Even though it was like that, nevertheless I kept thinking about/pondering those things. [TEXT: Aramaic ends here. Shifts back to Hebrew.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) End of P section"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) End of P section</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) niTret: I kept"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) niTret: I kept</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yishtannown (shnh hitpaʕʕel): it changed."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yishtannown (shnh hitpaʕʕel): it changed. UBS: the change in physical appearance that comes over a person when he is paralyzed with fear.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ziyway: my brightness, splendor, color"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ziyway: my brightness, splendor, color of my face</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəvahəlunnaniy (bhl paʕʕel): they alarmed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəvahəlunnaniy (bhl paʕʕel): they alarmed me</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) raʕyownay: my thoughts"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) raʕyownay: my thoughts</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) saggiy': much"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) saggiy': much</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) milləta': the matter"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) milləta': the matter</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Sofa': conclusion, end"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Sofa': conclusion, end</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kah: thus far"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kah: thus far</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Daniel pung mimpi so'al domba laki satu deng kambing satu<bt>Daniel's dream about a male sheep and a goat</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="8" />
      <v n="1" />Satu kali lai, Daniel tulis dia pung pangalaman bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta mau tulis beta pung mimpi satu lai. Ini jadi waktu raja Belsasar balóm pegang parenta tiga taon di Babel. Beta ada lia banya hal, tingka ke beta mimpi. Ma ini sonde sama deng itu mimpi partama yang beta su parná tulis dolu.<bt>Another time/once again, Daniel wrote his experience saying, &lt;&lt;I'm going to write (about) another dream of mine. This happened when Belsasar had not yet held rule/governed for three years in Babel. I saw many things, as if I was dreaming. But this was not the same as that first dream which I have written about previously. [TEXT: Original text shifts from Aramaic here back to Hebrew.] [DISCOURSE: high level structure and cohesion made explicit.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) təchillah: at the beginning, first"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) təchillah: at the beginning, first</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nir'ah (r'h nif): it was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nir'ah (r'h nif): it was seen</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chazown: BDB vision, oracle, prophecy"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chazown: BDB vision, oracle, prophecy (divine communication)</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Dalam mimpi kadua ni, beta lia beta pung diri di benteng di kota Susa di propinsi Elam. Beta ada badiri di kali Ulai pung pinggir.<bt>In this second dream, I saw myself in the fort in the city of Susa in the Elam province. I was standing at the side/bank of the Ulai river. [NOTE to daughter translations: check how you handled “fortress in Susa” in Esther 2:3,5,8.] [EXEG: Heb. 'uwval: canal. The Ulai was an artificial ditch that connected the two rivers that went by Susa. NRSV, TB, NLT, CEV all say ‘river’. Several have notes that this word can also mean ‘gate’. See discussion in TH. Our protocols say we follow the TB here, since it has plenty of support.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'uwval: canal. The Ulai was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'uwval: canal. The Ulai was an artificial ditch that connected the two rivers that went by Susa.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mədiynah: district, province"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mədiynah: district, province</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) biyrah: citadel, fort, fortified part"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) biyrah: citadel, fort, fortified part of the town</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Ju beta lia ada satu domba laki badiri di kali pung pinggir. Dia ada pung dua tandok yang panjang, ma satu lebe panjang. Padahal yang lebe panjang tu, muncul datang di balakang hari.<bt>And/then I saw a male sheep (=ram) standing at the side/bank of the river. He/it had two long horns, but one was longer. In fact the longer one appeared later on/afterwards/at the back. [EXEG: looked up and saw = Hebraism indicating one action. See TH.] [NOTE: balakang hari so they don't think the horn came out of the sheep's back.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) gəvohowt (pl): long"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) gəvohowt (pl): long</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'uval: canal"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'uval: canal</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) da mo short one start"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) da mo short one start fo grow firs.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Ais beta lia itu domba pake dia pung tandok dong ko pi tabrak ame samua barang di sablá barat. Ais itu, dia bekin ulang pi sablá utara. Abis, baru dia bekin ulang pi sablá salatan. Sonde ada yang bisa malawan sang dia. Sonde ada yang bisa kasi salamat dia pung korban dong, te itu domba talalu kuat na! Dia bekin ancor iko dia pung mau. Tarús dia jadi batamba-batamba.<bt>Then I saw that sheep use his horns to go butt/batter everything to the western side. After that, he did it again on te northern side. Then, he did it again on the southern side. Nobody could (successfully) oppose him. There was nobody who was able to rescue/save his victims, cuz (elaboration) that sheep was too strong [+emphatic]! He destroyed as he liked. Then he kept increasing. [EXEG: Heb. ‘increased’ NRSV, ‘became strong, NLT ‘became great’. Sources vague as to in what sense it ‘increased’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) higdiyl (gdl hif): TWOT: physical"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) higdiyl (gdl hif): TWOT: physical growth of people and other living things as well as for the increase of things tangible and intangible whether objects, sounds, feelings or authority.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rətsonow: his pleasure"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rətsonow: his pleasure</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yadow: his hand, his power"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yadow: his hand, his power</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mattsiyl (ntsl hif partcpl): one"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mattsiyl (ntsl hif partcpl): one who delivered</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mənaggeach (ngch piʕel partcpl): pushing,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mənaggeach (ngch piʕel partcpl): pushing, thrusting; butting; charging</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ais waktu beta masi lia-lia, ju ada kambing laki satu muncul datang dari sablá barat. Ma dia cuma ada satu tandok di dia pung mata pung teng-tenga. Deng itu tandok tu, talalu kantara. Ju itu kambing lari datang dari dunya pung sablá, ma dia pung kaki sonde sonto ame di tana.<bt>Then while I was still looking, there was a male goat who appeared coming from the west. But he only had one horn between his eyes. And that horn was very visible/prominent. Then that goat ran coming from the other side of the earth, but his feet did not (actually) touch the ground. [DISCOURSE: reordered for background-foreground.] [EXEG: Heb. chazuwt: conspicuous. HCE, TH.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chazuwt: conspicuous"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chazuwt: conspicuous</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nogeaʕ (partcpl): [not] touching"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nogeaʕ (partcpl): [not] touching</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) maʕərav: west"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) maʕərav: west</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) haʕizziym: the goats, the herd"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) haʕizziym: the goats, the herd</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tsəfiyr: male goat. TWOT: Sometimes"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tsəfiyr: male goat. TWOT: Sometimes fierce, it is a symbol of power especially in domineering sheep (cf. Ezk 34:17; Zech 10:3).</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) meviyn (byn hif partcpl): while"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) meviyn (byn hif partcpl): while understanding, trying to understand</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Ais itu kambing lari datang mara-mara ko mau batabrak deng itu domba yang ada pung dua tandok, yang ada badiri di kali pung pinggir tu.<bt>Then that goat ran coming angrily wanting to/going to butt/crash the sheep that had two horns, who was standing at the side/bank of the river.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kochow: its strength"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kochow: its strength</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəmat: anger, rage"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəmat: anger, rage</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vayyarats: he ran to him"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vayyarats: he ran to him</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Ju itu kambing datang pi itu domba. Waktu dia lari, dia pung mara batamba-tamba tarús. Ais dia tabrak kuat-kuat itu domba, ju bekin pata itu domba pung tandok dua-dua. Itu domba sonde ontong sang dia. Ais itu kambing banting ame itu domba pi tana, ju inja-inja sang dia. Sonde ada yang bisa kasi salamat itu domba dari kambing pung kuasa.<bt>And that goat came to/toward that sheep. As he ran, his anger kept increasing. Then he strongly/forcefully crashed/butted into that sheep, and broke off both of the sheep's horns. That sheep could not withstand him. Then that goat threw that sheep down on the ground, and stomped all over him. There was nobody who could rescue/save that sheep from the goat's power/authority/ strength.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vayyirməSehuw: he trampled him"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vayyirməSehuw: he trampled him</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vayyashliykhehuw (shlk hif): he threw"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vayyashliykhehuw (shlk hif): he threw him down</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vayyakh (nkh hif): he struck"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vayyakh (nkh hif): he struck</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vayyitmarmar (mrr hitpalpel): he embittered"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vayyitmarmar (mrr hitpalpel): he embittered himself, worked himself into a rage</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'etsel: beside, up to, near"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'etsel: beside, up to, near</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) maggiyaʕ (ngʕ hif partcpl): reaching"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) maggiyaʕ (ngʕ hif partcpl): reaching</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Ais ju itu kambing batamba kuat deng batamba hebat. Waktu dia su paling kuat, ju ada yang kasi pata dia pung tandok yang hebat tu. Ma di itu tandok pung tampa tu, ada ampa tandok baru yang muncul datang. Itu ampa tandok dong kasi tunju ampa mata angin di langit.<bt>Then that goat increased in strength and increased in greatness. When he was already most strong (=at the peak of his strength), there was someone/thing that broke off that amazing horn of his. But in the place of that horn, there were four new horns which appeared. Those four horns showed/pointed to the four points of wind in the sky.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chazuwt: conspicuous"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chazuwt: conspicuous</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕatsmow: his mightiest"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕatsmow: his mightiest</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ma dari satu tandok batumbu satu tandok lai yang kici. Itu tandok kici tu pung kuasa batamba tarús, sampe itu kuasa sampe di sablá salatan, sablá timur, deng sampe di itu tana yang paling bagus tu, andia tana Isra'el.<bt>But from one horn grew another small horn. That small horn's power/authority grew/increased continually. to the point that it's power/authority reached the south side, the east side, and reached that most beautiful land, that is the land of Isra'el. [EXEG: Heb. tseviy: beautiful. TWOT: The best in regards to splendor and honor is referred to as beautiful or glorious: the promised land (Ezk 20:6, 15; Dan 11:16, 41). UBS: the Beautiful Place is Israel. NLT, TH, IVP.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tseviy: beautiful. TWOT: The best"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tseviy: beautiful. TWOT: The best in regards to splendor and honor is referred to as beautiful or glorious: the promised land (Ezk 20:6, 15; Dan 11:16, 41). UBS: da Beautiful Place is Israel.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mizrach"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mizrach</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yeter: excellency"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yeter: excellency</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tsəʕiyrah: small, insignificant"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tsəʕiyrah: small, insignificant</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Itu tandok baru tu, batumbu tinggi sampe di langit. Ju dia bakalai deng tantara di langit, sampe lempar kasi tabanting tantara saparu deng bintang saparu pi bumi. Ju dia inja-inja sang dong.<bt>That new horn grew high/tall to the sky. And it fought with the army in the sky, to the point that it threw down some of the soldiers/army and some stars to the earth. Then it trampled on them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vattappel (npl hif): it caused"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vattappel (npl hif): it caused to fall</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tsəva': host"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tsəva': host</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dunya Model Baru 12:4</note><v n="11" />Itu tandok pung kuasa batamba tarús sampe dia barani malawan sang panglima di langit. Di Tuhan Allah pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat yang barisi, itu tandok kasi barenti korban bakar yang orang dong bawa tiap-tiap hari, ju bongkar bekin rusak di situ.<bt>That horn's power/authority kept increasing to the point that it was bold/had courage/dared to oppose the commander in the sky. In God's holy/clean Temple (lit: Central House of Worship/Prayer, that horn stopped the burnt offerings/sacrifices which people brought every (single) day, and tore the place apart. [EXEG: Q: Is last clause about physical destruction or spiritual/ ritual defilement? A: Aram: hushlakh (hof): it was thrown down. TWOT associates this root with ‘throw (to the ground), cast, hurl, felling of a tree’. NLT1: destroying his Temple. NRSV: overthrew the place of his sanctuary (attempting to be literal, but result is vague). HCE: He bus up da Temple. TB: dirobohkannya (demolished, made to become rubble, made into debris). TH uses disappointing principles of exegesis to argue backwards from what happened later at the purported fulfillment of the prophecy that it should be ‘profaned’ here, rather than from the meaning of the text. Note that the current state is debris, except for the western wall, but that is secondary to interpeting the text.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) miqdashow: his sanctuary, holy place"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) miqdashow: his sanctuary, holy place</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məkhown: the established place"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məkhown: the established place</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hushlakh (hof): it was thrown"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hushlakh (hof): it was thrown down</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tamiyd: continual. TWOT: The word"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tamiyd: continual. TWOT: The word is used alone to designate the daily burnt offering in Dan 8:11-13; 11:31; 12:11.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) heriym hif (q. huram hof):"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) heriym hif (q. huram hof): was abolished</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) sar: prince, leader. Probably refers"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) sar: prince, leader. Probably refers to God</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Itu tandok pung tantara dong bekin jahat macam-macam, ju suru kapala agama dong ko barenti bekin korban bakar yang dong su biasa bekin. Ais dong larang karás samua agama yang batúl. Samua-samua yang itu tandok mau bekin iko dia pung suka, na, jadi.<bt>The army/soldiers of that horn did all sorts of evil, and ordered the *priests (lit: heads of religion) to stop making the burnt offerings/sacrifices which they normally made. Then they strongly forbade all true/correct religion. Everything which that horn wanted to do according to its desires, na, happened/came into being. [EXEG: NRSV, NLT, TH all acknowledge that the Heb. is unclear here. We follow HCE on some points.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hitsliychah (hif): it prospered, succeeded"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hitsliychah (hif): it prospered, succeeded</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕastah: it produced, brought about"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕastah: it produced, brought about</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əmet: truth, faithfulness, loyalty"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əmet: truth, faithfulness, loyalty</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tashlekh (shlk hif jussive): so"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tashlekh (shlk hif jussive): so it would be thrown down</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) pashaʕ: transgression"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) pashaʕ: transgression</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tinnaten (ntn nif): had inflicted"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tinnaten (ntn nif): had inflicted on it, had given to it; BDB be given, be bestowed, be provided, be entrusted to, be granted to, be permitted, be issued, be published, be uttered, be assigned; be set, be put, be made, be inflicted</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tsava': host. KD point out"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tsava': host. KD point out that this use is without an article, so can refer to any 'host,' not necessarily the host of heaven.</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:12" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Ibrani asli di ini ayat sonde jalás.<bt>The original Ibrani language writing in this verse is not clear.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ais itu ju, beta dengar Tuhan pung ana bua dua dari sorga ada batanya satu deng satu. Satu tanya bilang, &lt;Botong musti tunggu barapa lama, baru ini mimpi pung isi ni, bisa jadi? Sampe kapan dong mau barenti bekin itu korban bakar yang jalan tiap hari dong? Sampe kapan orang dong mau malawan sang Tuhan? Dong mau bekin rusak itu Ruma Sambayang Pusat yang barisi sampe barapa lama? Sampe kapan tantara di sorga dong kaná inja-inja?&gt;<bt>After that, I heard two of God2's underlings (*angels) from heaven questioning each other. One asked saying, &lt;How long must we-exc wait, before the contents of this dream can happen? Until what point/when are they going to stop the offerings/sacrifices which go on every day? Until what point/when are people going to oppose God2? They are going to destroy the clean/holy Central Worship House for how long? Until what point/when will the soldiers in heaven get stomped on?&gt; [EXEG: TH “How long is the vision…? The wording of the question in RSV is misleading. The real question is not how long the actual vision will last but relates rather to the duration of the terrible events seen in the vision.”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mirmaS: trampling (in this context,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mirmaS: trampling (in this context, probably the pagan army that comes in and tramples everything: army of trampling)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qodesh: holy one, holy place"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qodesh: holy one, holy place</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tet (ntn inf): giving"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tet (ntn inf): giving</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shomem (adj): BDB be desolated,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shomem (adj): BDB be desolated, be deflowered, be deserted, be appalled; be appalled, be awestruck</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) lappalmowniy: to a certain one"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) lappalmowniy: to a certain one</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shomem (partcpl): NIV says &quot;rebellion"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shomem (partcpl): NIV says "rebellion of desolation". Mt. 24.15 "Dat ting so bad, goin mess up eryting, an make erybody jus bag."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ju ana bua yang satu lai manyao bilang, &lt;Dia pung biasa, kapala agama dong bekin korban tiap kali matahari nae deng matahari tanggalám. Nanti dong kasi barenti itu korban dong sampe 2.300 kali, andia salama 1.150 hari. Ais baru orang dong bisa bekin itu Ruma Sambayang Pusat barisi kambali sang Tuhan Allah.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>Then the other underling/angel responded saying, &lt;The norm is for the priests to make the offerings/sacrifices each time the sun rises and the sun sinks. Later they will stop those offerings/sacrifices for 2,300 times, that is for 1,150 days. Only then will people be able to make the Central House of Worship clean/holy again for God.&gt;&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: restructured for background-foreground.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nitsdaq (nif): it will be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nitsdaq (nif): it will be made right</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Gabriel buka ame itu mimpi pung arti<bt>Gabriel reveals the meaning of that dream</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ais Daniel sambung dia pung carita so'al dia pung mimpi bilang, &lt;&lt;Waktu beta, andia Daniel, ada coba-coba ko mau mangarti samua-samua yang beta su lia dalam itu mimpi, ju ada yang badiri di beta pung muka. Beta sangka dia tu, manusia.<bt>Then Daniel continued his story about his dream saying, &lt;&lt;While I, that is Daniel, was trying to understand everything that I had seen in that dream, then there was someone/thing standing in front of me. I thought/assumed that he was human. [DISCOURSE: quote formula added to make the higher level structure more explicit.]</bt><v n="16" />Tarús beta dengar manusia pung suara ada pange-pange dari kali Ulai pung pinggir bilang, &lt;Gabriel, tolong tarángkan kasi tau itu mimpi pung arti, ko biar ini orang bisa mangarti bae-bae.&gt;<bt>Then3 I heard a human voice calling from the side/bank of the Ulai river saying, &lt;Gabriel, please explain the meaning of that dream, so that this person can understand well.&gt; [EXEG: from the canal? NRSV by the Ulai, CEV from beside the Ulai. See discussion in TH.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mar' eh: what he sees,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mar' eh: what he sees, the appearance</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhallaz: this one"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhallaz: this one</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) haven (byn hif imperv): explain"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) haven (byn hif imperv): explain</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ben: between, in the middle"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ben: between, in the middle</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 1:19, 26</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ais Gabriel datang deka-deka deng itu tampa yang beta badiri tu. Ju beta rasa taku deng jato di tana di dia pung muka. Ma dia omong bae-bae sang beta bilang, &lt;Lu ni, manusia. Lu musti mangarti bilang, ini hal dong yang lu su lia dalam itu mimpi tu, nanti jadi waktu hari kiamat.&gt;<bt>Then Gabriel came close to the place where I was standing. And I felt afraid and fell to the ground in front of him. But he spoke nicely/kindly/gently to me saying, &lt;You are human. You must understand that these things that you have seen in that dream will happen at the end of the world/last days.&gt; [NOTE: Q: Ask UNS why they think Gabriel said ‘You are human’? It certainly was not new information. A: The Heb here ben-adam ‘son of humans’ is quite different from the Aramaic messianic title in 7:13 kebar ʔenas, even though TH equates the two, but points out this one is addressing Daniel. In eastern Indonesian lgs and cultures, people are constantly bringing up the litany excuse for themselves and others that they are /cuma manusia sa/ ‘merely human’  Depending on context, this may focus on mortality (NRSV, TH), sinful nature, frailness, lesser being in comparison to God's sovereignty (CEV). Through Kupang worldview, this sounds like mortality, frail, and not equal with God's sovereign power in relation to what is to happen.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nivʕatiy (bʕt nif): I was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nivʕatiy (bʕt nif): I was terrified</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Waktu dia masi ba'omong deng beta, na, beta tingka ke samaput deng jato matono, sama ke sonde sadar. Ma dia sonto ame deng kasi bangun sang beta, ju kasi beta badiri.<bt>While he was still speaking to me, na, it was as if I fainted/collapsed and fell face down, as if unconscious. But he touched (me) and raised me up, and stood me up.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vayyiggaʕ"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vayyiggaʕ</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nirdamtiy (nif): I was unconscious,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nirdamtiy (nif): I was unconscious, in a deep sleep, sleeping</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ais dia omong bilang, &lt;Beta mau kasi tau sang lu apa yang nanti jadi, ko biar lu mangarti. Tuhan Allah su tau dia pung waktu ko dunya kiamat. Ma di itu jaman, Dia mara batúl, te Dia sonde mau tarima manusia pung jahat.<bt>Then he spoke saying, &lt;I am going to tell you what will happen, so that you understand. God already knows the time for the end of the world/last days. But in that era/age, He is/will be truly angry, cuz (elaboration) He does not want to accepts the evil of humans.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mowʕed: appointed time"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mowʕed: appointed time</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) zaʕam: anger, indignation. TWOT: experiencing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) zaʕam: anger, indignation. TWOT: experiencing or expressing intense anger... It is regularly translated "indignation," referring more often to God than to man.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'achəriyt: latter time of, prophetic"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'achəriyt: latter time of, prophetic time of</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Itu domba laki yang ada pung dua tandok yang lu lia tu, andia raja tana Media deng raja tana Persia dong.<bt>That male sheep which has two horns that you saw, that is the raja(s) of the land of Media and the raja(s) of the land of Persia.</bt><v n="21" />Itu kambing laki yang babulu tu, andia raja tana Yunani. Itu tandok yang bésar tu, andia dong pung raja partama.<bt>The furry male goat, that is the raja(s) of the land of Yunani (=Greece). That large horn, that is their first raja.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yavan: Greece"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yavan: Greece</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) saʕiyr: he-goat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) saʕiyr: he-goat</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Itu ampa tandok yang muncul datang waktu itu tandok partama pata tu, andia ampa raja yang ganti itu raja partama. Ma sonde ada raja dari dong yang sama hebat deng itu raja partama tu.<bt>Those four horns which appear when the first horn breaks off, that is four rajas who replace the first raja. But none of them have the same greatness/impressiveness as that first raja.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yaʕəmodnah"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yaʕəmodnah</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) malkhuyowt: kingdoms"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) malkhuyowt: kingdoms</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tachteyha: in its place; BDB"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tachteyha: in its place; BDB in place of, instead of (in transferred sense)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vattaʕəmodnah: it came on the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vattaʕəmodnah: it came on the scene, took its place</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nishberet (nif partcpl fem): the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nishberet (nif partcpl fem): the one broken off</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Waktu itu ampa raja dong pung parenta su mau deka abis, ju dong pung jahat deng sala dong su mau kalewat batas, na, ada satu raja baru muncul datang. Dia tu, karás mati pung, deng talalu pintar putar-balek.<bt>When the rule of those four rajas is nearing an end/about to finish, and their evil and wrong/sins/offences is about to pass over the limit, na, there is a new raja who appears. He is extremely hard/harsh/severe, and very skilled at deception.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hiydowt: double dealing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hiydowt: double dealing</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) meviyn (hif partcpl): discerning, understanding"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) meviyn (hif partcpl): discerning, understanding</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕaz: strong, might, fierce"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕaz: strong, might, fierce</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kəhatem (tmm hif inf): BDB"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kəhatem (tmm hif inf): BDB v. finish, complete, perfect; finish, cease doing, leave off doing</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Dia batamba kuat tarús, ma bukan tagal dari dia pung kuasa sandiri. Nanti dia bekin rusak bam-banya, sampe orang dong taheran-heran. Dia mau bekin karmana iko dia pung mau, na, jadi. Dia kasi ancor buang pamimpin yang kuat dong, ju bekin rusak buang Tuhan pung orang barisi dong.<bt>He is increasingly strong, but not because of his own power/authority. He will destroy many things, to the point that people are amazed/surprised. He does whatever according to his liking, na, it happens/succeeds. He destroys strong leaders, and ruins God2's clean/holy people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕətsuwmiym: mighty people"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕətsuwmiym: mighty people</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hishchiyt (hif): he will destroy"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hishchiyt (hif): he will destroy</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vəʕ asah: what he does"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vəʕ asah: what he does</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hitsliach: he will succeed, prosper"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hitsliach: he will succeed, prosper</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yashchiyt: he will spoil, ruin,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yashchiyt: he will spoil, ruin, destroy</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nifla'owt (nif partcpl pl): marvelous"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nifla'owt (nif partcpl pl): marvelous things</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kochow: his strength"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kochow: his strength</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕatsam: it will be mighty"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕatsam: it will be mighty</Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Dia tipu ame orang dong, sampe dia jadi sombong. Waktu orang dong kira samua aman, na, takuju sa, dia kasi ancor buang dong bam-banya. Dia baparáng malawan sang Tuhan, andia Raja di atas samua raja. Biar bagitu, ma nanti ada yang kasi ancor sang dia, ma sonde pake manusia pung kuasa.<bt>He deceives2 people, with result that he becomes arrogant. When  people think that everything is safe/stable/free from threat, na, suddenly/without warning he destroys many of them. He wars against God2, that is the King of all kings. Even that being the case, nevertheless there is (someone/ thing) who destroys him, but he does not use human power/authority. [EXEG: Heb. yisshaver (nif): he will be broken, crushed (passive as in NRSV, NLT1, TB, HCE). TH: He shall be broken: in those languages where it is necessary to transform the passive formulation to an active one, it is not recommended that the agent be named. It will probably be better to say something like "he will fall" or "he will suffer punishment." If required, a more radical restructuring may name the agent: "God will break (or destroy) him without the help of any human being." I think CEV (active voice) approach “But God will crush him!” is going beyond the text and context here. The immediate context identifies God/Messiah as the target, and the grammar suggests the possibility of indirect causation here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yisshaver (nif): he will be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yisshaver (nif): he will be broken, crushed</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'efeS: in the end"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'efeS: in the end</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yashchiyt (hif): he will destroy"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yashchiyt (hif): he will destroy</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shalwah: at ease, in prosperity"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shalwah: at ease, in prosperity</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) bəyadow: by his power"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) bəyadow: by his power</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mirmah: deceit, scamming. TWOT: describing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mirmah: deceit, scamming. TWOT: describing the swindle perpetrated on Esau by Jacob. It is used particularly of treacherous or deceitful speech (Gen 34:13; Ps 10:7; 17:1; 24:4 et al.). mirma= is also used of false weighted scales which are said to be "falsifying the scales with deceit" (Amos 8:5).</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hitsliyach (hif): he will cause"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hitsliyach (hif): he will cause to prosper</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) sikhlow: his cunning, craftiness"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) sikhlow: his cunning, craftiness</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Parcaya sang beta! Te apa yang beta lia deng omong tu, batúl, so'al kasi barenti korban sampe 2.300 kali tiap matahari nae deng matahari tanggalám. Pasti jadi bagitu! Ma dia pung waktu masi jao-jao, jadi kalo su tulis ini mimpi, na, tutu ame sang dia pake segel, ko biar orang dong sonde usa tau memang.&gt;<bt>Believe me! Cuz (elaboration) what I see and say is true, about stopping the offerings/sacrifices for 2,300 times each sunrise and sun sinking. It will surely happen like that! But the time is still very far, so (consequently) if/when you have written this dream, na, close it off using a seals, so that people don't need to know beforehand.&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Sətom: shut, close, seal up"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Sətom: shut, close, seal up</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'attah: you (fronted)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'attah: you (fronted)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Waktu beta, andia Daniel, ada lia ini hal dong samua, na, beta pung kuat ilang buang, ju beta saki-saki sampe barapa hari. Abis, beta bangun, ju kasi jalan raja pung tugas. Ma beta pung hati rasa tar enak, ko beta jadi pikiran tagal itu mimpi. Te beta sonde mangarti batúl.&gt;&gt;<bt>When I, that is Daniel, was seeing all these things, na, my strength completely disappeared, and I was sickly for several days. After that, I got up, and carried out the raja's work. But my liver felt upset/unsettled/disturbed, so I worried about that dream. Cuz (elaboration) I did not truly understand (it).&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'eshtowmem (shmm hitpolel): I was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'eshtowmem (shmm hitpolel): I was appalled, astounded</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nechəleytiy (chlh nif): BDB make"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nechəleytiy (chlh nif): BDB make oneself sick; be made sick; be tired</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nihyeytiy (hyh nif): it happened"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nihyeytiy (hyh nif): it happened to me; I was done, overcome</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Daniel sambayang kasi sang dia pung orang Isra'el sandiri<bt>Daniel prays for his own people of Isra'el</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="9" />
      <v n="1-2" />Ais satu kali, Daniel tulis bagini: &lt;&lt;Ada satu raja, nama Darius. Dia tu, raja Ahasuweros pung ana, yang lahir jadi orang Media. Ma lama-lama dia pegang parenta di orang Babel dong ju.<bt>Then one time Daniel wrote like this: &lt;&lt;There was a raja named Darius. He was the offspring/child of Ahasuweros, who was born as a Media person. But eventually he held rule/government over the Babel people as well.</bt><note reference="9:1-2" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Orang Babel dong, sama deng orang Kasdim.<bt>The Babel people are the same as the Kasdim people. [EXEG: NLT, TH]</bt></note>Waktu Darius balóm pegang parenta satu taon, ju beta ada baca taliti TUHAN Allah pung kata-kata yang Dia kasi tau sang Dia pung jubir Yeremia. Deng bagitu, beta dapa tau bilang, kota Yerusalem pung rusak tu, musti jalan sampe 70 taon.<bt>When Darius had not yet ruled/governed for one year, I was reading carefully the LORD God's words that He told His spokesperson (*prophet) Yeremia. In that way I came to know that the destruction of the city of Yeruslaem, had to go/last until 70 years. [DISCOURSE: verses bridged and repackaged to get background, foreground, and chronology right for RL patterns.] [EXEG: “word of the LORD” = “what God had revealed to Jeremiah”, not the Scriptures in general. See TH,]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) miSpar: number"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) miSpar: number</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Səfariym: books. UBS: the term"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Səfariym: books. UBS: the term is used here in the technical sense of the holy books known to Daniel—including the book of the prophet Jeremiah. For this reason it is legitimate to translate "the Scriptures" (AT, REB, NAB, and NIV).</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) biynotiy: I understood, considered, perceived."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) biynotiy: I understood, considered, perceived. UBS: it is probably better to take the verb in the sense of "was studying" (TEV, NJB) or "carefully considering."</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hamlakh (hofʕal): was made king"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hamlakh (hofʕal): was made king</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) zeraʕ: seed, offspring, progeny"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) zeraʕ: seed, offspring, progeny</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əchashwerowsh: Ahasuerus (better known in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əchashwerowsh: Ahasuerus (better known in history as Xerxes)</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:1-2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeremia 25:11-12, 29:10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3-4" />Waktu beta dapa tau bagitu, ju beta rasa susa. Andia ko beta mau minta tolong sang TUHAN Allah, yang hak parenta sang beta. Jadi beta buka beta pung pakean biasa deng ganti pake karong goni. Beta ju dudu di abu ra'o deng taro abu ra'o di beta pung kapala. Beta bekin bagitu ko kasi tunju beta pung hati susa. Ais ju beta puasa, ko sambayang minta tolong sang Tuhan bilang,<bt>When I came to know that, I felt troubled. That is why I asked for help from the LORD God, who has the right to order/command me. So (consequently) I took off my normal clothes and put on a gunny sack [NOTE: rough hemp fibre, used for rice and corn. Term used elsewhere.] I sat in the ashes and put ashes on my head. I did that to indicate me troubled liver. And I also fasted, to pray asking God2 for help saying, [EXEG: In Heb. vs. 2 uses YHWH, vs. 3 Adonai Elohim, vs. 4 YHWH Elohay. Since we bridge and conflate 3-4 that is why it misleadingly appears that we missed this distinction. We're good.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tachənuwniym: supplications, requests"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tachənuwniym: supplications, requests</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) təfillah: [in] prayer"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) təfillah: [in] prayer</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) va'ettənah (ntn): I gave my"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) va'ettənah (ntn): I gave my face, I concentrated my attention.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">&lt;Aduuu, Tuhan, é! Tuhan yang ada pung kuasa! Deng Tuhan yang talalu hebat sampe orang jadi taku! Kalo Tuhan su janji satu hal, pasti Tuhan bekin iko. Tuhan ju suka kasi tunju sayang sang orang yang sayang sang Tuhan deng yang bekin iko Tuhan pung parenta dong.<bt>&lt;Aduuu [+regret, grief], God2, é! God2 (=you) are the one who has power/authority! And God2 (=you) are so amazing/impressive to the point that people become afraid! If/when God2 (=you)  promise something, surely God2 (=you) do accordingly. God2 (=you) also like to show love/pity to people who love God2 (=you) and who do according to your commands. [EXEG: Heb. nowra' (yr' nif partcpl): the one who is to be feared. BDB be fearful, be dreadful, be feared; cause astonishment and awe, be held in awe; inspire reverence or godly fear or awe. NLT, NRSV ‘awesome’, CEV ‘fearsome’, HCE ‘scary’, TB dahsyat ‘imposing, terrifying, dreadful, awe-inspiring’]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nowra' (yr' nif partcpl): the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nowra' (yr' nif partcpl): the one who is to be feared. BDB be fearful, be dreadful, be feared; cause astonishment and awe, be held in awe; inspire reverence or godly fear or awe</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'anna' (exclamation): ah now! I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'anna' (exclamation): ah now! I beseech you!</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) va'etwaddah (ydh hitp): acknowledge; confess."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) va'etwaddah (ydh hitp): acknowledge; confess. TWOT: The Hithpael form is normally employed when this verb is used to convey the confession of national sins. This stem was also employed when the great confessions of Israel's sins were made by Daniel (Dan 9:4, 20), Ezra (Ezr 10:1), Nehemiah (Neh 1:6), and the people of Israel (Neh 9:2-3) during and after the Babylonian captivity.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'etpaləlah (hitp): when I prayed,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'etpaləlah (hitp): when I prayed, interceded</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ma botong sonde sama deng Tuhan. Te botong bekin sala macam-macam. Botong bekin hal jahat. Botong malawan sang Tuhan. Botong su serong dari Tuhan pung parenta deng atoran dong.<bt>But we-exc are not the same as God2 (=you). Cuz (elaboration) we-exc do various sorts of wrongs. We do evil things. We oppose God2 (=you). We have strayed away from God2's (=your) commands and regulations.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Sowr (inf): turn aside, depart"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Sowr (inf): turn aside, depart from, avoid</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) maradnuw: BDB we have rebelled,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) maradnuw: BDB we have rebelled, revolted; against human king, against God, against light (poetic). UBS: It has to do with something that is abnormal, disjointed, or outside the realm of accepted behavior. In some cases it may have to be translated "done what we should not have done."</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vəhirshaʕnuw (q. hirshaʕnuw): we have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vəhirshaʕnuw (q. hirshaʕnuw): we have acted wickedly. TWOT: act wickedly (in ethics and religion)</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Padahal Tuhan su utus orang ko jadi Tuhan pung jubir. Ais dong datang ba'omong bawa Tuhan pung nama. Dong kasi tau Tuhan pung pasán bagitu sang raja dong, sang raja pung ana-ana dong, sang botong pung nene-moyang dong, deng kasi samua orang di Isra'el. Ma botong sonde mau dengar deng sonde mau bekin iko apa yang dong su omong tu.<bt>Whereas in fact God2 (=you) have sent/commissioned people to be God2's (=your) spokesperson(s) (*prophet). And/then they came speaking in God2's (=your) name/reputation (lit: bringing/bearing your name). They told/explained God2's (=your) message(s) in that way to the rajas, to the children of the rajas, to our-exc ancestors, and to everyone in Isra'el. But we-exc did not want to listen and did not want to do according to what they had said.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) simkha: in your name, with"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) simkha: in your name, with understanding of your character</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Jadi, Bos yang batúl. Deng botong yang bekin sala bagitu, yang malu. Tuhan su buka kasi talanjang botong pung jahat, deng botong sonde bisa angka muka lai. Biar botong jao ko, biar botong deka ko, botong samua su serong dari Tuhan pung parenta. Andia botong dari tana Yahuda, dari kota Yerusalem, dari tana Isra'el anteru, kaná buang sampe jao-jao di orang laen dong pung negrí, botong samua su langgar Tuhan pung parenta deng su tola buang Tuhan pung sayang sang botong.<bt>So (consequently), Bos (=you) are the one who is right/correct. And we-exc the ones who have done wrong like that, are the ones who are ashamed/embarrassed. God2 (=you) have exposed naked our evil, and we are not able to lift our faces again/anymore. Whether we are far away, or whether we are near, we have all strayed from God2's (=your) commands. That is, those of us from the land of Yahuda, from the city of Yerusalem, from throughout the land of Isra'el, are thrown out/exiled until far away in other people's countries, we have all violated/transgressed God2's (=your) commands and have rejected God2's (=your) love for us. [EXEG: Heb. hiddachtam (dchh hif): BDB thrust out, banish. NIV: in all the countries where you have scattered us; CEV: you dragged away to foreign lands; NLT1: scattered near and far, wherever you have driven us because of our disloyalty to you.]  [EXEG: Heb. maʕəlam: their treachery. Also NRSV. NLT ‘disloyalty’. CEV ‘unfaithful’. HCE ‘broke yoa rules an no stay tight wit you’. See also TH.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) maʕəlam: their treachery. TWOT: the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) maʕəlam: their treachery. TWOT: the breaking or violation of religious law as a conscious act of treachery. The victim against whom the breach is perpetrated is God.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hiddachtam (dchh hif): BDB thrust"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hiddachtam (dchh hif): BDB thrust out, banish</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) boshet happaniym: shame of our"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) boshet happaniym: shame of our faces; covered with shame, open shame, loss of face</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Andia ko sakarang botong malu, deng sonde bisa angka muka. Botong samua kaná, andia: botong, botong pung raja, botong pung pagawe dong, deng botong pung nene-moyang, tagal botong su bekin sala deng langgar TUHAN pung parenta dong.<bt>That is why now we are ashamed/embarrassed, and unable to lift our faces. We are all hit/affected/(guilty), that is: we, our rajas, our high officials, and our ancestors, because we have done wrong and have violated/transgressed the LORD's commands.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Biar botong su malawan sang Tuhan deng bekin sala bagitu, ma cuma Tuhan sa yang bisa kasi tunju rasa kasian deng lupa buang botong pung sala dong.<bt>Even though we have opposed God2 (=you) and done wrong like that, nevertheless only God2 (=you) alone is the one who is able to show love/pity/mercy and (completely) forget our wrongs.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Səlichowt: acts of forgiveness"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Səlichowt: acts of forgiveness</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) harachəmiym: acts of compassion"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) harachəmiym: acts of compassion</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Botong yang sonde mau dengar, deng sonde mau bekin iko TUHAN Allah pung parenta dong. Botong yang sonde mau idop iko Tuhan pung jalan lurus. Padahal Tuhan su kirim datang Tuhan pung jubir dong, ko biar dong bisa kasi tau Tuhan pung mau-mau sang botong.<bt>We are the ones who did not want to listen, and did not want to do according to the LORD God's commands. We are the ones who did not want to live according to God2's (=your) straight path/way. Whereas in fact God2 (=you) have sent your spokespeople/prophets here, so that they could tell us God2's (=your) will/desires.</bt><v n="11" />Yang batúl, andia samua orang Isra'el su langgar Tuhan pung parenta dong. Samua su serong dari Tuhan pung jalan idop yang lurus. Samua sonde mau dengar deng bekin iko Tuhan pung pasán dong.<bt>In truth/fact, all the people of Isra'el have violated/transgressed God2's (=your) commands. All have strayed from God2's (=your) life way/path that is straight/true/correct. All have not wanted to listen and do according to God2's (=your) message/instructions.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Andia ko sakarang, samua hukuman barát yang ba'i Musa parná tulis so'al orang yang sonde mau dengar-dengar sang Tuhan su jato kaná di botong. Padahal dia tu, Tuhan pung orang suru-suru ju. Itu hukuman dong jato kaná di botong tagal botong pung sala-sala dong.<bt>That is why now, every heavy/severe punishment that forefather Musa has ever written about people who do not want to listen to/obey/submit to God2 (=you) have fallen on us-exc. Whereas in fact he was also God2's (=your) servant. Those punishments have fallen upon us because of our (various) wrongs.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hasshəvuʕah"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hasshəvuʕah</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'alah: curse. TWOT: used to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'alah: curse. TWOT: used to express the very solemn covenant between God and his people (Deut 29:12 [H 11]) and more particularly, the warnings of judgment attached to that covenant should the people prove to be faithless (Deut 29:14-21 [H 13-20]). It is used in this latter sense also in Isa 24:6; Jer 23:10; 29:18; 42:18; 44:12 and Dan 9:11.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vattittakh (ntk): you have poured"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vattittakh (ntk): you have poured out</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shmowaʕ (inf): obeying"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shmowaʕ (inf): obeying</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləbiltiy: except"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləbiltiy: except</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) towratekha: your laws, your teachings"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) towratekha: your laws, your teachings</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕavruw: pass over, leave behind"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕavruw: pass over, leave behind</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 27:14-26; 28:15-68</note><v n="12" />Tuhan parná kasi tau memang sang botong deng botong pung pamimpin dong bilang, kalo botong sonde bekin iko Tuhan pung parenta bagitu, na, Tuhan pung hukuman barát nanti jato kaná di botong. Lama-lama ju botong langgar Tuhan pung parenta bagitu, ais Tuhan bekin jadi samua yang Tuhan su janji. Dari dolu sampe sakarang ju, balóm parná ada hukuman barát ke yang jato kaná di kota Yerusalem sakarang.<bt>God2 (=you) have forewarned (lit: told beforehand) us and our leaders saying, if we do not do according to God2's (=your) commands, na, God2's (=your) heavy/severe punishment will fall upon us. Eventually/after awhile we violated/transgressed God2's (=your) commands like that, so God2 (=you) brought into being/made happen everything that God2 (=you) had promised. From long ago until now, there has never been a punishment as heavy/severe as what has fallen upon the city of Yerusalem now. [DISCOURSE: restructured a bit like CEV so the logic works better in the RL.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) neʕestah"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) neʕestah</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shfaTuwnuw: they govern us"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shfaTuwnuw: they govern us</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shofTeynuw: our rulers; the ones"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shofTeynuw: our rulers; the ones governing us</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vayyaqem (qwm hif): he raised"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vayyaqem (qwm hif): he raised up. BDB raise up, rouse, stir up, investigate; raise up, constitute; cause to stand, set, station, establish; make binding; carry out, give effect to</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Ini sangsara jato kaná di botong, parsís sama ke yang ba'i Musa parná tulis. Biar bagitu, ma botong ju sonde minta TUHAN kasi tunju rasa kasian, botong sonde bale balakang kasi tenga buang botong pung sala-sala, deng botong sonde toe sang Tuhan pung kata-kata yang batúl dong, yang Tuhan su kasi tau memang sang botong.<bt>This suffering/torment/misery has fallen upon us, precisely as forefather Musa once wrote. Even that being the case, nevertheless we have not requested the LORD to show pity/mercy, we have not turned our backs abandoning our (various) wrongs, and we do not care about God2's (=your) true words/sayings/teachings, which God2 (=you) has told us beforehand. [EXEG: see TH, HCE notes, and CEV. Complex and abstract verse.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əmittekha: your truth. TWOT: carries"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əmittekha: your truth. TWOT: carries underlying sense of certainty, dependability. We find it used in several categories of contexts, all of which relate to God directly or indirectly. First, it is frequently applied to God as a characteristic of his nature. In Gen 24:27, for example, it describes God who leads Abraham's servant to the right wife for Isaac. In Ex 34:6, it is given as one of the verbal descriptions of God which constitute God's goodness. Other examples are Ps 25:5; 31:5 [H 6]; Jer 4:2; 10:10. It is a term fittingly applied to God's words (Ps 119:142, 151, 160; Dan 10:21).</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhaskiyl (skl hif inf): to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhaskiyl (skl hif inf): to give attention. BDB look at or upon, have insight; give attention to, consider, ponder, be prudent; have insight, have comprehension</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕəwonenuw: our iniquity. BDB iniquity;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕəwonenuw: our iniquity. BDB iniquity; guilt of iniquity, guilt (as great), guilt (of condition); consequence of or punishment for iniquity</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chilliynuw (piʕel): soften, sought favor,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chilliynuw (piʕel): soften, sought favor, appease. UBS: literally "we have not softened the face of," meaning to appease, placate, or mollify. This phrase is used with either God or human beings as the object, and it occurs in Psa 119.58 and 2 Chr 33.12, among other places. Translators should look for a verb meaning "appeased" (NAB, NJB), or "sought the favor of" (NIV), or "tried to please" (TEV) in their language. The addition of the negation Scripture"&gt;not indicates an intentional refusal.</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Andia ko TUHAN lia-lia itu samua, ais pas dia pung waktu, Tuhan kasi biar itu calaka jato kaná di botong sakarang ju. TUHAN sonde sala ju, te botong yang sonde mau dengar sang Tuhan na!<bt>That is why the LORD is seeing all of that, and right at the appropriate/appointed time, God2 (=you) allowed that calamity to fall upon us now. The LORD is not wrong, cuz (elaboration) we are the ones who do not want to listen to/obey God2 (=you) [+emphatic]! [EXEG: kept watch over ... until He brought it upon us. We take this as “at the right time” (implied). “Brought upon us” can be read in an active sense “direct action”, or a lesser more indirect sense “allowed this to happen to us”. See discussion in TH, NJB, NEB.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) raʕah: evil, disaster"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) raʕah: evil, disaster</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vayyishqod"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vayyishqod</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Tuhan Allah yang ada pung hak parenta sang botong. Tuhan yang antar botong, andia Tuhan pung orang pilihan dong, kaluar dari tana Masir pake Tuhan pung kuasa yang hebat. Andia ko Tuhan pung nama bae tasiar pi mana-mana sampe sakarang ju. Biar bagitu, ma botong bekin sala deng idop bekin jahat tarús.<bt>God (=you) are the one who has the right to command us. God2 (=you) are the one who led us, that is God2's (=your) chosen people, out of the land of Masir (=Egypt) using God2's (=your) amazing power/authority. That is why God2's (=your) good name/reputation has spread everywhere even up to now. Even that being the case, nevertheless we keep doing wrong and live doing evil continually.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yad chəzaqah: strong hand, using"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yad chəzaqah: strong hand, using your power</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) howtse'ta (nts' hif): you brought"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) howtse'ta (nts' hif): you brought out</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Padahal samua yang Tuhan bekin tu, batúl. Andia ko beta minta ko Tuhan jang mara tarús sang botong. Deng jang maruak deng orang di Tuhan pung kota deng Tuhan pung gunung barisi tu, andia Yerusalem. Orang di samua negrí yang badeka dong olok-olok sang Tuhan pung orang deng Tuhan pung kota Yerusalem, tagal botong pung sala-sala, deng botong pung nene-moyang pung jahat macam-macam.<bt>Whereas in fact everything that God2 (=you) have done is right/true/correct. That is why I ask God2 (=you) to not be angry continually with us. And do not be fed up with people in God2's (=your) city and on God2's (=your) clean/holy mountain, that is Yerusalem. People in all countries which are nearby mock God2's (=your) people and God2's (=your) city of Yersulaem, because of our (various) wrongs, and the assorted evil of our ancestors.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləcherpah"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləcherpah</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəmatkha"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəmatkha</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yashav-na' (shwb jussive): may you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yashav-na' (shwb jussive): may you turn back</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tsidqotekha: your righteous acts"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tsidqotekha: your righteous acts</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Naa, sakarang, Tuhan, beta minta ko Tuhan dengar beta pung sambayang ni, te beta ni, Tuhan pung orang suru-suru. Tarima apa yang beta minta ni, biar ko jaga Tuhan pung nama bae. Taro mata ulang lai di Tuhan pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat yang sakarang su kosong deng rusak tu.<bt>Naa [+shift], now, Lord, I ask that God2 (=you) listen to this prayer of mine, cuz (elaboration) I am God2's (=your) servant. Receive/accept what I am requesting here, so that (you) guard God2's (=your) good name/reputation. Attend to (lit: place eyes) once again on God2's (=your) Central House of Worship (*Temple) which is now empty and ruined. [EXEG: Heb. hasshamem: the one that is desolated, devastated, deserted.] [DISCOURSE: KM Naa, signals shift from the lead up to the request of the prayer.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hasshamem: the one that is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hasshamem: the one that is desolated, devastated, deserted</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) miqdashkha: your holy place"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) miqdashkha: your holy place</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ha'er ('wr hif imperv): make"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ha'er ('wr hif imperv): make your face shine</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Tuhan, coba dengar ame sang beta doo! Buka mata deng taro hati ko lia bae-bae sang botong yang su ancor buang. Taro mata kambali di kota Yerusalem yang bawa Tuhan pung nama. Botong sonde ada pung hak minta apa-apa tagal botong pung karjá yang batúl. Te sonde ada satu ju! Andia ko botong minta Tuhan kasi tunju hati bae, tagal Tuhan pung rasa kasian sa! Te botong sandiri sonde pantas.<bt>Lord, please listen to me now! Open (your) eyes and have compassion (lit: place liver) to look carefully at us-exc who are (completely) destroyed. Attend again (lit: place eyes) to the city of Yerusalem which bears God2's (=your) name/reputation. We do not have the right to ask for anything because of our working correctly/righteous deeds. Cuz (elaboration) there is not even one! That is why we ask God2 (=you) to show your good liver/goodness/kindness/ generosity/grace, just because of God2's (=your) pity/mercy! Cuz (elaboration) we ourselves are not worthy.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rachəmeykha: your mercy, loving compassion"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rachəmeykha: your mercy, loving compassion</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mappiyliym (npl): praying"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mappiyliym (npl): praying</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) haTTeh: stretch out, inclune your"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) haTTeh: stretch out, inclune your ear</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="19" />Tuhan, dengar coba sang beta doo!<bt>Lord, please listen to me now!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tuhan, lupa buang botong pung sala-sala ju!<bt>Lord, (completely) forget our various wrongs/sins also!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tuhan, dengar deng bekin apa yang batúl!<bt>Lord, listen and do what is true/right/correct!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Jang tunggu-tunggu, ko biar tatáp jaga Tuhan pung nama bae,<bt>Do not wait/delay, so that you continue to guard God2's (=your) good name/reputation,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">te Tuhan pung orang dong, deng Tuhan pung kota Yerusalem ada bawa Tuhan pung nama.&gt;&gt;<bt>cuz (elaboration) God2's (=your) people, and God2's (=your) city of Yerusalem are bearing God2's (=your) name/reputation.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Heb. name/reputation: avoid saying ‘good name/reputation, since that is the heart of the problem that Daniel is praying about.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕammekha: your people"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕammekha: your people</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tə' achar (piʕel imperv): do"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tə' achar (piʕel imperv): do not delay</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) haqəshiyvah (hif imperv): give attention"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) haqəshiyvah (hif imperv): give attention</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Səlachah (imperv): forgive, pardon"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Səlachah (imperv): forgive, pardon</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Gabriel buka ame so'al 7 kali 70<bt>Gabriel reveals about 7 times 70</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ais ju Daniel tulis sambung bilang, &lt;&lt;Waktu beta masi sambayang ba'omong deng TUHAN Allah, beta buka hati ko mangaku beta pung sala-sala dong. Beta ju mangaku botong orang Isra'el pung sala-sala dong. Deng beta ada minta ko Tuhan bekin barisi kambali Tuhan pung kota deng Tuhan pung gunung barisi tu, andia Yerusalem.<bt>Then Daniel continued writing saying, &lt;&lt;While I was still praying talking with the LORD God, I opened my liver to confess/acknowledge my sins/wrongs. I also confessed/acknowledged the people of Isra'el's sins/wrongs. And I was asking God2 to make clean/holy again God2's city and God2's clean/holy mountain, that is Yerusalem. [EXEG: Hebraism taken as single action. See TH. Heb. “supplication on behalf of the holy mountain” as rendered in last sentence. Cf. HCE, TH.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) təchinnatiy: my supplication"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) təchinnatiy: my supplication</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mitwaddeh (ydh hitp partcpl): confessing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mitwaddeh (ydh hitp partcpl): confessing</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Naa, waktu beta masi sambayang bagitu, ju Gabriel tarbáng datang capát-capát. Dia datang sore, pas kapala agama dong biasa bekin korban binatang dong. Gabriel tu, andia yang dolo beta sangka dia tu, manusia.<bt>Naa [+shift], while I was still praying like that, then Gabriel flew coming quickly. He came in the late afternoon, just when the priests normally make the animal sacrifices. That Gabriel, is the one whom I had previously thought was human. [EXEG: “the man Gabriel” cf. Dan. 8:15 and TH.] [EXEG: Heb. muʕaf biyʕaf: 1) flying fast, vs. 2) wearied in weariness. We take #1 as does NRSV, NLT, CEV, TB, HCE.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nogeaʕ (partcpl): touching, reaching"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nogeaʕ (partcpl): touching, reaching</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) muʕaf biyʕaf: flying fast (Gabriel)?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) muʕaf biyʕaf: flying fast (Gabriel)? extremely worn out (Daniel)? NET: The Hebrew expression "muʕaf biʕaf" is very difficult. The issue is whether the verb derives from ʕuf, "to fly" or from yaʕaf, "to be weary." Many ancient versions and modern commentators take the first of these possibilities and understand the reference to be to the swift flight of the angel Gabriel in his coming to Daniel. The words more likely refer to the extreme weariness, not of the angel, but of Daniel. Cf. 7:28; 8:27; 10:8–9, 16–17; also NASB. JG: If it were Daniel, one would expect a first person pronoun somewhere in the phrase. UBS: according to some interpreters, the traditional Hebrew text here can only mean "wearied in weariness," but this is not very meaningful in the present context. Most others read it as "flying in flight," and this is taken to mean "in rapid flight."</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) təchillah: BDB the first time;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) təchillah: BDB the first time; from the beginning, in the beginning</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'ish: man. 8:15 does not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'ish: man. 8:15 does not identify him as an angel, but as one who looked like a man.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) təfillah: prayer"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) təfillah: prayer</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 1:19, 26</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Sampe deng sampe ju, dia kasi tau sang beta bilang, &lt;We, Daniel! Beta su datang ko biar lu bisa mangarti ini hal dong.<bt>Upon arriving, he told me saying, &lt;We [+attention], Daniel! I have come so that you can understand these things.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhaskiylkha: to teach you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhaskiylkha: to teach you</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Waktu lu mulai sambayang tadi, Tuhan su mau karjá memang. Andia ko Dia langsung suru sang beta datang di lu. Te Dia talalu sayang sang lu. Jadi lebe bae, lu dengar bae-bae Tuhan pung pasán, ko biar lu bisa mangarti samua-samua yang lu su dapa lia. Bagini:<bt>When you began to pray earlier, God2 was already wanting to work immediately/directly. That is why He directly2 commanded me to come to you-sg. Cuz (elaboration) He loves/pities you very much. So (consequently) it would be best/better for you to listen to God2's message/instructions, so that you can understand everything that you have seen. It's like this:</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) haveyn (imperv): understand"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) haveyn (imperv): understand</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) viyn (imperv): understand"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) viyn (imperv): understand</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəmuwdowt: highly esteemed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəmuwdowt: highly esteemed</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="24" />Tuhan su putus bilang, ada 7 kali 70 musim kasi lu pung orang deng bosong pung kota barisi tu.<bt>God2 has already decided saying, there are 7 time 70 seasons for your-sg people and your-pl clean/holy city.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Itu tu waktu yang cukup, ko biar:<bt>That is enough/sufficient time so that:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">bosong barenti langgar Tuhan pung atoran dong;<bt>you-pl stop violating/transgressing God2's regulations;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">bosong sonde idop bekin jahat lai;<bt>you-pl no longer live doing evil;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">bosong bekin lurus bosong pung sala-sala dong;<bt>you-pl straighten out/correct your wrongs/sins;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">bosong bekin yang batúl tarús-tarús;<bt>you-pl do what is true/right/correct continually;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">bosong kasi tunju bukti bilang Tuhan pung jubir omong batúl, sama ke bosong taro segel;<bt>you-pl show evidence (assimilated loan) that God2's spokeperson/prophet(s) spoke true/right, as if you have placed a seal (assim. loan);</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng bosong bekin barisi ulang kambali Tuhan pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat.<bt>and you-pl make clean/holy once again God2's Central House of Worship/Temple. [EXEG: complex verse. We follow NRSV, NLT, HCE, TH. “annoint” taken as rededication as per CEV, TH.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) limshoach: to anoint. May refer"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) limshoach: to anoint. May refer to the rededication of the Temple after Antiochus Epiphanes defiles it.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləkhapper: atone. TWOT: From the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləkhapper: atone. TWOT: From the meaning of koper "ransom," the meaning of kapar can be better understood. It means "to atone by offering a substitute."</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chaTTa'owt (q. chaTTa't)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chaTTa'owt (q. chaTTa't)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) lachtom (q. lachtem tmm hif"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) lachtom (q. lachtem tmm hif inf): BDB finish, cease doing, leave off doing</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) peshaʕ: transgression, rebellion"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) peshaʕ: transgression, rebellion</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləkhalle' (piʕel inf): bring to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləkhalle' (piʕel inf): bring to completion</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nechtakh (nif): has been determined,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nechtakh (nif): has been determined, resolved. God may be the actor.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Lu musti mangarti bilang, Tuhan su ator memang bagini: mulai dari bosong tarima pasán ko mau bangun kambali kota Yerusalem, sampe deng itu Orang yang Tuhan su pili memang ko pegang parenta datang, na, itu makan waktu 7 kali 7 musim (andia 49 musim) tamba lai deng 62 kali 7 musim (andia 434 musim).<bt>You-sg must undertand that God2 has already arranged like this: beginning from you-pl receiving the message to want to rebuild the city of Yerusalem, until that Person whom God2 chose beforehand to hold rule/govern comes, na, that eats/takes time of 7 times 7 seasons (that is 49 seasons) adding another 62 times 7 seasons (that is 434 seasons).</bt><note reference="9:25" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Samua jadi 483 musim.<bt>Altogether that is 483 seasons.</bt></note>Waktu itu musim dong su abis, na, biar ada susa deng kaco, ma bosong su bangun kambali itu kota langkáp deng dia pung jalan deng kali dong yang bekin musu dong susa maso di situ.<bt>When those seasons are over, na, even if/though there are difficulties and chaos, nevertheless you-pl (will) have already rebuilt that city complete with its roads and rivers that make it difficult for enemies to neter there. [EXEG: Heb. seven sevens plus sixty-two sevens. See discussion in TH.] [EXEG: Heb. moat, here intended for defense. Cf. NLT, TH]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕittiym: times, occasions"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕittiym: times, occasions</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tsowq: great external pressure"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tsowq: great external pressure</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) charuwts: moat? cut in the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) charuwts: moat? cut in the wall? UBS: literally the word for "cut" and refers to a trench cut into the rock on the exterior walls of a city in order to make the wall a more difficult obstacle for those who would attempt to attack from the outside. This is the only time in the Old Testament where the word is used in this sense. It is translated "ramparts" by njb and more generally as "strong defenses" in tev. TWOT: The concept of "cut" is evident in its reference to a moat (Dan 9:25). IVPBC: "Trench" can only refer to the dry moat that was a common element of a city's defenses. The combination indicates that Jerusalem will again be a place of security and prosperity, providing all of the civic functions of a smoothly operating urban center.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tashuwv (fem): it will return,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tashuwv (fem): it will return, be redone</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shənayim: two"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shənayim: two</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) motsa': act (or event?) of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) motsa': act (or event?) of going out</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) taskel (hif jussive): BDB [may"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) taskel (hif jussive): BDB [may he] look at or upon, have insight; give attention to, consider, ponder, be prudent; have insight, have comprehension</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Kalo itu 62 kali 7 musim su abis, nanti orang dong bunu bekin mati itu Orang yang Tuhan su pili memang, tingka ke Dia sonde ada pung apa-apa, deng sonde parná karjá satu apa ju. Tarús ada tantara dong dari orang laen yang pegang parenta datang kasi ancor buang itu kota deng dia pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Dia pung ahir, nanti ada banjer datang, ada paráng, deng Tuhan su putus musti ada susa deng sangsara dong.<bt>If/when those 62 times 7 seasons are completed, then people will murder that Person whom God2 has chosen beforehand, as if He has nothing, and has never accomplished anything either. Then3 there are/will be soldiers from other/foreign people who hold rule/govern come and (completely) destroy that city and its Central House of Worship/Temple. In the end, a flood will come, there will be war, and God2 has already deceided that there must be difficulty and suffering/trauma (pl). [EXEG: very complex verse and interpretations. We are conservative here. Heb. “cut off” = killed (NLT, CEV, TH).] [DISCOURSE (STYLE): After the sixty-two seasons: TEV gives a reduced summary “at the end of that time.” We have many natural texts in which the specific details of time frames are repeated in the discourse, so my feeling is stylistically the repetition is preferred over the TEV reduced summary. When queried, speakers and MTTs (in several languages including Kupang) both seem to feel the repeated detail associated with momentous events raises its credibility as authoritative and important.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shomemowt: destructions, desolations. TWOT: The"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shomemowt: destructions, desolations. TWOT: The book of Daniel has four passages employing the Polel form of the verb (mesho4me4m and sho=me4m). There is a causative (or, better, factitive) force here similar to the use of the Hiphil, except that the Hiphil generally involves a physical devastation, while the Polel seems to put more stress on the fact that someone has caused the sanctuary or altar to be polluted, thus rendering it unfit for the worship and service of God. These passages are Dan 8:13; 11:31; 9:27; and 12:11. In the first two, Antiochus Epiphanes is depicted as doing away with proper sacrifices and in 11:31 as setting up an "abomination" (shiqqu4s[), generally understood to be an idol or pagan altar. In this activity he foreshadows the Antichrist as described in 9:27 and 12:11.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nechəretset (chrts nif): will be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nechəretset (chrts nif): will be decisive</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) milchamah: war"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) milchamah: war</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) sheTef: a flood, floodwaters"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) sheTef: a flood, floodwaters</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qittsuw: its end, the end"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qittsuw: its end, the end of its time</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yashchiyt (hif): [the people] will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yashchiyt (hif): [the people] will destroy</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) və'eyn low: UBS: kjv translated"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) və'eyn low: UBS: kjv translated them "but not for himself." Other interpretations are (1) "leaving no one to succeed him" (at and Mft); (2) "when the city is no longer his" (nab and ab); (3) "with no one to take his part" (neb); (4) "and vanish" (njv); (5) "unjustly" (tev); and (6) "his Kingdom still unrealized" (lb). This wide variety of possible translations simply shows that no one knows what this passage means. Nevertheless the translator is forced to make a choice. The textual change proposed by nab and ab is quite appealing. The translator can therefore possibly translate the idea "when he does not possess the city."</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yikkaret (nif): he will be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yikkaret (nif): he will be cut off</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Ju itu orang laen yang pegang parenta tu mau ba'akór deng orang banya dong sampe tuju musim. Ma kalo su sampe tenga jalan, na, itu orang suru barenti samua macam korban deng persembahan dong. Ais ju dia ganti deng kasi badiri satu barang yang sonde pantas, yang bekin kamomos tampa barisi, sampe bekin noju itu tampa. Dia pung bekin tu talalu jahat, sampe bekin kaco samua, deng orang dong angka kaki kasi tenga itu tampa, sampe waktu yang Tuhan su ator memang. Tuhan pung waktu su sampe bagitu, baru Dia bekin itu orang barenti.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>Then that other/foreign person who holds rule/governs is going to agree with many people until seven seasons. But if/when it is half way, na, that person will order stopped all kinds of sacrifices and offerings. Then he will replace and erect something that is not appropriate, which makes dirty/defiles that clean/holy place, to the point that it makes that place repugnant/revolting/loathsome. What he does is so very evil, to the point that it causes chaos for everything/one, and people lift their feet abandoning that place, until the time which God2 has arranged beforehand. [When] God2's time has arrived, only then will He cause that person to stop.&gt;&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Heb. for one seven] [ NOTE to daughter translations: Compare with your phrasing in Mrk. 13:14.] [EXEG: shomem (partcpl): the one who is desolated, deflowered, deserted, appalled. TWOT: the desolation caused by some great disaster, usually as a result of divine judgment. The Kupang SVC ‘lift their feet abandoning’ is idiomatic, indicating willful neglect, rejection, distancing, or abandonment.] [EXEG: NRSV: until the decreed end is poured out upon the desolator; NLT1 “until the end that has been decreed is poured out on this defiler”; Heb. kalah: conclusion, end, (in this context ‘final destruction’?) TWOT: The basic idea of this root is “to bring a process to completion.” “full end, completion, perfection”. So CEV “And it will stay there until the time God has decided to destroy this one who destroys” may be overtranslation. NRSV and NLT better reflect that the text does not actually tell us the nature of of what happens at that “appointed end”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) End of P section."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) End of P section.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shomem (partcpl): the one who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shomem (partcpl): the one who is desolated, deflowered, deserted, appalled. TWOT: the desolation caused by some great disaster, usually as a result of divine judgment.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tittakh (ntk nif): it is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tittakh (ntk nif): it is poured out</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nechəratsah (nif partcpl): that is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nechəratsah (nif partcpl): that is decided, decreed, cut in stone</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kalah: conclusion, end, final destruction"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kalah: conclusion, end, final destruction</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məshomem (polel partcpl): appalling, causing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məshomem (polel partcpl): appalling, causing horror, desolation</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shiqquwtsiym: idols, abominable things. TWOT:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shiqquwtsiym: idols, abominable things. TWOT: This noun is always used in connection with idolatrous practices, either referring to the idols themselves as being abhorrent and detestable in God's sight, or to something associated with the idolatrous ritual.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kənaf: wing, extremity"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kənaf: wing, extremity</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) minchah: offering; grain offering"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) minchah: offering; grain offering</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) zevach: sacrifice"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) zevach: sacrifice</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yashbiyt (hif): he will BDB"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yashbiyt (hif): he will BDB cause to cease, put an end to; exterminate, destroy; cause to desist from; remove; cause to fail</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) higbiyr (hif): he will confirm"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) higbiyr (hif): he will confirm</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 11:31, 12:11; Mateos 24:15; Markus 13:14</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Daniel dapa lia satu Orang dalam dia pung mimpi<bt>Daniel sees a (certain) Person in his dream</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="10" />
      <v n="1" />Waktu raja Kores pung pegang parenta su lewat dua taon, Tuhan Allah buka kasi tau Dia pung pasán satu kasi sang Daniel (yang dia pung nama laen, andia Beltasasar). Itu pasán kasi tau so'al satu paráng bésar yang pasti nanti jadi. Tuhan kasi tunju samua dalam satu mimpi, sampe Daniel mangarti itu pasán.<bt>When raja Kores's rule/governing had passed two years, God revealed one of His message's to Daniel (whose other name was Beltasasar). That message told about a great war which was certain to happen. God2 showed everything in a dream, until/to the point that Daniel understood that message. [EXEG: Heb. ʔəmet: true, trustworthy = NLT ‘certain to happen in the future’] [NOTE to daughter translations: How would you say “In the third year of the reign of king X...?” cf. Dan 8:1 -- which phrasing is most clear and natural?]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mar'eh"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mar'eh</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tsava': host? war? struggle?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tsava': host? war? struggle?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʔəmet: true, trustworthy"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʔəmet: true, trustworthy</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) niglah (glh nif): it was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) niglah (glh nif): it was disclosed, God revealed himself? TWOT: in a passive sense it means "to be uncovered": of nakedness (Ex 20:26; Isa 47:3), of skirts (Jer 13:22), and of foundations (II Sam 22:16=Ps 18:16) where it is parallel to the Niphal of ra4)a= "to be visible." Thus it also means "to be known" (Isa 23:1) and "to be revealed"—of a word from God to Daniel (Dan 10:1).</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) khowresh: Cyrus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) khowresh: Cyrus</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Ju Daniel tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Waktu Tuhan kasi tau Dia pung pasán bagitu, beta hati barát tiga minggu anteru.<bt>Then Daniel wrote saying, &lt;&lt;When God2 revealed His message like that, my liver was heavy/sad for three whole weeks. [EXEG: Heb. word ‘mourn’ is about Israel's relationship with God, not about family dying. So avoid words like /duka/ that evoke someone dying.]</bt><v n="3" />Beta sonde makan daging, ko, minum anggor, ko, makan orang kaya dong pung makanan sadiki ju. Deng beta sonde goso minya wangi di beta pung kulit ko rambu ju.<bt>I did not eat meat, or drink wine, or eat rich people's food even a little. And I did not rub fragrant oil on my skin or hair either. [DISCOURSE: reordered for information load and focus.] [ EXEG: ‘anointed’ is for hygiene here, not religion. See TH, NLT, CEV, IVP.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Tanggal 23 April,<bt>On the 23rd of April,</bt><note reference="10:4" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Ibrani tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;hari ke-24, bulan partama&gt;&gt;. Di kotong pung kalendar sakarang, itu jato kaná di tanggal 23 April.<bt>The Ibrani language Bible writes saying, &lt;&lt;24th day, first month&gt;&gt;. In our calendar these days, that falls on the date of 23 April.</bt></note>beta ada badiri di kali Tigris pung pinggir.<bt>I was standing at the endge/bank of the Tigris river. [EXEG: On date, see NLT + Note; TH]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) daqel: Tigris"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) daqel: Tigris</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Ais beta lia, ju ada satu laki-laki yang pake kaen lenan, yang dia pung ika pinggang dari mas tulen.<bt>Then I looked/saw, and there was a male who was wearing linen cloth, whose waistband/belt was from pure gold. [EXEG: Heb. gold from Uphaz; NLT ‘pure gold’, CEV ‘solid gold’; see discussion in TH.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'uwfaz: unknown place where gold"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'uwfaz: unknown place where gold was found. Possibly Ophir in Yemen, but not necessarily</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) khetem: gold, late word"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) khetem: gold, late word</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chaguriym (passive partcpl): were girded"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chaguriym (passive partcpl): were girded</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) matnayw: his waist, loins"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) matnayw: his waist, loins</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:5-6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dunya Model Baru 1:13-15, 2:18, 19:12</note><v n="6" />Dia pung badan sama ke batu mangkilat. Dia pung muka basinar sama ke kilat. Dia pung mata manyala sama ke obor. Dia pung kaki deng tangan basinar sama ke tambaga yang orang su goso bekin mangkilat. Dia pung kata-kata dong babunyi sama ke orang banya dong batarea.<bt>His body was like a shiny/precious/gemstone. His face shone like lightning. His eyes flashed/flamed like a torch. His feet and hands shone like bronze that people/a person has rubbed making it shine. His words sounded like many people shouting. [EXEG: there is no agreement on what kind of precious stone this is, so we follow NLT and CEV in going generic. See TH, HCE.] [EXEG: what is the point of comparison with lightning? NLT says ‘flashed like lightning’, but people questioned find that hard to visualise. We use our phrasing in Mat. 28:3 ‘shone like lightning’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Rev. 1:12-16"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Rev. 1:12-16</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hamown"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hamown</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qalal (adj): burnished, polished"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qalal (adj): burnished, polished</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕeyn: sparkle? glitter?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕeyn: sparkle? glitter?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) margəlotayw: his feet"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) margəlotayw: his feet</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) zəroʕotayw: his arms"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) zəroʕotayw: his arms</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) lappiydey: torches of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) lappiydey: torches of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) baraq: lightning"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) baraq: lightning</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mar'eh: appearance"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mar'eh: appearance</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tarshiysh: chrysolite (yellow)? yellow jasper?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tarshiysh: chrysolite (yellow)? yellow jasper?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) gəwiyyatow: his body"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) gəwiyyatow: his body</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Padahal cuma beta sandiri sa, andia Daniel, yang dapa lia ini hal dong. Orang dong yang ada sama-sama deng beta sonde lia bagitu. Ma dong samua gamatar, ais dong lari sambunyi.<bt>Whereas in fact it was only I myself, that is Daniel, who was able to see these things. The people with me did not see like that. But they all trembled (NOTE; lex choice evokes fear), then fled and hid.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hechave' (chb' nif inf): hiding"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hechave' (chb' nif inf): hiding themselves</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vayyivrəchuw (brch nif): they fled"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vayyivrəchuw (brch nif): they fled</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) naflah: it fell"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) naflah: it fell</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəradah: fear. BDB fear, anxiety,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəradah: fear. BDB fear, anxiety, quaking, trembling, (extreme) anxiety, anxious care</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əval: however, contrariwise"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əval: however, contrariwise</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Jadi tenga beta sandiri sa yang dapa lia itu hal yang hebat, yang tingka ke dalam mimpi. Beta badan noe. Beta pung muka pucat. Beta sonde kuat sadiki ju.<bt>So (consequently) there remained myself alone who was able to see those amazing things, as if in a dream. My body was weak. My face was pale. I had no strength at all.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) koach: strength"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) koach: strength</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕatsartiy: I [did not] retain"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕatsartiy: I [did not] retain</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mashchiyt: destruction, ruin"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mashchiyt: destruction, ruin</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nehəppakh (hpk nif): was changed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nehəppakh (hpk nif): was changed into</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) howdiy: vigor, splendor. TWOT: Dan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) howdiy: vigor, splendor. TWOT: Dan 10:8, Daniel (translated by the KJV as "comeliness" and by the RSV as "radiant appearance")</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) koch: strength"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) koch: strength</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nish'ar-biy (sh'r nif): it left"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nish'ar-biy (sh'r nif): it left me</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mar'ah: thing seen, vision"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mar'ah: thing seen, vision</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nish'artiy (sh'r nif): I was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nish'artiy (sh'r nif): I was left there</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Ais beta dengar itu orang pung kata-kata. Waktu beta dengar dia pung suara, ju beta samaput, sampe jato matono di tana.<bt>Then I heard that person's words. When I heard his voice, I fainted/collapsed, to the point of falling face.down on the ground.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nirdam (rdm nif partcpl): fast"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nirdam (rdm nif partcpl): fast asleep. TWOT: Perhaps the most interesting occurrences deal with the unconscious state of prophetic insight. Daniel 8:18; 10:9 both envision the prophet "unconscious" before the theophany.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Ais beta rasa ada orang pung tangan yang sonto ame sang beta, ju angka kasi nae sang beta ko tenga beta pung tangan deng lutut dong yang sonto tana. Ma beta gamatar tarús.<bt>Then I felt there was a person's hand which touched me, and lifted me up so that only my hands and knees were touching the ground. But I kept shaking. [CHECK: crawling position prior to standing (in vs. 11. Challenging to express.] [EXEG: TB has /siku/ ‘elbow’, but Heb is ‘palm of hand’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) birkay (dual): my two knees"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) birkay (dual): my two knees</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vattəniyʕeniy (nwʕ hif):"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vattəniyʕeniy (nwʕ hif):</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nagʕah: it touched, struck"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nagʕah: it touched, struck</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ais, itu orang kasi tau sang beta bilang, &lt;We, Daniel! Tuhan talalu sayang sang lu! Pasang talinga bae-bae, ko dengar deng pikir ame beta pung omong. Bangun badiri su, te Tuhan yang utus sang beta ko kasi tau ini pasán sang lu.&gt;<bt>Then, that person told me saying, &lt;We [+attention], Daniel! God2 loves you-sg very much! Fasten your ears well, to hear and think about/ponder/meditate what I am saying. Stand up, cuz (elaboration) God2 has sent/commissioned me to tell this message to you-sg.&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dia suru bagitu, ju beta bangun badiri. Ma beta gamatar tarús.<bt>He ordered like that, and I stood up. But I kept trembling.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) marʕiyd (rʕd hif partcpl): trembling"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) marʕiyd (rʕd hif partcpl): trembling</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shullachtiy (puʕal): I have been"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shullachtiy (puʕal): I have been sent</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕamdekha: your standing place"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕamdekha: your standing place</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) dover (dbr partcpl): I am"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) dover (dbr partcpl): I am about to say</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) haven (byn hif imperv): understand,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) haven (byn hif imperv): understand, consider carefully</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəmudowt: beloved, desired"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəmudowt: beloved, desired</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ais dia kasi tau sang beta bilang, &lt;Lu jang taku. Te dari hari partama yang lu mulai sambayang ko minta Tuhan buka kasi taráng Dia pung pasán, ais lu randá hati di Tuhan pung muka bagitu, ju Tuhan dengar lu pung sambayang. Andia ko sakarang Dia utus sang beta ko datang sini. Itu, tagal lu pung minta tu.<bt>Then he told me saying, &lt;You needn't be afraid. Cuz (elaboration) from the first day in which you began to pray to ask God2 to reveal/explain His message, and you were low livered/humble before God2 like that, God2 heard your prayer. That is why now He has sent/commissioned me to come here. That is because of your request.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhitʕannowt (ʕnh 2 hitp): to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhitʕannowt (ʕnh 2 hitp): to humble yourself</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Ma roh jahat yang pegang parenta di Persia malawan sang beta sampe 21 hari. Ais ju, Mikael datang tolong sang beta. Dia tu, Tuhan pung ana bua di sorga pung mandor. Ju beta kasi tenga sang dia ko baparáng lawan sang itu roh jahat di Persia.<bt>But the evil spirit who holds rule/governs in Persia opposed me for 21 days. Then Mikael came and helped me. He is the supervisor (assimilated loan) of God's underlings (*angels) in heaven. And I left him/allowed him to war against that evil spirit in Persia. [EXEG: Heb. sar: prince; in this context, guardian angel in charge; NLT ‘spirit prince’; CEV ‘guardian angel’. See also TH.] [EXEG: Michael: check your wording in Jude 1:9.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) malkhey: kings of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) malkhey: kings of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'etsel: near"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'etsel: near</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nowtartiy (ytr nif): I remained,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nowtartiy (ytr nif): I remained, was detained, left</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) sariym: princes; UBS: the guardian"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) sariym: princes; UBS: the guardian angel of the people of God. Compare Zech 3.1-2, where the angel of the Lord resists Satan, and Jude 9, where Michael is mentioned by name. Here Michael is further described as "one of the chief princes", or "a prince of the first rank" (njv), or "one of the archangels" (at and Mft). TWOT: "Rulers" (sariym), a common word means head man, one of recognized authority in whatever realm he operates ("powers that be," Rom 12:1). There is no metaphor when leading merchants are denominated princes (sariym, Isa 22:8). Certain angels are called sariym (Dan 10:13, 21).</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕomed lənegdiy: was standing in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕomed lənegdiy: was standing in opposition to me; stood in my way</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) malkhuwt: kingdom (not the king)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) malkhuwt: kingdom (not the king)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) sar: prince; in this context,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) sar: prince; in this context, guardian angel in charge</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">, 21: Dunya Model Baru 12:7</note><v n="14" />Ais sakarang beta su datang ko tolong sang lu, ko biar lu bisa mangarti apa yang nanti jadi di lu pung bangsa dong di hari kiamat. Te ada mimpi laen so'al itu hari dong.&gt;<bt>And/so now I have come to help you-sg, so that you can understand what will later happen to your people/race in the last days. Cuz (elaboration) there is another dream(s) about those days.&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Waktu dia masi ba'omong deng beta, beta ada lia pi tana, deng sonde bisa omong sadiki ju.<bt>While he was still speaking with me, I was looking at the ground, and not able to speak even a little.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ne'əlamtiy ('lm nif): I am"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ne'əlamtiy ('lm nif): I am bound, unable to speak</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ais ju ada satu orang yang model sama ke manusia, datang sonto ame beta pung bibir. Sonto abis bagitu, ju beta bisa buka mulu ko ba'omong lai! Ais beta kasi tau sang itu orang yang ada badiri di beta pung muka bilang, &lt;Bagini, bos! Beta pung hati rasa tar enak, tagal samua yang beta su lia ni. Beta lia, ma beta rasa noe batúl.<bt>And then there was a person whose form/model was like a human, who came and touched my lips. After touching (me) like that, I could open my mouth and speak again! Then I told that person who was standing in front of me saying, &lt;It's like this, bos! I feel unsettled/upset (lit: my liver feels not sensory.nice), because of all that I have seen here. I see (it), but I feel truly weak/limp.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕatsartiy: I [do not] retain"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕatsartiy: I [do not] retain</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tsiyray: my pangs, distress"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tsiyray: my pangs, distress</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nehefkuw: they are mixed up."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nehefkuw: they are mixed up. BDB be turned, be turned over, be changed, be turned against; be reversed; be overturned, be overthrown</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) va'eftach-piy: I opened my mouth?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) va'eftach-piy: I opened my mouth? I became able to speak?</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Beta ni, bos pung orang karjá. Ma beta sonde pantas ba'omong deng bos. Beta gamatar dingin. Beta badan noe, tingka ke sonde bisa hela napas lai.&gt;<bt>I here am bos's (=your) servant/worker. But I am not worthy to speak with bos (=you). I shiver cold (=tremble with fear). My body is weak/limp, as if I cannot pull another breath.&gt; [EXEG: Heb. ‘How can I speak?’ a) not capable; b) not worthy. We take b following TH, CEV.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nəshamah: breath"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nəshamah: breath</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) meʕattah: from now"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) meʕattah: from now</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yuwkhal: can"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yuwkhal: can</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) heykh: how?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) heykh: how?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ais, itu orang yang model sama ke manusia, sonto ulang lai sang beta. Sonto abis bagitu, ju beta rasa kuat kambali.<bt>Then, that person whose form/model was like a human, touched me again. After touching (me) like that, then I felt strength return/strong again.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vaychazzəqeniy (piʕel): he restored my"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vaychazzəqeniy (piʕel): he restored my strength</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Ais dia omong bilang, &lt;Tuhan talalu sayang sang lu! Jadi sonde usa taku. Lu su aman! Kasi kuat lu pung hati! Jang ondor!&gt;<bt>Then he spoke saying, &lt;God2 loves you-sg very much! So (consequently) you do not need to be afreiad. You are safe! Be encouraged (lit: strengthen your liver)! Don't retreat/withdraw!&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Omong abis bagitu, ju beta rasa kuat kambali. Ais beta omong bilang, &lt;Bapa tolong kasi tau samua-samua sang beta sakarang. Te bapa su bekin beta rasa kuat.&gt;<bt>After speaking like that, I felt strength return. Then/so I spoke saying, &lt;Father/sir please tell/explain everything to me now. Cuz (elaboration) father (=you) have made me feel strong.&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hitchazzaqtiy (hitp): I strengthened myself"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hitchazzaqtiy (hitp): I strengthened myself</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ais dia kasi tau bilang, &lt;Beta mau ko lu mangarti bae-bae akurang ko beta datang pi sang lu sakarang. Bagini: sonde lama lai, te beta kambali baparáng lawan sang itu roh jahat yang pegang parenta di Persia. Kalo beta su abis paráng di sana, ju roh jahat yang pegang parenta di Yunani mau muncul datang.<bt>Then he told/explained saying, &lt;I want you-sg to understand well why I came to you now. It's like this: soon, [+contrary to expectation] I will return warring against that evil spirit who holds rule/governs in Persia. If/when I have finished the war there (remote), then the evil spirit who holds rule/governs in Yunani (=Greece) is going to appear.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yowtse' (partcpl): on going out"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yowtse' (partcpl): on going out = when I am done? when I leave that place?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhillachem (nif): to make war"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhillachem (nif): to make war</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hətadaʕta: do you know? (rhetorical"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hətadaʕta: do you know? (rhetorical question)</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Biar bagitu, ma beta masi mau kasi tau sang lu apa yang su tatulis di buku yang mua apa yang batúl. (Naa, cuma Mikael sandiri sa yang tolong beta baparáng lawan sang itu roh jahat yang pegang parenta dong. Dia tu, ana bua dari sorga pung mandor yang jaga sang bosong orang Isra'el.)<bt>Even that being the case, nevertheless I still want to/am going to tell/explain to you-sg what has been written in the book that contains what is true. (Naa [+shift] only Mikael himself is the one who helped me war against those evil spirits who hold rule/govern. He is the supervisor of the underlings from heaven (*angels) who guard you-pl people of Isra'el.) [DISCOURSE: do we need to bridge 20-21 and reorder?] [EXEG: Heb. sarkhem: the guardian angel for you (pl); TWOT: prince, ruler, steward, master, keeper; Michael as guarding Israel, see TH, CEV, HCE.] [DISCOURSE: referent tracking: phrasing as archangel or guardian angel in charge from Dan. 10:13.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) End of P section. But"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) End of P section. But not the end of the quotation; it goes on through 11:1.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) sarkhem: the guardian angel for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) sarkhem: the guardian angel for you (pl)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mitchazzeq (hitp): BDB strengthen oneself;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mitchazzeq (hitp): BDB strengthen oneself; put forth strength, use one's strength; withstand; hold strongly with</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) bikhtav: in the writing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) bikhtav: in the writing</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rashuwm (pass partcpl): inscribed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rashuwm (pass partcpl): inscribed</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'aggiyd (ngd hif): I will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'aggiyd (ngd hif): I will inform you</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əval (adv): BDB truly, verily,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əval (adv): BDB truly, verily, surely; but, however, howbeit; contrariwise, nay rather (neg.)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="11" />
      <v n="1" />Taon partama waktu itu orang Media, andia raja Darius, pegang parenta di Persia, na, beta, andia Tuhan pung ana bua dari sorga, maju ko bantu deng kasi kuat sang Mikael tu.&gt;<bt>The first year, when that Media person, that is raja Darius, held rule/governed in Persia, na, I, that is God2's underling from heaven, went forward to help and strengthen that Mikael.&gt; [TEXT: See discussion in TH for overview of textual variants. NRSV, NLT, TB, NIV, NET, HCE, and CEV group this verse with ch.10. Our protocols say when there is equal support, we follow the TB.] [EXEG: Heb. “support and strengthen him” Q: who is ‘him’? Most sources take it as Michael, the referent in 10:21; Only CEV seems to take it as Darius, ignoring the discussion in TH.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləmaʕowz (noun): refuge. TWOT: Place"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləmaʕowz (noun): refuge. TWOT: Place or means of safety, protection, stronghold, fortress. As is sometimes the case, the mem prefix adds the meaning "place" to the verbal root. Natural and man made places of safety can be designated by this word such as a mountain (Jud 6:26), harbor (Isa 23:4), cities (Isa 17:9), and temple (Ezk 24:25). These strongholds, in sharp contrast to God, are not invincible but are rather subject to destruction (Isa 23:11, 14; Ezk 30:15). The noun also possibly appears in Ps 52:7 [H 9] (however that may be from ʕazaz "be strong") showing the futility of riches as a shelter.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləmachziyq (hif partcpl): as one"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləmachziyq (hif partcpl): as one who strengthens, supports. BDB make strong, strengthen; make firm; support</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) No paragraph; this is actually"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) No paragraph; this is actually the end of Chapter 10.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Raja dari salatan, deng raja dari utara<bt>The raja from the south, and the raja from the north</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Ais, itu ana bua dari sorga sambung dia pung omong bilang, &lt;Beta kasi tau memang sang lu bagini: nanti ada tiga raja lai yang pegang parenta di Persia. Ais itu, baru nomer ampa, ma dia lebe kaya dari dong samua. Ju dia pake dia pung kaya ko jadi tamba kuat lai. Kalo dia su jadi kuat batúl, na, dia jadi tukang kipas ko urus banya negrí ko baparáng malawan negrí Yunani.<bt>Then that underling from heaven continued speaking saying, &lt;I tell you directly like this: there will be three more rajas who hold rule/govern in Persia. After that, then number four, but he is wealthier than all. And he uses his wealth to become even stronger. If/when he has become truly strong/powerful, na, he becomes a fanner (=provocateur) to incite/organise many countries to war against the country of Yunani (=Greece). [NOTE: NIV: 3 more kings: Cambyses (530-522 BC), Pseudo-Smerdis or Gaumata (522), and Darius I (522-486). Fourth Xerxes I (486-465) who attempted to conquer Greece in 480, turned back at Marathon and Salamis, in the 2007 movie ‘300’. There were other kings in Persia; these are the prominent ones.] [NOTE 2: Heb. malkhuwt yavan: kingdom of Greece. Greece didn't actually have one king at the time Xerxes took them on. They were more like a network of city states, especially Sparta, Corinth, and Athens. Under Themistocles (not a king) they defeated the Persians in the naval Battle of Salamis. Wikipedia: In 480 BC, after massive preparation King Xerxes led a very large force to subjugate Greece. At the Battle of Thermopylae, a small force of about 7,000 Greeks led by King Leonidas of Sparta held off a large Persian army that numbered around 200,000. For three days, the Greeks fought a desperate action to delay the entry of the Persians into the Greek heartland. They caused very large Persian casualties, but all the Greeks were eventually killed in the battle. Now in Greece proper, the Persians sacked and razed the city of Athens under the orders of Xerxes, but the Persian fleet was defeated in the battle of Salamis. Xerxes left Mardonius with part of the original force to finish the job and returned to Asia Minor. The next year Mardonius was defeated and killed in the battle of Plataea; the remaining Persian fleet was destroyed in the battle of Mycale. JG: This passage gives an overview of what is going to happen, but the details of what is going to happen 50 to 150 years in the future are fuzzy.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) malkhuwt yavan: kingdom of Greece."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) malkhuwt yavan: kingdom of Greece. Greece didn't actually have one king at the time Xerxes took them on. They were more like a network of city states, especially Sparta, Corinth, and Athens. Under Themistocles (not a king) they defeated the Persians in the naval Battle of Salamis. Wikipedia: In 480 BC, after massive preparation King Xerxes led a very large force to subjugate Greece. At the Battle of Thermopylae, a small force of about 7,000 Greeks led by King Leonidas of Sparta held off a large Persian army that numbered around 200,000. For three days, the Greeks fought a desperate action to delay the entry of the Persians into the Greek heartland. They caused very large Persian casualties, but all the Greeks were eventually killed in the battle. Now in Greece proper, the Persians sacked and razed the city of Athens under the orders of Xerxes, but the Persian fleet was defeated in the battle of Salamis. Xerxes left Mardonius with part of the original force to finish the job and returned to Asia Minor. The next year Mardonius was defeated and killed in the battle of Plataea; the remaining Persian fleet was destroyed in the battle of Mycale. JG: This passage gives an overview of what is going to happen, but the details of what is going to happen 50 to 150 years in the future are fuzzy.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yaʕiyr (ʕuwr hif): he will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yaʕiyr (ʕuwr hif): he will rouse, stir up, agitate</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yaʕəshiyr ʕosher (hif): he will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yaʕəshiyr ʕosher (hif): he will gain huge riches</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕomdiym: standing up, arising, coming"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕomdiym: standing up, arising, coming to power</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV: 3 more kings: Cambyses"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV: 3 more kings: Cambyses (530-522 BC), Pseudo-Smerdis or Gaumata (522), and Darius I (522-486). Fourth Xerxes I (486-465) who attempted to conquer Greece in 480, turned back at Marathon and Salamis, in the 2007 movie '300'. There were other kings in Persia; these are the prominent ones.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əmet: true, reliable. Make sure"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əmet: true, reliable. Make sure it doesn't sound like what he said before wasn't true.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ais nanti ada satu raja muncul datang yang pintar baparáng. Dia tu, pegang kuasa parenta yang hebat. Ju dia bagarák iko dia pung suka.<bt>Then later there is one raja who appears who is skilled at war. He holds an impressive power/authority to rule/govern. And he moves/takes action as he likes. [NOTE: NIV: Alexander the Great (336-323). Defeated Persia in 333.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kirtsownow: according to his preference"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kirtsownow: according to his preference</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV: Alexander the Great (336-323)."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV: Alexander the Great (336-323). Defeated Persia in 333.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Ma kalo dia pung nama su jadi paling hebat, ju dia mati. Ais orang dong bagi kasi pisa dia pung wilaya parenta jadi ampa bagian. Bukan itu raja pung turunan dong yang pegang parenta di itu ampa bagian, ma orang laen dong. Pegang parenta bagitu, ju dong pegang tamba di negrí baru dong lai.<bt>But when his name/reputation has become most impressive (=at its peak), he dies. Then people divide and separate his regions that he governed into four parts. It is not that rajas descendants who hold rule/govern in those four parts, but other people. Governing in that way, then they add new countries that they govern also. [EXEG: Heb. and NRSV unclear. Follow HCE, NLT, and TH. Heb. “4 winds” undertranslated as in HCE, NLT, CEV. Directions are not in focus -- see discussion in IVP and TH.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) milləvad: besides"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) milləvad: besides</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tinnatesh (nif): it will be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tinnatesh (nif): it will be plucked up</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) lə' achəriytow: to his posterity"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) lə' achəriytow: to his posterity</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) techats (chtsh nif): it will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) techats (chtsh nif): it will be divided, parceled out</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV: four winds. See note"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV: four winds. See note on four heads (Dan 7.4-7)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ais itu, ju raja dari sablá salatan, andia negrí Masir, nae jadi kuat. Ma dia pung pagawe satu nanti jadi lebe kuat lai, ju pegang parenta di situ pake tangan besi.<bt>After that, the raja from the south side, that is the country of Masir (=Egypt), ascends becoming strong/powerful. But one of his officials will later become even more strong/powerful, and hold rule there using an iron hand (=strict, severe, can also imply cruel). [EXEG: ‘Egypt’ is named in the Heb. text in vs. 8; see also IVP, TH, HCE, and NIV note: Ptolemy I Soter of Egypt (323-285). One of his commanders Seleucus I Nicator (311-280). His own kingdom, initially Babylonia, to which he then added extensive territories both east and west. Many different interpretations of the last clause. We follow NLT.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) On most islands in the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) On most islands in the Pacific including this one, north and south are not relevant terms; mountainward and seaward are. If you want confirmation, Google a street map of Honolulu and you'll find that East-West Road runs almost exactly north and south. There are words for north and south in Polynesian Hawaiian and Pidgin, but they're like technical vocabulary that don't get used in everyday life.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV: Ptolemy I Soter of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV: Ptolemy I Soter of Egypt (323-285). One of his commanders Seleucus I Nicator (311-280). His own kingdom, initially Babylonia, to which he then added extensive territories both east and west.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Lewat barapa taon ju, raja Masir di salatan, deng raja Siria di utara, basakongkol ko mau babantu. Ais raja Masir kasi dia pung ana nona ko kawin deng itu raja Siria di utara, ko biar dong ika itu janji. Ma itu parampuan pung pangaru sonde batahan lama. Dia pung kuasa ju, ilang buang. Ais ju, itu parampuan deng dia pung orang dong, abis buang.<bt>After several years, the raja of Masir in the south, and the raja of Siria in the north, conspire to help each other. Then the raja of Masir gives his daughter to marry that raja Siria in the north, so that they bind that promise. But that female's influence does not endure long. Her power/authority also disappears. After that, the woman and her people are finished. [DISCOURSE: paragraph added at shift in time.] [EXEG: several Heb. idioms in this verse, so it should not be translated literally. See TH.] [EXEG: the use of Kupang /abis/ here preserves the ambiguity of the Heb. variously interpreted as abandoned, handed over, or killed.] [NOTE: NIV: Berenice, daughter of Ptolemy II Philadelphus (285-246) of Egypt. King of the north: Antiochus Ii Theos (261-246) of Syria. Alliance: treaty cemented by marriage of Berenice to Antiochus. Will not last: his former wife conspired to have the couple killed. Berenice's father died about the same time.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) baʕittiym: at the times"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) baʕittiym: at the times</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) machəziqahh: the one supporting her"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) machəziqahh: the one supporting her</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hayyolədahh: the one who begot"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hayyolədahh: the one who begot her. Theodotion, Syriac, Vulgate read it as yaldah 'her child'. UBS: hottp/ctat advises against following this change in the text, but it is adopted by the majority of modern versions (neb, njb, tob, nab, frcl, at, Mft). It is therefore permissible to follow this option, if translators wish to do so.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məviy'eyha (bw' hif partcpl): the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məviy'eyha (bw' hif partcpl): the one bringing her</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tinnaten (nif): she will be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tinnaten (nif): she will be given</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) zərowaʕ: arm"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) zərowaʕ: arm</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kowach: power of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kowach: power of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) taʕətsor: she will [not] retain"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) taʕətsor: she will [not] retain</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) meyshariym: straight things, upright things"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) meyshariym: straight things, upright things</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tsafown: north in general, in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tsafown: north in general, in this context Syria</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) negev: south in general, in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) negev: south in general, in this context Egypt</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yitchabbaruw (chbr hitp): they will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yitchabbaruw (chbr hitp): they will make an alliance, league together</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qets: end of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qets: end of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV: Berenice, daughter of Ptolemy"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV: Berenice, daughter of Ptolemy II Philadelphus (285-246) of Egypt. King of the north: Antiochus Ii Theos (261-246) of Syria. Alliance: treaty cemented by marriage of Berenice to Antiochus. Will not last: his former wife conspired to have the couple killed. Berenice' father died about the same time.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ma lama-lama ju, itu parampuan pung kelu satu muncul datang. Ju dia pegang parenta, ais dia kumpul tantara bam-banya. Tarús dia sarbú malawan sang raja Siria di sablá utara. Ju dia maso pi dalam benteng ko kasi kala sang dong.<bt>But eventually one of that woman's descendants appears. And he holds rule/governs, and he gathers many soldiers/a large army. Then3 he attacks against the raja of Siria on the north side. And he enters into the fort to defeat them. [EXEG: Heb. one of the shoots of her roots Q: relative? or descendant? A: netser: branch, offshoot, always used figuratively a member of her family. harasheyha: her roots. TWOT: In Dan 11:7 a "branch of the roots" that is, one of her descendants will gain prominence. NIV/NET: one from her family line: NLT1/CEV: one of her relatives. Our use of /kelu/ allows either interpretation. Note: the botanical ‘offshoot’ is a common metaphor in the region for a descendant (could be a son) who replaces someone in authority.] [NOTE:  Berenice's brother, Ptolemy III Euergetes (246-221) of Egypt, who did away with Laodice. King of the North: Seleucus II Calinius (246-226) of Syria. His fortress: Either Seleucia (see Acts 13.4), which was the port of Antioch, or Antioch itself.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) maʕowz"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) maʕowz</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kannow"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kannow</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) sharasheyha: her roots. TWOT: In"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) sharasheyha: her roots. TWOT: In Dan 11:7 a "branch of the roots" of the daughter of the king of the south will arise, that is, one of her descendants will gain prominence.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) netser: branch, always used figuratively."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) netser: branch, always used figuratively. Here it's another member of her family (her brother). TWOT: The Daniel passage uses our word to refer to a royal power, here one of the Ptolemies, not of the messianic royal person to come from the line of David.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV: one from her family"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV: one from her family line: Berenice's brother, Ptolemy III Euergetes (246-221) of Egypt, who did away with Laodice. King of the North: Seleucus II Calinius (246-226) of Syria. His fortress: Either Seleucia (see Acts 13.4), which was the port of Antioch, or Antioch itself.</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Waktu dia pulang pi negrí Masir, ju dia angka bawa dong pung patong songgo dong, deng barang mas-perak laen dong ju. Ais dia barenti cape deng sonde ganggu raja Siria di sablá utara sampe barapa taon.<bt>When he returns to the country of Masir, then he carries away their statues of traditional.worship, and other things of gold-silver too. Then he rests and does not disturb the raja of Siria on the north side for several years. [NOTE: NIV Their gods: images of Syrian deities, and also of Egyptian gods that the Persian Cambyses had carried off after conquering Egypt in 525 BC.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yaviy' (bw' hif): he will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yaviy' (bw' hif): he will take</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shəviy: take captive, here as"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shəviy: take captive, here as 'take as booty'</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chemdatam: their pleasant, precious things"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chemdatam: their pleasant, precious things</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nəSikheyhem: their molten images, idols"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nəSikheyhem: their molten images, idols</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV Their gods: images of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV Their gods: images of Syrian deities, and also of Egyptian gods that the Persian Cambyses had carried off after conquering Egypt in 525 BC.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ma lama-lama itu raja di utara mau maso sarbú pi raja Masir pung wilaya parenta di salatan. Ais ju dia pulang pi dia pung tana sandiri.<bt>But eventually that raja in the north wants to/will/is going to go attack into the raja of Masir's region of governance in the south. Then he returns to his own land. [EXEG: Heb. “the latter” = king of the north; NLT, CEV, TH.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Tarús raja Siria pung ana-ana dong mau kumpul ame tantara banya ko mau siap baparáng. Ais ju dong maju pi sarbú sang raja di salatan, sama ke aer banjer datang. Ju dong baparáng sampe di benteng pung tembok. Te raja Masir ada di situ.<bt>Then3 the raja of Siria's children/offspring/underlings are going to  gather many soldiers to prepare for war. Then they go forward to attack the raja in the south, like floodwaters coming. And they battle up to the wall of the fort. Cuz (elaboration) the raja of Masir is there. [DISCOURSE: implicit-explicit following HCE.] [NOTE: NIV: His sons: Seleucus III Ceraunus (226-223 BC) and Antiochus III the Great (223-187 BC) sons of Seleucua II. His fortress: Ptolemy's fortress at Raphia in southern Palestine.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) maʕuzzah"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) maʕuzzah</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shaTaf: it overflowed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shaTaf: it overflowed</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəyaliym: forces, people skilled in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəyaliym: forces, people skilled in fighting</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) həmown: tumult, uproar, crowd"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) həmown: tumult, uproar, crowd</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'aSfuw: they will gather"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'aSfuw: they will gather</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yitgaruw (grh hitp): they will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yitgaruw (grh hitp): they will excite themselves, get psyched up. BDB excite oneself against, engage in strife; excite oneself (against foe), wage war</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV: His sons: Seleucus III"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV: His sons: Seleucus III Ceraunus (226-223 BC) and Antiochus III the Great (223-187 BC) sons of Seleucua II. His fortress: Ptolemy's fortress at Raphia in southern Palestine.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Lia bagitu ju, raja Masir makan gigi. Ais dia kaluar deng dia pung tantara dong, ko mau baparáng malawan sang raja Siria yang datang dari sablá utara. Biar raja Siria su kumpul ame banya tantara, ma raja Masir kasi kala sang dong ju.<bt>Seeing that, the raja of Masir is furious/bitter (lit: eats teeth). Then he comes out with his soldiers to war against the raja of Siria who comes from the north side. Even though the raja of Siria has already gathered up many soldiers, nevertheless the raja of Masir defeats them. [NOTE: NIV: King of the south: Ptolemy IV Philopator (221-203 BC) of Egypt. King of the north: Antiochus III defeated at Raphia in 217.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yad: hand; into his power"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yad: hand; into his power</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nittan (nif): it will be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nittan (nif): it will be given</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) heʕəmiyd (ʕmd hif): he will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) heʕəmiyd (ʕmd hif): he will cause to stand. BDB station, set, cause to stand firm, maintain; cause to stand up, cause to set up, erect; present (one) before (king); appoint, ordain, establish</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nilcham (lchm nif): he will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nilcham (lchm nif): he will engage in battle, wage war</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yatsa': he will go out"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yatsa': he will go out</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yitmarmar (mrr hitp): he will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yitmarmar (mrr hitp): he will make himself embittered</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV: King of the south:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV: King of the south: Ptolemy IV Philopator (221-203 BC) of Egypt. King of the north: Antiochus III defeated at Raphia in 217.</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Kasi kala abis, ju raja Masir tangkap ame raja Siria pung orang dong, ko jadi dia pung tahanan paráng. Ma raja Masir tu, kapala bésar, ais dia suru dia pung orang ko bunu bekin mati dia pung musu dong, sampe baribu-ribu. Biar bunu banya orang bagitu, ma dia balóm manáng batúl.<bt>After defeating them, the raja of Masir captures the raja of Siria's people, to become his prisoners of war. But that raja of Masir has a big head (=arrogant), so he orders his people to kill his enemies, to the thousands. Even though he killed many people like that, nevertheless he does not yet truly win. [NOTE: NIV: Slaughter many thousands: The historian Polybus records that Antiochus lost nearly 10,000 infantrymen at Raphia.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ya'owz (ʕzz): prevail. TWOT: When"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ya'owz (ʕzz): prevail. TWOT: When used of man, this word carries the idea of prevailing as in a war or struggle (Jud 3:10; 6:2; Dan 11:12; cf. UT 19: no. 1835) or as being belligerent, particularly to God.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ribbo'owt: tens of thousands, myriads"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ribbo'owt: tens of thousands, myriads (a number word for 10,000 in Greek and Hebrew, but it only means 'lots and lots of' in English)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hippiyl (hif): he will cause"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hippiyl (hif): he will cause to fall = kill. It doesn't say specifically that this will be Syrians, but in this context it's hard to think of anything else that will fit.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV: Slaughter many thousands: The"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV: Slaughter many thousands: The historian Polybus records that Antiochus lost nearly 10,000 infantrymen at Raphia.</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Dia sonde manáng, tagal raja Siria mau kumpul ame satu tantara baru. Ma tantara baru dong tu, lebe bésar dari dia pung tantara lama dong. Lewat barapa taon ju, dia su siap dong pung sanjata deng banya alat paráng, ais dia kaluar deng dia pung tantara banya dong ko mau pi baparáng.<bt>He did not win, because the raja of Siria wants to/is going to gather a new army. But those new soldiers/army is bigger than his old/previous army. After several years, he (will have) prepared many of their weapons and war instruments/equipment, then he goes out with his many soldiers to go to war. [EXEG: Heb. ləqets haʕittiym shaniym: at the end of the times of years.] [NOTE: At the end of a period of years. The Fourth Syrian War was in 217 BC; the Fifth, referred to here, was 202-200 BC, so there was a fifteen year gap.] [EXEG: equipment. TH argues convincingly that in this context it does not mean wealth, but implements of war.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rəkhuwsh: moveable goods, supplies, equipment"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rəkhuwsh: moveable goods, supplies, equipment</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləqets haʕittiym shaniym: at the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləqets haʕittiym shaniym: at the end of the times of years. At the end of a period of years. The Fourth Syrian War was in 217 BC; the Fifth, referred to here, was 202-200 BC, so there was a fifteen year gap.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Itu waktu, bukan raja Siria sandiri sa yang malawan sang raja Masir, ma banya negrí laen dong ju. Daniel, lu pung orang Yahudi saparu yang suka baparáng, iko malawan sang raja Masir ju. Te dong mau pegang parenta di dong pung tana sandiri, deng mau lapás diri dari raja Masir pung wilaya parenta.<bt>At that time it is not the raja of Siria alone who opposes the raja of Masir, but many other countries as well. Daniel, some of your-sg Yahudi people who like to/often war, participate in opposing the raja of Masir also. Cuz (elaboration) they want to hold rule/govern in their own land, and want to free/release themselves from the raja of Masir's region of governing. [EXEG: Heb. fulfillment of vision = independence, HCE ‘fo make dea own govmen’, TH ‘those who would resort to armed struggle to liberate Israel’, CEV (implied by ‘rebellion’)] [NOTE: NIV: King of the South: Ptolemy V Epiphanes (203-181 BC) of Egypt. Violent men among your own people: Jews who joined the force of Antiochus without success. The Ptolemaic general Scopas crushed the rebellion in 200.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nikhshaluw (nif): they will stumble,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nikhshaluw (nif): they will stumble, be tottering, be feeble</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chazown: dream, vision (the dream"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chazown: dream, vision (the dream of the upstarts who want to fight as Syrians to get out from under Egyptian control -- not Daniel's vision)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhaʕəmiyd (ʕmd hif inf): to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhaʕəmiyd (ʕmd hif inf): to raise an army? to make a vision stand? implement what they have dreamed of (in the Martin Luther King sense of "I have a dream")?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yinnasə'uw (ns' hitp): they will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yinnasə'uw (ns' hitp): they will exalt themselves, lift themselves up, engage in an armed uprising</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) pariytsey: (sons of) violent ones"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) pariytsey: (sons of) violent ones of your people</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV: King of the South:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV: King of the South: Ptolemy V Epiphanes (203-181 BC) of Egypt. Violent men among your own people: Jews who joined the force of Antiochus without success. The Ptolemaic general Scopas crushed the rebellion in 200.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Ju raja Siria dari sablá utara datang kasi tumpuk tinggi-tinggi tana isi di benteng pung tembok, ko biar tantara dong bisa maso lewat situ. Deng bagitu, dong kasi kala dong pung musu di itu kota deng dia pung benteng. Ju raja Masir pung tantara dong sonde batahan, ais dong kala. Dia pung tantara yang paling pintar baparáng ju sonde batahan, te dong sonde kuat malawan tarús-tarús.<bt>Then the raja of Siria from the north side comes piling up very high soil at the wall of the fort, so that the soldiers can enter via that. In that way, they defeat their enemies in that city with its fort. And the raja of Masir's soldiers do not endure/stand, so they lose/are defeated. His soldiers who are most skilled/clever at warring also do not endure, cuz (elaboration) they are not strong to oppose continually. [EXEG: Heb. ʃowləlah: TWOT: Mound, siege rampart. (Cf. Egyptian tʕrr.f "siege mound.") This term is often employed by the prophets in contexts of judgment (Jer 6:6; 32:24; 33:4; Ezk 17:17; Dan 11:15).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mivcharayw: the picked troops, elite"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mivcharayw: the picked troops, elite troops</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) zəroʕowt: arms of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) zəroʕowt: arms of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mivtsarowt: fortifications"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mivtsarowt: fortifications</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) lakhad: he will capture, seize"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) lakhad: he will capture, seize</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Sowləlah: TWOT: Mound, siege rampart."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Sowləlah: TWOT: Mound, siege rampart. (Cf. Egyptian tʕrr.f "siege mound.") This term is often employed by the prophets in contexts of judgment (Jer 6:6; 32:24; 33:4; Ezk 17:17; Dan 11:15).</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yishpokh: he will pour out"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yishpokh: he will pour out (in this context, dump dirt)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV: Mediterranean port of Sidon."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV: Mediterranean port of Sidon.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ma raja dari Siria tu, bagarák iko dia pung suka sa. Sonde ada satu ju dari Masir pung tantara yang bisa malawan batúl sang dia pung tantara dong. Jadi negrí Isra'el yang talalu bagus tu, yang dolu musti dengar-dengar sang raja Masir, sakarang musti dengar-dengar sang raja Siria. Ma dia pung maksud ko mau kasi ancor buang sang Isra'el ju.<bt>But that raja from Siria, moves/does just what he likes. There is not a single one of Masir's soldiers who is able to truly/successfully oppose his soldiers. So (consequently) the country of Isra'el that is so beautiful, which previously had to listen to/obey the raja Masir, now must listen to/obey the raja of Siria. But his intention is wanting to (completely) destroy Isra'el. [DISCOURSE: new paragraph signalling shift in theme/focus, as per NLT.] [EXEG: Heb. beautiful/glorious land = Israel, TH, HCE, NLT, CEV; Heb. kalah: terminate, consume. TWOT: The idea of being consumed is most commonly applied to violent destruction, often by war (Deut 7:22, I Sam 15:18; Jer 16:4). NLT, CEV, HCE, TH.] [NOTE: NIV: Antiochus was in control of Palestine by 197 BC.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kalah: terminate, consume. TWOT: The"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kalah: terminate, consume. TWOT: The idea of being consumed is most commonly applied to violent destruction, often by war (Deut 7:22, I Sam 15:18; Jer 16:4).</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tsəviy: beautiful, glorious"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tsəviy: beautiful, glorious</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV: Antiochus was in control"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV: Antiochus was in control of Palestine by 197 BC.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ais, itu raja Siria putus ko kumpul ame dia pung tantara dong samua-samua ko mau maju pi Masir di sablá salatan. Ma dia kasi salák ko sonde usa baparáng lai. Ju dia tawar ko kasi kawin satu ana parampuan dari Siria deng raja Masir. Te dia pung maksud mau pake itu parampuan ko kasi ancor buang sang tana Masir. Biar dia pung maksud bagitu, ma sonde tau jadi ju. Dia sonde dapa ontong bagitu.<bt>Then that raja of Siria decides to gather together all his soldiers to go forward to the south side of Masir. But he gives opportunity so they do not need to war anymore. And he offers to marry off one daughter from Siria with the raja of Masir. Cuz (elaboration) his intention is to use that female to completely destroy the land of Masir. Even though that is his intention, nevertheless he is unable to pull it off (lit: not know to happen--common construction in lgs of this region). He is unable to succeed like that. [EXEG: see TH for referent tracking and other complex issues and Heb. idioms in this verse. Also HCE.] [NOTE: NIV: Antiochus gave his daughter Cleopatra I in marriage to Ptolemy V in 194 BC.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhashchiytahh (shcht hif inf): in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhashchiytahh (shcht hif inf): in order to destroy her? the land of Egypt? probably the latter.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) bat hannashiym: a daughter of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) bat hannashiym: a daughter of the women; not necessarily his own daughter, but somebody from his land</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yshariym (adj pl): upright, fair."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yshariym (adj pl): upright, fair. BDB that which is upright (subst), or here, "those things that are upright"</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) malkhuwtow: his kingdom. Since the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) malkhuwtow: his kingdom. Since the Syrian king is topic at this point, "his" is probably the Syrian king, though Egypt "is preferred by neb, njb, njv, and ab. (UBS)"</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) toqef: authority, strength, energy of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) toqef: authority, strength, energy of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yasem panayw: he will set"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yasem panayw: he will set his face (like Jesus to go to Jerusalem). Luke 9:51 make up his mind</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV: Antiochus gave his daughter"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV: Antiochus gave his daughter Cleopatra I in marriage to Ptolemy V in 194 BC.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ais itu ju, raja Siria pi sarbú sang orang dong yang tenga di laut pung pinggir deng di pulo-pulo. Ju dia tangkap ame banya orang.<bt>After that then the raja of Siria goes attacking the people who live at the edge of the sea and on the islands. And he captures many people. [EXEG: TH recommends using the clarification of Heb. “coastlands” from Gen 10:5 as meaning the people “who live along the coast and on the islands”. This is followed by HCE. And it makes sense in an island region such as ours.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma ada satu panglima paráng dari tampa laen yang paksa raja Siria ko ondor. Te raja Siria kurang ajar, deng sonde tau tunju hormat kasi sang orang laen. Ondor bagitu, ju dia jadi malu, te sonde ada yang hormat sang dia lai!<bt>But there is one war commander from another place who forces the raja of Siria to withdraw/retreat. Cuz (elaboration) the raja of Siria is rude/untaught, and does not know how to show respect to other people. Retreating like that, he becomes embarrassed/ashamed, cuz (elaboration) there is none that respects him anymore! [EXEG: see TH, NLT ‘cause him to retreat in shame’, HCE for interpretation of Heb. idiom.] [NOTE: NIV: he Antiochus. Coastlands Asia Minor and perhaps also mainland Greece. Commander Roman consul Lucius Cornelius Scipio Asiaticus, who defeated Antiochus at Magnesia in Asia Minor in 190 BC.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) biltiy"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) biltiy</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) cherpatow: his scorn, reproach, lack"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) cherpatow: his scorn, reproach, lack of respect</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qatsiyn: chief, ruler, commander. TWOT:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qatsiyn: chief, ruler, commander. TWOT: a military term. It signifies the man responsible for recruiting, an administrator in the army. It appears to denote the one at the head (parallel to "head ones," Mic 3:1, 9) of an army (Josh 10:24), or people (i.e. as political ruler; cf. Isa 1:10; Mic 3:1).</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hishbiyt (shbt hif): BDB cause"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hishbiyt (shbt hif): BDB cause to cease, put an end to; exterminate, destroy; cause to desist from; cause to fail</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV: he Antiochus. Coastlands Asia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV: he Antiochus. Coastlands Asia Minor and perhaps also mainland Greece. Commander Roman consul Lucius Cornelius Scipio Asiaticus, who defeated Antiochus at Magnesia in Asia Minor in 190 BC.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ais itu ju, raja Siria pulang kambali pi dia pung negrí sandiri ais maso pi dia pung benteng. Lama-lama ju, dia sonde kuat lai. Dia su jato, ais orang sonde dapa lia sang dia lai.<bt>After that, the raja of Siria goes back home to his own country and then enters his fort. After awhile/eventually he is no longer strong anymore. He has fallen (socially, politically, morally), and then people don't see him anymore. [NOTE: NIV: Antiochus died in 187 BC while attempting to plunder a temple in Elymais.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yimmatse' (mts' nif): BDB be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yimmatse' (mts' nif): BDB be found; be encountered, be lighted upon, be discovered;  appear, be recognised; be discovered, be detected; be gained, be secured; be, be found; be found in; be in the possession of;  be found in (a place), happen to be; be left (after war)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nikhshal (nif): BDB stumble; be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nikhshal (nif): BDB stumble; be tottering, be feeble</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) maʕuwzzey: BDB place or means"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) maʕuwzzey: BDB place or means of safety, protection, refuge, stronghold</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV: Antiochus died in 187"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV: Antiochus died in 187 BC while attempting to plunder a temple in Elymais.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ais itu ju, raja yang nae ganti sang dia, angka satu pagawe ko tagi bea dari dia pung da'era parenta anteru. Dia pung maksud pake itu bea ko kasi tunju raja pung hebat. Ma itu pagawe tendes bekin susa sang rakyat. Andia ko sonde ada yang hormat sang raja lai. Jadi lewat dua-tiga taon sa, raja su jato. Dia pung jato tu, bukan tagal paráng, deng bukan ju tagal orang mara.<bt>After that, the raja who ascends replacing him, elevates/appoints an official to collect tax from his entire region of governance. His intention is to use that tax to show the raja's amazingness. But that official presses/oppresses causing difficulty for the populace. That is why there is nobody who respects the raja anymore. So (consequently) after only two-three years (=2 or 3, approx.) the raja (will) have fallen. His fall is not because of war, and not because people are angry. [EXEG: See TH, HCE, NLT, CEV.] [NOTE: NIV: Seleucius IV Philopator (187-175 BC), son and successor of Antiochus the Great. Tax collector: Seleucus's finance minister, Heliodorus. Seleucus was the victim of a conspiracy engineered by Heliodorus.] [DISCOURSE: last sentence reordered for RL values.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yisshaber (nif): will be broken"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yisshaber (nif): will be broken</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əchadiym: a certain (number of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əchadiym: a certain (number of days) = a relatively short period</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) heder: glory, beauty, majesty. TWOT:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) heder: glory, beauty, majesty. TWOT: associated with: (1) the glory of nature as it reflects the goodness of God (Lev 23:40; Ps 111:3, Isa 35:2); (2) man (Isa 53:2, the suffering servant, "comeliness"); man as he is created by God (Ps 8:6); the elderly man's gray hair (Prov 20:29); the ideal wife (Prov 31:25). (3) It is applied to cities: Jerusalem (Isa 5:14); Zion (Lam 1:6); and the areas of Persia, Lud, and Put (Ezk 27:10); (4) to the Joseph tribes (Deut 33:17) and perhaps to all of Palestine (Dan 11:20, heder).</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) noges: one who presses, drives,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) noges: one who presses, drives, oppresses, exacts, exerts demanding pressure. Taken by most as a tax collector who squeezed everybody; but KD maintain that it is broader than taxes and the Holy Land; it is oppression over the whole kingdom, and results in the quiet end of the king without displays of anger or battles.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) maʕəviyr (ʕbr hif partcpl): one"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) maʕəviyr (ʕbr hif partcpl): one causing to pass through</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kannow: his place, his kuleana"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kannow: his place, his kuleana</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV: Seleucius IV Philopator (187-175"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV: Seleucius IV Philopator (187-175 BC), son and successor of Antiochus the Great. Tax collector: Seleucus's finance minister, Heliodorus. Seleucus was the victim of a conspiracy engineered by Heliodorus.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ais itu ju, ada satu orang yang nae ganti dia, ma itu orang tar bae. Yang batúl, itu orang bukan turunan raja, jadi sonde ada pung hak pegang parenta bagitu. Ma dia nae sa. Te dia datang takuju, pake mulu baminya deng putar-balek orang ko janji omong kosong macam-macam, ais dia dapa pegang parenta di Siria bagitu.<bt>After that, there was a person who ascended replacing him, but that person was no good. In fact, that person was not descended from a raja, so (consequently) he did not have the right to hold rule/govern like that. But he ascended anyway. Cuz (elaboration) he came suddenly/unexpectedly, using an oily mouth (=smooth talker) and deceiving people with various sorts of empty/baseless promises, so then he was able to hold rule in Siria in that way. [EXEG: Heb. chəlaqlaqqowt: flattery, slipperiness, fine promises, intrigues; see TH, NLT, HCE.] [NOTE: NIV: Seleucus's younger brother, Antiochus IV Epiphanes (175-164 BC). Not be given the honor of royalty: Antiochus seized power while the rightful heir (Demetrius I), was still very young. The kingdom was Syro-Palestine.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəlaqlaqqowt: flattery, slipperiness, fine promises"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəlaqlaqqowt: flattery, slipperiness, fine promises</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shalwah: quietness, prosperity"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shalwah: quietness, prosperity</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) howd: majesty, glory"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) howd: majesty, glory</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nivzeh (nif): be despised"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nivzeh (nif): be despised</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV: Seleucus's younger brother, Antiochus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV: Seleucus's younger brother, Antiochus IV Epiphanes (175-164 BC). Not be given the honor of royalty: Antiochus seized power while the rightful heir(Demetrius I), was still very young. The kingdom was Syro-Palestine.</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Ju dia kasi ancor buang banya tantara. Ais dia cabu ame kuasa dari kapala agama Yahudi dong pung bos bésar yang jaga Tuhan Allah pung janji deng Dia pung orang dong.<bt>And he destroyed many soldiers. Then he took away/withdrew power/authority from the high priest of the Yahudi religion who guards/watches over God's promise and His people. [EXEG: see TH, HCE, CEV for ‘covenant priest’.] [NOTE: NIV: Either the high priest Onias III, who was murdered in 170 BC, or Ptolemy VI Philometor of Egypt (181-146 BC)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nəgiyd: leader, prince, chief, prominent"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nəgiyd: leader, prince, chief, prominent person. KD argue this cannot be Onias, who was priest of Antioch, not Jerusalem, and whose murder cannot be traced to Antiochus; nor is there any mention anywhere of a covenant involving Philometor. TWOT: It is perhaps in this derivative that the idea of prominence, which is in the root, comes to fullest expression. The word is used almost fifty times and is applied to leaders in several fields—governmental, military and religious. The word usually is singular and refers to the man at the top, the king, the high priest, etc. But there are references to leaders and captains in the army.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yisshaveruw (nif): they will be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yisshaveruw (nif): they will be broken BDB be broken, be maimed, be crippled, be wrecked; be crushed (fig)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yisshaTfuw (nif): they are swept"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yisshaTfuw (nif): they are swept away, rinsed out</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) sheTef: flood, overflowing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) sheTef: flood, overflowing</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) zəroʕowt: forces (political and military)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) zəroʕowt: forces (political and military)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV: Either the high priest"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV: Either the high priest Onias III, who was murdered in 170 BC, or Ptolemy VI Philometor of Egypt (181-146 BC)</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Dia janji macam-macam ko biar orang dong dukung sang dia. Padahal omong kosong sa. Dia pake itu jalan ko jadi kuat, biar orang yang iko sang dia sadiki sa.<bt>He makes various sorts of promises so that people support him. Wehreas in fact they are empty/baseless/deceptive. He used that way/means to become strong/powerful, even though the people who follow him are only a few.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məʕaT: small amount"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məʕaT: small amount</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕatsam: he will increase in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕatsam: he will increase in power</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mirmah: deceit, treachery"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mirmah: deceit, treachery</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hitchabbəruwt (chbr hitp): join oneself"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hitchabbəruwt (chbr hitp): join oneself to, make an alliance, league together</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV: Antiochus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV: Antiochus</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Sonde sangka-sangka, te dia rampas ame tampa yang paling subur dong. Deng bagitu, dia pegang parenta di da'era yang luas, yang dia pung nene-moyang sonde parná parenta dong. Ju dia bagi kasi orang yang iko sang dia barang mas-perak, deng barang laen yang dia rampas ame dari orang-orang dong. Dia basakongkol ko mau sarbú ame kota yang ada pung benteng dong, ma yang dia bekin tu sonde batahan lama ju.<bt>Surprisingly/without any hint of warning, [+contrary to expectation] he snatches up the most fertile places. In that way, he rules/governs in a wide area, in which his ancestors never ruled. And he divides out to people who follow him things of gold-silver, and other things which he snatches/robs away from other people. He conspires to want to attack the cities that have forts, but what he (actually) does, does not endure long. [EXEG: Heb. mishmanney: fertile spots of; see TH, HCE, NLT for rest of verse. Much vagueness in the Heb.; HCE interprets last clause ‘but only for a time’ as attacking the strongholds “one by one”. It is attractive, but I could not find additional support.] [NOTE: NIV: Either Palestine or Egypt fortresses in Egypt. UBS: As in verse 18, the possible historical references of this verse are too general to be identifiable with any degree of certainty.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) machshəvotayw: his thoughts, plans, intentions"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) machshəvotayw: his thoughts, plans, intentions</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəchasshev (piʕel): think about, devise,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəchasshev (piʕel): think about, devise, plan</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mivtsariym: fortified places, strongholds"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mivtsariym: fortified places, strongholds</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yivzowr: he scattered"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yivzowr: he scattered</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rəkhuwsh: moveable goods"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rəkhuwsh: moveable goods</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shalal: prey, plunder"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shalal: prey, plunder</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) bizzah: spoil, booty"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) bizzah: spoil, booty</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mədiynah: district"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mədiynah: district</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mishmanney: fertile spots of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mishmanney: fertile spots of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shalwah: quietness, prosperity. TWOT: it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shalwah: quietness, prosperity. TWOT: it can become an open door to disaster. Note that one of Sodom's sins was "abundance" of idleness (sha4gat[, Ezk 16:49). It may produce "carelessness" (Prov 1:32).</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV: Either Palestine or Egypt"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV: Either Palestine or Egypt fortresses in Egypt. UBS: As in verse 18, the possible historical references of this verse are too general to be identifiable with any degree of certainty.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ais ju raja Siria di sablá utara kasi samangat sang dia pung tantara dong, ko biar dong baparáng malawan raja Masir di sablá salatan. Ma itu raja Masir kumpul ame tantara lebe banya lai, ju malawan bale sang dia pung musu. Ma raja Masir sonde bisa manáng, tagal raja Siria ator siasat deng pake putar-balek macam-macam.<bt>Then the raja of Siria on the north side encourages/inspires his soldiers, so that they warr against the raja of Masir on the south side. But that raja of Masir gathers together even more soldiers, and opposes back against his enemies. But the raja of Masir could not win, because the raja of Siria conspires/ plotts and uses various sorts of deception(s). [EXEG: referent tracking of Heb. unclear in this vs. E.g. who plots against whom? See TH. We follow HCE in unravelling it.] [NOTE: TH: Verses 25 and 26 are probably a reference to the conflict that pitted Antiochus IV against his nephew, Ptolemy VI (son of his sister Cleopatra; compare verse 17). In the course of the conflict Ptolemy VI was betrayed by certain of his generals.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) machəshavowt: plans, schemes"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) machəshavowt: plans, schemes</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yachshəvuw: people will plan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yachshəvuw: people will plan</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕatsuwm: mighty, strong, countless"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕatsuwm: mighty, strong, countless</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yitgareh (grh hitp): BDB excite"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yitgareh (grh hitp): BDB excite oneself against, engage in strife; excite oneself (against foe), wage war</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yaʕer (hif): BDB he will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yaʕer (hif): BDB he will stir up, rouse; act in an aroused manner</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV: Ptolemy VI."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV: Ptolemy VI.</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Te ada orang Masir yang biasa makan-minum sama-sama deng raja di istana, ma dong sandiri yang cari jalan ko biar raja Masir jato. Nanti dia kaná ancor buang. Dia pung tantara ju lari, sama ke aer banjer kasi anyo kayu karíng. Tantara bam-banya dong ju mati dalam itu paráng.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) there are Masir people who often/normally eat-drink together with the raja in the palace, but they themselves are the ones who look for way(s) so that the raja of Masir falls. Later he will be destroyed. His soldiers will run/flee, like floodwaters sweeping away dry wood. Many soldiers die in that war.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəlaliym: the ones slain"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəlaliym: the ones slain</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yishTowf: it will overflow (like"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yishTowf: it will overflow (like when a river overflows its banks and washes everything away)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) cheylow: his army, his forces"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) cheylow: his army, his forces</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yishbəruwhuw: they will break him"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yishbəruwhuw: they will break him</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) bagow: his delicacies"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) bagow: his delicacies</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) fat: portion"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) fat: portion</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV: Ptolemy's army"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV: Ptolemy's army</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ais itu ju, itu raja dua orang dudu ko makan di satu meja. Satu baputar-balek satu, tagal dong dua pung hati cuma tau pikir jahat tarús sa. Satu coba batipu ame satu, ma sonde jadi, te Tuhan Allah yang nanti ator dia pung waktu yang pas.<bt>After that, the two rajas sit to eat at the same table. One deceives the other, because  the two of them's livers only know how/are able to think evil continually. One tries to trick the other, but do not succeed, cuz (elaboration) God is the one who will arrange the perfect/appropriate time. [NOTE to daughter translations: check your wording in Gen. 6:5.] [EXEG: complex. See discussion in TH. Some take ‘table’ to mean ‘eating’, whereas NLT takes it as a ‘conference table’ to discuss terms. But that may be anachronistic. There is also dispute if this is a one-off, or an ongoing thing, repeated over time.] [NOTE: TH: During the course of his military campaign, Antiochus IV took his nephew (Ptolemy VI) prisoner but apparently treated him well (receiving him at his own table) in order to scheme and seek ways of seizing political power in Egypt.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mowʕed: appointed time"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mowʕed: appointed time</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) titslach: it will [not] advance,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) titslach: it will [not] advance, prosper, make progress, succeed, be profitable</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kazav: lie, untruth, falsehood, deceptive"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kazav: lie, untruth, falsehood, deceptive thing</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləmeraʕ: to do mischief; dirty"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləmeraʕ: to do mischief; dirty tricks, evil</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləvavam: their &quot;hearts&quot; (= minds)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləvavam: their "hearts" (= minds)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV: Antiochus and Ptolemy, who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV: Antiochus and Ptolemy, who was living in Antiochus's custody.</Message></Annotation><v n="28" />Waktu raja Siria mau pulang pi dia pung negrí sandiri, dia bawa ame banya barang mahal dong. Ma dia sonde puas, te dia putus bekin rusak Tuhan pung janji deng Dia pung orang Isra'el dong. Dia bekin iko dia pung mau, ais baru dia pulang pi dia pung negrí sandiri.<bt>When the raja of Siria is going to return home to his own country, he takes away many expensive things. But he is not satisfied, cuz (elaboration) he decides to destroy/damage God2's promise with His people of Isra'el. He does what he like, and only then does he go back to his own country. [EXEG: ‘holy covenant’ = God with the Jews; TH, CEV, HCE.] [NOTE: NIV study Bible says Antiochus plundered the temple in Jerusalem, set up a garrison there and massacred many Jews in the city.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV study Bible says Antiochus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV study Bible says Antiochus plundered the temple in Jerusalem, set up a garrison there and massacred many Jews in the city. God's spesho deal=the holy covenant.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ma pas dia pung waktu ju, raja Siria pi ulang lai ko baparáng malawan sang raja Masir di salatan. Ma ini kali sonde sama ke waktu dolu.<bt>But just at the right time, the raja of Siria goes again to war against the raja of Masir in the south. But this time is not the same as the previous time(s).</bt><v n="30" />Te ada banya kapal dari sablá barat yang datang baparáng malawan sang raja Siria tu. Andia ko dia pung hati jato, ais dia deng dia pung tantara dong ondor. Ma dia maruak, sampe dia kasi tunju dia pung mara, malawan samua orang yang pegang Tuhan pung janji. Ma dia ju kasi tunju dia pung hati bae sang orang yang bale balakang kasi tenga Tuhan pung janji.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) there are many ships from the west side who come warring against the raja of Siria. That is why his liver fell (=discouraged, depressed), and/so he and his soldiers withdrew/retreated. But he was fed up, to the point that he displayed his anger, opposing everyone who holds God2's promise. But he also showed his good liver/goodness/kindness/favour to people who turned their backs and abandoned God2's promise. [EXEG: see discussion in TH. Heb. kittiym: Cyprus, but also used as a generic term for ships used in the Mediterranean Sea. Used generically this was in Qumran texts.] [NOTE: NIV: Ships of the west coast, LXX Romans: Roman vessels under the command of Popilius Laenas. Those who forsake the holy covenant: Apostate Jews (see also Dan 11.32).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) bəriyt: covenant, agreement"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) bəriyt: covenant, agreement</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕozvey: the ones that forsake"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕozvey: the ones that forsake</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yaven: he will pay attention"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yaven: he will pay attention</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) zaʕam: have indignation, be indignant,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) zaʕam: have indignation, be indignant, be angrily indignant, be defiant; be abhorrent; express indignation in speech, denounce, curse</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nikh'ah (k'h nif): he will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nikh'ah (k'h nif): he will be disheartened, cowed</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kittiym: Cyprus, but also used"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kittiym: Cyprus, but also used as a generic term for ships used in the Mediterranean Sea. Used generically this was in Qumran texts.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tsiyyiym: ships, large boats (in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tsiyyiym: ships, large boats (in Pidgin the huge Queen Elizabeth II, which has visited here, is still a 'boat.')</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV: Ships of the west"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV: Ships of the west coast, LXX Romans: Roman vessels under the command of Popilius Laenas. Those who forsake the holy covenant: Apostate Jews (see also Dan 11.32).</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ais raja Siria utus dia pung tantara dong, ko maso pi benteng di kota Yerusalem. Ju dong maso pi dalam Tuhan Allah pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat di situ, ais bekin kamomos itu tampa barisi. Dong suru bilang, &lt;Kapala agama dong sonde bole bekin korban bakar, yang dong biasa bekin tiap hari!&gt; Ais itu ju, dong kasi badiri satu patong songgo di tampa yang sonde pantas buat dia, andia di tampa pamali di Tuhan Allah pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat, sampe orang dong sonde sambayang lai di itu tampa. Andia ko Tuhan Allah bale balakang kasi tenga itu tampa.<bt>Then the raja of Siria sent/commissioned his soldiers to enter into the fort in the city of Yeruslaem. And they want into God's Central House of Worship (*Temple) there, and made filthy/defiled that clean/holy place. They ordered saying, &lt;The priests may not make the burnt sacrifices which they do every day!&gt; After that they erected a statue of traditional worship in a place that was inappropriate for it, that is the taboo place in God's Central House of Worship (*Temple), to the point that people no longer prayed/worshipped in that place. That is why God turns (His) back abandoning that place. [EXEG: (last sentence) Heb. məshowmem (shmm poʕel): appalling, causing horror. BDB be stunned; appalling, causing horror (participle). TWOT: The book of Daniel has four passages employing the Polel form of the verb (mesho4me4m and sho=me4m). There is a causative (or, better, factitive) force here similar to the use of the Hiphil, except that the Hiphil generally involves a physical devastation, while the Polel seems to put more stress on the fact that someone has caused the sanctuary or altar to be polluted, thus rendering it unfit for the worship and service of God. These passages are Dan 8:13; 11:31; 9:27; and 12:11.] [NOTE to daughter translations: compare with your wording in Mark 13:14, Matt. 24:15, and Dan. 9:27, but don't force identical wording if it doesn't fit this context.] [DISCOURSE: prohibition of sacrifices made into direct speech, following RL patterns.] [NOTE: NIV: The altar of the pagan god Zeus Olympius set in in 168 BC by Antiochus Epiphanes and prefiguring a similar abomination that Jesus predicted would be erected. -- (CEG) so it appears this happened more than once.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məshowmem (shmm poʕel): appalling, causing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məshowmem (shmm poʕel): appalling, causing horror. BDB be stunned; appalling, causing horror (participle). TWOT: The book of Daniel has four passages employing the Polel form of the verb (mesho4me4m and sho=me4m). There is a causative (or, better, factitive) force here similar to the use of the Hiphil, except that the Hiphil generally involves a physical devastation, while the Polel seems to put more stress on the fact that someone has caused the sanctuary or altar to be polluted, thus rendering it unfit for the worship and service of God. These passages are Dan 8:13; 11:31; 9:27; and 12:11.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shiqquwts: BDB detestable thing or"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shiqquwts: BDB detestable thing or idol, abominable thing, abomination, idol, detested thing. TWOT: This noun is always used in connection with idolatrous practices, either referring to the idols themselves as being abhorrent and detestable in God's sight, or to something associated with the idolatrous ritual. Idols generally are referred to as an abomination (Jer 16:18; Ezk 5:11; 7:20; II Chr 15:8, etc)... Antiochus Epiphanes, as prophesied in Dan 11:31, and who is typical of Antichrist, set up an altar to, and image of, Zeus in the temple. This is called the "abomination that causes desolation," a desecration of the altar which destroys its true purpose. Just so will Antichrist establish an abomination in the sanctuary, a demonic counterfeit worship (Dan 9:27, 12:11).</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tamiyd: continuity. TWOT: used alone"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tamiyd: continuity. TWOT: used alone to designate the daily burnt offering in Dan 8:11-13; 11:31; 12:11.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) heSiyruw (Swr hif): they will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) heSiyruw (Swr hif): they will remove. BDB cause to turn aside, cause to depart, remove, take away, put away, depose</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) maʕoz: place or means of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) maʕoz: place or means of safety, protection, refuge, stronghold</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) miqdash: TWOT: Holy place, sanctuary,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) miqdash: TWOT: Holy place, sanctuary, chapel, hallowed part. (ASV and RSV similar except that RSV translates "holy things" in Num 10:21, Ezk 44:8; "sacred area" in Ezk 43:21 and "temple" in Dan 11:31.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hilləluw (piʕel): they will destroy"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hilləluw (piʕel): they will destroy its sacred character, profane, render unusable for worship</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yaʕəmoduw: they will take their"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yaʕəmoduw: they will take their positions to attack an enemy, get into position</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV: Dan 9.25, 12.11; Mt"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV: Dan 9.25, 12.11; Mt 24.15, Lk 21.20. The altar of the pagan god Zeus Olympius set in in 168 BC by Antiochus Epiphanes and prefiguring a similar abomination that Jesus predicted would be erected.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:31" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 9:27, 12:11; Mateos 24:15; Markus 13:14</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Ais raja Siria mulu baminya deng bajanji omong kosong macam-macam, ko biar orang yang bale balakang kasi tenga Tuhan pung janji, iko sang dia. Ma orang yang kanál Tuhan Allah deng batúl, deng iko sang Tuhan nanti sonde ondor, te dong tanam kaki ko malawan sang itu raja.<bt>Then the raja of Siria oily mouthed (=smooth talk) and made various empty/baseless promises, so that people turn their backs and abandon God2's promise, following him. But people who truly know God, and follow God2 will not retreat, cuz (elaboration) they place their feet (=are committed) to oppose that raja. [NOTE: TH: Antiochus IV knew how to use promises and threats at the same time. He mercilessly persecuted those who remained faithful to the religion of their ancestors, and he promised rewards to those who would renounce it.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕasuw: do what they are"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕasuw: do what they are going to do. Could be a reference to the Maccabees.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yachəziquw: be strong; BDB have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yachəziquw: be strong; BDB have or take or keep hold of, retain, hold up, sustain, support</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəlaqqowt: smooth words, flattery"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəlaqqowt: smooth words, flattery</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yachəniyf (chnp hif): he will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yachəniyf (chnp hif): he will seduce, corrupt, pervert, make apostasize; BDB pollute; make profane, make godless, cause to be defiled</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) marshiyʕey (rshʕ hif partcpl): the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) marshiyʕey (rshʕ hif partcpl): the ones who act wickedly concerning</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Ada pamimpin dong yang mangarti banya hal, yang tunju jalan kasi sang banya orang ko biar dong tau musti idop karmana deng bekin karmana. Ma ada pamimpin saparu, dong lempar maso pi dalam bui; saparu, dong rampas ame dong pung barang; saparu, dong bunu bekin mati pake kalewang; deng saparu lai, dong bakar idop-idop.<bt>There are leaders who understand many things (=wise [short form]), who show the way for many people so that they know how they must live and what they must do. But there are some leaders, who they throw into prison; some, they rob their belongings; some, the kill with a sword; and some others, they burn alive. [EXEG: Heb. ‘wise among the people’ = leaders, TH, NLT, HCE.] [DISCOURSE: reordered for information load and for a better RL progresion.] [NOTE: NIV: The godly leaders of the resistance movement, the Hasidim. Heb 11.36-38.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) bizzah: spoil, booty"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) bizzah: spoil, booty</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shəviy: captivity"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shəviy: captivity</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) lehavah: flames"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) lehavah: flames</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nikhshəluw (kshl nif): they will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nikhshəluw (kshl nif): they will be made weak, wobbly. BDB stumble; be tottering, be feeble</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yaviynuw (byn hif): cause to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yaviynuw (byn hif): cause to understand</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) maskiyley (skl hif partcpl): the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) maskiyley (skl hif partcpl): the ones who understand the reasons why things are happening</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV: The godly leaders of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV: The godly leaders of the resistance movement, the Hasidim. Heb 11.36-38.</Message></Annotation><v n="34" />Waktu ini sangsara macam-macam ni jato kaná di pamimpin Yahudi dong, orang dong cuma bantu asal-asal sang dong sa. Banya orang janji mau tolong, ma dong pung janji omong kosong sa.<bt>When these varous sufferings fall upon/effect the Yahudi leaders, people only go through the motions of pretending to help/for the sake of appearances  (lit: they only help as long as-REDUP). Many people promise to want to help, but their promises are empty. [EXEG: Heb. ‘little help’ = a) not much effort, or b) not many people? Most authorities lean towards (a). Heb. chəlaqlaqqowt: fine promises but no action.] [NOTE: NIV: The early successes of the guerilla uprising (168 BC) that originated in Modein, 17 miles NW of Jerusalem, under the leadership of Mattathias and his son Judas Maccabeus. In December 165 BC the altar of the temple was rededicated. See TH discussion for 2 more views on this verse.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəlaqlaqqowt: fine promises but no"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəlaqlaqqowt: fine promises but no action</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nilwuw: they will join"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nilwuw: they will join</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məʕaT: a little"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məʕaT: a little</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yeʕazruw: they will help. Macccabees?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yeʕazruw: they will help. Macccabees?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hikkashlam (hif inf): in their"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hikkashlam (hif inf): in their tottering, precarious circumstances</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV: The early successes of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV: The early successes of the guerilla uprising (168 BC) that originated in Modein, 17 miles NW of Jerusalem, under the leadership of Mattathias and his son Judas Maccabeus. In December 165 BC the altar of the temple was rededicated.</Message></Annotation><v n="35" />Pamimpin saparu yang mangarti banya hal, kaná siksa, ais dong pung parcaya tagoyang. Deng bagitu, dong kaná coba, ko biar dong jadi barisi sama ke mas tulen, te sonde ada kamomos di dong pung hati deng dong pung idop lai. Ini sangsara dong maen jalan tarús-tarús sampe pas dia pung waktu.&gt;<bt>Some leaders who understand many things (=wise), are tortured/persecuted, and/so their belief is shaken. In that way, they are tested, so that they become clean/pure like pure gold, cuz (elaboration) there is no filth/impurity in their liver and in their lives anymore. This suffering/torment keeps on going continually until the appropriate time.&gt; [EXEG: Heb. yikkashluw (kshl nif): they will be made to totter, knocked off balance. NRSV, UBS ‘fall’. However NJB and NIV take another sense ‘stumble’, which seems to fit the larger context better. NLT takes middle ground ‘fall victim to persecution’ -- focusing on the process and leaving the result up for grabs (do they, or don't they fall?), which seems to better reflect the Heb. KD take it as all the things that happen to the leaders have a purifying effect not only on the ones suffering, but on all God's people.] [EXEG: Heb. ‘it is yet for the time appointed’ 2 views: a) there is a gap of time before the designated time, b) this keeps happening right up until the designated time. We follow (b), which is explicit in HCE and implied by NLT, CEV, NET.].</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mowʕed: appointed time"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mowʕed: appointed time</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) lalben (hif inf): to make"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) lalben (hif inf): to make white, spotless, clean</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləvarer (piʕel inf): to purify"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləvarer (piʕel inf): to purify</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) bahem: test them? test others"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) bahem: test them? test others by means of what happens to them?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) litsrowf (inf): to test [them]"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) litsrowf (inf): to test [them]</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yikkashluw (kshl nif): they will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yikkashluw (kshl nif): they will be made to totter, knocked off balance. UBS: "Fall" taken by tev as in the two previous verses to refer to death. Note, however, that njb and niv seem to take it in another sense, translating "stumble." Similarly ab takes it to mean "will be tested." Given the immediate context, probably the idea of being killed is intended. JG: In 33 some are killed and some are not, both referred to as "made to totter, knocked off balance." KD take it as all the things that happen to the leaders have a purifying effect not only on the ones suffering, but on all God's people.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV: See Dan 11.40, 12..4,9."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV: See Dan 11.40, 12..4,9. Daniel concludes his predictions about Antiochus Epiphanes and begins to prophesy concerning the more distant future.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ada raja yang kapala bésar<bt>There is a raja with a big head (=arrogant)</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Ais, itu ana bua dari sorga sambung dia pung omong bilang, &lt;Itu raja dari Siria mau bekin iko dia pung suka sandiri sa. Dia angka-angka dia pung diri. Dia kasi tau orang bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta ni, lebe hebat dari samua dewa-dewi dong!&gt;&gt; Dia ju omong bekin rusak nama bae dari Tuhan Allah yang Paling Tinggi, yang lebe hebat dari samua dewa-dewi dong. Itu raja karjá apa sa, na, jadi, sampe waktu yang Tuhan pung mara su turun. Te samua yang Tuhan kasi tau memang bilang mau jadi, na, pasti jadi pas dia pung waktu.<bt>Then, that underling from heaven (*angel) continued his speaking saying, &lt;That raja from Siria likes to/is going to just do what he likes. He keeps elevating/promoting himself. He tels people saying, &lt;&lt;I am greater/more amazing than the deities!&gt;&gt; He also speaks ruining the good name/reputation (=slander/blaspheme) of the Most High God, who is greater/more amazing that all the deities. That raja does whatever, na, it happens/comes into being/succeeds, until the time when God2's anger descends. Cuz (elaboration) everything that God2 has foretold is going to happen, na, surely will happen just at its appropriate/appointed time. [DISCOURSE: made direct speech following RL norms.] [EXEG: Heb. ‘God of gods’. See discussion in TH for issues to watch out for.] [EXEG: Heb. ‘until the indignation is accomplished’. TH recommends ‘God's anger’, followed by CEV and HCE. But in our lgs we need to avoid saying /Tuhan pung mara su abis/ ‘God's anger is finished’, which can give the impression ‘done, once and for all time’; we also need to avoid /Tuhan pung mara su dingin/ ‘God's anger is cooled’, which implies the reason has been dealt with and relationships are back in order--which is not what seems to be in focus here. That is only accomplished through Christ's sacrificial death.] [DISCOURSE (pericope structure 11:36-45): Seems to be a big shift in theme here. The best discussion is in a NET note. NIV puts a section break here and says these next verses don't fit Antiochus Epiphanes. They say it is talking about the Antichrist (see Dan 7.8, 9.27; Rev. 13.5-8). HCE also puts a section break here. UBS: still the king of Syria.  NRSV, NLT, CEV, TB, NET don't put a break here. Some put it at vs. 40, other don't. Our protocols say where two positions have equal support we follow the TB. So no break here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) neʕəsatah (nif): it is done;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) neʕəsatah (nif): it is done; made; produced; offered; observed; used</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nechəratsah (chrts nif): be decisive."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nechəratsah (chrts nif): be decisive. UBS: God will bring about what he has planned</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) zaʕam: anger, indignation. UBS God's"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) zaʕam: anger, indignation. UBS God's anger. KD God's anger against his people</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kalah: it is finished"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kalah: it is finished</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hitsliyach (tslch hif): he will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hitsliyach (tslch hif): he will succeed, prosper. BDB make prosperous, bring to successful issue, cause to prosper; show or experience prosperity, prosper</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nifla'owt: extraordinary things; in a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nifla'owt: extraordinary things; in a negative sense, dreadful things</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yitgaddel (hitp): he will make"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yitgaddel (hitp): he will make himself great, magnify himself</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yitrowmem (hitp): he will exalt"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yitrowmem (hitp): he will exalt himself</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV: says this doesn't fit"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV: says this doesn't fit Antiochus Epiphanes. They say it is talking about the Antichrist (see Dan 7.8, 9.27; Rev. 13.5-8). UBS: still the king of Syria.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:36" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 7:8, 9:27; 2 Tesalonika 2:3-4; Dunya Model Baru 13:5-8</note><v n="37" />Itu raja pung nene-moyong parná songgo sang dong pung dewa-dewi, ma itu raja sonde tunju hormat kasi sang dong ju. Parampuan dong suka songgo sang dewi satu, ma itu raja sonde kasi tunju hormat sang dia ju. Biar lai dewa-dewi mana sa, na, itu raja sonde tunju hormat kasi sang dia. Te dia anggap diri lebe hebat dari samua dewa-dewi dong.<bt>That raja's ancestors had once traditional.worshipped their deities, but that raja does not show respect to them either. Women like to traditional.worship a certain goddess, but that raja does not show respect to her either. Even more than that, whatever deity, na, that raja does not show respect to him/her. Cuz (elaboration) he considers himself greater/more impressive than all the deities.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chemdat: the one who is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chemdat: the one who is precious, pleasant, desired</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yaviyn (byn hif): he will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yaviyn (byn hif): he will [not] pay attention</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV The one desired by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV The one desired by women: usually interpreted as Tammuz (Eze 8.14) or the Messiah. Tammuz was a Babylonian fertility god. The women of Jerusalem wailed his dying, which they thought caused the annual wilting of vegetables.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Biar bagitu, ma itu raja mau songgo sang dewa satu yang dia pung nene-moyang sandiri dong sonde kanál, andia dewa yang tukang jaga benteng dong. Ais dia kasi itu dewa mas, perak, batu mangkilat, deng barang mahal yang laen dong.<bt>Even that being the case, nevertheless that raja wants to traditional.worship one god whom his own ancestors did not know/recognise, that is the god/deity who guards forts. Then he gives that god gold, silver, precious stones, and other expensive things.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəmudowt: precious things"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəmudowt: precious things</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəqarah: precious, expensive"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəqarah: precious, expensive</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yədaʕuhuw: they [did not] know"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yədaʕuhuw: they [did not] know him</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəkhabbed (piʕel): make honorable, glorify"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəkhabbed (piʕel): make honorable, glorify</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kannow: his place?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kannow: his place?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) maʕuzziym: strongholds, refuges"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) maʕuzziym: strongholds, refuges</Message></Annotation><v n="39" />Dia baparáng malawan sang benteng yang paling kuat dong, bawa nama dewa dari tampa yang jao ko tolong sang dia. Kalo orang mangaku dia, ju dengar-dengar sang dia, na, dia tunju hormat kasi sang dong, ais angka sang dong ko dong pegang parenta sang banya orang. Dia ju bagi tana kasi sang dong, asal dong bayar.<bt>He wars against the strongest forts, bearing the name/reputation of a far/foreign deity to help him. If/when people acknowledge him, and listen to/obey him, na, he shows respect to them, and elevates/appoints them to hold rule/govern many people. He also divides out land to them, as long as they pay. [EXEG: Q: what does he do to people who acknowledge him? Heb. ‘increase, multiply’ is vague. NRSV he makes them more wealthy; NLT he honors them; CEV undertranslated (again).] [EXEG: TH recognises ‘numerous problems regarding the text and its interpretation in this verse’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məchiyr: price, gain. TWOT: the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məchiyr: price, gain. TWOT: the pagan Cyrus, whom God raised up, released the captives of Israel for no price or reward (Isa 45:13). This is the opposite of Antichrist who will divide the land for personal gain (Dan 11:39).</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəchalleq (piʕel): he will apportion,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəchalleq (piʕel): he will apportion, assign, divide</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) himshiylam (hif): he will cause"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) himshiylam (hif): he will cause them to rule, exercise dominion</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yarbeh (rbh hif): he will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yarbeh (rbh hif): he will increase, multiply</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hikkiyr (nkr hif): recognize; KD"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hikkiyr (nkr hif): recognize; KD prefers this (q. yakkiyr (nkr hif)): recognize with honor</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nekhar: foreigner"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nekhar: foreigner</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mivtsərey: fortifications of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mivtsərey: fortifications of</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40" />Kalo itu waktu su mau deka abis, na, raja Masir di salatan baparáng ko mau usir buang sang raja Siria di utara. Ma raja Siria mau sarbú bale sama ke satu angin tofan yang fuu datang. Te dia datang bawa banya kareta paráng, tantara nae kuda dong, deng kapal bam-banya. Dong nae sarbú malawan banya negrí. Kasi kala sang dong, ju dong lari lewat sama ke satu banjer bésar datang.<bt>When that (future) time is about to end, na, the raja of Masir in the south wars to try to evict the raja of Siria in the north. But the raja of Siria wants to attack back like a (wind)storm/cyclone which blows coming. Cuz (elaboration) he comes bringing many war wagons/chariots, soldiers on horseback/cavalry, and many ships. They ascend attacking against many countries. Defeating them, they run past/over them like a great flood coming.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕavar: he will pass through"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕavar: he will pass through</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shaTaf: he will overflow (used"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shaTaf: he will overflow (used of floods)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əratsowt: countries"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əratsowt: countries</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) va': he will go, in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) va': he will go, in the sense of 'attack'</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'əniyyowt: ships"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'əniyyowt: ships</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) farashiym: cavalry, nâ kanaka noholio"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) farashiym: cavalry, nâ kanaka noholio</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yistaʕer (sʕr hitp): storm against,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yistaʕer (sʕr hitp): storm against, come as a storm</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yitnaggach (hitp): engage in thrusting,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yitnaggach (hitp): engage in thrusting, like the ram in 8:4</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dong nae sarbú malawan banya negrí,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">Dong nae sarbú malawan banya negrí, ju lewat sang dong sama ke satu banjer bésar datang.</Message></Annotation><v n="41" />Dia ju maso sarbú ame itu Tana Bagus, andia tana Isra'el. Orang bam-banya dong jadi korban. Ma orang dong di tana Edom, tana Moab, deng orang Amon saparu lolos, deng dong sonde kala batúl-batúl dari dia.<bt>He also enters attacking that Beautiful Land, that is the land of Isra'el. Many people become victims. But some of the people in the land of Edom, the land of Moab, and the people of Amon get through/survive, and they are not fully/truly defeated by him. [EXEG: Heb. ‘beautiful land’ = Israel. TH, NLT, CEV, HCE. (cf. Daniel 11:16, 11:45, 8:9) Heb. rabbowt: many taken by some as “tens of thousands” but you have to change the Heb text to do that. We follow our protocols and the Heb. text. See discussion in TH.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yimmalTuw miyyadow: they will escape"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yimmalTuw miyyadow: they will escape from his power</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yikkasheluw (nif): they will be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yikkasheluw (nif): they will be destabilized</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rabbowt: many"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rabbowt: many</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'erets hattsəviy: beautiful land. 11:16,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'erets hattsəviy: beautiful land. 11:16, 11:45, 8:9</Message></Annotation><v n="42" />Dia kasi kala banya negrí. Tana Masir ju sonde lolos.<bt>He defeats many countries. The land of Masir (=Egypt) also does not get through/survive.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) lifleyTah (noun): deliverance"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) lifleyTah (noun): deliverance</Message></Annotation><v n="43" />Dia rampas ame hak ko ator barang mas deng perak, deng samua macam barang mahal yang orang Masir kasi sambunyi dong. Dia ju pegang parenta di tana orang Libya, orang Etiopia, deng orang Sudan.<bt>He snatches the right to manage things of gold and silver, and all types of expensive things which the Masir people have hidden. He also holds rule/governs in the land of the people of Libya, the people of Etiopia, and the people of Sudan. [EXEG: Heb. kushiym includes both Ethiopia and northern Sudan. HCE, TH, TEV. Ethiopia by itself is too narrow, as is Sudan by itself.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mitsʕadayw: at his footsteps"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mitsʕadayw: at his footsteps</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kushiym: Sudanese"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kushiym: Sudanese</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) luviym: Libyans"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) luviym: Libyans</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chəmudowt: precious things"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chəmudowt: precious things</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mikhmanney: hidden treasures"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mikhmanney: hidden treasures</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mashal: he will rule"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mashal: he will rule</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="44" />Ma dia dengar kabar dari sablá timur deng dari sablá utara yang bekin dia pung hati jadi tar enak. Andia ko dia maruak, ais pi ko mau kasi ancor buang banya tampa.<bt>But he hears news from the east side and the north side which makes his liver unwell/unsettled/disturbed. That is why he gets fed up/reaches his limit and goes to try to destroy many places. [EXEG: Heb. yəvahəluhuw (bhl piʕel): alarm, dismay, terrify.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhachəriym (hif): to completely destroy"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhachəriym (hif): to completely destroy</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləhashmiyd (shmd hif): to exterminate"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləhashmiyd (shmd hif): to exterminate</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chema': rage, displeasure, anger"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chema': rage, displeasure, anger</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tsafown: north"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tsafown: north</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mizrach: east"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mizrach: east</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yəvahəluhuw (bhl piʕel): dismay, terrify"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yəvahəluhuw (bhl piʕel): dismay, terrify</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shəmuʕowt: report, news, rumor"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shəmuʕowt: report, news, rumor</Message></Annotation><v n="45" />Nanti dia pasang raja pung tenda di satu tampa. Di situ, Laut Tenga ada di dia pung sablá barat, deng Tuhan pung gunung yang hebat ada di dia pung sablá timur. Waktu dia di situ ju, dia pung waktu su abis, ma sonde ada yang datang tolong sang dia.&gt;<bt>Later he will set up the raja's tent in one place. At that place, the Middle Sea (=Mediterranean) is on his west side, and God2's amazing mountain is on his east side. While he is there, his time is over/finished, but there is none who comes to help him.&gt; [EXEG: Heb. ‘beautiful holy mountain’. NIV ‘Jerusalem's temple mount’, CEV ‘Mount Zion’. but the term is also sometimes used for Sinai. TH notes that it may be deliberately vague. We keep it vague as does NRSV, NLT, HCE, TB.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) qittsow: his end"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) qittsow: his end</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'appadnow: his palace (from Persian)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'appadnow: his palace (from Persian)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) 'ahəley: tents of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) 'ahəley: tents of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yiTTaʕ (nTʕ): he will plant."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yiTTaʕ (nTʕ): he will plant. TWOT: Other figurative uses of naTaʕ include "pitching" tents (Dan 11:45) and "driving" nails (Eccl 12:11).</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV: Jerusalem's temple mount. Rev."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV: Jerusalem's temple mount. Rev. 16.13-16.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Nanti orang dong dapa idop kambali<bt>Later people will be brought back to life/live again</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="12" />
      <v n="1" />Itu ana bua dari sorga sambung dia pung omong sang beta bilang, &lt;Itu waktu, Tuhan Allah pung ana bua dari sorga dong pung panglima yang jaga lu pung bangsa tu, andia Mikael, nanti dia lia bae-bae sang dong. Te biar ada hari-hari susa, yang orang sonde parná rasa dari dolu-dolu waktu manusia dong baru mulai bekin negrí, sampe deng itu waktu. Biar bagitu ju, ma lu pung bangsa dapat salamat. Andia orang yang pung nama dong ada tatulis dalam Tuhan pung buku yang dapat salamat.<bt>That underling from heaven (*angel) continued speaking to me saying, &lt;At that time, God's underlings from heaven's (top military) commander who guards your-sg people/race, that is Mikael, he will look after them carefully. Cuz (elaboration) even though there are days of difficulty which people have never felt/experienced from long ago when humans first started making countries, until that time. Even that being the case, nevertheless your-sp people/race are rescued/saved. That is the ones whose names are written in God2's book of those who are rescued/saved. [DISCOURSE: reestablish speaker, as suggested in TH.] [EXEG: Heb. yaʕəmod: he will stand up/ arise. Q: in what sense? assume a position? take a stand? take responsibility? Context favours ‘rise to the occasion = do his job guarding Israel’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yimmaleT (nif): he will escape"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yimmaleT (nif): he will escape</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) gowy: nation. UBS: this may"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) gowy: nation. UBS: this may be understood to refer to the beginning of nationhood in general (nrsv has "since nations first came into existence"). However, it is also possible that it refers to the beginning of the nation of Israel. But since the people of Israel almost certainly thought of themselves as being the first nation to come into existence, the two may be thought of as being identical.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hyowt (hyh qal inf): BDB"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hyowt (hyh qal inf): BDB happen, fall out, occur, take place, come about, come to pass; come into being, become; arise, appear, come</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nihyətah (hyh nif): BDB occur,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nihyətah (hyh nif): BDB occur, come to pass, be done, be brought about; be done, be finished, be gone</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tsarah: distress, trouble"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tsarah: distress, trouble</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕomed: the one standing (to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕomed: the one standing (to protect)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) sar: commander, leader, prince. TWOT:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) sar: commander, leader, prince. TWOT: the angelic princes of Persia and Greece who contend with Michael "the great prince" (10:13, 20, 21; 12:1).</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yaʕəmod: he will stand up"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yaʕəmod: he will stand up (in what sense)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV: Michael."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV: Michael.</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 24:21; Markus 13:19; Dunya Model Baru 7:14, 12:7</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Banya orang yang su mati ais orang su kubur ame sang dong, nanti idop kambali. Dong saparu dapa idop yang batúl, yang sonde tau putus-putus. Dong saparu dapa idop kambali deng malu yang sonde tau putus-putus ju. Deng samua orang yang inga sang dong, rasa malu ju.<bt>Many people who have already died and whom people have buried them, will later live again. Some of them get true life which never ceases/without interruption. Some of them are brought back to live with shame that also never ceases. And everyone who remembers/thinks of them also feels shame. [EXEG: Heb. ‘sleep in the dust of the earth’ = NLT ‘whose bodies lie dead and buried’] [EXEG: ‘sleep’ and ‘awake’ here seem to be universally accepted as ‘died’ and ‘come back to life’. See TH,] [EXEG: Heb. dir'own ‘abhorrence, aversion, contempt, disgrace’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) End of S section"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) End of S section</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) dir'own: abhorrence, aversion. Isaiah 66:24"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) dir'own: abhorrence, aversion. Isaiah 66:24 feel pilau</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chərafowt: reproaches, blame"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chərafowt: reproaches, blame</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chayyey: lives of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chayyey: lives of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yaqiytsuw (hif): they will wake"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yaqiytsuw (hif): they will wake up. TWOT: used four times with the meaning "to awaken from the dead," i.e. resurrection. Before Elisha brought the Shunammite widow's son to life, Gehazi reported, "The lad has not awakened" (II Kgs 4:31). Job, in a pessimistic section, speaks of man lying down and not rising again, indeed, "He will not awake nor be aroused out of his sleep" (Job 14:12; see also v. 14). Job did, however, hope for the resurrection (19:25; 14:14b (NIV), see h[a4lap). In Isaiah's apocalypse, the resurrection hope is explicitly stated with respect to Judah, "Their corpses will rise. You who lie in the dust, awake and shout for joy" (26:19). But it is Daniel (12:2) who gives the clearest expression of the eschatological hope of resurrection: "And many of those who sleep in the dust of the ground will awake, these to everlasting life, but the others to disgrace and everlasting contempt."</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yosheney (noun? partcple?): the sleepers"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yosheney (noun? partcple?): the sleepers of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) NIV: John 5.24-30. Others to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) NIV: John 5.24-30. Others to shame and everlasting contempt. Isaiah 25:7, but here two destinies. 2 Timothy 1:10</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 25:7, 26:19; Mateos 25:46; Yohanis 5:24-30; 2 Timotius 1:10</note><v n="3" />Orang yang mangarti banya hal iko Tuhan pung pikiran, nanti basinar sama ke langit. Deng orang yang kasi tunju Tuhan pung jalan lurus sang banya orang, nanti dong manyala tarús-tarús sama ke bintang-bintang.<bt>People who understand many things according to God2's thinking, will shine like the sky. And people who show God2's straight/true/correct path to many people, they will shine2 continually like the stars. [EXEG: Heb. yazhiruw (hif, only here): ‘they will shine’; most authorities take ‘shine’ here as literal, and consistent with the world view re: those who excel. See TH.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) End of P section."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) End of P section.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ʕed: future time"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ʕed: future time</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) matsdiyqey (tsdq hif partcpl pl):"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) matsdiyqey (tsdq hif partcpl pl): the ones who turn people to righteousness</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) raqiyaʕ: expanse, firmament. TWOT: The"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) raqiyaʕ: expanse, firmament. TWOT: The Mosaic account of creation uses raqiyaʕ interchangeably for the "open expanse of the heavens" in which birds fly (Gen 1:20 NASB), i.e. the atmosphere.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) zohar: brightness"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) zohar: brightness</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yazhiruw (hif, only here): they"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yazhiruw (hif, only here): they will shine</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) maskiliym (skl hif partcpl pl):"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) maskiliym (skl hif partcpl pl): those who understand the reasons why things happen. TWOT: While biyn indicates "distinguishing between," sakal relates to an intelligent knowledge of the reason. There is the process of thinking through a complex arrangement of thoughts resulting in a wise dealing and use of good practical common sense. Another end result is the emphasis upon being successful.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ma lu, Daniel, musti jaga ini kata-kata dong, ko biar orang sonde tau. Lu musti taro segel di ini tulisan sampe hari kiamat. Te banya orang lari pi-datang ko mau cari tau so'al ini hal dong.&gt;<bt>But you-sg, Daniel, must guard these words, so that people don't know. You must place a seal on these writings until the last days. Cuz (elaboration) many people run back-and-forth trying to find out about these things.&gt; [EXEG: ‘knowledge/evil shall increase’. See TH for summary of widespread confusion surrounding this phrase. We follow HCE, which makes sense of connecting the last 2 clauses in context.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tirbeh: they will cause to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tirbeh: they will cause to increase</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shoTəTuw (shwT polel): they will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shoTəTuw (shwT polel): they will rush to and fro</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) chətom (imperv): seal it up."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) chətom (imperv): seal it up. BDB seal, affix one's seal; seal up, fasten up by sealing</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Sətom (imperv): keep hidden. BDB"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Sətom (imperv): keep hidden. BDB stop up; shut up, keep close; secret (participle)</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dunya Model Baru 22:10</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Hari kiamat<bt>The last day(s)</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ais itu ju, beta, andia Daniel, ada lia-lia. Tarús ada dua orang muncul datang. Satu badiri di kali pung pinggir di sablá sini. Satu badiri di kali pung pinggir di sablá sana.<bt>After that, I, that is Daniel, was looking (around-REDUP). Then3 there were two people who appeared. One stood at the side/bank of the river on this side. One/the other stood at the side of the river on that side.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yə' or: river (Egyptian word)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yə' or: river (Egyptian word)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) sfat: lip, bank of a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) sfat: lip, bank of a river</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Ju satu dari dong dua kasi tau sang itu ana bua dari sorga yang pake kaen lenan, yang ada di kali pung hulu sadiki, bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini tanda heran dong, masi barapa lama, baru jadi?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then one of those two told that underling from heaven (*angel) who wore linen cloth, who was a bit upstream, saying, &lt;&lt;These amazing signs (*miracles), are still how long before they happen?&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Heb. ‘above the waters’ taken by some as ‘upstream’, and by others as ‘over the water’. See TH.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) pəla'owt: amazing things. TWOT: The"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) pəla'owt: amazing things. TWOT: The root may also be used negatively to mean "unbelievable." The reference in Dan 8:24 and 11:36 to the diabolical apocalyptic figure who hatches "incredible schemes" or speaks "incredible blasphemies" illustrates this.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləmeymey (dual, with singular meaning):"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləmeymey (dual, with singular meaning): water of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mimmaʕal: from above, from higher"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mimmaʕal: from above, from higher ground than. Some suggest 'upstream', but he could have been floating in the air over the river, or one foot on each bank.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ais, itu ana bua angka dia pung tangan dua-dua, ju angka sumpa bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta sumpa bawa Tuhan Allah yang idop tarús-tarús pung nama. Bilang, masi tiga taon satenga, kalo Tuhan pung orang barisi dong pung kuasa su abis, na, ini hal dong samua su jadi.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then, that underling lifted both his hands, and made an oath saying, &lt;&lt;I swear bearing God who lives continually's name/reputation. Saying/that, there are still three and a half years, if/when God2's clean/holy people's power/authority has ended, na, all of these things will have happeneed.&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE (referent tracking): ‘the man clothed in linen’ reduced for RL pattern (like CEV).] [DISCOURSE: (info load): ‘raised his right hand and his left hand’ reduced for RL pattern (like NLT, CEV, HCE).] [DISCOURSE: indirect oath (NRSV) made direct (similar to NLT).] [EXEG: Heb. ‘for a time, two times, and half a time’ = 3-1/2 yrs (TH). Heb. unclear if it is ‘after 3-1/2 yrs, then...’ or ‘when it starts, then it will go for 3-1/2 yrs’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) tikhleynah (klh): it will be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) tikhleynah (klh): it will be accomplished</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yad-ʕam-qodesh: the power of the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yad-ʕam-qodesh: the power of the holy people</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) nappets (piʕel inf): dashing to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) nappets (piʕel inf): dashing to pieces, shattering</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) kallowt (klh piʕel inf): on"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) kallowt (klh piʕel inf): on finishing a task</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mowʕed: appointed time (one and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mowʕed: appointed time (one and two and a half = 3-1/2)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) vayyisshavaʕ (piʕel): he swore an"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) vayyisshavaʕ (piʕel): he swore an oath</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) mimmaʕal: from above"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) mimmaʕal: from above</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dunya Model Baru 10:5, 12:14</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Beta dengar itu ana bua pung omong, ma beta sonde tangkap dia pung arti. Ais beta tanya sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa. Nanti dia pung ujung karmana?&gt;&gt;<bt>I heard what that underling said, but I did not catch his meaning. So I asked him saying, &lt;&lt;Father. Later its end/result will be how?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) End of P section."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) End of P section.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Daniel, dengar bae-bae sang beta. Itu hal dong bukan lu pung urusan. Lebe bae, lu pi suda, ko taro mata di lu pung urusan sandiri. Te ini hal dong tasambunyi tarús, sampe dunya kiamat.<bt>He responded saying, &lt;&lt;Daniel, listen to me carefully. Those things are not your business/handling/managed things. It would be better/best for you to just go, in order to attend to your own business/handling. Cuz (elaboration) these things will continue to be hidden until the last day(s).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) Sətumiym vachətumiym: as in verse"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) Sətumiym vachətumiym: as in verse 4.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="10" />Tuhan mau uji banya orang.<bt>God2 is going to test many people. [DISCOURSE: Heb. is chiastic structure. See TH. Restructured for RL patterns.] [DISCOURSE: Ellipted proposition seems to be that this is about responses to testing (NLT, HCE). Heb. yittsarfuw (tsrp nif? hitp?): they will be tested, refined. God is the agent.] [NOTE to daughter translations: One UNS pointed out that in James the TB says God does not /coba/ ‘test’ people. The Gk there say God does not ‘tempt’ people (to do wrong/evil). OV Kupang /coba/ ‘test1’ works fine, but we shifted to /uji/ ‘test2’, to avoid the clash with the unfortunate translation of the TB.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Andia, orang barisi deng orang jahat dong.<bt>That is, clean/holy people and evil people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ada orang saparu pung hati tamba barisi,<bt>There are some people whose liver is increasingly clean/holy/pure,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng hati tamba lebe bae lai.<bt>and (their) livers are increasingly good.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Orang yang mangarti hal iko Tuhan pung pikiran,<bt>People who understand things according to God2's thinking,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">nanti tamba mangarti lai.<bt>will increase in understanding.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ma orang jahat dong sonde barenti bekin jahat.<bt>But evil people will not stop doing evil.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Sonde ada dari dong yang mangarti.<bt>There are none of them who understand.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yaviynuw: they will understand"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yaviynuw: they will understand</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) maskiliym: those who understand why"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) maskiliym: those who understand why things happen the way they do</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) rəshaʕiym: wicked people"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) rəshaʕiym: wicked people</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) hirshiyʕuw (rshʕ hif): they will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) hirshiyʕuw (rshʕ hif): they will act wickedly</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yittsarfuw (tsrp nif? hitp?): they"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yittsarfuw (tsrp nif? hitp?): they will be tested, refined</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yitlabbənuw (lbn hitp): they will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yitlabbənuw (lbn hitp): they will make themselves white</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yitbarəruw (brr hitp): they will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yitbarəruw (brr hitp): they will purify themselves. TWOT: "Purge" or "purify" is found in Ezk 20:38 where the Lord God says he will purge the rebellious transgressors out of scattered Israel. In Dan 11:35; 12:10 it is said that many people in the future will purify themselves. UBS: The first two verbs, "purify themselves" and "make themselves white", are translated reflexively in rsv, but the underlying Hebrew forms may be understood as passives, "be purified" and "be made white" (as in nrsv, niv, njv, njb, nab, and tob). Since there is a significant difference in meaning between the reflexive (in which the subject of the verb does something for himself or herself) and the passive (where someone else does something for the subject), translators must decide which of these two meanings to adopt. The passive meaning is recommended, but in those languages where the passive is unnatural or does not exist at all, they may be forced to make the verbs active and state clearly who performs the action.</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dunya Model Baru 22:11</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Dari waktu itu orang jahat tu suru kasi barenti samua macam korban deng persembahan dong, deng kasi badiri satu barang yang sonde pantas, yang bekin kamomos tampa barisi sampe bekin noju itu tampa, ada saribu dua ratus sambilan pulu (1.290) hari.<bt>From the time those evil people order to stop all kinds of sacrifices and offerings, and erect something that is not appropriate which makes filthy/defiled the clean/holy place to the point of making that place repugnant, there are one thousand two hundred ninety (1,290) days. [NOTE to daughter translations: cf. wording in Dan. 9:27 and 11:31.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shomem (partcpl): BDB be desolate,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shomem (partcpl): BDB be desolate, be appalled, stun, stupefy</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) shiqquwts: BDB detestable thing or"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) shiqquwts: BDB detestable thing or idol, abominable thing, abomination, idol, detested thing</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) huSar (Swr hofʕal): be taken"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) huSar (Swr hofʕal): be taken away, be removed, be abolished (Pidgin requires a subject)</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 9:27, 11:31; Mateos 24:15; Markus 13:14</note><v n="12" />Ma orang yang bisa batahan sampe saribu tiga ratus tiga pulu lima (1.335) hari abis, nanti dong ontong.<bt>But people who are able to endure/persever until 1,335 days are over, they will be fortunate. [EXEG: Heb. ashar corresponds here and elsewhere to LXX Gk makarios, used in the beatitudes. ‘how fortunate in the eyes of God’. Happiness may be a result, but is not really part of the core meaning. So CEV handles this verse a bit better than NRSV or NLT.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) yaggiyaʕ (ngʕ hif): BDB reach,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) yaggiyaʕ (ngʕ hif): BDB reach, extend, attain, arrive, come</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) məchakkeh (chkh piʕel partcpl): the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) məchakkeh (chkh piʕel partcpl): the one[s] who wait. BDB wait, tarry; wait (in ambush); wait for, long for. UBS: The verb "waits" should not be understood in the sense of waiting passively in desperation. The idea is rather that of waiting confidently. It is for this reason that tev translates "remain faithful."</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Kalo lu, Daniel, lu musti batahan kuat ko bekin iko lu pung tugas sampe waktu lu mati. Ais baru lu bisa barenti cape. Ma nanti kalo dunya kiamat, lu idop kambali ko tarima ame lu pung bagian yang Tuhan su simpan memang kasi sang lu.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>As for you, Daniel, you must persevere strongly to do according to your task/responsibilities until you die. Only then will you be able to rest (lit: stop tired). But later when it is the last days, you will live again to receive your portion which God2 has stored away beforehand for you.&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(ne) ləgoralkha: your lot. TWOT: Recompense"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2017-09-22 09:10:41Z">(ne) ləgoralkha: your lot. TWOT: Recompense or reward may be one's lot (Isa 17:14; Dan 12:13). UBS: Here the idea of drawing lots is not in focus, and the word simply means "that which is set aside (by God) for a person." JG: This is not the usual word of inheritance from father to son.</Message></Annotation></p>
  </book>
</bible>